(505, 1, 'Calibre Environmental Ltd.', 'shayne@calibregroup.ca', '6224 - 29 Street S.E., Calgary, Alberta, ', 'www.RecyclePaint.com', '+1 (403) 287-7728 ex', '+1 (403) 287-7792', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Calibre Environmental Ltd. was incorporated in the fall of 2003 .Calibre Environmental initially recycled industrial and commercial paints in small amounts, creating white, beige and grey ecocoat which was tested and marketed as an industrial primer. In September 2004, Calibre obtained the contract to process City of Calgary post-consumer paint and began searching for a better way to recycle latex paints. In November 2004, Calibre Environmental established a relationship with an American organization that had been recycling latex paint since 1992. Calibre was able to adopt their methods and practices, and in the spring of 2005 ecocoat was launched to the Canadian retail market with 14 consistent colours of 100% recycled premium quality latex paint.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In June of 2006, Calibre Environmental was a proud recipient of an Alberta Emerald Award for environmental excellence. These awards celebrate and showcase the outstanding achievements&nbsp; of Albertans committed to protecting, preserving, enhancing and sustaining our environment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2008, Calibre Environmental became a key part of the new Alberta Paint Stewardship program which significantly increased&nbsp; the recycling of unused latex paint from across the province of Alberta.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(270, 1, 'Solmax International Inc. ', 'international@solmax.com', '2801 Marie-Victorin Blvd, VARENNES, Quebec, , ', 'www.solmax.com', '+1 (450) 929-1234', '+1 (450) 929-1227 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Solmax International Inc. is a corporation exclusively dedicated to the manufacturing of polyethylene geomembranes (HDPE, LLDPE) and the pre-assembly of oversized polyvinyl chloride (PVC) panels. For over 20 years, Solmax has been recognized as one of the leading experts in the geomembrane industry. Our expertise benefits companies seeking the highest degree of imperviousness to minimize the impact of their activities on the environment. By working with your engineering consulting firm, we are prepared to help you validate some of your choices and use our experience to make recommendations that will enable you to define the key parameters of your project. Solmax\'s experience: Since 1997, over 100 000 MT of Solmax polyethylene geomembranes have been used in thousands of projects around the world (~70 million m&sup2; of 1.5 mm)</p>', ''),
(272, 1, 'Davert Tools Inc. ', 'rcollier@davert.org', '5676 Progress St., NIAGARA FALLS, Ontario, , ', 'www.davert.org', '+1 (905) 353-0531', '+1 (905) 353-0449', '', '<p>Davert is a total solution provider for all your metal fabrication, engineering, design and prototype needs.  We are dedicated to provide our customers with quality engineered products by blending innovation, strict quality control, engineering expertise, the latest technology and a sincere dedication to the needs of our customers. It is our goal to provide the finest fabricated steel products available, always meeting strict standards for consumer quality and satisfaction. Our pledge is to produce excellent products.   We will face every experience as a challenge to improve, knowing that our future success depends on meeting our commitments and following an aggressive continuous improvement plan.  In recognizing our customers as our most important business partners, we know that satisfying their needs makes our existence possible.  We continue to invent new solutions and improve our products and services. Whether you require prototyping or full-scale production, contact us.</p>', ''),
(271, 1, 'Solmax International Inc. ', 'international@solmax.com', '2801 Marie-Victorin Blvd, VARENNES, Quebec, , ', 'www.solmax.com', '+1 (450) 929-1234', '+1 (450) 929-1227 ', '', '<p>Solmax International Inc. is a corporation exclusively dedicated to the manufacturing of polyethylene geomembranes (HDPE, LLDPE) and the pre-assembly of oversized polyvinyl chloride (PVC) panels.  For over 20 years, Solmax has been recognized as one of the leading experts in the geomembrane industry. Our expertise benefits companies seeking the highest degree of imperviousness to minimize the impact of their activities on the environment. By working with your engineering consulting firm, we are prepared to help you validate some of your choices and use our experience to make recommendations that will enable you to define the key parameters of your project.  Solmax\'s experience: Since 1997, over 100 000 MT of Solmax polyethylene geomembranes have been used in thousands of projects around the world (~70 million m&sup2; of 1.5 mm)</p>', ''),
(273, 1, 'Wood Group Pressure Control Canada', 'sales@woodgroup.com', '8743, 50th Ave, N.W., Edmonton â€“ AB, , ', 'www.woodgroup.com', '+1 (780) 450-3401', '+1 (780) 450-3413', '', '<p>Wood Group (John Wood Group) is an international energy services company with $5.0bn sales, employing approximately 26,000 people worldwide and operating in 46 countries. The Group has three businesses - Engineering &amp; Production Facilities, Well Support, and Gas Turbine Services - providing a range of engineering, production support, maintenance management and industrial gas turbine overhaul and repair services to the oil &amp; gas, and power generation industries worldwide. Wood Group Pressure Control (WGPC) is a subsidiary company of John Wood Group and part of the Well Support Division. WGPC was formed through the acquisition of complementary companies that manufacture and remanufacture equipment which controls pressure when drilling for oil or gas.</p>', ''),
(274, 1, 'Wood Group Pressure Control Canada', 'sales@woodgroup.com', '8743, 50th Ave, N.W., Edmonton â€“ AB, , ', 'www.woodgroup.com', '+1 (780) 450-3401', '+1 (780) 450-3413', '', '<p>Wood Group (John Wood Group)  is an international energy services company with $5.0bn sales, employing approximately 26,000 people worldwide and operating in 46 countries. The Group has three businesses - Engineering &amp; Production Facilities, Well Support, and Gas Turbine Services - providing a range of engineering, production support, maintenance management and industrial gas turbine overhaul and repair services to the oil &amp; gas, and power generation industries worldwide.    Wood Group Pressure Control (WGPC) is a subsidiary company of John Wood Group and part of the Well Support Division.  WGPC was formed through the acquisition of complementary companies that manufacture and remanufacture equipment which controls pressure when drilling for oil or gas.</p>', ''),
(275, 1, 'Adventure Marine Mfg. Inc.', 'action@adventuremarine.net', '16886-21st Ave, SURREY, British Columbia, , ', 'www.adventuremarine.net', '+1(604)535-2217', '+1(604)535-4272', '', '<p>The owner of Adventure Marine Manufacturing Inc., Gerard Raps, started in the marine manufacturing business in 1974. Most marine products manufactured by Adventure Marine started with an idea; others were existing boat accessories which needed improvements. This 34 year tradition for quality and performance in boating products continues and Adventure Marine Manufacturing Inc. has built a solid reputation that understands the special needs within the Marine Industry. Gerard Raps has introduced many new and improved products to the marine industry over the years. Adjustable feature for outboard motor brackets, poly propylene mounting boards to outboard motor brackets, dinghy swivel outboard motor brackets, adaptors for outboard motor brackets, first aluminum stabilizer in the early 70\'s and more. Gerard Raps is also the owner of several patents and in November 2002 received a US patent for the propeller safety guards.</p>', ''),
(276, 1, 'Global Repair Ltd.', 'sales@globalrepair.ca', '22 Bellefair Ave, Toronto â€“ On, , ', 'www.globalrepair.ca', '+1-416-686-3690', '+1-416-686-1744', '', '<p>Global Repair Ltd, International Marketing Office for Sittler Manufacturing, provides compost equipment for nutrient recovery and soil regeneration, Natural Soil Amendments, Education and Consulting. Our products, used in over 21 countries, reduce greenhouse gases and provide sustainable solutions for Agriculture, Municipalities and Industry. As your &ldquo;One Stop Compost Shop&rdquo; we offer Compost Windrow Turners, Compost/Lime Spreaders, Trommel Screeners, Conveyors and Baggers. With our Advanced Biological Composting method we help growers &quot;Utilize Resources and Maximize Profits&quot;. Technical backup includes a database for compost calculations, easy to follow instructional booklets and DVDs to insure our clients make the highest quality product. Discover more about how our method of composting can improve efficiency and profit with your operation. Please enjoy your stay.</p>', ''),
(277, 1, 'Precision Metalform Limited', 'davh@pmform.com', '118-1680 Broadway St., PORT COQUITLAM, British Columbia, , ', 'www.precisionmetalform.com', '+1 (604) 464-3939', '+1 (604) 464-1212 ', '', '<p>Precision Metalform is a quality manufacturer of close tolerance sheet metal parts and products. It was founded in 1992 by the merger of a metal fabrication subsidiary from an engineering group, and a high precision fabricator, specializing in small electronic enclosures. The former had rare welding capability, able to weld down to the thickness of tin foil. The latter was spun off as the fabrication division of a large electronics manufacturer, Glenayre Electronics.  Complementing and building on these combined skill sets, Precision added the most sophisticated, close tolerance, high volume punching and forming equipment available. This CNC hardware, from the German manufacturer Trumpf is generally recognized as the industry leader at maintaining repeatable close tolerances over a large number of identical activities, as well as being the most versatile in its industry.</p>', ''),
(278, 1, 'BioVectra dcl', 'info@biovectra.com', '11 Aviation Ave, CHARLOTTETOWN - Prince Edward Island, , ', 'www.biovectra.com', '+1(902) 566-9116 ', '+1 (902) 566-2498', '', '<p>Who is BioVectra DCL?       We are an Eastern Canadian pharmaceutical/biologic manufacturer with over 35 years of experience serving a global customer base. BioVectra provides small to large scale custom manufacturing of advanced intermediates, active pharmaceutical ingredients and biologics along with a complement of core products targeted toward bioprocessing.  Overview Presentation:     We currently operate out of three FDA-inspected facilities (June 2005) which are equipped to provide a range of contract services for our clients (highlighted below). BioVectra dcl\'s staff is knowledgeable in the requirements for commercialization of API\'s and we currently have seven DMF\'s registered with the FDA.</p>', ''),
