(583, 1, 'K Squared', 'shackymousa@gmail.com ', '141 Wildwood Trail, BARRIE,  Ontario, canada', 'www.dykeoutfitters.com ', '(289) 795-5033', '', '', '<p>We, Karen and Kirsty, are a couple of Canadian dykes, who after years  of shopping frustrations, decided to use our experience in the <strong>gay women clothing</strong> industry, not to mention almost 100 years of combined dyke experience, to create a store that we would like to shop in.</p>\r\n<p>We hope our collection of clothing makes <strong>shopping for gay women clothing</strong>  a more positive experience rather than searching the mall where sizes  do not cater to lesbian women. Unfortunately, we are limited to what is  available in the current marketplace. As our company grows, it is our  goal to manufacture our own line of gay women clothing. This line would  consist of garments that are not readily available in the current  market, in women&rsquo;s sizes. We are constantly searching for new items to  add to our store, so please visit often.</p>', ''),
(584, 1, 'K&D Pratt Instrumentation', 'charles.lacey@kdpratt.com', '126 Glencoe Dr., MOUNT PEARL, Newfoundland and Labrador, canada', 'www.kdpratt.com', '(709) 722-5690 ', '(709) 722-6975 ', '', '<p>Capitalizing on our long history and expertise in the Fire Protection  business, we have aligned ourselves with many of the leading fire  equipment manufacturers to bring our customers field tested and proven  products meeting today\'s rigorous Fire Equipment Standards. K&amp;D Pratt is committed to providing an extensive line-up of  specialized safety products, backed by full technical support, training  and service to all industry sectors. Products will always meet or exceed industry standards for acceptable safety practices.</p>', ''),
(585, 1, 'K&P Auto & Marine Electric (1997) Inc.', 'gord@kpautoelectric.com, help@kpautoelectric.com', '8-160 Pony Dr., NEWMARKET, Ontario, Canada', 'http://www.kpautoelectric.com  ', '(905) 895-5831', '(905) 830-0554', '', '<p>K&amp;P Auto and Marine Electric is York Region\'s leading starter and alternator rebuilder. Whether it\'s your  daily driver, work vehicle, transport truck, construction equipment, fork lift, farm equipment or your weekend  toy, the staff at K&amp;P will have you back on the road, the job site or cruising across the water in no time!</p>', ''),
(586, 1, 'K+S Windsor Salt Ltd.', 'mprevost@windsorsalt.com', '700-755 Saint-Jean Blvd, POINTE-CLAIRE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.windsorsalt.com', '(514) 630-0900', '(514) 694-2451', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 13.5pt; font-size: 8pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">It\'s more than just the white, granular seasoning that enhances the flavour of so many foods. Salt is one of the most widely used minerals on Earth. It\'s a natural preservative that inhibits the growth of bacteria, and an essential element in our diet. It helps regulate our blood pressure and volume, facilitates the transmission of nerve impulses, and plays a vital role in heart and muscle contractions.</span><span style=\"line-height: 13.5pt; font-size: 8pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height:13.5pt\"><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">It was 1893, in Windsor (Ontario), when three employees of the Canadian Pacific Railway Company (C.P.R.) began a subsidiary they called The Windsor Salt Company Limited. Within a few years, the fledgling operation was sold and became The Canadian Salt Company Limited. Over the years since, the Company has changed hands at least twice, but it has remained a leader in modern salt processing methods. Today, the company is known as K+S Windsor Salt Ltd. and it is Canada\'s largest salt manufacturer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;color:#666666;mso-ansi-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">The Company is engaged in the recovery, processing and sale of salt, and provides over 200 evaporated and rock salt products under its well-known Windsor and Safe-T-Salt brand names.</span></p>', ''),
(587, 1, 'K.W. Leather Products Ltd.', 'kwleather@bellnet.ca', '594 Colby Dr, WATERLOO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.kw-lp.com', '(519) 746-3510', '(519) 746-8317', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">K<b>-W Leather Products Ltd. (KWLP Manufacturing) is a Canadian Owned and Operated contract manufacturing company located in Waterloo Ontario. The company is in its 30th year of operation.&nbsp;His original&nbsp;</b></span><b>products were fine personal&nbsp;leather goods manufactured&nbsp;under contract for other Canadian based companies.</b></p>', ''),
(588, 1, 'K&Y Diamond Ltd.', 'yguillaume@kydiamond.ca', '2645 Diab St, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.kydiamond.ca', '(514) 333-5606', '(514) 339-5493', '', '<p>K&amp;Y Diamond is an ultra-precision diamond tool manufacturer  recognized worldwide. We combine more than 50 years of expertise with  cutting edge technology to provide our customers with <a href=\"http://kydiamond.ca/technical/diamonds/\">high-end tools</a> that rank among the most competitive ones on the market.</p>\r\n<p>Our strength lies in our optimal manufacturing processes. They are at  the core of what we are able to offer today: an unrivalled precision to  the nanometer.</p>\r\n<p><em>Ultra precision, attention to detail and performance, it&rsquo;s what we do daily and what we do best.</em></p>', ''),
