(596, 1, 'Le Courrier de la Nouvelle-Ecosse ', 'administration@lecourrier.com', '9250, route 1, METEGHAN RIVER, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.lecourrier.com', '(902) 769-3078', '(902) 769-3869', '', '<p>&nbsp;<font style=\"color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.2000007629395px;\">In 1937, D&eacute;sir&eacute; d\'Eon Le Petit Courrier based Southwest, which was to become Courier Nova Scotia in 1972, only French-language newspaper in the province.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.2000007629395px;\">Recipient of numerous awards, including an &Eacute;loize Award for best media coverage in 2008, the newspaper informs its readers, advocates for Acadians and Francophones and creates a bridge between all Acadian regions.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.2000007629395px;\">Published every Friday, The Courier is managed by the Acadian Press Company.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.2000007629395px;\">It is distributed by mail to subscribers, and is also found on newsstands.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18.2000007629395px;\">He published various supplements (Christmas, graduation, Acadian Day) as well as a summer tourist guide pulled 20,000 copies.</font></p>', ''),
(597, 1, 'L&K Industries', 'leslie@lkindustries.ca', '227 Finchdene Sq , SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.lkindustries.ca', '(416) 292-4039', '(416) 292-8500', '', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 1994, L&amp;K INDUSTRIES continues to provide a wide range of in-stock gauges, colours, coatings and treatments of flexible plastic films. We service such industries as, window patch, wet laminating, vertical and horizontal form fill and seal, labeling, bag and pouch, bag liner and decorative outer web. To enhance our product lines we offer color process or line print as well as mutli-layer barrier films. L&amp;K INDUSTRIES will also cater to those companies who need to have materials converted, either into roll or sheet form.</p>', ''),
(598, 1, 'L&L Maritime Corporation', 'llmcorp99@hotmail.com', '780 Eden Pl., WEST VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.llmaritime.com', '(604) 922-8342', '(604) 922-8829', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">L&amp;L Maritime Corpn (LLMC) incorporated in 1987 is a distributor of quality instruments for the Marine, Fire Protection, Petrochemical, Oil and Gas, Defense, Government organisations, Rail and other industries worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LLMC in co-operation with Alere Toxicology has been providing international occupational health and substance abuse testing programs for the marine and the offshore oil &amp; gas industry for over a decade. Only a handful of companies are positioned to provide these services because doing it well requires commitment, investment, knowledge, experience and expertise ... our specific strengths. The LLMC team is highly qualified and dedicated to meeting the needs of its customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LLMC provides consultancy to the marine industry and with over 30 years experience in chartering, operating and ship management of both bulk carriers and offshore vessels, the company has the expertise for carrying out Pre-Purchase Condition Surveys, P&amp;I Surveys, Ultrasonic Watertight Integrity Testing, feasibility studies and marketing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LLMC pride ourselves on providing the best customer service. When there is a difference, overall customer cost cannot be measured by the item cost alone. The quality and integrity of our services are also measured by the knowledge, experience and expertise that provides cost savings in the long term.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(599, 1, 'L K Specialties Inc', 'philt@primus.ca', '6-1180 Mid-Way Blvd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 564-2616', '(905) 795-0384', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(29, 35, 38); font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;\">Manufacturing Industry, Sporting and athletic goods in Mississauga, Ontario or in another place in the Canada.</span></p>', ''),
(600, 1, 'La Chambre de commerce de l\'Est de Montreal', 'info@ccemontreal.ca', '5600, rue Hochelaga Bureau 100, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.ccemontreal.ca', '(514) 354-5378', '(514) 354-5340', '', '<p><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The economic development of our members presents many challenges.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Indeed, in 2014, one can not think without thinking innovation economic development, regardless of sustainable development or human resource planning in the context of labor shortages.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">We can think of economic development without considering the development of overseas markets.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">However, the Chamber is equipped to support entrepreneurs in the East, among others by its export assistance service, its networking events and numerous outreach activities.</font><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Also, the Chamber must exercise increasingly recognized leadership in lobbying activities and representation in strategic development issues such as transport and the development of the Maisonneuve pole, to name a few.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">The House is an ideal networking where members can develop profitable business opportunities and promising future for their organizations.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Verdana, Tahoma, \'DejaVu Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">In the House, our main goal is to be open and accessible while focusing on opportunities to increase the success of our member companies and the growth of our territory.</font></p>', ''),
(601, 1, 'La Cie Canada Tire Inc.', 'info@cdatire.com', '21500 Trans-Canada Hwy, BAIE-D\'URFE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.cdatire.com', '(514) 457-0155', '(514) 457-1158', '', '<p>Tire-Dealers-Retail</p>\r\n<p>Auto Repair Shops Auto and Home Supply Stores</p>', ''),
(602, 1, 'Labequip Ltd.', 'ask@labequip.com', '2-170 Shields Crt, MARKHAM, Ontario, Canada', 'www.labequip.com', '(905) 475-5880', '(905) 475-1231', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Largest stock of used lab equipment under one roof in North America ... Experienced, professional sales staff ...&nbsp; Top-notch service before and after the sale!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Over 4000 items in stock.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Quality, dependable second hand laboratory equipment for sale.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Save 40% to 70%, and help the environment by buying recycled equipment for your lab. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Each laboratory instrument is carefully refurbished, and rigorously tested.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We supply a wide range of brand new equipment for the laboratory.&nbsp; Reliable, brand-names:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Autoclaves, balances, centrifuges, conductivity,&nbsp; pH, petroleum products testers, freezers, furnaces, incubators, ovens, microscopes, stomachers, titrators, viscometers, &hellip; and more.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(603, 1, 'LABEX CANADA INC', 'info@labexcanada.com', '79 Bridgeview Dr., HALIFAX, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.labexcanada.com', '(902) 431-8022', '(902) 405-6463', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">LABEX CANADA INC. is a Distributor &amp; Business Development Consultancy company offering professional export services for Canadian manufacturers in the field of Medical &amp; Laboratory Diagnostics to many countries around the world.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">LABEX CANADA INC. is also avtive on designing different types of laboratories (Clinical Labs in the Hospitals, Physician Office Labs, Mobile Labs &amp; Veterinary Labs).&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">We provide a wide range of high quality Laboratory Instrumentations, Diagnostics reagents &amp; kits and consumables to distributors, Clinical Laboratories located in Hospitals, clinics, educational institutes and veterinary labs.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">We also provide Installation, Setup, Maintenance services for different Laboratory Equipments.&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(604, 1, 'LabelLighthouse.com', 'contactus@labellighthouse.com', '11195, 5th Line, ROCKWOOD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.LabelLighthouse.com', '(905) 854-3790', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The superior Stikins&trade; name label is a one size name label that can be used on both clothing and items. Stikins&trade; advanced name label simply stick to the care tag of your clothing and is also used for shoes, water bottles, snack packs, books, pens and lots of other things. One label does it all! These labels are easy to use - simply peel and stick.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our name labels are washer/dryer, dishwasher and microwave safe. Use Stikins&trade; name labels for camp, school, daycare and long term care facilities. The letters are large making it easy for a child or senior to read.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(605, 1, 'Laboratoire Delon (1990) Incorpore', 'arcogrp@bellnet.ca', '69 Brunswick Blvd, DOLLARD-DES-ORMEAUX, Quebec, Canada', 'www.labdelon.com ', '(514) 334-9515', '(514) 956-7849', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(109, 109, 109); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 21.6000003814697px; text-align: justify;\">We are dedicated to providing innovative products and solutions to our partners in the Health and Beauty Industry. We bring our 64-year legacy of health and beauty expertise with a range of products that address personal care needs from the inside out, and bring you the highest level of integrity and value. Our skin cream line products are based upon botanical remedies. Our philosophy derives from combining the decades-old wisdom inherent in botanical, herbal and floral treatments with modern ingredients and formulations. Using natural herbs and pH-balanced, many biodegradable formulas, each product is carefully formulated to deliver all the benefits of each unique blend. All of our products reflect our ongoing efforts to preserve the earth\'s natural resources by being environmentally friendly and cruelty-free.</span></p>', ''),
(606, 1, 'LABORIE', 'webmaster@laborie.com', '2-6415 Northwest Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.laborie.com/', '(905) 612-1170', '(905) 612-9731', '', '<div>&nbsp;LABORIE is a market leader in global pelvic health, dedicated to providing complete solutions that provide better diagnostics and treatment outcomes. Founded in 1967, LABORIE Medical is the leading global manufacturer and supplier of medical testing equipment and consumables with exceptional brand recognition and industry-leading technologies.</div>\r\n<div>LABORIE&rsquo;s world headquarters is based in Toronto, Canada with additional offices located in Montreal (Canada), Williston, VT (USA), Rugby (UK), Paris (France), Ghent (Belgium), Sao Paulo (Brazil), and Beijing (China).</div>\r\n<div>LABORIE has over 85 distributors worldwide supplying physician offices, hospitals, and mobile providers on 6 continents. In addition to our global workforce, we work with leading clinician-researchers and local universities to incorporate the most recent advancements and technical knowledge into our products while reflecting practical realities of the typical pelvic floor clinic.</div>', ''),
(607, 1, 'LaboVal', 'info@laboval.com', '1688, 50e av., LACHINE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.laboval.com ', '(514) 633-6826', '(514) 633-9679', '', '<p>&nbsp;LaboVal specializes in pharmaceutical product testing and is devoted to protecting public health by providing the highest level of laboratory services to pharmaceutical and healthcare sectors.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We believe our client&rsquo;s R&amp;D and quality department deserves to be free from daily stress caused by lack of reliability in generated results and by excessive delays for obtaining them</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We have a rigorous internal quality control system, guaranteeing an exceptional service, as well as reliable and precise results. Our equipment consists solely of the latest technology.</div>', ''),
(608, 1, 'Labplas Inc.', 'sales@labplas.com', '1950, rue Bombardier, SAINTE-JULIE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.labplas.com ', '(450) 649-7343', '(450) 649-3113', '', '<p>&nbsp;To offer to the professionals serving the laboratory and industrial communities, a line of superior quality sterile sampling and processing products that are designed to meet the consistency and reliability requirements of the multitude of applications within their respective industries.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our focus is on quality and service. We understand the importance of sterility, dependability and consistency.</div>\r\n<div>Labplas maintains an in-house R&amp;D function for both product development and production process improvement.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Labplas team understands the need to be flexible and how to make things simple for its customers. Do you need customization? A different size? Some specialty printing? Specific inserts? Our customer service staff will be pleased to explore the possibilities with you.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We pride ourselves on responding to your information request within 24 hours, whether you\'re in our time zone or on the other side of the world.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;Labplas has supported the Missing Childen\'s Network for many years now. Our products are shipped to over 40 countries, and we post the Missing Children\'s Network bulletins on all our shipments.</div>', ''),
(609, 1, 'Laboratoire Orthopedique Medicus', 'jacinte.bleau@medicus.ca', '5135, 10e av., MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'medicus.ca ', '(514) 525-3757', '(514) 525-9915', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;&nbsp;M&eacute;dicus was founded in 1957 by an orthotist-prosthetist named Jean-Claude Bleau. The only francophone in this profession, Mr. Bleau opened his first laboratory and began his career in a modest 300 sq.ft. office. Fueled by his passion, he opened the first Orthotics and Prosthetics Laboratory fabricating and adjusting orthopedic shoes. Because of his avant-garde outlook, he rapidly became a source of reference in his field . It was around this time that a new product known as &ldquo;Space Shoes&rdquo; became available in the United States. These shoes were custom made using a plaster mold of the patient&rsquo;s foot. For the next 10 years, M&eacute;dicus had exclusive Space Shoe distribution which brought in customers, suffering from foot problems, from all over North America.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, M&eacute;dicus is considered to be the leading employer of Orthotics &amp; Prosthetics graduates in Qu&eacute;bec and has several companies<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(610, 1, 'Laboratoire M2', 'sauray@laboratoirem2.com', '4005A De La Garlock St, SHERBROOKE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.thymox.com/en/', '(866) 898-0697', '(819) 562-5211', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laboratoire M2 is the lab which has developed this technology branded as Thymox.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laboratoire M2 is renowned for its innovations and expertise in disinfection and safety. It owns and operates a state-of-the-art level 2 containment microbiology laboratory. It has developed a thymol-based disinfectant-cleaner formulation which is available for private labeling to distributors for institutional, agricultural, hospital and household use.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">aboratoire M2 manufactures innovative disinfection products from its proprietary platform named Thymox Technology. Laboratoire M2 is also working on expanding its line of Thymox Technology products and applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laboratoire M2&prime;s R&amp;D team is specifically working on disinfectant wipes for household surfaces, new concentrated disinfectants for industrial and institutional markets, and on new solutions for hoof care.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(611, 1, 'EpilVite Hairaway', 'info@labreynard.com', '6465, rte Transcanadienne, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'cires-epilatoires.com ', '(514) 856-6996', '(514) 856-6999', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The hair removal brand Hair Away offers more than thirty years of quality, experience and service excellence to its clientele. Its mission is to supply innovative and professional quality depilatory wax products that answer customers specific needs, all the while offering efficient and amicable customer service. Hair Away offers all types of hair removal products available on the market. This includes sugar based cold wax, resin based lukewarm wax as well as stripless hard wax made with bees wax.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At its beginning in 1969, Hair Away launched the innovative Epil Minute on the market, a sugar based wax paste washable with water. In 1972, Hair Away launches resin based lukewarm wax on the Canadian market. This format still remains the most popular among beauty professionals. In 1975, Hair Away launches the practical ready-to-use sugar waxing strips on the market. This format is one of the most popular based on its ease of use and cleanliness. Following these developments, Hair Away continues to innovate in order to offer new and practical product types that answer its clients current needs. The Research and Development Department regularly develops specific formulations for various combinations of hair and skin types in order to optimize waxing and lessen pain.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(612, 1, 'Lady Sandra Home Fashions Inc.', 'info@ladysandra.com', '12-8600 Decarie Blvd, MONT-ROYAL,, Quebec, Canada', 'www.ladysandra.com ', '(514) 325-6715', '(514) 739-8128', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lady Sandra Home Fashions Inc. is a privately owned Canadian importer of textile home furnishing products. At the helm of Lady Sandra are Marvin Reiskind (President), whose father founded the company in 1965 and Martin Novack (CEO). Located in Montreal, Lady Sandra&rsquo;s facility houses a warehouse, offices and a showroom.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lady Sandra&rsquo;s primary range of products includes comforters, bedspreads, quilts, duvet covers, sheet sets, decorative pillows, throws, blankets, window coverings, juvenile bedding, tabletop and kitchen textiles, and bath textiles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Lady Sandra team is a complete package: inspiration and creation of product, sourcing capabilities within a global network, selling product to all major retailers and specialty boutiques, and post-sales analytical support and customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lady Sandra currently holds the following licenses: Playboy, Justin Bieber, Apple Bottoms, Swarovski, Deadmau5, Kiss, The Beatles, Grateful Dead, Cody Simpson and Doctor Who.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(613, 1, 'LAE Technologies Inc.', 'info@laetechnologies.com', '11-145 Welham Rd, BARRIE, Ontario, Canada', '', '(705) 728-7000', '(705) 728-3594', '', '<p>&nbsp;LAE TECHNOLOGIES is a rapid prototyping &amp; product development company specializing in leading technologies,worldwide development capabilities &amp; reliable service. We develop defaultized solutions that help businesses reducetheir time-to-market.</p>\r\n<p>LAE Technologies is rapid prototyping and product development company. Our focus is to partner with companies through every stage of product development and manufacturing. Specializing in leading technologies, worldwide development capabilities and reliable service, we develop customized solutions that help businesses reduce their time-to-market. Rapid Prototyping SLS SLA RTV CNC Machining Tooling and Injection Molding Engineering Services</p>', ''),
(614, 1, 'Lacroix & Associates Consulting', 'lacroix@netidea.com', '406 Richards St, NELSON, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.smallbusinessconsultant.ca ', '(250) 352-3878', '(250) 352-3801', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our team brings years of on-the-job experience to you. Because we have worked in all aspects of small business, you are assured that we understand the business and can provide you with top quality consulting which gets results.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lacroix &amp; Associates Consulting is a Canadian company based in British Columbia. We are a team of professionals with extensive experience in tourism and small business training and operations. Our services include consulting, speaker\'s topics and workshops, and meeting and group facillitation services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company and principal partners believe in constant upgrading of their skills and certification, in order to maintain a high level of competency.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(615, 1, 'Lafarge Canada Inc.', 'don.zakariasen@lafarge.ca', '9028 44th St SE, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', 'www.lafarge-na.com ', '(403) 292-9220', '(403) 236-7554', '', '<p>&nbsp;Lafarge North America is the largest diversified supplier of construction materials in the United States and Canada. Our products are used in residential, commercial, and public works construction projects across North America.Lafarge North America has offices in approximately 900 locations with main offices in Chicago, IL, Calgary, AB and &nbsp;Toronto, ON. Lafarge products-cement, ready-mix concrete, aggregates, asphalt, and related products-are essential in creating the structures that shape our landscape.</p>', ''),
(616, 1, 'LAFCO TOOLING Inc.', 'info@lafco.ca', '7700 Bombardier St, ANJOU, Quebec, Canada', 'www.lafco.ca', '(514) 327-7556', '(514) 327-7625', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lafco Tooling\'s primary mission remains to be Canada\'s most reliable source for Jig &amp; Fixture Tooling Components. We are dedicated to stocking, with a 30% inventory growth each year for the last several years, which has earned us the reputation of a &quot;Stocking Source&quot;! Over and above our traditional inventory, we also offer to carry your inventory... that is, standard or special items that we can release at the time of your choosing, on a blanket-order basis! We are indeed a stocking company!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lafco\'s People... are qualified, specialized technicians ready to help solve your technical problem. We form a solid core of individuals bent on serving you well. We work through lunch hours, and invest the time necessary to get the job done. Our company\'s primary component is people!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lafco Service... is measured in terms of &quot;customer satisfaction&quot;. Long before our ISO 9002 accreditation, our commitment to meeting or surpassing customer expectation has earned us an enviable reputation. Stock orders are shipped the same day, and we strive to deliver all orders on time, as promised! We are not in a trouble-free world however, but we are boastful of how we work for a solution in all difficult situations. Such is the value-added service for which we are known!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For your next Jig &amp; fixture tooling component requirement, call us, and find out why people say we are... Trustworthy!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(617, 1, 'Laflamme Engineering', 'services@laflamme-ing.com', 'P.O. Box 2025, SAINT-JOSEPH-DE-COLERAINE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.laflamme-ing.com', '(418) 423-5050', '(418) 423-7659', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Laflamme Engineering our team is made up entirely of experienced engineers and technicians, all of whom possess undeniable practical abilities and an exceptional passion for engineering. We can handle every engineering problem no matter how complex; by using the most advanced designing tools we can offer you practical and efficient solutions, promptly.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">What makes us different? Our team is extremely dynamic and ever ready to take on challenges. We work every day to develop performing solutions that will allow our customers to excel. We are state-of-the-art in every way and passionate about it.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are committed to working with our customers in order to find the right strategy. Letting their needs be our guide, we will solve their engineering challenges in the most efficient way possible. We develop good designs, backed by thorough calculations and analyses, so our customers can keep competing at the highest level.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(618, 1, 'Lafleur Industries Inc.', 'thibault@industrieslafleur.com', '2359 Fiset Blvd, SOREL-TRACY, Quebec, Canada', 'www.industrieslafleur.com', '(450) 743-3918', '(450) 743-3906', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Our company specializes in the manufacturing of metal bodies for the truck industry, with well over 30 years of experience.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">We are proud to say that cities and large corporations rely on us to custom-build special vehicles, service-units and rescue trucks.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Industries Lafleur inc. meets the standards of the Canadian Welding Bureau W47.1 (steel) and W47.2 (aluminum) as well as to the standard of quality ISO 9001. The Quality Assurance is present in all aspects of our production.&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(619, 1, 'Laforge Doors Ltd', 'laforged@nb.aibn.com', 'P.O. Box 7849, GRAND-SAULT/GRAND FALLS, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.laforgedoors.com ', '(800) 665-3667', '(800) 667-9881', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more than three decades Laforge Doors has been a market leader of quality residential and commercial overhead doors. All our garage doors are manufactured in Atlantic Canada and we proudly services the Canadian, United States and European markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Using only the best components, state of the art manufacturing processes and our focus on quality ensures your door is built to last. Our wide range of styles, options and fully customizable designs allow you to create the door of your dreams.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We offer the widest selection of designs under one roof from the most popular designs to specialty products such as wood, pinch-resistant, fiberglass and screen doors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Find the dealer nearest you to discover why Laforge Doors in the right choice for selection, quality and custom solutions garage doors.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(620, 1, 'LAGA Sports', 'info@lagasports.com', 'P.O. Box 2981 Stn Terminal, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.lagasports.com', '(866) 887-7584', '(866) 379-3114', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LAGA Sports custom manufactures premium quality association and team sports wear. Our company is 100% Canadian owned and operated and is located in Burnaby, BC.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We share our clients\' vision of athletic and team wear perfection. LAGA Sports team wear is built to suit each client\'s specific requirements. Efficient order delivery and short fulfillment wait times are among our top priorities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LAGA Sports delivers sports wear garments of the highest quality. We are an increasingly popular choice for associations and distributors desiring a best-in-class presence with a creative edge.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LAGA Sports is unrivaled in the industry for customer design and creation partnerships. We are rewriting the rules on athletic team apparel performance and presentation and the difference shows on-ice and off. We utilize cutting edge technologies, providing you with unparalleled product design and development options at your fingertips.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LAGA Sports is a young, dynamic company with a clear vision to change the face of athletic team wear. Our partnerships within the athletic community allow us to develop and test products that focus on the unique needs of athletes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LAGA Sports develops and manufactures team wear 100% customized to each team\'s and player\'s individual needs. We commit to create and provide unique, premium quality, leading edge sports wear at a competitive price.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(621, 1, 'Lagace & frere inc.', 'info@benneslagace.com', '1285, rue de l\'Industrie, BELOEIL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.benneslagace.com', '(450) 446-5000', '(450) 446-1594', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All our trucks models have the same characteristics, only the steel varied thicknesses. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Therefore, the difference will be marked by the weight of each. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our trucks are manufactured with premium steel. They are inspected, cleaned with a jet of abrasive, coated with an epoxy primer, sanded and inspected again before the final application of two coats of paint with urethane. All joints exposed to wear are lubricated.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A fast and courteous service is one of the qualities that make legacy &amp; brother\'s reputation. in addition to manufacturing and installing new bins, we can offer even more ...<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- General maintenance of your bucket <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- steel welding work <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- installation of trailer hitch <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- complete hydraulic system installation truck tractor<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(622, 1, 'LaHave Seafoods Limited', 'lahaveseafoods@eastlink.ca', 'P.O. Box 100, LAHAVE, Nova Scotia, Canada', '', '(902) 688-2773', '(902) 688-2766', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Seafood Product Preparation &amp; Packaging</span></p>', ''),
(623, 1, 'Laidback We \'\'R\'\' Inc', 'doug@laptop-laidback.com', 'P.O. Box 271, ARICHAT, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.laptop-laidback.com', '(902) 226-3092', '(902) 226-0066', '', '<p>&nbsp;Using a laptop is often exhausting and painful. &nbsp;This is even more so for anyone with health or mobility issues. &nbsp;We all need to remain productive, connected and contributing even while we are on the mend. &nbsp;Often described as a &ldquo;must have post-op product&rdquo;, &nbsp;the LAPTOP LAIDBACK, a laptop bed table designed for the reclined, delivers the upside of being down. &nbsp; &nbsp;Placing your laptop keyboard precisely where needed by your fingertips, this laptop table for bed, sofa or recliner gets you back in the game while you&rsquo;re flat on your back.</p>', ''),
(624, 1, 'Laipac Technology Inc.', 'diego@laipac.com', '5-20 Mural St, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, Canada', 'www.locationnow.com', '(905) 762-1228', '(905) 763-1767', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LocationNow Inc. is a wholly owned subsidiary of Laipac Technology Inc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laipac Technology is the leader in M2M and location based products. We deliver innovations of location technology for vehicles, assets, merchandise, people and pets. We provide custom-tailored solutions for justice departments and law enforcement agencies. Laipac invests in R&amp;D innovations to develop cutting-edge products and solutions. The company&rsquo;s award-winning products are utilized in over 80 countries world-wide. Share our cause to improve the quality of life and safety for all people.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LocationNow provides high quality of location based service for worldwide customers. The main idea is to provide the peace of mind for company&rsquo;s management, supervisors, health organizations, law enforcement agencies, parents and families. We will help you to select the right device for your application. Do not hesitate to contact us. Thank you for choosing LocationNow.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(625, 1, 'Laiterie de Coaticook Ltée', 'info@laiteriedecoaticook.com', '1000 Child St, COATICOOK, Quebec, Canada', 'www.laiteriedecoaticook.com ', '(819) 849-2272', '(819) 849-4246', '', '<p>&nbsp;<font style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">It was in 1608 that Champlain introduced the first dairy in New France.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Raw milk quickly occupied an important place in the diet of the settlers.</font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 17px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">The birth of big cities and the growing needs of the population brought great changes in the distribution of milk.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">In the 19th century a new economic activity in the country appeared;&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">milk production dedicated to consumption.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">That\'s when the first qu\'&eacute;merg&egrave;rent milk processing establishments;&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">small butter and cheese are created in all regions.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 17px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Marketing of milk and its derivatives is organized.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Some butter and cheese is a dairy equip - where the milk is received and stored before distribution.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">It is this name &quot;Milk&quot; or &quot;Dairy&quot;, which later became the official name of these companies.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 17px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Over time, the &quot;dairy&quot; begin to transfer their milk cans to bottles.&nbsp;</font><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">They will develop larger equipment for washing containers and refrigerate milk, cream and butter.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 17px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">It was in early 1900 that sees the first pasteurizers that allow milk to keep its main qualities of the farm to the table.</font></p>', ''),
(626, 1, 'Lake Erie Warehousing Inc.', 'linem@lakeriewarehousing.com', 'PO Box 339, SIMCOE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.lakeeriewarehousing.com/', '(888) 455-2622', '(888) 455-2622', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lake Erie Warehousing Inc. is a full service 3PL warehouse committed to customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We provide a full range of order fulfillment (pick and pack) services for your growing business. We will take care of your eStore orders and product distribution. Our WMS (Warehouse Management System) will allow us to complete, on time and with precision, your internet fulfillment requirements.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We also have an industrial warehousing division. We have all of the heavy equipment ready to service your Canadian Manufacturing customers. We provide service to many industrial customers in Ontario, with our own trucks and our logistics connections. We will never let a customer\'s plant shut down.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">LEW is big enough to do it right, yet small enough to take the time to care and provide the service you deserve...<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(627, 1, 'Lake Foundry Ltd.', 'mail@lakefoundry.com', '287 South Service Rd., GRIMSBY, Ontario, Canada', 'www.lakefoundry.com', '(905) 643-1248', '(905) 945-2188', '', '<p>&nbsp;Lake Foundry is a Gray Iron Foundry with casting capabilities</p>\r\n<div>for individual items weighing from 1/2 lb. to 15,000 lbs. each.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The foundry is conveniently located just North of the USA/Canadian border midway between Buffalo, NY, USA and</div>\r\n<div>Toronto, ON, Canada.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our American customers have the added advantage of a highly favourable exchange rate between the US and</div>\r\n<div>Canadian currencies.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Lake Foundry focuses on a specific product line which includes</div>\r\n<div>gray iron castings, gear boxes, agricultural machine parts, industrial and residential pumps, as well as electric motor frames for units up to 2,000 hp.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&quot;Over the years, we have invested millions of dollars to make the operation environmentally friendly and are proud to say that emissions from the furnace are now zero&quot;, says Mr. Verdinsek.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>US customers especially like the added cost advantage offered by the highly favourable currency exchange rate between the</div>\r\n<div>US and Canada.</div>\r\n</div>', ''),
(628, 1, 'LakeCity Woodworkers', 'cfyles@lakecityemployment.com', '386 Windmill Rd., DARTMOUTH, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.lakecityemployment.com ', '(902) 465-5000', '(902) 465-2494', '', '<p>&nbsp;LakeCity Employment Services Association is a non-profit agency that offers free employment services to people with a mental illness. Our service is mobile &ndash; which means that we can come to you. And service is available throughout the Halifax Regional Municipality (HRM) &ndash; from Ecum Secum to Hubbards. Our programs use a client-centred approach that encourages clients to build skills that are necessary to sustain themselves in employment.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our goal is to help mental health consumers to improve their quality of life by assisting them to gain independence through work. akeCity began in 1972 as the Dartmouth Activity Centre. As part of the Canadian Mental Health Association, the Centre provided life skills and recreation for clients of mental health services who were reintegrating into the community. Early on, clients identified work as an important means of maintaining their health and LakeCity Woodworkers was begun in response to this demand. Our association was incorporated in 1982 and we moved to our current location. In 1988, the Community Employment Program was added to access a wider variety of employment opportunities.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our retail operation started with a limited range of simple furniture. Today, LakeCity&rsquo;s Retail Store offers a large variety of high quality solid wood products. We assist 50+ individuals in our On Site program, 400 in our Community Employment Program and employ 31 ful-time staff members. We&rsquo;ve recently expanded our building to allow us to continue to grow.</div>', ''),
(629, 1, 'Landmark Feeds Inc. ', 'info@landmarkseeds.com ', 'Highway 205 West, Box 159, ROSENORT, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.landmarkfeeds.com ', '(204) 746-2338 ', '(204) 746-8961 ', '', '<p>Landmark Feeds is a leader in Western Canada&rsquo;s livestock and poultry  industry and has been providing producers with superior quality products  and innovative animal nutrition solutions since 1954. From its humble  beginnings in Landmark, Manitoba, Landmark Feeds now operates 5  state-of-the art manufacturing facilities serving Western Canada and the  north western USA.</p>\r\n<p>At Landmark Feeds, delivering exceptional  customer service and value is our number one goal. Early on, that  philosophy helped Landmark Feeds become a leader in the poultry and  dairy markets while still serving the unique needs of local hog  producers. Landmark Feeds expanded into Alberta in 1995, adding a unique  beef cattle feedlot program to its list of successful programs, which  have rapidly grown and are now setting the standard in the industry. In  1999 Landmark Feeds built the Landmark Nutrition plant, a  state-of-the-art, medication free, micro premix plant in Landmark,  Manitoba. The Landmark Nutrition plant gave our business the opportunity  to continue to be a leader in feed management, nutrition and research,  and to push this advantage beyond the Canadian borders.</p>\r\n<p>Landmark Feeds research is directly linked to the needs of producers and  their industry. The ideas and technology created directly reflects the  real needs of producers. Our research team is comprised of highly  specialized researchers and technical experts that retain the most  profitable technology and transfer it into products and programs that  are more efficient and yield better performance. Thanks to its  recognized Canadian research facilities located across the country,  Landmark Feeds ensures that you benefit from each discovery so that you  maximize performance on your farm.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLandmark Feeds is also committed to bringing you highly skilled field  sales and service teams. The Nutrition Advisor program involves  extensive training and coaching on important topics such as; nutrition  and physiology, growth modeling, barn observation skills, and data  recording and analysis. The investment in our sales and service teams  ensures that we meet your needs and provide sound fact based solutions  for your operation.</p>', ''),
(630, 1, 'Landry Filtration Products Inc.', 'davidl@landryfiltration.com', '11 Cidermill Ave, CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.landryfiltration.com', '(905) 660-1900', '(905) 660-1701', '', '<p>Landry Filtration Products Inc. is an international supplier of custom engineered filtration products. We are located in the Toronto , Ontario region. The company was incorporated in 1988 to offer superior filter media design and quality at competitive prices.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith access to over 4,000 different types of Industrial Textiles and our technical knowledge we provide the ideal solution for any filtration application.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLandry Filtration Products extensive experience in the Pulp &amp; Paper, Mining, Food, Pharmaceutical, Chemical, Plastics and other industries ensures that we provide the most technically advanced products available.</p>', ''),
(631, 1, 'Landview Systems', 'pbarlott@landview.com ', '600-10665 Jasper Ave NW, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.landview.com  ', '(780) 448-7476 ', '(780) 449-5395', '', '<p>BCL Landview Systems Inc. (also known as Landview&trade;, Landview Systems&trade; and Landview On-Line&trade;) provides agri-food production management, GIS and mapping solutions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBCL Landview Systems Inc. is located in Alberta (Western Canada), a province with a thriving agri-food industry. Our parent company Barlott Consulting Ltd. (BCL) has been serving agricultural producers and agribusinesses since 1989 and started the development of the Landview software in 1992. Barlott Consulting Ltd. and BCL Landview Systems Inc. amalgamated in 2011 and now operate as one company BCL Landview Systems Inc. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLandview&trade; is currrently delivering consulting services and field efficiency and obstruction mapping and analysis services through a joint venture partnership with Serecon (offices in Edmonton and Calgary).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur Mission statement to our clients, customers and business partners: &quot;We strive to provide high quality products and responsive professional and technical services. We believe in honesty, integrity and excellence and are sensitive to the needs of our clients and business partners and are dedicated to their satisfaction.&quot;</p>', ''),
(632, 1, 'Lang BoatWorks', 'ChristopherLang@shaw.ca;langboatworks@gmail.com', '7255 Brentview Rd, BRENTWOOD BAY, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(250) 652-5552 ', '', '', '<p>We build and sell a variety of solid wood caskets, coffins and urns,  that are completely biodegradable.  NO particleboard, toxic glues or  finishes.                                                               At Lang BoatWorks we build, maintain, and repair quality  marine joinery (woodwork).  We also build custom soild wood doors and  millwork.</p>', ''),
(633, 1, 'Langfab Fabricators Ltd. ', 'reception@langfab.com;langfab@uniserve.com ', '19405 Enterprise Way, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.langfab.com', '(604) 530-7227', '(604) 530-4482', '', '<p>LangFab Fabricators Ltd is a manufacturing company specializing in the production of high quality, but cost effective truck bodies, trailers and related equipment for the Canadian and U.S. trucking industry.</p>', ''),
(634, 1, 'Langley Awning Co. Ltd.', 'sales@langleyawning.com', '304 - 20445 - 62nd Ave, LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.langleyawning.com', '(604) 530-2554', '(604) 530-1382', '', '<p><br />\r\nLANGLEY AWNING &amp; SIGN is a family owned business that has been operating for over 20 years. We specialize in the manufacturing and installation of various types of signs, awnings and rollshutters. The staff at Langley Awning and Sign are highly qualified professionals who have extensive experience in the installation and application of all of our products. We take great pride in making our customers happy with their purchases from us. We service all areas of the Lower Mainland, including Vancouver, Surrey, Langley, Burnaby, New Westminster, Richmond, Coquitlam, Port Moody, Port Coquitlam, Maple Ridge, Abbotsford, and Chilliwack. In addition, we service Vancouver Island. Come to Langley Awning and Sign and see the difference quality makes. Enjoy peace of mind, knowing that we are fully insured and our employees are covered by the Worker&rsquo;s Compensation Board of B.C.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe offer a full range of product options for both commercial and residential applications, including manual and motorized awnings equipped with sun and wind sensing devices. There is a full range of colors and fabrics to choose from. Let our experienced and knowledgeable staff create the perfect outdoor area for you with a retractable awning. Our retractable awnings are custom ordered for you and are of the highest European quality. They will last many, many years when properly cared for.</p>', ''),
(635, 1, 'Langley Concrete LP ', 'jasono@langleyconcretegroup.com', '20152 Logan Ave, LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.langleyconcretegroup.com', '(604) 533-1656', '(604) 533-8191', '', '<p>Langley Concrete and Tile Ltd. was incorporated in 1961, sixteen years after being started in 1945 when Jacob Omelaniec began making well linings (tile) for his neighbours and other farmers in Aldergrove.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs his business grew he made a decision to move to Langley Prairie (now Langley City) in 1947 to continue expanding his production capabilities and to expand his market. With Jacob making the product and Nettie, his wife, helping and doing the books, business continued on with their two sons Mike and Sam helping out after school and on the weekends.<br />\r\nThe plant in Langley, currently the site of the companies head office and a distribution yard for local customers, was expanded four times over the next ten years.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe untimely death of Mike in 2003 due to complications while being treated for lung cancer slowed the building process but in 2006 the highly productive and efficient &lsquo;Superplant&rsquo; was commissioned.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe strength of The Langley Concrete Group lies in it&rsquo;s employees. We currently employ 95 people at the Chilliwack plant and another 25 in Victoria at Lombard Precast. The company closed the Abbotsford and Langley production facilities but retained a distribution yard in Langley on the site of the Logan Ave. plant.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCurrent management has a philosophy of increasing market share by reducing costs and increasing production capabilities while investing in new forms and equipment to expand product capabilities. Investments made to protect position in the market, stream line production, and further product lines match a desire to be the most efficient concrete products manufacturer in B.C. and the Pacific Northwest.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThrough the cooperation of our employees and the constant reinvestment of the shareholders the company is continuing to grow and progress with a culture of safety, enabling of employees and responding to the direct needs of customers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe future of Pre-cast concrete products is strong and Langley Concrete Group is confident that through perseverance and hard work it will be able to satisfy the needs of both their customers and their employees.</p>', ''),
(636, 1, 'Lapaco Paper Products Ltd. ', 'info@lapaco.com ', 'P.O. Box 119, Bureau-Chef Stn, SAINTE-CATHERINE, Canada', 'www.lapaco.com ', '(450) 632-5140', '(450) 632-5142', '', '<p>Lachine Paper Company was founded in 1950 by a young tool designer,  Ren&eacute; Derail, who enjoyed the challenge of building machinery that could  generate high quality products. While his first equipment was designed  to create butterchips, he quickly saw the need to build machinery that  delivered premium quality disposable products, specifically, placemats,  traycovers and doilies. When Ren&eacute; began his company it was based in the  town of Lachine but in 1970, as his business grew, he invested in land  in Ville Ste-Catherine and built, what is now, our corporate  headquarters. With the change in town came the change in name and  Lachine Paper Company became Lapaco Paper Products Ltd.</p>\r\n<p>In the mid-1960&rsquo;s Henry Pascone joined Lapaco in operations and in  the mid-1970&rsquo;s Dan Derail joined his father in the business as a sales  person. Today Dan and Henry jointly own Lapaco and have carried on the  tradition of producing the highest quality disposable tabletop, bakery  and other related items in the industry.</p>', ''),
(637, 1, 'LapTech Precision Inc.', 'salesl@laptech.com', '230 Simpson Ave S, BOWMANVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.laptech.com  ', '(905) 623-4101', '(905) 623-3886', '', '<p class=\"info-text\">Lap-Tech Inc. was founded in 1972 to provide quartz  blanks and proprietary crystal processing equipment to the Frequency  Control industry.</p>\r\n<p class=\"info-text\">A  change of name to Laptech Precision Inc followed the company purchase by RFX Ltd in 2010 and adds the facility to the group.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs pioneers in industrial lapping and polishing techniques the  company evolved into a key supplier of high quality components to  Aeronautical and Telecom Industries. In 1980 the company began  production of finished quartz resonators and today provides high quality  oscillators and resonators to Telecom Industries throughout the world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"info-text\">The company, which is located in a 15,000 square  foot facility in Ontario Canada, employs  highly skilled personnel, its   unique blend of products and services include precision quartz  resonators supplied to oscillator manufacturers worldwide, quartz and  alloy material fabrication to exacting parallel and optical polish  standards and high precision OCXO, TCXO and VCXO oscillators  manufactured by the parent company. Additionally a range of miniature  smd oscillators purchased from qualified sources are provided to augment  the group manufactured products.</p>\r\n<p class=\"info-text\">In  2010 a joint group Research and Development  programme was initiated to study resonator Phase Noise performance   under severe shock and vibration. This programme will provide valuable  data to improve Phase Noise performance in precision crystals and  oscillators for use in telecomms, transport and military applications.</p>\r\n<p class=\"info-text\">Continued factory development with new clean room  facilities and equipment for crystal production to 500MHz will maintain  Laptech precision Inc at the forefront of quartz resonator design.</p>', ''),
(638, 1, 'LAR Machinerie Inc.', 'info@lar.qc.ca', '1760, rte 169, MÉTABETCHOUAN-LAC-A-LA-CROIX, Quebec, Canada', 'www.lar.qc.ca', '(418) 349-2875', '(418) 349-8415', '', '<p>Today, Groupe LAR and its subsidiaries make up a dynamic industrial group. They are one of the few who are able to offer integrated DESIGN, MANUFACTURING and INSTALLATION services for a wide range of markets including aluminum smelting, hydroelectric generation, mining or any industrial production.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis completely integrated approach, along with the acquisition of its latest subsidiary, iCrane, has enabled Groupe LAR to reinforce its position in the national and international arenas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nGroupe LAR developed from LAR Machinerie inc., founded in 1942 in M&eacute;tabetchouan in Lac-Saint-Jean.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nIn 1988, LAR Matagami inc. was founded. Located in northwest Quebec, it was created during the construction of the enormous dams on James Bay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nIn 1989, Consultants Procad inc. was created.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nIn 2008, the acquisition of iCrane Systems inc. completed the current structure of Groupe LAR.</p>', ''),
(639, 1, 'LARCAN', 'jadamson@larcan.com', '228 Ambassador Dr, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 564-9222', '(905) 564-9244', '', '<p>TV Technology has learned that LARCAN, a Canadian television and radio transmitter manufacturer that has been in operation since the early 1950s, ceased operating on July 10, several sources familiar with the situation confirmed. One said the company shut its doors and dismissed the roughly 35-40 employees remaining at its Mississauga, Ontario and Lafayette, Colo. operations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to one source, employees were given no notice of the impending closure. They were told only that they were now without jobs and given orders to remove their personal belongings and turn in keys and company-issued credit cards.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnother source reported that the order to discontinue operations had come from Sumavision, Larcan&rsquo;s majority owner based in China. LARCAN began a partnership with Beijing&rsquo;s Sumavision Technologies Co., Ltd. in 2009, with that company acquiring a controlling interest in LARCAN in late 2013.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMultiple LARCAN executives did not respond to queries about the shutdown, which one source said came after orders for transmitters &ldquo;dried up.&rdquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLARCAN had a long-established global reputation in the field of both solid-state and vacuum television transmitters in all power ranges. The company also manufactured FM broadcast transmitters and translators, as well as mobile DTV products. LARCAN has also provided of a range of engineering services in connection with transmitter installations.<br />\r\n&nbsp; <br />\r\nLARCAN was formally established in 1981 when employees of the Canadian General Electric and the LeBlanc and Royale organization purchased CGE&rsquo;s broadcast operation. The name LARCAN is an acronym for LeBlanc And Royal CANada. Until recently, LARCAN has been Canada&rsquo;s only manufacturer of both radio and television transmitters. (Editor\'s note: Nautel introduced its first DTV transmitter line at NAB last year, and Technaligix, which came to our attention in the comments below, was &ldquo;derived from a major U.S. broadcasting company,&rdquo; according to its website, and &ldquo;incorporated in 1995.&rdquo; - See more at: http://www.tvtechnology.com/article/larcan-closes-its-doors/271300#sthash.bVMzR4l3.dpuf</p>', ''),
(640, 1, 'Laria Inc ', 'info@laria.ca', '425-1396 Sainte-Catherine St W, MONTRÉAL, Quebec, Canada', '', '(514) 908-9753', '(514) 313-5655', '', '<p>Laria Inc. is an electronic seals manufacturer for the tank transport  industry. The product line also includes standard security seals, fleet  management systems and oil spill control equipment.</p>', ''),
(641, 1, 'Larken Automation', 'larken@storm.ca ', '13-5350 Canotek Rd, GLOUCESTER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.larkencnc.com ', '(613) 746-5685 ', '(613) 746-6451 ', '', '<p>Founded in 1989 by Larry kenny , Larken Automation started building small xy tables for printed circuit board drilling and prototyping. In 1991 we started producing large xyz systems for the signmaking and woodworking industries. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll mechanical, electronic and software has been developed by Larken Automation over a period of 13 years.<br />\r\nOur design goals have been to reduce mechanical and electronic complexity by designing advanced software and also utilizing modern IBM-PC technology to provide a very reliable and powerful motion control.<br />\r\nOur new StarCam Windows control sets the standard for easy to use CNC .<br />\r\nCustomer satisfaction is very important to us and we are constantly developing new and inovative products.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe reliability of our many systems in the field is extremely high and we offer one of the best warrantees in the business. </p>', ''),
(642, 1, 'LaSalle NHC Inc', 'info@lasallenhc.com', '9620, rue Saint-Patrick, LASALLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.lasallenhc.com  ', '(514) 366-2970', '(514) 366-2971 ', '', '<p>Lasalle | NHC offers high quality services in various fields of hydraulics, i.e. hydraulic structures, open channel hydraulics, ice hydraulics, urban hydraulics, coastal engineering and microclimate studies. For each project, we provide studies tailored to the needs of our clients.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs of May 1st, 2014, we have decided to join forces with Northwest Hydraulic Consultants (NHC), a company specialized like us in hydraulic modelling and water resources. The new company called Lasalle | NHC will remain in the Montreal facilities that have been housing LaSalle since its foundation in 1956 and will be an independent subsidiary of NHC&rsquo;s parent company, based in Edmonton. The new company will be managed by LaSalle&rsquo;s current owners, who will also become NHC shareholders.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis merger will confirm our presence all over the continent, with offices or laboratories in Canada (Montreal, Edmonton, Vancouver), the United States (Seattle, Sacramento), as well as in Brazil (Sao Paulo).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile still relying on the quality of the expertise for which the LaSalle Consulting Group is renowned, our clients will now benefit from a broader range of services, spanning all aspects of water resources. Our network of laboratories and experts will also lead to a more rapid and efficient answer to our clients&rsquo; modelling needs.</p>', ''),
(643, 1, 'Laser Metal Profiles Limited ', 'cbuffone@lasermetalprofiles.com', '15-225 Sheldon Dr., CAMBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.lasermetalprofiles.com', '(519) 623-8965', '(519) 623-1053', '', '<p>Our laser cutting work is in support of multiple industry sectors. Accurate and intricate laser cut shapes can be cut into a wide variety of materials. The dimensions of laser cut profiles can be nested to meet customer specified tolerances and exact reproductions can be guaranteed. Virtually no distortion of the laser cut part is caused due to low heat input.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLaser cutting is faster than traditional profiling and will often be competitive on cost alone. Our expert nesting process allows us to optimize material yields to also keep costs down.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe also offer state-of-the-art bending/forming services. Secondary processes such as machining/welding/plating and painting services are available to complete your order requirements. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLaser Metal Profiles Limited was incorporated in June of 2002 to supply precision laser cut parts in carbon and stainless steel, and aluminum materials.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe team at Laser Metal Profiles has considerable previous experience in the laser cutting business, and mandated a policy to acquire the very best equipment available, to ensure quality products, on a timely basis, and at competitive prices.</p>', ''),
(644, 1, 'Latem Industries Limited', 'sales@latem.com', '90 Struck Crt, CAMBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.latem.com', '(519) 740-0292', '(519) 740-8436x', '', '<p>Specializing in ultrasonic metal cleaning, vibratory metal finishing, machine tumbling, metal polishing, blasting, and metal part washing processes for your metal finishing needs.&nbsp; As an ISO registered company, we pride ourselves on supplying every industry with top quality products and offering expert technical knowledge and metal finishing solutions. Whether you are developing a new product or looking to improve an existing one, let our 35 years of experience work for you.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLatem Industies specializes in metal finishing technologies. Over 35 years of experience, expertise, and engineering have allowed Latem to become a world leader in their industry. Companies in the automotive, aerospace, furniture, military, recreational vehicles, rail, and tools industry rely on metal finishing services from Latem Industries. Latem also offers a unique approach to the metal finishing business: products can be packaged and labelled immediately by Latem, so that they can be shipped directly to their end destination, saving time and inventory costs for our customers. Parts can also be coated or painted directly at Latem Industries, which also shortens the time between manufacturing, and getting parts to their end destination. Latem industries is the only provider needed, for all things metal finishing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLatem is an expert at providing services in a rapid manner, allowing higher productivity, and greater output for our customers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLatem Industries has one of the strongest reputations in the part finishing and part washing, across many different indsutries including automotive, aerospace, furniture, military, recreational vehicles, rail, and hand tools. Our upper management has over 100 years of combined industry experience, and our business has been in operation for over 35 years. Trust Latem with your next metal finishing project.</p>', ''),
(645, 1, 'Latest Jewels', 'finegem@hotmail.com;anu@latestjewels.com ', '602-60 Bristol Rd E, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.latestjewels.com', '(905) 507-0483', '', '', '<p>You probably heard diamonds are a girls best friend. Ladies like their jewelry, always have and always will. At Latest Jewels you&rdquo;ll find over 700 unique jewelry products. Including Anniversary Rings, Anklets, Children&rsquo;s Jewelry, Choker Necklaces, Engagement Rings and more&hellip; I hope you find what you&rsquo;re looking for.</p>', ''),
(646, 1, 'LatinAffaires', 'info@latinaffaires.com', '2257, rue Parthenais, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.latin-affaires.com', '(514) 528-0717 ', '(514) 528-1932', '', '<p>We are a Canadian company with over 10 years of experience specialized in communication management focused on business, strategic and operational development projects in Canada and Latin America.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur service area ranges from the creation of advertising campaigns to market research.Latin Affaires makes the difference because we have a vast market experience in communications between Latin America and Canada.Our company is well aware of the Canadian communications media and customs of its travelers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLatin Affaires speaks your language; we believe that with our help your country will be one of the favorite destinations for Canadians.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBusiness Planning and Development:<br />\r\nBusiness Plan (launch or relaunch)<br />\r\nStrategic Development Plan<br />\r\nFeasibility Studies<br />\r\nStudies of economic benefits</p>\r\n<p>Media Strategic Relationship between Canada and Latin America:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLatin Affaires has a vast network of contacts including TV channels in Latin America and business partnerships with the largest Canadian communication companies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(647, 1, 'Lauga & Associates Consulting Ltd', 'tomlauga@port-plan.com', '4716 Meadfield Pl., WEST VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.port-plan.com', '(604) 926-7905', '(604) 909-4915', '', '<p>Lauga &amp; Associates are port planning and marine consultants.&nbsp; Our work is port planning, computer simulation, waterways management and management consulting to marine sector public and private agencies.We plan marine terminals, assess waterways development projects, develop port master plans, prepare port marketing strategies, optimize port operations and determine the operational and financial feasibility of new port and marine investments.We prepare baseline studies that our clients use to make decisions about investments and operations.We use computer simulation to test the efficiency of port plans and operational plans.&nbsp; <br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nEstablished in 1983, Lauga &amp; Associates Consulting Ltd. is an independent privately held consulting firm.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMore than 100 port planning and marine projects have been completed.&nbsp; Project locations have included: Canada, Vietnam, China, India, Pakistan, Jordan, Iraq, the Sudan, Brazil, the Netherlands, Ireland, U.S.A., Southern Africa, New Zealand, Australia and the Caribbean.&nbsp; We apply the following methodologies:<br />\r\nOperational Analysis - The firm has experience with developing port industrial lands, equipment costing, industrial warehouse location and layout analysis.&nbsp; Operations for containers, bulk materials, forest products and general cargoes have been assessed.<br />\r\nOperations Research - Using techniques such as computer simulation, operations research methodologies have been applied to: terminal operations optimization, materials handling systems analysis, ship logistics, river transport systems, cargo wharves and their supporting cargo storage areas and warehouses and linking truck and rail systems, vessel traffic management and the design of aids to navigation systems.<br />\r\nProject Management - Services in project management include: developing terms of reference and detailed work specification documents, creating work breakdown structures, project plans of operations, project evaluation, project mission reports, project progress reports, management of project consultants, project budgeting and scheduling.<br />\r\nEconomic and Financial Analysis - Services include: cost benefit studies, economic risk analysis, financial analysis, market studies, multi-modal and system optimization of transport networks, and defining development concepts and economic strategies.<br />\r\nManagement Consulting - This work has included: developing business plans, development master plans, marketing opportunity studies, new enterprise financial projections and conducting management seminars.</p>', ''),
(648, 1, 'Laurentide Aviation', 'info@laurentideaviation.com', '870, ch. Saint-Fereol, LES CEDRES, Quebec, Canada', 'www.laurentideaviation.com', '(450) 452-4882', '(450) 452-4405', '', '<p>Learning to fly is one of life\'s most rewarding adventures.Whether you are considering learning to fly for recreation, or to pursue a career in aviation, you are about to embark on one of the most exciting and enjoyable experiences of your life.<br />\r\n&nbsp;There are many options available for people who wish to go sightseeing.Our pilots can give a custom tour of Montreal and the beautiful surrounding region for one, two or three passengers. A typical tour over downtown Montreal is about one hour in duration. Our fully trained and certified, on-site maintenance staff takes care of our entire fleet, as well as aircraft owned by our customers.We also provide maintenance services to many private aircraft owners.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLaurentide Aviation is based at Les Cedres Aerodrome (CSS3), which is located just west of the Island of Montreal<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLaurentide Aviation first got off the ground in 1946, when founder Jack Scholefield completed his military career with the R.C.A.F. His original goal: to provide the best professional flight training in Canada.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are still a family business, owned and operated by Terry McConnon, and proud of our personalized service. Our staff continues to be committed to friendly, competent first class service, including a guarantee that there will be no waiting around for takeoff.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are still determined to provide the best professional flight training in Canada. The major United States airlines hired over 15,000 pilots in previous years.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(649, 1, 'Laurier Glass Ltd.', 'laurier@laurierglass.com', '300-153 Laurier Blvd, LAURIER-STATION, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.laurierglass.com', '(418) 728-2023 ', '(418) 728-2961', '', '<p>Located in Quebec City, LAURIER is a third generation family business with a reputation that is second to none. Founded in 1950, through the years it has developed solid expertise in glass processing. The company specializes, among other things, in the production of sealed units, tempering coloring and shaping of glass. Its reputation has also been built on the many variants of its products, developed over time to meet the needs and requirements of its clients. At LAURIER, the field of expertise is as much in the manufacturing industry as it is in the commercial, institutional and residential construction sectors. Located in Laurier-Station, its 145,000 ft2 of facilities house highly specialized equipment, allowing LAURIER to meet the most demanding requirements of the market with unequaled quality and service. The reputation for excellence that LAURIER has acquired is based primarily on its reliability, one of the company&rsquo;s most important foundational values. Its mission is to offer all its clients a service that is personalized and attentive. Its high-quality products are consistently delivered on schedule, as promised. LAURIER enables its clients to distinguish themselves with a unique and innovative image, which is why the company is a proven partner of your success! LAURIER is proud to be able to count on its qualified and dedicated team. In addition to contributing to the growth of the company, the team reflects the effort it invests to achieve a high level of excellence.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLAURIER is specialized in the manufacture and production of all types of glazing, both functional and decorative. This wide range of glass products will meet all your needs, whether your project is architectural, commercial or industrial. </p>', ''),
(650, 1, 'LAUZON Inc', 'info@lauzonltd.com; lauzon@lauzonltd.com ', '2101, côte des Cascades, PAPINEAUVILLE, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.lauzonflooring.com  ', '(819) 427-5144 ', '(819) 427-6531', '', '<p>Great design, like great art and architecture, has the power to transform our world and lift us up. Wood, with its organic and intricately patterned grains, has inspired artists and artisans, designers and architects for millennia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor today&rsquo;s discerning homeowners, fine hardwood flooring lends a mark of distinction to any room.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor nearly 30 years we have dedicated ourselves to marrying the artistry of finely crafted wood with the science of producing resilient, naturally comfortable and &ndash; equally important &ndash; comforting floors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis allows us to manufacture unparalleled hardwood flooring in an impeccable array of woods, tones, and colors. Lauzon floors compliment any style, from urban minimalist through classic contemporary to more traditional d&eacute;cors. Each of our collections offers refined elegance.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe beauty of a wood floor begins with a sapling. At Lauzon, we take pride in the sustainable stewardship that guides us through the entire process, from forest to floor.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLong before it was fashionable, we were dedicated to building a business that embodies best practices in environmental and social responsibility. With the latest advances in science and manufacturing, our Pure Genius hardwood floors even help make your home a healthier living space, adding to your sense of well-being.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur designers understand your relationship with the surfaces you and your family walk on, rest on, play on and live on. When you choose our exemplary comfort and visual appeal you are choosing to minimize your environmental footprint, too.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWelcome to Lauzon and rediscover beauty in nature.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(2147, 387, 'JEN Ecuador Import & Export Corporation', '', NULL, 'JarabedeMapleSyrupEcuador.com', '6092239217 Magic Jac', '', '', 'Distributor, manufacturers rep. New Business however was in business in Canada for over 30 years, Service industries, housing, Marine etc.', ''),
(2148, 388, 'Forest Hill Family Dental', 'foresthillfamdentistry@bmwquest.com', 'Suite 26, 395 Greenbrook Drive Kitchener, , Kitchener, ontario, canada', 'http://foresthillfamilydental.com', '519-578-1300', 'Forest Hill Family D', '', '', ''),
(2149, 388, 'Forest Hill Family Dental', 'foresthillfamdentistry@bmwquest.com', 'Suite 26, 395 Greenbrook Drive Kitchener,, Kitchener, ontario, Canada', 'http://foresthillfamilydental.com', '519-578-1300', 'Forest Hill Family D', '', '<p>&nbsp;<style type=\"text/css\"><!--td {border: 1px solid #ccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--></style><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\" data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Our clinic serves a wide number of dentistry needs. We can provide preventative dental care, as well as performing interventions when necessary. Our experienced team can help provide you with cosmetic dentistry services such as veneers, teeth whitening services, and more. If our team also helps provide dental care for fillings, hygiene and cleanings, crowns, bridges, root canals, and more.&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:15107,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;4&quot;:[null,2,16777215],&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0,&quot;14&quot;:[null,2,3355443],&quot;15&quot;:&quot;inherit&quot;,&quot;16&quot;:12}\">Our clinic serves a wide number of dentistry needs. We can provide preventative dental care, as well as performing interventions when necessary. Our experienced team can help provide you with cosmetic dentistry services such as veneers, teeth whitening services, and more. If our team also helps provide dental care for fillings, hygiene and cleanings, crowns, bridges, root canals, and more.</span></p>', ''),
(652, 1, 'Law Offices of Sylvain Roy', 'info@sroy.ca', '1508-507 Place D\'Armes, MONTREAL, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.sroy.ca  ', '(514) 946-8300', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sylvain Roy is a Canadian attorney (Quebec Bar), IP strategy consultant and IP valuation specialist. Sylvain offers a vast experience of licensing, and generally, of helping technologies moving to world markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We assist SME&rsquo;s, research centers, institutions and individual inventors with regard to technology transfer, intellectual property licensing, IP valuation and IP management projects.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our focus: the commercialization and monetization of intellectual property (IP) rights and technologies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We guide and accompany our clients through the fast-paced and high-pressured rigors of exploiting their valuable inventions; from concept ideas to full market deployment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">His past entrepreneurial experiences with technology companies provided him with a holistic know-how of operation, marketing and finance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sylvain operates from Canada (Montreal) and is regularely available for meetings across Europe and S-E Asia.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">His experience of local markets covers China, Europe (Western and Central), North-America, S-E Asia.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lawyer practicing in Intellectual Property (IP), commercial law and corporate law legal areas. Consultant in licensing strategies and IP valuation for a corporate clientele in Europe, America and Asia (1999-present).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Held executive positions at technology companies, as general counsel, COO and CEO. (1994-2002)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founding partner and COO of Kunst Macchina (Montreal), a developer of software-based media control environments and control systems. (1995-1998)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Solicitor in civil law, commercial law and civic rights legal areas. (1994-1996)</span></p>', ''),
(653, 1, 'Lawry Shooting Sports Inc. ', 'derek@lawryshootingsports.com', 'P.O. Box 2153, CALEDONIA, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.lawryshootingsports.com', '(905) 765-3343', '(905) 765-5450', '', '<p>Lawry Shooting Sports Inc. has been in the business of manufacturing clay targets since 1975. We produce the most precise, consistent and uniform target on the market today. All of our target lines meet ATA, NSSA, and NCSA specifications. We supply factory direct targets at very competitive prices across North America. Trailer load and partial trailer load quantities are delivered with our own fleet of air ride trailers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll of the targets we manufacture are non-toxic to the environment. Unlike most other manufactures this claim has been verified by an accredited independant body.</p>', ''),
(654, 1, 'Layer 7 Technologies Inc.', 'info@layer7.com', '405-1100 Melville St , VANCOUVER, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.Layer7.com', '(604) 681-9377', '(604) 681-9387', '', '<p>In April 2013, Layer 7 was acquired by CA Technologies, which has continued to develop the company&rsquo;s award-winning API, mobile, SOA and cloud technologies as CA API Management. It&rsquo;s the same great API management technology, with many new features and innovations planned for release in the near future.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCA Technologies (NASDAQ: CA) creates software that fuels transformation for companies and enables them to seize the opportunities of the application economy. Software is at the heart of every business, in every industry. From planning to development to management and security, CA is working with companies worldwide to change the way we live, transact and communicate.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCA software and solutions help our customers drive enterprise-wide productivity, offer differentiated user experiences and open new growth opportunities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd, we are able to deliver this value across multiple environments &ndash; mobile, private and public cloud, distributed and mainframe.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur goal is to be recognized by our customers as their critical partner in the new application economy. </p>', '');
