(655, 1, 'MAAX Bath Inc', 'info@maax.com', '160 Saint-Joseph Blvd, LACHINE, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.maax.com', '(514) 844-4155', '(514) 985-4155', '', '<p>At MAAX we\'re driven to bring the most popular trends and innovations to our customers to help them create their dream bathroom.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMAAX offers a broad range of bathtubs, showers and shower doors that provide the unique style, lasting quality and simple solutions desired by all our customers. By meeting rigorous quality and durability standards while offering a wide variety of product shapes, sizes, styles and prices, MAAX aims to be your brand of choice for bath products.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nInnovative product features and designs, achieved by being at the forefront of research and development in our industry, coupled with the use of quality materials and continued operational excellence, will make us the proud choice provider of complete bath product solutions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSupporting our products by delivering a superior customer experience for all customers, those who buy, sell and install them, with the use of proper tools, training, and systems makes doing business with us as easy and pleasurable as using one of our products.</p>', ''),
(656, 1, 'Marcor Woodwork Ltd.', 'martym@marcorwoodwork.com', '3245, 54th Ave SE, CALGARY, Alberta, CANADA', 'www.marcorwoodwork.com  ', '(403) 258-2088 ', '(403) 258-0269 ', '', '<p>Marcor Woodwork Ltd. based in Calgary, Alberta, CA&nbsp; has been manufacturing quality architectural millwork throughout Canada and the U.S.A. for various sectors of the building industry for over 20 years. We provide complete manufacturing services through our 20,000 sq. ft. facility with in-house engineering, drafting, design, custom veneering, state of the art CNC machining processes, a finishing shop and expert installations. We enjoy the challenge of customized projects in providing quality workmanship and completion to the customer\'s satisfaction. with an unwavering commitment to providing clients with personalized service and superior craftsmanship. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarcor specializes in creating contemporary, as well as traditional commercial environments, including but not limited to, institutions, healthcare, offices, high-end residential and public spaces. We are multi-level tasked; our shop can integrate solid woods and veneer components with stone, glass, metal, solid surfaces and fabrics. Our manufacturing includes all varieties of interior custom woodwork, such as doors, and frames, cabinets, counters, displays, bars, wall panels, casings, furniture, work stations, boardroom tables and fixtures.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarcor is a Fabrication Partner of www.3form.com a leading manufacturer of translucent building materials solutions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarcor\'s team of highly-skilled woodworking cabinetmakers and professionals with a broad range of experience in engineering, drafting, finishing and installation of your custom millwork will guarantee your satisfaction. We have completed projects across Canada and the United States for our customers who are major and independent retailers, professional firms, contractors, developers, architects and designers. A list of past projects and clients is available upon request.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarcor is a member of AWMAC (Architectural Woodwork Manufacturers Association of Canada). On Feb. 24, 2012&nbsp; Marcor received the award of Product Design and Quality for Excellence in Architectural Woodwork for building the new Birks&nbsp; store in TD Square, Calgary.</p>', ''),
(657, 1, 'Mac Skylights ', 'info@macskylights.com', '5214, 93rd St NW, EDMONTON, Alberta, CANADA', 'www.macskylights.com  ', '(780) 435-3761', '(780) 435-1716', '', '<p>Mac Skylights has been in business for almost 40 years and has built the reputation of being the premier business for producing and installing plastic and glass skylights in Western Canada. We invite you to browse around our site and get a good look at our products and services.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo provide maximum natural lighting, a skylight is the answer. Unlike conventional wall windows, skylights are never totally in the shade. The amount of daylight reaching the interior of a structure through a skylight is up to 5 times greater than the amount of light from a wall window of equal size. Skylights also provide a more even distribution of natural light.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStudies have shown that natural light is crucial to our well being and healthier for our eyes than artificial light. Artificial lighting is depressing and has an adverse effect on our minds and bodies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSkylights not only improve visual conditions in a building; they also create an atmosphere more stimulating to its occupants. In homes and buildings with skylights, plants grow abundantly no matter where they are placed within a room. Interior furnishings are seen in their true colors only under natural light. Not only are skylights an asset to any room because of the natural light they transmit, they also offer savings in electric power costs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn industrial and commercial buildings, skylights improve working conditions and offer unrestricted use of floor and wall space. The likelihood of vandalism and break-ins is reduced. Operable skylights provide ventilation and roof access. Skylights can be beneficial in building entrances, lobbies or foyers to spotlight pleasing features such as planters, fountains or works of art.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe use of skylights is bringing about new design concepts in both residential and commercial construction. Skylights bring the outdoors indoors; yet with an abundance of light, are wonderfully private.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMac Skylights are available in a variety of sizes, shapes, styles and colors for individual or clustered installation on all types of buildings. Don\'t be deceived by imitations, insist on a Mac Skylight, the ultimate in design, variety and quality!</p>', ''),
(658, 1, 'Madawaska Doors Inc.', 'mdi@madawaska-doors.com', 'PO Box 850, BOLTON, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.madawaska-doors.com ', '(905) 859-4622', '(905) 859-4654', '', '<p>Madawaska Doors is a family owned, Canadian manufacturer of custom solid wood doors. Since 1974, our team has worked hard to earn an international reputation for beauty, craftsmanship and environmental responsibility.We at Madawaska Doors are committed to the environment. Wood is a renewable, reusable, recyclable and biodegradable. Non-wood products require far more energy to manufacture than wood.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe supplies of ores and petroleum for the production of metal and plastic are finite and cause pollution of the air and water, contributing to global warming. One pound of wood grown in a vigorous younger forest removes 1.47 pounds of carbon dioxide from the atmosphere and replaces it with 1.07 pounds of life-sustaining oxygen.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWood is also the best insulator of all structural building materials, with millions of tiny air cells trapped within its cellular structure providing a barrier against the heat and cold. An inch of wood is 15 times as efficient an insulator as concrete, 400 times as efficient as steel and 1770 times as efficient as aluminium. Homes built from wood require far less energy to heat and cool, thus conserving fossil fuels and coal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a very real sense, wood products are the most environmentally responsible building material anyone could ever use. In addition, our manufacturing facility gathers all saw dust made from our equipment into a silo where a machine compresses the saw dust into firewood briquettes. These firewood briquettes are used to heat our manufacturing facility.We are proud of our \'special order\' association with many of North America\'s most reputable home improvement and millwork retailers. </p>', ''),
(659, 1, 'Madina Mechanical Inc.', 'info@madinamechanical.com', '200-5818 Sheppard Ave E, SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.madinamechanical.com ', '(416) 424-4328 ', '(416) 424-4328 ', '', '<p>The people behind Madina Mechanical Inc. have been specializing in heating and cooling products whether it be conventional heating furnaces and air conditioners or ductless products for your home, business and industry since 1994. We provide sales, installation and support for all the leading ductless tankless, Hydronic and conventional manufacturers. We can help you choose which products are that right for your needs in Air Conditioning , Heating, Hot Water Heating (domestic, radiators) and Air Quality (ERV/HRV\'s and Humidifiers).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe provide services anywhere within the Greater Toronto Area.Our sales personnel know what works best for your situation, we understand that product placement is a leading concern for home owners along with equipment that works. Therefore we will strive to work with you to make your living and working space both highly attractive and functional.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur installation crews are professional, courteous, knowledgeable and highly experienced in their fields. Our crews attend industry seminars and classes regularly to keep up-to-date with all the latest products and technology. We use only&nbsp; the best material for your home during installation so that your unit looks just as good in 15 years as it did the first day. We strive to provide only the best service for our customers and we will try and exceed your expectations for both installations quality and post-installation clean up.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe provide industry leading support, post-installation for all of our customers with personalized troubleshooting, knowledgeable staff and competitive warranty terms with Lifetime heat exchanger warrnty for furnaces, 1 years parts and labour for all of our products (5 years for all Bryant products) and 5~6 year terms for compressors with air conditioning products through the manufacturer. Additional warranties can also be purchased by the client.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHeating and cooling is not a luxury when you are living in Toronto, It is a necessity. In fact if you have no heat in winters it can become life threatening. A reliable heating and air cinditioning system is a must. Having said that the energy costs are also becoming absurd day by day, which demands for the latest energy efficient technology.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe new energy efficient furnaces, programable thermostats, Hydronic heating and cooling systems, ductless air conditioners, and tankless boilers are some of the latest smart energy options for heating and cooling your home and office.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA reliable and efficient heating and cooling systems is also useful in keeping you fit and healthy. Every one wants to be warm during winters and cool in the summer without spending a fortune. Ask our certified&nbsp; technicians to provide you customized heating and cooling solutions to save energy and lots of money. <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(660, 1, 'Maribex ', 'info@maribex.com', '805-277 St George St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.maribex.com ', '(416) 925-2735 ', '(416) 925-1873 ', '', '<p>We are located in Toronto, Canada, and provide quality translation and interpretation services from Japanese to English and from English to Japanese. Our services also include Russian-Bulgarian-English translation.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe specialize in various business and technical fields, which are of interest to companies whose goal is to conduct business successfully in North America or Japan. Our major areas of specialization include: manufacturing process implementation, automotive industry, energy related industries, advertising and marketing. Japanese interpretation services are also provided in the field of social service.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur language services include translations of documents and other materials of general, technical, and marketing nature. We also provide translation of website contents.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur interpreting services provide help for business meetings, business conferences and seminars, as well as any other language assistance in the communication between Japanese and English speakers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe help you overcome the language barriers and provide value-added services. </p>', ''),
(661, 1, 'Marid Industries Limited', 'marid@marid.ns.ca', '99 Windsor Junction Rd, WINDSOR JUNCTION, Nova Scotia, CANADA', 'www.marid.ca', '(902) 860-1138', '(902) 860-4500', '', '<p>Marid Industries is a leading manufacturer of custom steel structures with export capabilities throughout North America.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarid specializes in the construction and reinforcement of high rises, railroads, hospitals, office buildings and highway bridges.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe company has been expanding its capabilities since 1983.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe will be the preferred company for structural and architectural metal fabrication and services, in Canada, the U.S and abroad.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe will constantly seek ways to provide more value to our clients.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are committed to supporting and challenging our employees to be the most capable, competent and well trained in the industry.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarid is a full-service contractor unlike many companies in the structural steel business. Marid is a fabricator as well as a construction company with ample engineering capabilities. At Marid, we are used to dealing with both owners and general contractors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMarid is able to reduce costs for clients through standardized design elements. Under the Nova Scotia private-public partnership agreement, Marid has been involved in the construction of no fewer than 25 new schools. This innovative construction program produced substantial savings in on-site construction costs over traditional methods.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIntegrity and trust explain success, a success that has resulted in continued strong relationships within the Industry. Marid is also price competitive, while consistently aiming for zero project deficiencies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(662, 1, 'Market Pursuits Inc.', 'bonnie@marketpursuits.com', '2 Jullin Court, HAMMONDS PLAINS, Nova Scotia, CANADA', 'www.marketpursuits.com', '(902) 476-3333', '', '', '<p>We are Marketing Consultants, Business Consultants and Instructors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you need an experienced business consultant, management coaching, training, marketing plan, business plan, qualified prospects, process redesgn or a funding proposal, we are here to help.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe have a wide variety of experience in many industries, home and abroad.&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur business consultants provide assistance with business start-up, business development and growth. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe have cut costs, avoided costs, increased quality and improved customer service. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur Marketing Consultants and Business Consultants in Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada, will work with you to help your business development needs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur experienced consultants will help you with business development, marketing plans, business plans, productivity, and funding proposals.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nYour organization will benefit from leadership coaching, team facilitation, training, business development consulting, or leave it all to us to develop.</p>', ''),
(663, 1, 'Mason Place', 'info@masonplace.com', '25987 Woodbine Ave R.R. 2, KESWICK, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.masonplace.com', '(905) 476-5545 ', '(905) 476-7163', '', '<p>Over the years, we have endeavoured to please our customers with quality products and excellence in workmanship and service. Many of our satisfied customers have returned to thank us for the work we have done for them, and to express the enjoyment they are receiving from their fireplace or stove.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur company is a member of the Hearth, Patio and BBQ Association of Canada. A number of our staff members are also certified by the Wood Energy Technology Transfer Inc. (WETT), the national registrar of the Wood Energy Technical Training Program, recognized by insurance companies. We have an experienced, safety conscious, certified gas fitter for our gas installations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHPBAHearth, Patio &amp; Barbecue Association (HPBA) is an international trade association first established in 1980 to represent and promote the interests of the hearth products industry in North America. Mason Place is also proud to be associated with them. It is yet another way that we believe you can have confidence in purchasing products from us.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMason Place is pleased to offer you top quality product at an affordable price.</p>', ''),
(664, 1, 'Matador Converters Co. Ltd.', 'matador@matador.ca', '270 De Louvain St W, MONTRÉAL, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.matador.ca', '(204) 632-6663', '(204) 633-8826', '', '<p>Matador Converters, with head office in Montreal and a production facility in Winnipeg, Manitoba, has been serving the textile industry for over half a century, since 1945.Matador Converters is also an international player in domains as diverse as geotextiles, air filtration mediums, medical and health products, lingerie, home decoration, furniture, upholstery, aircraft manufacturing, military government, to name a few and is constantly developing new products, through innovative manufacturing systems and processes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEarthwrapTM and PowderfillTM are also available throughout the Far East from our production facility in China. </p>', ''),
(665, 1, 'Matrix Solutions Inc.', 'calgaryreception@matrix-solutions.com', '200 - 150 - 13 Ave SW, CALGARY, Alberta, CANADA', 'www.matrix-solutions.com', '(403) 237-0606 ', '(403) 263-2493 ', '', '<p>Matrix is a Canadian and employee-owned environmental and engineering consulting company that has roots dating back to 1984. Our long history gives us an edge in understanding environmental challenges facing our clients. We are proud of our record of providing innovative and cost-effective solutions to environmental challenges and helping our clients meet regulatory and shareholder expectations for environmental performance.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Solutions&rdquo; are our focus. We understand that our clients&rsquo; business involves a number of stakeholders from regulatory agencies to landowners and neighbours, and environmental challenges can be straight forward or very complex. This understanding allows us to integrate our technical knowledge and team experience across disciplines and locations and develop effective solutions for each challenge.</p>', ''),
(666, 1, 'McArthur Medical Sales Inc. ', 'mmsi@mcarthurmedical.com', '1846, 5th Concession W, ROCKTON, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mcarthurmedical.com', '(519) 622-4030', '(519) 622-1142 ', '', '<p>At McArthur Medical Sales Inc. (MMSI) we offer high quality products for home and professional healthcare, personal fitness and asthma control. Today many people take a keen interest in their health. As a result, individuals require products in their homes that will enable them to maintain a healthy lifestyle.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEstablished in 1984, MMSI represents manufacturers from Canada, United States, England and Europe. Through our four business units: Hospital Specialty Products, Medical Supply Dealers, Home Health Care and Retail Pharmacies we are proud to offer innovative, cost effective and high quality products, prompt service and informed advice.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;...McArthur Medical Sales Inc. work tirelessly to create and maintain long-term business relationships. Our continued success is only a result of our customers satisfaction...&quot;</p>', ''),
(667, 1, 'McCoy Foundry Co.', 'foundrysales@amccoy.com', '1890 Highway 5 W, TROY, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.amccoy.com', '(519) 647-3411 ', '(519) 647-3740 ', '', '<p>Foundry producing all Iron Grades &amp; all Steel Grades of Castings from pounds to 1600 lbs.</p>', ''),
(668, 1, 'McLean Systems Inc.', 'jpullam@mcleansystems.com', '78 Apricot St., THORNHILL, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mcleansystems.com', '(416) 571-5552 ', '(905) 881-8752', '', '<p>We create websites that help small and mid-sized businesses serve their customers. We understand how to get the right traffic and how to convert leads into sales.&nbsp; And we&rsquo;ll be there in the long term to answer your questions and keep your website timely.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe love to tackle the unusual.Whether you need a project manager,a troubleshooter, or an experienced professional to help you assess a strategy, we have the know-how.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe have broad experience on a variety of information technology and general business disciplines. Are you looking for help from someone who has been there? We enjoy tackling the unusual; let us know what your needs are and we\'ll be happy to advise.</p>', ''),
(669, 1, 'MDG', 'info@MDGFOG.com', '10301 Pelletier Ave, MONTREAL-NORD, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.mdgfog.com', '(514) 272-6040', '(514) 722-3229', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For over 30 years, MDG has created superior-quality fog and haze generators for entertaiment, industrial, firefighting and military customers. From day one, we have pursued advancing our technology to keep making the best generators on the market.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe result? Our generators are used on a majority of Broadway and West End productions, as well as on large-scale performances like the Cirque du Soleil and major theme park attractions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur fog generators are also put to more intense use to train firefighters, military and industrial workers in disaster simulations.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are a proud Canadian company based in Montreal, Quebec, and our products are distributed worldwide.</p>', ''),
(670, 1, 'Measurand Inc.', 'support@measurand.com', '2111 Hanwell Rd, HANWELL, New Brunswick, CANADA', 'www.measurand.com', '(506) 462-9119', '506) 462-9095', '', '<p>What do Measurand Sensors do?<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- Track shape and motion where cameras cannot see...<br />\r\n- The snap of a neck during a car crash<br />\r\n- The shape of a seat<br />\r\n- A complex curve for a car body design<br />\r\n- The motion of an athlete\'s knee<br />\r\n- The sweeping moves of a dancer<br />\r\n- Eddying currents of hot explosive gas<br />\r\n- A crumpling door just before the airbag deploys<br />\r\n- The position of a medical tool<br />\r\n- The shape of a spine<br />\r\n- Who needs these sensors?<br />\r\n<br />\r\n- Auto companies designing safer and more comfortable cars<br />\r\n- Manufacturers improving efficiency of industrial processes<br />\r\n- Manufacturers of simulation and training systems<br />\r\n- Manufacturers of games and internet tools<br />\r\n- Aerospace designers and maintenance workers<br />\r\n- Remotely operated vehicle pilots<br />\r\n- Physicians and biomedical workers<br />\r\n- Rehabilitation clinics<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHow do Measurand Sensors work?<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCameras take in reflected light and form images. Measurand<br />\r\nsensors mimic the complex curves of human or inanimate bodies,<br />\r\ntranslating shape into electronic signals. Unlike cameras, they<br />\r\ndo this directly on the objects, requiring no extra space,<br />\r\nfocusing, or bright lights, and can move with the bodies,<br />\r\ntranslating even the fastest moves into computer images or<br />\r\ncontrol signals. Measurand sensors do this with specially<br />\r\ntreated optical fibers used not to send telephone and television<br />\r\nsignals, but to sense curvature (bend and twist).</p>', ''),
(671, 1, ' Mecanarc Inc. ', 'info@mecanarc.com', '180, rue Lucien-Thibodeau, PORTNEUF, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.mecanarc.com  ', '(418) 286-6060', '(418) 286-6416', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Depuis sa cr&eacute;ation, M&eacute;canarc inc. a su se d&eacute;marquer comme leader en entrepreneur g&eacute;n&eacute;ral en construction industrielle mais aussi comme sp&eacute;cialiste dans le domaine de la fabrication m&eacute;canique, du d&eacute;veloppement de produits sp&eacute;ciaux ainsi que dans la construction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCette pme qu&eacute;b&eacute;coise a vu le jour en 1996 alors que son propri&eacute;taire, M. Romain Julien remarqua les carences et les besoins en sous-traitance industrielle, en machineries et en pi&egrave;ces de toutes sortes des grandes entreprises du comt&eacute; de Portneuf. Il d&eacute;cida&nbsp; donc d&rsquo;implanter, dans sa ville natale, une entreprise se vouant &agrave; la conception, &agrave; la fabrication, &agrave;&nbsp; la sous-traintance industrielle, &agrave; la soudure adapt&eacute;e, &agrave; la tuyauterie et &agrave; la m&eacute;canique au niveau des grandes entreprises et des industries.<br />\r\nDepuis ses d&eacute;buts, M&eacute;canarc n\'a cess&eacute; de grandir et d\'innover dans plusieurs sph&egrave;res touchant de pr&egrave;s les bases premi&egrave;res de l\'entreprise. L\'usine a subit de maintes agrandissements et innovations pour r&eacute;pondre &agrave; la demande croissante, tels que la chambre de peinture, la salle de jets de sable, la table de coupe au plasma et la menuiserie. Un service complet d\'ing&eacute;nierie permet &agrave; M&eacute;canarc d\'&ecirc;tre les meneurs en r&eacute;alisations de projets sur-mesure complexes dans divers domaine. De plus, M&eacute;canarc se sp&eacute;cialise, depuis 2002, en construction r&eacute;sidentielle, commerciale et industrielle pour offrir un cl&eacute;-en-main &agrave; ses clients.</p>', ''),
(672, 1, 'MF1 Marketing', 'ideas@mf1.ca', '1-535 Panet Rd, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, CANADA', 'www.mf1.ca', '(204) 237-8514', '(204) 233-8908 ', '', '<p><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you&rsquo;ve come here wanting to find out how big we are, how many awards we&rsquo;ve won or how many clients we&rsquo;ve served in our 25 years, here are your answers: Not too big. Enough. Quite a lot, actually.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow we&rsquo;ve got that out of the way, let&rsquo;s discuss what&rsquo;s really important: how special you are. There&rsquo;s no one else out there exactly like you. Not only is your brand unique, but so are your challenges and needs.&nbsp; That&rsquo;s why before we can start creating things like print ads, brochures or websites for you, we&rsquo;ll need to get to know you better. We&rsquo;ll ask lots of questions, like where have you been, and where is it you want to go? We&rsquo;ll also want to know about who you are talking to. What do they care about? What motivates them? Why buy you over the competition? And don&rsquo;t worry; if you don&rsquo;t have all the answers we can help there too.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe important thing is, our inquisitive nature means that you won&rsquo;t be getting a cookie cutter solution. Instead you&rsquo;ll end up with something that makes sense for both your brand and your business, and helps you truly move the needle.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs someone special you&rsquo;d expect nothing less.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHow we can help.<br />\r\nBranding and Marketing Support<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBrand strategies, marketing plans, research, product packaging, POS materials, brochures, dealer/retailer support<br />\r\nAdvertising and Promotions<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAdvertising (print, radio, TV, interactive, outdoor), direct mail, email marketing, social media consultation, media planning and buying<br />\r\nInteractive Media<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCustom websites, database integration, eCommerce, multimedia<br />\r\nCorporate Identity and Communications<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBrand identities and logos, stationery, signage, annual reports, newsletters, visual presentations, trade displays, press releases<br />\r\nSports and Event Marketing<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEvent management, fundraising initiatives, press conferences, community and brand activation, celebrity integration</p>', ''),
(673, 1, 'MGP Information Systems Ltd. ', 'info@mgpinfo.com', '201-140 Renfrew Dr., MARKHAM, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mgpinfo.com', '(905) 513-0170', '(905) 513-0177', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Malone Given Parsons Ltd. is a consulting firm providing services in: Master Planning, Project Planning, Environmental Planning, Tourism &amp; Recreation, Market Analysis, Development Management, Geographic Information Systems<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Malone Given Parsons Ltd. has provided planning and development consulting services to private and public sector clients since 1978. The firm is committed to the multidisciplinary team approach with experience and expertise in all areas of the process - from land use and environmental planning to market analysis and development management. Our business is assisting our clients to plan and execute change. This requires the knowledge and imagination to recognize opportunities and identify development concepts, the rigour to analyze and evaluate options, the insight to define the appropriate plan of action and the organization and committee to manage implementation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Malone Given Parsons Ltd. has an international reputation for providing advanced technical expertise and management skills to the design and implementation of utility and municipal information systems, using GIS technology. Malone Given Parsons was founded in Toronto, Canada in 1978.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Malone Given Parsons Ltd. specializes in advanced research and practical applications of technical and organizational issues in GIS implementation for utility and municipal applications. The research results are applied to advanced, flexible and practical applications for utility and municipal clients. The wide range of issues involved in the development of a complex municipal and utility management system requires an equally broad range of skills and experience. Our project experience in large utilities and municipal governments effectively places Malone Given Parsons Ltd.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">in the forefront to address the broad vision and complex issues that face municipal governments and utilities today.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(674, 1, 'MHS - Mold Hotrunner Solutions', 'info@mhs-hotrunners.com', '60 Armstrong Ave, GEORGETOWN, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mhs-hotrunners.com', '(905) 873-1954 ', '(905) 873-0131', '', '<p>MHS is an advanced manufacturing company specialized in high performance, runnerless injection molding systems. We add value to your plastic part by improving your processing methods as well as the tools that power them. Using thorough analysis and innovative design, we engineer and build complete hot runner solutions optimized for your specific goals. Our team of specialists always delivers measurable results, and is ready to support you and your project anywhere, anytime and throughout all stages of Our core objective is to always improve your Profitability, Part Quality and Environmental Footprint.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn a knowledge driven industry, access to the right people and their ideas is a highly critical asset. We draw on the expertise and insight gathered from thousands of successful molding applications to ensure that your project is in good hands. We think a hot runner supplier should be more than just a top quality hardware manufacturer. That\'s why MHS fosters a passionate environment of engineering excellence and true innovation. We are a research driven solution provider with a focus on real world applications. Count on us to be your expert resource with the highest level of processing experience anywhere.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince 2002, we have created products and services that improve the way your injection molded parts are made. We continue to deliver robust and sustainable solutions for our clients and industry partners around the world. Headquartered in Georgetown, Ontario, MHS is focused on driving industry-leading part designs and highly efficient molding operations. Our superior hot runner technologies are found in a variety of solutions ranging from medical devices to automotive components. Our sales, manufacturing and technical support centers in North America and Europe take proactive measures to ensure the highest level of customer service and system quality.</p>', ''),
(675, 1, 'Miccar Aerial Ltd', 'michael@goodspiritair.com', ' P.O. Box 128  Del. Centre Stn, YORKTON, Saskatchewan, CANADA', 'www.miccaraerial.com', '(306) 786-3345 ', '(306) 786-3339 ', '', '<p>Miccar Aerial Ltd. &amp; Good Spirit Air Service lease the entire Terminal Building at the Yorkton Municipal Airport.&nbsp; This is the main business base for all the related company operations. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the summer of 2011 Miccar Aerial completed the construction of a 10,800 sq ft heated hangar at the Yorkton Airport.&nbsp; This has provided the means for us to move to this next phase of growth and opportunity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe current fleet is a new Thrush 510P full dual controlled and 2 AT 401 Walter turbine equipped spray aircrafts also equipped with rotary atomizers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMiccar Aerial operates the aerial business guided by rules from the Canadian Air Regulations.&nbsp; A copy of our AOC is available which covers details of all operations of the company.&nbsp; Details of the Operations Manager, Chief Pilot and Person Responsible for Maintenance, as well as all operational aspects of the operation are contained in the Operations Manual.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(676, 1, 'MicroWay Systems Inc.', 'cd@microwaysystems.com', '193 Bloomfield Ave, OUTREMONT, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.microwaysystems.com', '(514) 239-3545 ', '', '', '<p>Microway Systems Inc. specializes in state-of-the-art technical domains since 1984. Our main activities cover research, development and consulting services.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOver the years, Microway developed several highly technical products and performed numerous consulting mandates. Our goal is to maintain the delicate balance between product development and consulting services.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe product development provides the hands-on experience and knowledge required to optimize the quality of our consulting services.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMicroway personal have over 100th of years of RTCA/DO-178B, RTCA/DO-178C, RTCA/DO-278 and RTCA/DO-254. Microway CEO is an independent TCCA Design Approved Representative.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMicroway systems inc. offers the following services:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTraining seminars on RTCA/DO-178B, RTCA/DO-178C, RTCA/DO-278 and RTCA/DO-254 standards.<br />\r\nGap analyses<br />\r\nIndependent Verification and validation (IV&amp;V)<br />\r\nOn the job coaching</p>', ''),
(677, 1, 'Milestone Inventions Ltd. ', 'at4000george@hotmail.com', '254A-25246 TWP Road, CALGARY, Alberta, CANADA', 'www.milestoneinventions.com  ', '(403) 234-7547 ', '(403) 234-7546 ', '', '<p>At Milestone Inventions, we invent quality parts, tools, and revolutionary <br />\r\nmachinery. At the present time we have several products out on the market, <br />\r\nand several which will be on the market soon.</p>', ''),
(678, 1, 'Millennium Marine Inc', 'cory@millenniummarine.ca', '244 Escuminac Point Rd, ESCUMINAC, New Brunswick, CANADA', 'www.millenniummarine.ca', '(506) 228-4619', '(506) 228-3688', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Millennium Marine is a fiberglass boat builder with over 65 years experience manufacturing specialized vessels for Serious Fishermen, Law Enforcement Departments, Research Organizations, and other Professional Operations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Guimond Family has been building boats since the 1940&prime;s in the small fishing village of Escuminac located near Miramichi, New Brunswick. Over 600 boats have been built over three generations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The performance, stability, and comfort of the &ldquo;Millennium&rdquo; design introduced 2002 has broadened the marketplace to specific clientele in need of specialized vessels for Serious Fishermen, Law Enforcement Departments, Research Organizations, and other Professional Operations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Now, with a production facility located in the United States, boats can be sold as commercial fishing boats, USCG certified passenger vessels, and other work boats without restrictions to our US customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Maine Built Boats of Superior Quality will be manufactured in a state of the art facility located in Eastport Maine, the Easternmost City in the United States.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Millennium Marine USA offers custom design, quality craftsmanship, and proven products. The product line consists of Miramichi, Millennium, and Donelle Series hulls ranging from 25&prime; to 52&prime;.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our team will build the boat YOU want from the design stage to all points of detail throughout the construction process.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We want your Business and Satisfaction is Guaranteed!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(679, 1, 'Miral International Inc. ', 'info@miral.ca', '7-2750 14th Ave, MARKHAM, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.miral.ca', '(905) 305-1005', '905) 305-0552 ', '', '<p>Consultant to manufacturers of Dietary Supplements, Herbal and Pharmaceutical products.</p>', ''),
(680, 1, 'Misfit Studios', 'admin@misfit-studios.com', '41 Trinnell Blvd, SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.misfit-studios.com', '(416) 857-2433', '', '', '<p>Misfit Studios Role Playing Games is a small press publishing company that endeavours (yes, we&rsquo;re based in Canada, so that&rsquo;s the sort of spelling you&rsquo;ll see on this site) to publish the kind of role-playing game products we ourselves want to bring to the gaming table to enjoy.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nQuite simply, we at Misfit Studios are, and shall always be, gamers first and foremost, and that fact shall be the driving force behind everything we do.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe publish a wide range of role-playing game products for a variety of game systems, often under license. Misfit Studios is also currently working on developing its first in-house set of rules, PD46FX, and a set of rules for dynamic miniature gaming.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are constantly in need of playtesters &mdash; even if it&rsquo;s just to proof read and double check game stats. If there is a product line you are interested in helping out with, email us with the subject line &ldquo;Playtesting&rdquo; and let us know why you think you&rsquo;d be a good fit and with which product lines you want to help.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnd when we say we want you to &ldquo;playtest&rdquo; for Misfit Studios Role Playing Games, we don&rsquo;t necessarily mean you have to put everything through its paces in an actual game. Usually, it is good enough to have a look at something, proof it, consider how it would operate in a game, and give feedback. Most playtesting is actually about assessing and evaluating new content.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSo, if you think you know the rules well enough for any of the role-playing game systems we are currently producing for, email us and sign up for some playtesting!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Misfit Studios Role Playing Games old message boards continued to break and find new problems arising with each required security update. The latest was the final straw that broke the software&rsquo;s back, rendering BBcode unusable. Considering this was the second iteration of the board we hosted on our own site that broke down during regular updating being glitchy, Misfit Studios has decided to move the message boards off-site.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor quite some time, most customer and fan interactions have been via our blog and other social media outlets, so the relevancy of the message boards have long since been downgraded anyway. Still, they remain handy for product announcements and running playtests, so we have created a new board off-site, where we won&rsquo;t have to worry about upgrades and the like. The new message boards may be found here. So far, there&rsquo;s little there (beyond the playtesting materials a typical visitor can&rsquo;t see), but this will change over time.</p>', ''),
(681, 1, 'Mitec Telecom Inc.', 'sales@mitectelecom.com', '3299 Jean-Baptiste-Deschamps Blvd, LACHINE, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.mitectelecom.com', '(416) 972-5066 ', '', '', '<p>Diosat Ltd. is a Canadian company based in Montreal, QC.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt was formed in June 2008 to provide in order to support clients who have satellite networks but need a place to find all relevant accessories.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe have a small team of dedicated professionals who can have years of experience in finding any kind of related equipment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe want to save our customers time so that they can focus on their business.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe original company renamed itself to Mitec Technologies and sold off all of its telecom and satellite assets.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor the passive components such as waveguide, couplers, terminations, etc... we keep the same Mitec part numbers to simplify the buying process for our clients.<br />\r\nFor active components such as BUCs or SSPAs in CBand, KuBand, XBand, we have suitable alternatives available for any Mitec WTX or MTX product.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you have any exisiting Mitec Telecom equipment which needs replaced or updated we can help. See the data sheet below on our passive components.</p>', ''),
(682, 1, 'MJM Furniture & Textile ', 'info@proffdesign.ca', '103-163 Cowie St , GRANBY, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.proffdesign.ca ', '(514) 978-0242', '(888) 574-9148 ', '', '<p>We are specialized in the manufacturing of fine furniture for 3 to 5 Star properties.<br />\r\nAn international team and our awarded designers guarantee the highest standards.<br />\r\nOur services comprise the design, planning, production and supply of fittings for all areas of the hotel, according to customer&acute;s individual wishes.<br />\r\nOur customers are the Mandarin Oriental Group, Ritz Carlton, Starwood, Radisson SAS, Best Western Hotels, IHC Hotels - Holiday Inn,&nbsp; Hampton Inn and many more.<br />\r\nWe have large Showrooms, where we present more than 30 fully equipped hotel rooms..<br />\r\nWe would be very happy to have you among our valued customers soon.</p>', ''),
(683, 1, 'MLT ', 'sdavidson@mlt.com', '1500-1874 Scarth St, REGINA, Saskatchewan, CANADA', 'www.mlt.com ', '(306) 347-8000', '(306) 352-5250', '', '<p>MLT is an expertise-based, full-service law firm of 130 lawyers serving clients across Western Canada from offices in Regina, Saskatoon, Calgary, Edmonton and Vancouver. We have been practicing in the west since 1920 and have in-depth knowledge of the region\'s business, legal and political landscapes. Over the past decade we have developed a significant regional presence in the west, and are one of the 30 Largest Law Firms in Canada (Lexpert / American Lawyer Media).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMLT and our lawyers receive high rankings for the quality of our work from Chambers Global, Benchmark Canada, Best Lawyers, Martindale-Hubbell and Lexpert. We are currently ranked as the leading Saskatchewan law firm by Chambers Global and the leading Saskatchewan litigation firm by Benchmark Canada. We have also been named one of the top Western Canadian law firms by Canadian Lawyer Magazine (based on legal excellence and expertise, service excellence, significant mandates, client base, and regional service coverage), and a Fortune Magazine Go-To Law Firm.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are committed to doing our part to make the communities in which we live and work better places for all. Our firm, and our lawyers and staff, donate significant time and financial resources to enhance the culture, health and well being of our communities. The following charities lead the extensive list of community and business initiatives we support United Way, Regina &amp; District Food Bank, Hospitals of Regina Foundation, St. Pauls Hospital Foundation, Royal University Hospital Foundation and Make A Wish Foundation.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe view ourselves as partners in the ventures of our clients. Our role is to help our clients succeed by bringing our experience and legal expertise to each assignment. We invest in understanding their business, the issues they face and their goals and objectives, and in turn, efficiently and effectively address legal, political and regulatory challenges.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(684, 1, 'MM Plastic (Mfg.) Co. Inc.', 'wayne@mmplastics.com', '1301 Blundell Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mmplastics.com', '(905) 277-5514', '(905) 277-3060', '', '<p>MM&reg; Plastic (Mfg.) Co. Inc. is a privately held manufacturing company that began operation in 1962. Our head office is located in Mississauga, Ontario and is comprised of both a manufacturing and warehouse facility. We have an additional manufacturing plant in the Buffalo, NY area.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are injection molders of high-volume, lightweight plastic products. Our areas of expertise range from the electrical industry to the automotive, consumer products, packaging, fittings and closures businesses. We have the ability to mold a variety of materials, including, but not limited to, nylon, polyethylene, polypropylene, styrene, thermoplastic rubbers, glass-filled nylon, polycarbonate and PVC. MM&reg; Employees work together to creatively satisfy the needs of our broad and diversified customer base.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe hold a number of patents, produce over 700 different products and export throughout North America and Mexico, as well as parts of Asia and the Caribbean.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur staff is closely involved with UL and CSA on the various harmonization committees in an attempt to not only develop, but to set high industry standards. MM&reg; Plastics believe that by bringing these standards to their highest levels, the result will be a greater safety for the public and end-users.</p>', ''),
(685, 1, 'MMG Canada Limited ', 'mail@mmgca.com ', '10 Vansco Rd., ETOBICOKE, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mmgca.com', '(416) 251-2831 ', '(416) 251-6790 ', '', '<p>MMG Canada Limited specializes in the design, development and manufacture of magnetic materials and components, including soft ferrites, permanent magnets and iron powder. Our products are used in a variety of applications in the RF and microwave communications, automotive, defence and aerospace electronics, CATV distribution, instrumentation and consumer markets. With manufacturing bases in both North America and Asia and applications engineering staffed facilities around the world, MMG Canada is perfectly positioned to provide local support to our customers for all of their magnetics needs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMMG Canada Ltd specializes in the design, development and manufacture of magnetic materials and components, including soft ferrites, permanent magnets and iron powder. Our products are used in a variety of applications in the in the RF and microwave communications, automotive, defence and aerospace electronics, CATV distribution, instrumentation and consumer markets. With manufacturing bases in both North America and Asia and applications engineering staffed facilities around the world, MMG is perfectly positioned to provide local support to our customers for all of their magnetics needs. Attention to detail and a knowledgeable staff meet specific needs if not with our vast array of standard parts, then with a custom component designed to your specifications.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMMG\'s beginnings goes back over 70 years as several different operating companies. The Neosid family of companies began manufacturing magnetic materials in the United Kingdom in 1936. They expanded their operations into Toronto, Canada in 1952 and Lilyfield, Australia in 1956. The Port Chester, New York Krystinel Corporation founded in 1954 was acquired by the UK based Magnetic Materials Group (MMG) in 1989. In 1990, the Group also acquired the magnetic interests of Salford Electrical Instruments (SEI). In 1974, the Chennai based EID Parry India Limited, a subsidiary of the Murugappa Group, with the assistance Siemens, began the operation of a soft ferrite plant in Chennai, India. This facility was later acquired by the TT Group in 1997. The UK based TT Group, now known as TT electronics, acquired MMG in 1992.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn 2010 MMG was acquired from TT Electronics. MMG Canada Ltd continues to be commited to it\'s global markets and customers and will continue it\'s supply focus into leading manufacturers in the automotive.&nbsp; telecommunications, computing and industrial electronics markets.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMMG Canada Limited,&nbsp; will also continue it\'s focus on global reach, establishing technical and manufacturing facilities in strategic countries and maintaining the successful formula of close liaison with our customers in most major overseas markets.</p>', '');
