(686, 1, 'MNTC', 'info@mntc.ca', '562 21st St W, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.mntc.ca', '(604) 773-9448', '(604) 200-7355', '', '<p>MNTC is one of the best Multinational diversified natural resource companies. The Group&rsquo;s industrial and marketing activities are supported by a global network of more than&nbsp; 8 offices located in 7 countries including but not limited to Canada, China, Malaysia, Singapore, Turkey, United Arab Emirates, and Iraq. Our diversified operations comprise of 2 steel Manufacturing plant in the Middle East, and oil production refineries. We employ approximately 90 people, including contractors.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMNTC combines the knowledge gained through our own diversified range of commodities with the strength of our unique marketing capability. We value our background, experience and we\'re proud of the service and quality we offer to our customers. We have a diverse range of products, customers and markets, outstanding management and an enviable portfolio of development projects.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nProject management is the application of Information skills, tools, and techniques to activities involved with a project in order to meet project needs. it can include&nbsp; developing requirements, determining realistic goals, managing the triple constraint, and adapting the various plans as needed to achieve the goals of the project and stakeholders. Project management can start with selection of the suitable process associated with completing the work of the project. In addition, it can involve using an established methodology to align project and product requirements with the product specifications. </p>', ''),
(687, 1, 'Mobile Energy Inc. ', 'mscheltema@mobileenergyinc.com', '925 Devonshire Ave, WOODSTOCK, Ont, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mobileenergyinc.com ', '(519) 537-2369', '(519) 537-6944 ', '', '<p>Mobile Energy Inc. is one of North America&rsquo;s premier suppliers of mobile substations, specializing in designing and manufacturing lightweight compact units.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur products feature superior functionality, enhanced safety and convenience. We custom build to your specifications and ship internationally.ISO certified manufacturer!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCustomized energy solutions Mobile Energy Inc. has been a specialty manufacturer of high-performing mobile substations, mobile circuit switchers and mobile circuit breakers for nearly 20 years. Our mobile transformers feature up to 60 MVA and 230 KV. Our design philosophy focuses on service and mobility. Each unit is custom designed to your exacting specifications. While other manufacturers may adapt traditional transformers and place them on wheels, our core business is mobile power technology. We build smaller, lighter, more compact units that can be transported easily on our custom trailers. Our mobile substations are user-friendly service vehicles &ndash; and smaller units mean big savings in transportation, installation and operating costs. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nImpeccable safety Our manufacturing facility is ISO 9001 certified. We have a perfect safety record &ndash; and all our units are ergonomically designed with the safety of your operators as our priority. Our management team Mobile Energy Inc. is led by Bill Scheltema who has worked with mobile power technology for 35 years. Bill champions Mobile Energy&rsquo;s mission to be the manufacturer of the most fully customized mobile substations in the world. Bill and his experienced team of engineers and technicians work with state-of-the-art technology at their new 180,000 square foot manufacturing facility in Woodstock, Ontario.</p>', ''),
(688, 1, 'Mobilextension Inc. ', 'info@mobilextension.com', '500-20 Adelaide St E, TORONTO, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mobilextension.com', '(416) 943-0001', '(416) 943-0002', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The versatility in mobilextension&rsquo;s functionality enables all types of users to utilize the tool for a variety of different purposes, offering a number of advantages that are sure to benefit all. Users ranging from students to business professionals, and family members to team mates, can all find value and enhanced efficiency through mobilextension, regardless of their goal.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Key benefits: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Time efficiencies: Decrease the amount of time required to share critical information with others through conventional methods<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Automatic syncing of information to mobile devices allows users to immediately use their list<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Increase productivity as a result of up-to-date information<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cost savings:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Communicate effectively to an unlimited number of people at a low cost<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">No limits or minimum requirements on uploading or distributing lists<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Organization and communication:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize schedules, contacts, listings and communicate in an efficient manner<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize distribution lists to ensure easy mobilization of data<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure instant communication of up to date information<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ease of Use:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">User-friendly interface enables any type of user to use tool.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Flexibility:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Same functionality across all mobile devices (iPad/iPhone, Android, Windows Phone or BlackBerry)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sync data and immediately utilize on any mobile device &ndash; e.g. activate maps, dial phone numbers, etc.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(689, 1, 'Molyslip (Canada) Inc', 'www.molyslip.com ', '20-1145 Bellamy Rd N, SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.molyslip.com', '(416) 438-5523', '(416) 438-5513', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 40 years Molyslip has been producing superior lubricating products for the Automotive, Industrial &amp; Marine and Home &amp; Recreational markets<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In the High Performance and Extreme Stress automotive and industrial environments, Molyslip is recognized for quality products that deliver high performance and durability and help to keep your equipment running longer, smoother, and at lower operating cost<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We&rsquo;ve been &lsquo;Road Tested&rsquo; for 40 years. We&rsquo;re proud of it and we&rsquo;re also proud of the company we keep, our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We look forward to serving you.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(690, 1, 'Momentum Technologies Inc', 'admin@momentum-tech.ca', '412-825 Lebourgneuf Blvd, QUEBEC, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.momentumtechnologies.ca', '(418) 681-6363', '(418) 681-7720', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES&rsquo; mission is to provide top-notch consulting services that meet our clients&rsquo; needs and exceed their expectations. Our focus is Oracle and Java. Making the most of our team&rsquo;s experience and providing for their ongoing professional development means we can offer our clients truly state-of-the-art IT solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our mission is guided by the core values that underpin the relationship of mutual respect and trust we build with every one of our clients. MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES&rsquo; core values are expertise, respect, quality, professionalism, and team spirit. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES&rsquo; quality management system is a set of business best practices designed to constantly improve the quality of service we offer our clients. Every assignment we undertake includes quality assurance plans, client satisfaction evaluation, and regular client follow-up at key junctures to ensure that we immediately identify potential problems and implement appropriate solutions. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES is exclusively licensed to provide and integrate MANITOU PSA (Professional Services Automation) solutions. MANITOU&reg; automates and streamlines business operations for enhanced productivity and quality management.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES started in 2003 as a result of a grouping of Oracle technology experts. They combined their expertise with the five (5) founders who were already knowledgeable and renowned in the area of Oracle and Java technologies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2008, MOMENTUM TECHNOLOGIES expended its reach by opening an office in Montreal, answering an increasing demand for growth of Oracle and Java technology experts.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(691, 1, 'Momzelle inc.', 'info@momzelle.com', '1255 Bélanger St, MONTRÉAL, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.momzelle.com', '(866) 941-5109', '', '', '<p>Our mission is to help mothers achieve a positive breastfeeding experience and feel confident breastfeeding anywhere. &nbsp;Nothing makes us feel better than a mom who tells us that she did not think that she could feel so confident and comfortable nursing her child.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Supporting Breastfeeding Moms</p>\r\n<div>We are proud to be encouraging and helping breastfeeding moms as much as we can. We have sponsored breastfeeding events across North America: the yearly breastfeeding challenge, breastfeeding coalitions\' activities, La Leche League events, etc. We have also donated nursing tops to women centres like the June Calwood Centre for women and families that help teenage mothers bring out the best in them and discover their great mothering potential.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(692, 1, 'Monaro Marine Ltd.', 'monaro@telus.net', '12711 No. 5 Rd., RICHMOND, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.monaromarine.com', '(604) 277-7433', '(604) 277-7403', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Monaro Marine Ltd. designs and builds its own unique brand of semi-custom 21\' to 30\' fibreglass power boats. We also sell used Monaros, and do expert repairs and custom upgrades on all types of fibreglass boats. Our rugged all-weather boats have cruised the west coast and explored the oceans as far north as the 75 deg. north latitude (1000 miles from the North Pole).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All of our models are trailerable including our largest model making it more versatile than many other boats the same length yet maintaining comfortable accommodations for extended trips.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A Monaro sport fishing boat is in the design and tooling stage. It will be based on our existing 24\' hull design which has a proven track record for efficiency and rough water performance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Construction has begun and we are hoping to have the first one on display at the 2015 Vancouver International Boatshow.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Details of the boat are now available. We will also be producing videos on the development of the boat.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(693, 1, 'Moncton Flight College', 'admissions@mfc.nb.ca', '1719 Champlain St, DIEPPE, New Brunswick, CANADA', 'www.mfc.nb.ca ', '(506) 857-3080', '(506) 857-9469', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1929, Moncton Flight College has been entrusted with the responsibility to provide its students with the skills and knowledge to successfully embark upon a career in the aviation industry. Over the decades, the College has been enabling dreams to take flight, by graduating over 18 000 students. The pilots trained at Moncton Flight College are flying and managing aviation operations around the world. They hold positions as Chief Pilots, Chief Flight Instructors, government officials, as well as flight crews in companies on every continent.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mr. Doiron took MFC to new heights in developing programs in China and Europe while improving MFC\'s curriculum and safety standards. In 2007, a second campus opened in Fredericton, in partnership with CANLink Aviation and its CEO, Mike Tilley. CANLink Aviation acquired Moncton Flight College in April, 2011 and will continue promoting to markets around the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Now, over 80 years later, Moncton Flight College has withstood the test of time. Its rich history is full of success stories from students, instructors, managers and other dedicated members who have navigated the school through good times and bad. Today, the College has state-of-the-art facilities, simulators, and aircraft. The people at Moncton Flight Collegeare looking ahead&nbsp; to the next 100 years of powered flight.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Over the years, the College has gained respect throughout the airline industry. This respect is based on recognition of MFC\'s training excellence,&nbsp; high safety standards and our ability to deliver superior pilots to the industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(694, 1, 'Mondien Services Inc.', 'info@mondien.com', '100-442 Saint-Gabriel St, MONTREAL, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.mondien.com', '(514) 909-0110', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mondien Services Inc. is a Montreal web design and Internet marketing company that strives to bring the best quality of work to its customers. We offer a wide range of services in the fields of web design, graphic design, internet marketing and copywriting. Since 2011, our company has provided numerous businesses and individuals with the right tools to publish, sell and advertise online.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our friendly team of web design and marketing experts can help you achieve success on the web by providing you with a clean and modern website, efficient and powerful marketing solutions and a long-term business relationship that will thrive and prosper over time. We take care of our clients and make sure they are satisfied with our work.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(695, 1, 'Monexa Services Inc.', 'info@monexa.com', '2650-1075 Georgia St W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.monexa.com ', '(604) 630-5660', '(604) 630-5652', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For the past 14 years, Monexa has broken ground in the online billing industry and worked with hundreds of subscription businesses to help them deliver innovative pricing plans that drive more online subscription sales. A deep skill-base derived from our many years of experience, combined with the online billing industries most robust set of API exposed billing, subscriber management and payment features, sets Monexa apart from other online billing companies and is why Monexa attracts established enterprise accounts.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1998, we started providing the operational support systems, including the billing and online payments engine for large ISPs and Telecom companies such as AOL and Bell Mobility as well as companies with complex reseller hierarchies like Amway. Monexa was one of the first billing platforms back in the early 2000&rsquo;s to introduce what are now common billing concepts seen in most bundled mobile phone plans. In 2003 and 2004 we acquired technical support and payment processing companies to broaden our scope of services into the general online subscription billing and automated payments space.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2007, the growth in Software as a Service (SaaS) and the cloud infrastructure markets was the catalyst for Monexa to take our already feature and function rich on-demand subscription billing and payments product and spend the next year on even more functionality and new user interfaces and billing language appropriate to these markets. In mid-2008, we launched our enhanced capabilities and priced them in such a way as to enable companies of any size to affordably obtain the same subscription billing and payments functionality as our large ISP and Telecom customers. Monexa continues to be the ground breaker in new online billing functionality with new releases every 6 to 8 weeks on top of what is already the most feature rich online billing application available.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Monexa was the first to offer an on-demand subscription billing and payments platform. Our technology has been a true multi-tenant, online billing solution from day one. 14 years of experience with sophisticated technology subscription customers has resulted in the most sophisticated product in the market and the most experienced team to guide your implementation.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(696, 1, 'Montfort International Ltd.', 'info@montfort-international.com', '360-850 Pierre-Bertrand Blvd, QUÉBEC, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.montfort-international.com ', '(418) 877-0778', '(877) 848-0548', '', '<p>&nbsp;Montfort International is a distributor and manufacturer of well-known industrial equipment and products.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our goal is to help our customers increase the efficiency of their operations and the quality of their products while reducing production costs. We also help to protect the members of their teams, again reducing their operating costs.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>MONTFORT INTERNATIONAL, is an industry leading distributor, representing metal, wood and glass working manufactures for over 20 years.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Montfort International was founded in 1989. Since the company&rsquo;s inception, customer satisfaction has been an integral part of our corporate culture. Whether our efforts are directed at product high performance, customer service, just-in-time delivery or research and development, our focus is always on the customer and what the customer wants and needs.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We take great pride in the many remarkable achievements that have marked our group&rsquo;s history over the years and, even more so, in the testimonials we get from our customers, who consistently mention the exceptional service they received throughout their project.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are covering four industrial fields.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>SAWING EQUIPMENT AND CUTTING TOOLS: For over 20 years Montfort International has been the leader in sawing technology, setting the standard with exclusive saw blades and equipment technologies and innovations than any other distributor.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>METALWORKING LUBRICATION AND FLUID MANAGEMENT: A large range of lubricants and equipments and management systems, primarily for the metalworking and foundry industries. We are proud to lead the market in the new generation soluble oils from the green technologies.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>SAFETY GUARDING: We offer a very wide range of high quality machine guards, including standard machine guards and modular systems. Our comprehensive range of service ensures we can fulfill every aspect of a machine guarding project, from survey, advice on technical and regulation issues, design, manufacture and installation &#150; for which we always use our own skilled and experienced.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>MASS FINISHING: From parts finishing equipment such as deburring machines, flat finishers and vibratory finishing machines to vibratory compounds and media; We have the finishing solution for you.&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(697, 1, 'Moog Components Group', 'focal@moog.com', '77 Frazee Ave, DARTMOUTH, Nova Scotia, CANADA', 'www.moog.com', '(902) 468-2263', '(902) 468-2249', '', '<p>&nbsp;Moog Inc. is a worldwide designer, manufacturer, and integrator of precision motion control products and systems. Moog&rsquo;s high-performance systems control military and commercial aircraft, satellites and space vehicles, launch vehicles, missiles, industrial machinery, wind energy, marine applications, and medical equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(698, 1, 'Moore Log and Timber Homes Ltd.', 'client.care@moorelogandtimberhomes.com', '63 West Railway Ave, ABBOTSFORD, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.moorelogandtimberhomes.com', '(604) 855-0602', '(604) 648-8526', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moore Log &amp; Timber Homes designs and builds the highest quality custom log home packages for clientele around the world. We deliver handcrafted log homes and timber frame components of unsurpassed quality, made from the finest Western Red Cedar and Douglas Fir, to virtually any location.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">If you\'ve been dreaming of having a beautiful timber or log home for a vacation spot or a place to permanently plant your feet, let us help you achieve your dream! We\'re recognized worldwide as one of the best custom log home builders in the business, and we\'re more than ready for the challenge.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(699, 1, 'Moran Mining & Tunnelling Ltd.', 'moranmmt@moranmining.com', 'P.O. Box 1270, COPPER CLIFF, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.moranmining.com ', '(705) 682-4070', '(705) 682-4340', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moran Mining &amp; Tunnelling Ltd. (MMT), was formed in 1988 and continues to grow and widen its areas of expertise in the mining sector. An expanding list of satisfied clients include INCO Limited, Falconbridge Limited, Battle Mountain Gold, Inmet Mining Corporation, Agnico-Eagle Mines Limited, Kinross Gold Corporation and The Canadian Salt Company Limited.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1999, MMT expanded operations into the United States. This new American service centre is a compliment to Canadian Operations and provides more immediate reaction to the demands of the US mining industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Years of MMT experience have developed a well-trained and highly qualified labour force available and easily mobilized for a wide range of mining and construction projects, regardless of size and scope.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MMT has a fleet of excellent contract mining equipment available to complete both Track and Trackless projects of all sizes. Equipment includes: Raise Climbers, Jumbos, Scooptrams, Scissorlifts, Bolting Machines, Locomotives, Mucking Machines and Ore Cars.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MMT\'s founder and President is John Moran. John has over 47 years progressive experience in all aspects of underground mining. In 1969, John started raise mining as a Labourer and progressed to the roles of Wingman, Leader, Project Superintendent, Area Manager and finally President &amp; CEO of his own company. John has consulted and provided employee training to major companies such as INCO Limited and Miramar Mining Corporation on raise mining projects.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(700, 1, 'Morbern Inc.', 'sales@morbern.com', 'P.O. Box 1207, CORNWALL, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.morbern.com', '(613) 932-8811', '(613) 932-9779', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Morbern is one of North America&rsquo;s leading manufacturers and innovators of decorative vinyl upholstery fabrics. For over 50 years our focus has been on delivering total design and performance solutions in vinyl upholstery for the Corporate, Healthcare, Hospitality, Marine, and Transportation markets and a wide variety of other markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From large stock selections to almost unlimited custom capabilities, Morbern vinyl upholstery is the choice for discerning engineers, designers, and specifiers. Our products are developed for and specified in numerous prestigious applications. Browse our product catalog, add vinyl upholstery and fabric products to your work room and place your swatch order online.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(701, 1, 'Mordiff Distribution Inc.', 'sales@mordiff-distribution.com', '16 Todd Brook Dr, ETOBICOKE, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.mordiff-distribution.com', '(416) 520-9827', '', '', '<p>We are the Canadian distributor of: DeeLuxe Alpine Snowboard Boots,Snowboards, bindings and related equipment for alpine snowboarding along with FTWO snowboards, bindings and related gear for freestyle snowboarding.</p>', ''),
(702, 1, 'Morneau Shepell Ltd', 'dbrochu@morneaushepell.com', 'C.P. 211 Succ. Tour de la Bourse, MONTREAL, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.morneaushepell.com ', '(514) 878-9090', '(514) 875-2673', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Morneau Shepell is Canada&rsquo;s only consulting and outsourcing company that takes an integrative approach to health, benefits, retirement, and employee assistance needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our clients are progressive leaders seeking to enhance the health, productivity, and financial security of their people. With more than 21,000 clients and 5 million plan participants, we help increase engagement, productivity, and financial outcomes, while reducing risk, to enhance competitiveness and business success.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Morneau Shepell Inc. is a public company listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange (TSX), trading under the symbol MSI.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Morneau Shepell has been a leading provider of human resources consulting and outsourcing services for nearly 50 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With our focus on innovative solutions, we deliver human resources and workplace health and productivity solutions that help clients across North America better manage their costs and enhance the strength of their organizations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(703, 1, 'MORREX INC', 'info@morrex.com', 'C.P. 34024, SHERBROOKE, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.morrex.com ', '(819) 200-1260', '(819) 200-7699', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MORREX INC is proud to serve the transformational world of digital currency. We believe Bitcoin and other peer to peer digital currency systems are putting power back into the hands of the people, and we are overjoyed to help bring the movement to the masses.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is simple &ndash; to provide Canadians with a reliable, secure, first-class digital currency exchanger. We want to help keep Canadian money in Canada, where it&rsquo;s safe.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">There are many digital currency options these days, but the most popular by far is Bitcoin. Bitcoin is a currency revolution. It&rsquo;s a decentralized virtual form of payment that is absolutely taking the world by storm, now boasting a market cap of over $7 billion. The Bitcoin network is comprised of thousands of computers run by individuals, called &ldquo;miners&rdquo;, all across the world. If you&rsquo;re looking to join the most world-changing financial experiment in the world, you&rsquo;re at the right place!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At MORREX, Canadians exchange Bitcoins, Litecoins, and Feathercoins into Canadian dollars. Our infrastructure is safe and secure. We know that trust is an important factor in your decision of using our exchange, we value your privacy.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MORREX is the first cryptocurrency exchanger in Quebec.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(704, 1, 'Mosher Motors Limited', 'mail@mosherford.ns.ca', 'P.O. Box 219, BRIDGEWATER, Nova Scotia, CANADA', 'www.mosherford.com ', '(902) 543-2459', '(902) 543-8363', '', '<p>&nbsp;G.W. Mosher Motors, a Ford dealer in Hebbville, Nova Scotia offers new Ford Cars, Crossovers, SUVs, Trucks &amp; Vans, Hybrids &amp; EVs online at http://www.mosherford.com. Search for all new 2014 and 2015 Ford, including Flex, SuperDuty, Explorer, F-150, Econoline Wagon, Expedition, Fiesta, Focus, Taurus, Fusion, Edge, Fusion Hybrid, Transit VanWagon, Escape, Transit Connect Wagon, Mustang, C-MAX, Transit Connect. Find your dream car from our Ford showroom of Cars, Crossovers, SUVs, Trucks &amp; Vans, Hybrids &amp; EVs or search our new Ford inventory to see what is on our lot, get new car pricing and free Ford price quotes. View our used car inventory, including our pre-owned Ford vehicles.</p>', ''),
(705, 1, 'Motif Textiles', 'mail@motiftextiles.com', '16 Winterport Crt, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.motiftextiles.com', '(416) 617-6495', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Motif Textiles &amp; Designs was founded by designer Sarah Stein, B.Des. in 2013. Motif\'s works include original creations for home decor, kitchen linens, and baby wear, as well as commissionable pieces.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All of Motif\'s works are produced as environmentally-friendly as possible, where natural fibres are used with water-based inks and weak acid dyes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With a background in fine art and photography, I can produce original and commissionable artwork. With technical training in various paint and drawing mediums, print and paper-making, as well as woodwork, ceramics and metalwork, my work ranges from abstract to antique-inspired.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(706, 1, 'Motion Canada', 'brent.pope@motioncanada.com', '8985 Fraserwood Crt, BURNABYii, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.motioncanada.com ', '(604) 433-6711', '(604) 433-5473', '', '<p>&nbsp;A leading distributor of quality products and services to 150,000 government and industrial customers in North America, Motion Industries operates in the MRO (maintenance repair and operating) replacement parts market as well as the OEM market (Original Equipment Manufacturer or Equipment and Machinery).</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Motion Industries serves its local markets with over 550 locations including 511 branches, 15 distribution centers and 42 service centers throughout North America. Through this extensive operating network, our customers have access to over 5.6 million quality parts, sourced from a global manufacturing base.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are committed to delivering superior service and value to all of our supply chain partners, including customers and suppliers. This means creating and sustaining a relationship of trust and transparency, and a platform for mutual benefit and growth. We value a culture of strong ethics, continuous service improvement, collaboration and responsiveness in our relationships.</div>', ''),
(707, 1, 'Motus Inc.', 'gklassen@motus.ca', '650 Park Blvd W., Winnipeg, Manitoba, CANADA', 'www.motus.ca ', '(204) 489-8280', '(204) 489-0450', '', '<p>&nbsp;MOTUS (Latin for motion) was founded in 1992 to make our garden tool grips. They are modeled after the grips on scythes that our forefathers used to cut grain on our farm. Over the years the grips have evolved to their current design using materials that are light and comfortable yet offer strength and durability to make your gardening experience more enjoyable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are a family owned and operated company. We make and ship our products directly from our own warehouse.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The D-grip and T-grip make a myriad of home and garden tools easier and safer to work with. The ergonomic design of these grips significantly increases leverage and improves posture. They reduce arthritis pain, back pain, blisters and fatigue. These grips are the best available and we guarantee you will find them as rewarding as we do.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Motus grips are an accessory that make home and gardening tools easier and safer to work with.</div>\r\n<div>They reduce back pain, arthritis pain, blisters, fatigue and other repetitive stress injuries.</div>\r\n<div>The ergonomic design adjusts to any stature, short or tall, left or right-handed.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The D-grip mounts mid-way down the garden tool handle and gives lifting leverage to the forward hand.</div>\r\n<div>The T-grip mounts at the upper end of the garden tool handle and gives pushing and pulling control</div>\r\n<div>to the back hand. In combination, they optimize their mechanical advantage.</div>', ''),
(708, 1, 'Moulding Warehouse Limited', 'sales@moulding-warehouse.com', '18 Caper Crt, HAMMONDS PLAINS, Nova Scotia, CANADA', 'www.moulding-warehouse.com ', '(902) 832-3217', '(902) 832-2097', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moulding Warehouse Ltd. a quality manufacturer of primed MDF mouldings and supplier of interior pre-hung doors, door hardware and accessories for home owners, developers and contractors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our dedicated staff is ready to assist you with those special projects including curved mouldings for that special window or wall treatment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Browse though our site to see the many profiles available for your home improvement project or new home construction.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(709, 1, 'Mountain Sky Soap', 'soapinfo@mountainskysoap.com', '2276 Hwy 6, CRESCENT VALLEY, British Columbia, CANADA', 'www.mountainskysoap.com ', '(250) 359-6850', '(250) 359-6881', '', '<p>&nbsp;Mountain Sky was created by Raynald Losier and Nina George in the beautiful Kootenay mountains in British Columbia, Canada.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All of our products contain water straight from a nearby mountain creek.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All of our products contain water straight from a nearby mountain creek.</div>\r\n<div>Mountain Sky has built-up a loyal following of Mountain Sky soap lovers because people trust Mountain Sky&rsquo;s naturally made products.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our company and products reflect our commitment to a higher quality of life for our family, employees, environment and community.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We strive to use naturally based products and minimize the impact of our products on the environment.</div>', ''),
(710, 1, 'Moveable Inc.', 'info@moveable.com', '502-77 Mowat Ave., TORONTO, Ontario, CANADA', 'www.moveable.com ', '(416) 532-5690', '(416) 532-0783', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moveable collaborates with graphic designers to produce high-quality projects, both in print and on the web. The company was founded in 1983 and has built a reputation for thoughtful attention to detail and great service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1983, when Moveable Type began as a small typesetting shop, there was no Macintosh computer, no desktop publishing, no Internet. Back then, typesetting was a stand-alone industry employing hundreds of thousands of people worldwide. But within a decade, once the introduction of desktop publishing systems enabled designers to handle their own typesetting, it had all but disappeared. Even the buggy whip industry lasted longer after the invention of the automobile than the typesetting industry did after the advent of desktop publishing.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(711, 1, 'MP Holistic Nutrition', 'info@mpholisticnutrition.com', '1857 Holy Cross St, Montreal, Quebec, CANADA', 'www.mpholisticnutrition.com ', '(438) 448-2394', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;I(Megan Pennington) went on to study at two Holistic Health institutes, and finally got a grip on my own struggles. I continued to follow the scientific literature and various health experts, and eventually developed a simple and effective system for maintaining my own well-being and to share with my clients.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Today, I combine my conventional knowledge in Dietetics with a holistic approach &ndash; &nbsp;the best of both worlds!I use my background and experience in both conventional and holistic nutrition to sort through the information for you (so you don&rsquo;t have to), prioritize according to your individual needs, and break everything down into key concepts that you can actually use and easily incorporate into your current lifestyle. I focus on physical and mental nourishment, stress reduction, lifestyle management, detoxification, and natural techniques. My methods are simple, effective, flexible, and science-based, with a huge dose of open-mindedness and forward-thinking.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I incorporate today&rsquo;s leading advances in science and wellness from a whole health perspective. This means that I address a client&rsquo;s well-being in totality, rather than focusing on any single element, as many practitioners do.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>I have helped many achieve their weight loss goals, treat disease, and gain control of their lives.</div>', ''),
(712, 1, 'NATIONAL PROCESS EQUIPMENT', 'webinquiries@natpro.com', '109 Wilkinson Rd, Brampton, Ontario, CANADA', 'WWW.NATPRO.COM ', '(905) 453-2639', '(905) 453-9391', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">WILRON EQUIPMENT LTD. and HYDRO DYNAMICS LTD came together in mid-1998 to form NATIONAL PROCESS EQUIPMENT INC. Both of these companies had been dedicated to serving pump and compressor users in Canada for over 30 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Together, as Natpro, we are Canada\'s largest independent distributor of pumps, compressors and related process equipment with over 160 employees working from eight facilities across the country. While bigger doesn\'t always mean better, we believe the depth of our company does give us some rather unique abilities to better serve our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The manufacturers we represent are among the finest in the world. Our product line-up allows us to provide innovative, reliable and efficient solutions for the vast majority of our customers\' pump and compressor applications. Whether the scope is a simple pump or compressor with driver, or a complex pre-packaged system with piping, instrumentation and controls, we\'ve got the experience and the shop capabilities to design it, build it, QC and commission it - anywhere in the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are fortunate to be of a size where we can afford to make ongoing significant investments in our company to serve our customers better. We believe that continuous investment in comprehensive production and service facilities and equipment, product inventory, technical training, state-of-the-art information and communication technology, are necessary to meet increased customer expectations in today\'s world.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(713, 1, 'N. Jefferson Ltd', 'njefferson@shawcable.com', '22 5th Ave E, Vancouver, Br, Canada', 'www.njeffersonltd.com ', '(604) 873-4641', '(604) 873-4644', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">N. Jefferson Ltd. has supplied goods and services to Canadian retailers, wholesalers, and manufacturers since 1926.&nbsp; As one of Canada&rsquo;s largest distributors of sewing and quilting notions, we stock more than 29,000 sku&rsquo;s in our 30,000 square feet Vancouver warehouse.&nbsp; Our product line is supplied by hundreds of suppliers from 34 countries around the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our commitment to provide a service level that sets us apart from our competitors is aimed at helping you, our customer, reap the rewards of increased sales and profits.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We have developed marketing partnerships with some of our suppliers, which allow us to act as representatives for them in arranging drop shipments to you at improved discounts.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(714, 1, 'N.R. Murphy Limited', 'c.moffatt@nrmurphyltd.com;4nodust@nrmurphy.com', '430 Franklin Blvd., Cambridge, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nrmurphy.com ', '(519) 621-6210', '(519) 621-2841', '', '<p>&nbsp;N.R. Murphy Limited manufactures, the most complete line of dry dust collecting equipment available. From very small units for individual machine applications, to huge collectors for many applications. We also manufacture our own exhausters and related equipment.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Founded in 1943 as Price Air Conditioning, it was renamed Murphy Sheet Metal in 1948 and began to specialize in supplying and installing dust collecting equipment. Murphy\'s experienced steady growth under the direction of William Murphy.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In 1956 the Company was taken over by Robert Murphy. Norman R. Murphy became Vice-President when the company moved to its present location in 1962. In 1966 Norm Murphy purchased the company and re-named it N.R. Murphy Limited to reflect the change to the manufacturing of dust collecting equipment.</div>', ''),
(715, 1, 'Nabco Housing Inc.', 'nabco@nabcohousing.com', '686, rang de la Riviere E R.R. 1, SAINTE-BRIGIDE-D\'IBERVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.nabcohousing.com ', '(450) 293-3125', '(450) 293-2160', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Habitations Nabco was founded in 1986 by Mr. Clermont Nadeau. Specializing in the construction of unimodular houses from the onset, the company quickly enhanced its offer by manufacturing factory-built houses. In early 2000, the company started to build panel houses by developing its own manufacturing method and its own assembly system. In 2011, Annie and Marc Nadeau took over the reins of the company with the intention of bringing it to new heights.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company now counts 40 permanent employees who are trustworthy individuals and who have been with the company for many years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Warranties from the various construction material manufacturers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nabco warranties for each house built and installed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To provide you with quality dwellings at a cost enabling you to realize your dreams is our Mission.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(716, 1, 'Nadurra Wood Corp.', 'info@nadurrawood.com', '157A Bentworth Ave, North York, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nadurrawood.com ', '(647) 345-8414', '(647) 342-0818', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NADURRA introduces the second generation of Composite&trade; bamboo floors with the TRAFFIC&trade; Series: bamboo floors tough enough for the work world, beautiful enough for your home. We took our hottest selling style, the dense Composite plank, 180% harder than maple, and put an ultra matte, zero solvent, commercial-grade finish from Bona&trade;. Add to this Bona\'s Lifetime Finish Support and you\'ve got our toughest floor yet!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Given that NADURRA has been importing bamboo flooring since 1994, we\'re intimately familiar with how it ought to be manufactured, kiln-dried, and handled to perform optimally in the North American climate. In fact, our ECO-Series line offers Canada&rsquo;s most ecologically sound bamboo flooring. Independently tested for low to zero formaldehyde emissions and now available in Forest Stewardship Council certified. FSC is your assurance that the bamboo has been harvested from forests monitored for the protection of endangered species, pesticide use, economic sustainability, and respect for workers&rsquo; rights.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(717, 1, 'Naija Foods', 'service@Naijafoods.ca', '4-188 Wilkinson Rd , Brampton, Ontario, Canada', 'www.Naijafoods.ca ', '(647) 367-1642', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Naija Foods, maker of Naija Meat Pies and other Foods Products welcomes you to our world. We are a Canadian Food Company committed to manufacturing and distributing a broad range of high-quality, affordable foods to families worldwide. We value and respect our employees, our business partners, our suppliers, our customers and the communities we serve while operating with accountability and integrity in everything we do.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We carefully select every single ingredient that goes into our pies, from water; tomatoes, beef and others. We regularly carry out audits of our product and process to ensure consistency</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Families and professionals around the world depend on Naija food for high quality products</div>', ''),
(718, 1, 'NAK interMEDIA', 'nick@nakintermedia.com', '3-100 West Beaver Creek Rd., RICHMOND Hill, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nakintermedia.com ', '(905) 764-7816', '(905) 764-8352', '', '<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Computer Consulting and Small Business Computer Solutions.</div>', ''),
(719, 1, 'Naleway Foods Ltd.', 'perogy@naleway.com', '233 Hutchings St, Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.naleway.com ', '(204) 633-6535', '(204) 694-4310', '', '<p>&nbsp; A food favourite of East Europeans for centuries, perogies are now widely eaten everywhere as snacks, side dishes or entire meals.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Naleway Perogies have a tender but firm, delicious dough, stuffed with a tasting filling. From Mexican or Italian style, to bacon-wrapped or vegetarian, Naleway Perogies are very nutritious, versatile, inexpensive, and can be prepared in minutes.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Available in major supermarkets in Canada and the United States, Naleway is the brand standard for quality, service and great taste!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(720, 1, 'NamSys Inc.', 'jason.siemens@namsys.com', '5 Loring Dr., Bolton, Ontario, Canada', 'www.namsys.com ', '(905) 857-9500', '(905) 857-9499', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1989, NamSys Inc. has offered value-added applications and capabilities to a number of currency handling and cash management sectors in the marketplace. NamSys has deployed network solutions that consolidate cash positions, orders, deposits, audit and security measures for organizations that handle large volumes of currency. Today, our solutions are in operation in world leading financial institutions, transit authorities, armored carriers and retailers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NamSys is a solutions oriented company with a focus on software to enhance leading edge products. NamSys&rsquo; highly skilled staff understand and develop leading-edge solutions that meet or exceed the need of clients with cash management challenges.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NamSys Inc. is a CencoTech Incorporated company.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(721, 1, 'Nanaimo Shipyard Ltd.', 'rvw@nanaimoshipyard.com', '1040 Stewart Ave, NANAIMO, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.nanaimoshipyard.com ', '(250) 753-1151', '(250) 753-2235', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nanaimo Shipyard Ltd usually offer: Norfolk Shipbuilding, Litton Ingalls Shipbuilding, Beihai Shipbuilding, Sun Shipbuilding, Universal Shipbuilding.</p>', '');
