(722, 1, 'Nanowave Technologies Inc.', 'jmiller@nanowavetech.com', '425 Horner Ave, ETOBICOKE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nanowavetech.com ', '(416) 252-5602', '(416) 252-7077', '', '<p>&nbsp;NANOWAVE Technologies Inc. is a leading designer and manu-facturer of advanced microwave, millimeter-wave and electro-optic components and sub-systems for custom designed tele-communication and Radar systems. Serving the leading sup-pliers for the aerospace, avionics, defence and communication markets, you will find Nanowave products in the world&rsquo;s most advanced airliners, business jets, helicopters, and military air-craft as well as in Electronic Warfare and Terrestrial Radar and Communications systems.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>NANOWAVE also offers solutions for refurbishment and system life extension by designing state of the art, form-fit and func-tion replacement components for legacy systems from UHF to 50 GHz and beyond.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>NANOWAVE is a vertically integrated engineering design and manufacturing company that uses its core technologies to design and manufacture innovative products that meet our customers\' needs in functionality, cost, scalability, quality and reliability.</div>', ''),
(723, 1, 'Napier Enterprises', 'customerservice@napieroutdoors.com', '3-4 Nihan Dr., St Catharines, Ontario, Canada', 'www.napieroutdoors.com ', '(905) 935-0427', '(905) 935-2918', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Napier is the world&rsquo;s largest developer and distributor of Vehicle Camping Tents.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1990, Napier has been changing the way people view camping by reshaping and merging the automotive and camping industries together. Observing a need for convenience and flexibility in outdoor adventures and the demand for exciting accessories in the automotive industry, Napier developed Vehicle Camping Tents. To learn more about our history, please click the Our History banner below.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Napier distributes Vehicle Camping Tents to automotive manufacturers and retailers across North America, Europe and Australia. Napier&rsquo;s brands include Sportz, Dome and Backroadz. Our signature brand Sportz, are the number one selling Truck and SUV Tents in the World!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Napier, we continuously strive to improve our products and develop new products to answer consumer demands. We constantly analyze consumer feedback and requests to further develop our innovated products; which contributes to Napier being the market leader in Vehicle Camping Tents.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(724, 1, 'NAS Software Inc.', 'info@nas.ca', '44 Joshua Crt, Thornhill, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nas.ca', '(905) 764-8079', '(905) 764-0695', '', '<p>NAS Software Inc. is one of the largest software distributors across Canada. Our programs are used in thousands of educational institutions in Canada and around the world. NAS Software Inc. has partnered with schools, colleges, universities, corporations and government ministries to implement numerous software tools within their various organizations. We carry a wide variety of exciting, interactive educational programs. We offer a variety of multi-media programs that are suitable for the classroom or independent learning. We have many platforms available that are both installable and online.</p>', ''),
(725, 1, 'Natayo Manufacturing Inc.', 'contact@natayo.com', '6060 86 Ave SE, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.natayo.com', '(403) 720-7700', '(403) 720-7750', '', '<p>&nbsp;Servicing the Oil &amp; Gas, Mining and Manufacturing ndustries.</p>', ''),
(726, 1, 'National Forest Products Ltd.', 'info@nationalforestproducts.com', '291 Boler Rd., London, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nationalforestproducts.com ', '(519) 474-0600', '(519) 474-0165', '', '<p>&nbsp;National Forest Products Ltd evolved from an older company that began in the 1930&rsquo;s. By the time it was incorporated in 1992, NFP already had 70 years of experience in the lumber industry. NFP is a distributor, wholesaler &amp; broker of the highest quality softwood lumber products. They service independent retail lumber dealers throughout all of Canada, and are beginning their transition into the U.S. market. NFP owns a distribution facility, strategically located in Orillia, ON. With a location just north of Toronto, and just south of the Muskoka region, it gives them a great central location to service Ontario and Quebec markets. NFP also facilitates warehouse space in Vancouver, Calgary, Edmonton, and now New Jersey, to have product able to service nearby markets.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Over the last decade, National Forest Products has grown and expanded its business. With the development of the Pinnacle programs, and the opening of two other divisions, NFP has begun to separate itself from the competition. In 2010, Thuja Transport Company was incorporated to offer long haul, on-time service to customers and distribution. In 2011, NFP began a manufacturing division that handles Western Red Cedar Specialties &amp; Exports. The Specialty &amp; Export division mainly focuses on cutting high quality cedar posts and timbers.</div>', ''),
(727, 1, 'Nautel Limited', 'info@nautel.com', '10089 Peggys Cove Rd., Hacketts Cove, Nova , ', 'www.nautel.com ', '(902) 823-2233', '(902) 823-3183', '', '', ''),
(728, 1, 'Nautel Limited', 'info@nautel.com', '10089 Peggys Cove Rd., Hacketts Cove, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.nautel.com', '(902) 823-2233', '(902) 823-3183', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nautel was born out of innovation starting with the first successful solid-state transmitters for broadcast, and today offers the most modern fleet of transmitters in the industry. Nautel&rsquo;s engineering team is even pushing its RF Amplifier expertise into space. That means there is a bit of rocket science in all of our transmitters. It shows in Nautel&rsquo;s digital broadcasting leadership and revolutionary approach to traditional transmitter design. Nautel&rsquo;s Advanced User Interface, built-in instrumentation, IP Audio, audio automation, Push Radio, HD PowerBoost, and built-in audio processing are just some examples of Nautel innovation in recent years.</p>\r\n<p>Nautel&rsquo;s latest generation of transmitters were designed to place enhanced control in to the hands of engineers so that they could become more efficient in their work. Years of interface development effort gives immediate access to almost any parameter imaginable, whether at the transmitter site or from the comfort of your living room. Imagine knowing in advance what parts and tools you&rsquo;ll need at the transmitter site. Having that much control remotely can help you avoid trips, save time and save money (more than 4,500 AUI capable transmitters have shipped to date).</p>', ''),
(729, 1, 'Navair Technologies Inc', 'sales@navair.com', '7-6375 Dixie Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.navair.com', '(905) 565-1583', '(905) 565-8325', '', '<p>&nbsp;Navair is a leading supplier of products and services to all levels of Government, Public Safety, Broadcast, Utilities, Automotive, Aerospace and the Land Mobile Radio (LMR) Markets.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Wireless access has come of age.Recent statistics indicate more than 70% of all cell phone calls originate inside buildings.</div>\r\n<div><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">		</span></div>\r\n<div>And there is no reason to expect that this trend will do anything but increase over time.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In a more generic sense, subscribers are demanding broadband wireless access to content, whatever that may be, wherever they are, for personal or professional use.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>From an enterprise perspective, wireless access to any service - be it private or commercial - is becoming more and more the norm. Wireless access also affords new and varied ways of boosting productivity.</div>', ''),
(730, 1, 'Naylor Canada Ltd.', 'garyg@naylor.com', '300-1630 Ness Ave, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.naylor.com', '(204) 975-0415', '(204) 947-2047', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Built on a strong foundation of hardworking individuals who displayed a commitment to excellence, honesty, integrity, ongoing improvement and exceptional customer service, Naylor is driven by these same principles today. Since 1969, Naylor&rsquo;s mission has been to build image by providing the finest products and services to associations everywhere. Over the years, we have expanded products and services and added expertise and offices &ndash; all for the sole purpose of effectively serving the association marketplace.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Over the years, we are proud to have built partnerships with our clients through honest and thoughtful dialogue. We believe that our core operating values, paired with our desire to serve as an extension of your staff, sets us apart from other companies. With unsurpassed expertise in selling integrated association media and events spread across 110 industries, we consistently renew more than 90% of our clients each year.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(731, 1, 'NBS Technologies Inc.', 'info@nbstech.com', '402-703 Evans Ave, ETOBICOKE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nbstech.com', '(416) 621-1911', '(416) 621-8875', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 40 years, NBS Technologies has remained a leading developer and provider of equipment for card personalization, EMV compliance/migration, smart card manufacturing and semiconductor handling equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We not only provide equipment but customized solutions that address all types of card personalization requirements. Our solutions and products address the requirements of a range markets worldwide: Financial EMV/Chip Card, TSM, GSM/Telecom, Government/Secure ID, Healthcare/Insurance, and Corporate markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our portfolio allows us to offer a truly tailored solution that will meet your specific needs. Whether your needs are high-volume card issuance or instant card issuance NBS Technologies is your total card solution.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NBS Technologies is a wholly owned subsidiary of Brookfield Asset Management, a specialist asset manager. Focused on property, power and infrastructure assets, Brookfield has approximately $150 billion of assets under management and is co-listed on the New York and Toronto Stock exchanges. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NBS Technologies is a global company with locations in Canada, U.S., France and the UK, along with a comprehensive worldwide dealer network.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(732, 1, 'NCP Homes LTD', 'NCP@KINGSTON.NET', '1045 John Counter Blvd, Kingston, Ontario , Canada', 'www.ncphomes.com', '(613) 546-4429', '(613) 546-5110', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NCP Homes is dedicated to building custom luxury homes of outstanding quality. NCP Homes builds homes designed by your own individual vision and needs. Designing your new home is a complex process; that is why we are here to guide you in making those crucial decisions every step of the way at no additional cost. Through our devotion to client needs and quality, we ensure complete satisfaction with one of our custom new homes or any of our other services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Driven by quality, value, integrity and service, NCP Homes does not just build homes, we turn your new home dreams into a reality that you will be proud of and cherish for many years to come.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NCP Homes specializes in new home construction, including pre-fab homes, but we also offer services in any home renovation, including custom kitchen cabinetry design and installation, and septic services and installations. Please feel free to contact us for a free in-home consultation or at our Design Centre.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(733, 1, 'NDT Technologies Inc.', 'rcourtois@ndt.ca', '20275 Clark-Graham Ave, BAIE-D\'URFE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.ndt.ca', '(514) 457-7650', '(514) 457-7652', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our fully equipped research, engineering and manufacturing facility is located just west of Montr&eacute;al, Qu&eacute;bec, Canada. Established in 1981, the company is dedicated to technology, innovation, integration and performance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NDT Technologies Inc. provides fully automated systems for on-line and off-line full body inspections of welded (ERW) and seamless (SMLS) pipes, bars, billets, heavy steel plates, railroad rails, train wheels, wheel sets and axles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NDT Technologies Inc.\'s turnkey automated systems are engineered to be mechanically robust to meet heavy industry requirements. In addition, our systems offer a high level of customization to accommodate clients\' specific production needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(734, 1, 'Neechie Gear', 'info@neechiegear.com', '3510, 8th St E Unit C5, SASKATOON, Saskatchewan, Canada', 'www.neechiegear.com ', '(306) 880-5598', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Neechie Gear is lifestyle apparel brand empowering youth through sports. A portion of proceeds help fund underprivileged youth to take part in sports!</p>', ''),
(735, 1, 'Neilson Digital', 'quinn@neilsondigital.com', '51 Wolseley St, TORONTO, Ontario , Canada', 'www.neilsondigital.com ', '(250) 514-1522', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Neilson Digital Inc. is a full service multi-media design studio with specific expertise in visualization, animation, and interactive environments for the Architectural, Real Estate, and Land Development community. Our studio builds branded stories and visual presentations to explain conceptual architectural design for competition proposals, marketing initiatives, and fundraising purposes.</p>', ''),
(736, 1, 'Nelson Machinery & Equipment Ltd.', 'sales@nelsonmachinery.com', '200-20641 Logan Ave , LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.nelsonmachinery.com ', '(604) 985-5331', '(604) 985-2074', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nelson Machinery &amp; Equipment Ltd. specializes in the sale of second-hand equipment for mining, mineral processing and cement. Relationships with many new product manufacturers, enable the company to offer competitive new product alternatives as well. The company conducts liquidations of closed mines and cement plants, and maintains a computerized database of surplus equipment located at numerous mine sites throughout North America and at various sites overseas.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company has used equipment available for virtually all aspects of the mining and minerals benification process, including equipment for underground mining and tunneling, surface mining, material handling, crushing, grinding, separating, concentrating, filtering, pumping, dewatering, drying and loading. Complete plants can often be matched or adapted to a purchaser\'s needs. Equipment and plants usually become surplus not because of obsolescence or breakdown, but because of changes in a process or depletion of an ore body. The pool of used surplus equipment allows purchasers to make savings in both cost and delivery time when compared to the purchase of new equipment. Nelson Machinery &amp; Equipment Ltd. can offer items on an &quot;as is&quot; basis, subject to the buyers inspection and approval, or alternatively on a &quot;reconditioned&quot; basis. The company also sells surplus and new parts for many types of mining equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to equipment sales, the company offers various services, including appraisals of used equipment and complete plants. Goods are accepted for consignment sale on a commission basis.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in the marketplace makes the company uniquely qualified to provide an accurate assessment of current market values. Whether the evaluation involves a single piece of equipment, or a complete plant, selling clients can be confident of a realistic and fair appraisal. An aggressive marketing program can then be developed, designed to bring the equipment to the attention of prospective buyers worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(737, 1, 'Nemko Canada Inc.', 'sim.jagpal@nemko.com', '303 River Rd., OTTAWA, Ontario , Canada', 'www.nemko.com ', '(613) 737-9680', '(613) 737-9691', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Market access is essential to every international business, and it is more complicated than just choosing your sales channels. You also have to comply with a number of national regulatory requirements. These may stop your product from being sold in some national markets. Alternatively, they may cause costly delays.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With Nemko Direct the approval process goes fast and smooth. As a result, you can reduce time to market and prevent loss of revenue.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nemko offers a very successful program for worldwide market access &ndash; Nemko Direct for Telecom. This program is designed as a means of gaining market access for your wireless telecom products. This program is based on a network of relationships with regulatory authorities throughout the world. Our network includes countries located in the Americas, the Far East, the Middle East, Africa, Asia, Europe, Eastern Europe and Oceania.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(738, 1, 'Neptune Marine Safety', 'sales@nepmar.com', '104-1990 William St , MONTREAL,  Quebec , Canada', 'www.nepmar.com ', '(514) 933-5555', '(514) 933-4489', '', '<p>&nbsp;We specialize in the sales and service of marine lifesaving and safety equipment, in particular, liferafts. We supply and source all types of marine safety equipment. If we don?t have it - we will find it for you</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(739, 1, 'Nestor Falls Marine', 'info@nestorfallsmarine.com', 'Highway 71, Nestor Falls, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nestorfallsmarine.com', '(807) 484-2134', '(807) 484-2762', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nestor Falls Marine has been servicing Lake of the Woods and the nestor Falls,Sioux Narrows area for almost 50 years. Don\'s grandfather used to sell Gale, Elto and Bucaneer outboard motors and a lot of people can not even remember that far back. Don is a 3rd generation marine dealer,so the marine business is in his blood,or ocasionally when his wrench slips the blood is in his marine. We service all brands of outboard motors but specialize in Mercury, Evinrude E-TEC and Johnson motors as we are a dealer for all three. We are a certified Platnum dealer for all with certified onsite tec\'s, a large parts supply and warranty departments. We also have one of the largest parts departments on Lake of the Woods,and in Northwestern Ontario.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our specialty is to get you back on the water the same day and if we have the parts in stock the chances are that this will happen. We have a 99% chance of having a prop for your outboard motor because we have more than 200 propellers in stock. We also sell and service Minnkota and Motorguide trolling motors. We carry a large inventory of Lowrance and Humminbird depthfinders and accessories for them,all to help service our valuable customer.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(740, 1, 'Netchem Inc', 'netchem@netcheminc.com', '35 Roy Blvd, Brantford, Ontario, Canada', 'www.netcheminc.com ', '(519) 751-4700', '(519) 751-3402', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Incorporated in 1991, Netchem is headquartered in Brantford, Ontario, Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Netchem distributes Specialty Chemicals throughout the Western Hemisphere, from strategically located warehouses, for just-in-time deliveries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Netchem partners with customers in a broad spectrum of markets, supplying cost effective chemistry and service solutions. Our energy is invested in challenging the status quo providing our customers with options for their product and service needs. Our primary focus is to provide our customers and<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">partners with the highest quality products and customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To promote total confidence in the quality of its products, Netchem visits and audits our manufacturing partners ensuring compliance to quality products and services. As a further commitment we work with local certified laboratory testing facilities to carry out third party testing on raw materials and pre shipment samples.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Netchem is operated by professionals in Chemistry,Chemical Engineering and Commerce with scores of years&rsquo; experience in various industries. It can<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">provide financing for almost any terms its customers may require and flexible distribution logistics to match.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Other companies related to Netchem have been involved with activities in:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Manufacture of Specialty Chemicals for the Pulp &amp; Paper industry, including joint ventures and partnerships with Caffaro of Italy, Mitsubishi Chemicals of Japan, SNF Floerger of France and Ashland Chemicals of America.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(741, 1, 'Newdog Inc', 'bernie@new-dog.com', 'E 908-53 Ave. N.E., Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.new-dog.com', '(403) 275-2336', '(403) 275-6818', '', '<p>Newdog Inc is a&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">supplier of imprinted advertising products, pens, calenders,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">watches, travel mugs, coffee cups, pencils, bags,</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">silkscreened and embroidered clothing, t shirts, sweatshirts,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">jackets, hats, and golf shirts.</span></p>', ''),
(742, 1, 'Newfoundland Styro Inc.', 'info@nfstyro.com', '12 Dominic St.Industrial Pk., BISHOPS FALLS, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', 'www.nfstyro.com ', '(709) 258-5890', '(709) 258-6015', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Expanded polystyrene, or EPS for short, is a simple material with a unique combination of qualities. It offers high resistance to the passage of heat energy - it is a very effective insulator. It is also economical, offering high R-value per dollar.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Expanded foams (EPS) are commonly known as bead boards. The raw material is a small bead. These are heated with steam and the softened plastic expands as the pentane gas trapped in the plastic beads expands. These pre-expanding beads are then cured during an aging process. The cured beads are than introduced to a mold where further contact with steam softens and expands the beads to fill the mold cavity and fuse the beads tightly together. The molded foam can be in large rectangular blocks that are further processed by cutting with hot wires into standard sized sheets or custom cut billets. This is known as block molding. The basic EPS blocks are cut and shaped to produce a variety of Truefoam sheet, board and panel products including Truewall, Truefit, Foundation Plus/Sheathing, Insulwall, and others.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For certain Truefoam products, such as Reward Wall ICFs and Styropack shipping containers, the polystyrene is shape moulded during final expansion.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">EPS is structurally rigid and stable, yet very light. It is very easy to cut and shape using the simplest of tools. It produces no irritating fibres or annoying dust. EPS products make the job quicker for both contractors and do-it-yourselfers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">EPS insulation doesn\'t change or deteriorate over time. EPS sheets and panels cannot sag or bunch. EPS insulation is unaffected by freeze-thaw cycles, and cannot rot or mould. EPS insulation\'s R-value is permanent.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">EPS insulation is very resistant to the passage of water, yet it &quot;breathes.&quot; Vapour passes through. This avoids condensation buildup within walls, a serious problem which can arise with other insulation systems. And because of the rigid closed-cell structure of EPS, there is no possibility of the kind of air movement inside the wall which can lead to heat loss in loose or blanket materials.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(743, 1, 'Newly Weds Foods Co.', 'rnahorniak@newlywedsfoods.ca', '450 Superior Blvd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.newlywedsfoods.com ', '(450) 641-2220', '(450) 641-2008', '', '<p>&nbsp;Newly Weds Foods recognized the potential of the frozen food industry in the early 1950s and broke new ground in manufacturing capabilities. We pioneered bakery-based technology that could withstand the rigors of freeze-thaw and longer distribution cycles in batters and breadings. Partnering with major food manufacturers allowed us to lead the industry as we became the top producer of customized food coatings in the United States&hellip;a position we proudly hold today.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As part of our overall strategic plan, we began to extend geographically, establishing a well-recognized presence across the globe. Today, you&rsquo;ll find us in the United Kingdom, covering the European continent as well as in the Asia-Pacific region with manufacturing facilities in Australia, Thailand and the Philippines. We&rsquo;ve also partnered with a joint venture in Israel covering Middle East markets, the opening of a Beijing, China production plant and the acquisition of three plants in Canada.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>At Newly Weds Foods, we don&rsquo;t just strive for excellence, it is expected. We constantly strive to improve ourselves by looking at what we do and how we can do it better. That internal check is what keeps this company head and shoulders above the competition. This is one of the reasons why we are the global leader and continue to work towards maintaining this leadership role.</div>', ''),
(744, 1, 'Newtrax Technologies', 'support@newtrax.com', '600-620 St Jacques St, MONTREAL, QUEBEC, Canada', 'www.newtrax.com', '(514) 288-6398', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 2002, Newtrax Technologies Inc. is an employee owned company with headquarters in Montreal, Canada. The company\'s vision is to provide the most reliable, user friendly and cost effective solutions for monitoring, control, messaging and tracking in harsh environments without grid power outlets. Solutions provided by Newtrax are based on its advanced wireless mesh/FHSS networking protocol and RF-based motion and proximity sensor. Benefits include low installation costs of large networks, new applications in dynamic or hazardous environments where wires are not an option and range extension with multiple hops.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vision: Safe, efficient and environmentally friendly mining of natural resources.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mission: In collaboration with our application partners:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide early warnings of safety, health and environmental hazards<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Optimize production via real-time operational intelligence<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Accelerate rescue activities via post-accident communications and tracking<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Values: Professional integrity, Teamwork, Global competitiveness and sustainability, Profitability for all stakeholders, Work-Life balance<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(745, 1, 'Bridgman & Durksen Chartered Accountants', 'info@bridgmananddurksen.com', '5 Race St, ST CATHARINES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.bridgmananddurksen.com ', '(905) 682-6677', '(905) 688-1881', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Bridgman &amp; Durksen Chartered Accountants. We deliver custom tailored financial and tax counselling services for small to medium size businesses and individuals. Our welcoming business environment, our focus on personalized service, and our knowledgeable, friendly team is what sets us apart. Treating every client as if they were our only client, we bring personal attention and peace of mind to your financial and tax needs. Our team of dedicated Chartered Accountants, Accountants and Bookkeepers will keep you perfectly balanced.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(746, 1, 'Nickel Lake Lumber', 'klundynll@xplornet.com', '913 Crowe Ave, Fort Frances, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nickellakelumber.com', '(807) 274-3848', '(807) 274-4483', '', '<p>&nbsp;roviding you with a superior product, quick, reliable delivery and many years of experience, Nickel Lake Lumber is your source for premium Ontario lumber products!</p>\r\n<div>We sell and ship a range of high quality lumber products to companies across Ontario, in Manitoba and to some of the northern states, including Minnesota and Wisconsin, as well as to our local market.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(747, 1, 'Nilex Inc.', 'edmonton@nilex.com', '9304 39 Ave, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.nilex.com ', '(780) 463-9535', '(780) 463-1773', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nilex was established in 1977 by Walter van Woudenberg in Edmonton, Alberta. These were considered the early days of the geosynthetics industry in North America and Nilex is recognized as one of the pioneers. In fact, many of the materials we provide our customers today either did not exist or were not yet manufactured in North America and had to be imported from Europe.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since then, Nilex has expanded throughout Canada with additional locations in Burnaby, Abbotsford, Vernon, Calgary, Saskatoon, Toronto, and into the US with an office in Denver, Colorado. Nilex consists of three companies &ndash; Nilex Inc. (Canada), Nilex Construction (Canada), and Nilex Environmental Inc. (USA). Our products and services fall into five key application areas: Roads, MSE Walls and Slopes, Erosion and Sediment Control, Drainage, and Containment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With over 35 years experience, a long-standing commitment to the environment, and highly qualified staff, Nilex delivers the products and technologies that give clients an economic advantage with environmental benefit.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(748, 1, 'Nine Clouds Beds & Mattresses', 'bill@nineclouds.ca', '2273 Dundas St W, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.nineclouds.ca ', '(905) 607-6862', '', '', '<p>Over the years we&rsquo;ve inconsistently provided beds to many local charities. More recently we have formed a passionate alliance with Interim Place Women&rsquo;s Shelter. Each month we happily deliver at no cost a minimum of six brand new mattress sets and supporting bed frames to families re-establishing themselves in our community and we are very happy to do so. Each December deliver a number of extra sets based customers purchasing master bedroom quality sets throughout the year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(749, 1, 'Nisku Industrial Coatings Ltd.', 'nicltd@telus.net', '2109, 5 St, Nisku, Alberta, Canada', 'www.niskucoatings.com ', '(780) 955-9696', '(780) 955-7676', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nisku Industrial Coatings Ltd. is a privately owned, Alberta-based company established in 2002. Over the past decade, we have built our reputation for service and quality products with our local markets, focusing on the oil and gas sector. We understand that time is valuable, mistakes are costly, and projects need to go to plan and on schedule. Our long background in the coating application industry has provided this insight to ensure our customers always receive the best service, never have to worry about product shortages or delays, and have access to hands-on troubleshooting to help make processes more efficient.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our commitment to providing superior quality products when you need them means Nisku Industrial Coatings is the first and only call you need. We specialize in product sourcing, carry crucial sundries and equipment for a one-stop shop, and quickly custom match colours to prevent project delays. With locations in the Edmonton-region and Calgary, we are focused on being accessible and available to our customers at all times.</div>', ''),
(750, 1, ' NLP Technologies inc.', 'info@nlptechnologies.ca', '52 Le Royer St W, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.nlptechnologies.ca ', '(514) 733-8884', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Based on the academic study and research project of Dr. Atefeh Farzindar, the company was established in February 2005 by Dr. Farzindar and Massoud Hosseiny, a graduate of the &Eacute;cole Polytechnique of Montreal.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Through the use of its patent-pending technologies of intelligent summarization and translation, NLP Technologies is now providing primary-source legal information to judges, lawyers, educators and other professionals in a timely and comprehensive manner. By focusing on specific areas of law such as Immigration, Intellectual Property, and Taxation, NLP supplies easy access to case law through weekly bulletins, and specially-adapted search solutions, as well as government statistics, and a virtual library of provincial and federal legislation, international instruments, manuals, forms etc. NLP&rsquo;s platform for presentation of these materials is unique and user-friendly. NLP Technologies constantly strives to improve its products and explore new ways to make the practice of law easier.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NLP Technologies is able to produce high quality translation in a timely and cost effective manner by using translation expertise and the latest in translation technology in the form of CAT (Computer Aided Translation). Computer Aided Translation, resulting from internal research and development, combined with a translation management system (TMS) enabled NLP Technologies, while maintaining translation quality and accuracy provide a translation service over a continuous demand cycle, processing large volumes of government documents.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(751, 1, 'Noble Foods Inc.', 'info@noblefoods.com', '250 Avro Rd, Pointe-Claire, Quebec, Canada', 'www.noblefoods.com ', '(514) 426-0680', '(514) 426-7291', '', '<p>&nbsp;ver the years that Noble Foods has co-packed bars for our customers, we have garnered a reputation for our close customer service and our ability to develop great tasting bars at a surprisingly quick pace. Whether you have a completed formula or are looking to have something developed for you, it is our pleasure to work with you to develop your bar in a timely fashion that ensures an opportune delivery to market.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Noble Foods produces it\'s bars on a Sollich slab line. All productions are temperature controlled, tightly monitored for consistency and texture and every single bar is metal detected and weighed on on-line check-weighers in order to ensure that they conform to our clients\' specifications.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Noble Foods adheres to all Good Manufacturing Practices and scrutinizes all documentation, records, operations and quality systems through independent auditors, client auditors, government inspections and self audits.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(752, 1, 'Nodelcorp Consulting Inc.', 'joan@nodelcorp.com', '106 Goodridge Dr., ST. ALBERT, Akberta, Canada', 'www.nodelcorp.com', '(780) 418-3380', '(780) 418-3384', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a boutique consultancy offering professional services in climate change adaptation, greenhouse gas mitigation and management, and facilitation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our clients include provincial and federal government agencies, companies and associations.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We can help you understand your climate change and greenhouse gas emission risks and develop pragmatic and cost effective strategies to manage those risks.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(753, 1, 'Nomad Boatbuilding', 'nomad@nomadboatbuilding.com', '1204 Clovelly Terr., Victoria, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.nomadboatbuilding.com', '(778) 433-0140', '', '', '<p>Builder and restorer of wooden boats, canoes and kayaks.</p>\r\n<p>Builders have used half hull models to shape their ideas into full sized boats for hundreds of years. It wasn\'t until the concept of a naval architect came into being that drawings became a means of conveying these shapes to three dimensions. Still there were many well-known builders who never could read a drawing, but worked exclusively from half hull models.</p>', ''),
(754, 1, 'Nor-Am Doors And Windows Ltd.', 'email@blissnoram.com', '30 North Wind Place, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.blissnoram.com', '(416) 755-0880', '(416) 755-3259', '', '<p>&nbsp;Bliss Nor-Am Steel Doors and Windows is a combination of two of North America\'s most respected Steel Window Companies, Bliss Cashier Metal Products and Nor-Am Doors and Windows Ltd.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Bliss Steel Products of Syracuse N.Y. was established in 1922. In 1982 the company became Bliss-Cashier Metal Products and produced Commercial steel windows at this location until 1996.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Nor-Am Doors and Windows was incorporated in 1983 by the executives of two Canadian Steel Window manufacturing and installation companies having continuous experience in the industry since 1959. Nor-Am has established an enviable reputation for quality products, delivered on time as agreed with the client.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Specializing in Heavy Intermediate Steel Doors and Windows, Nor-Am also produces Commercial Aluminum windows, Heavy Duty (hollow metal) doors and custom profile windows and miscellaneous metal products and railings in steel, aluminum and stainless steel.</div>\r\n<div>In 1996 a joint venture was formed between the two companies. The fabrication equipment of Bliss was moved to the manufacturing facility of Nor-Am in Toronto.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Bliss Nor-Am continues to provide a complete service to the industry, including design consultation, manufacture, finishing. Nor-am in addition provides installation and glazing to the Canadian market.</div>', ''),
(755, 1, 'Nordex Wood inc.', 'mlefebvre@boisnordex.com', '480, rue Hébert, MONT-LAURIER, QUEBEC, Canada', 'www.boisnordex.com ', '(819) 440-4600', '(819) 440-4200', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Lumber, Plywood and Millwork Wholesaler-Distributors</span></p>', ''),
(756, 1, 'North American Metalcraft Inc.', 'joseph@namc.ca', '840 Flint Rd, North York, Ontario, Canada', '', '(416) 665-5544', '(416) 665-8713', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; line-height: 16.2000007629395px;\">North american metalcraft designs and creates showcases that house the world\'s most exquisite merchandise. with old world craftmanship combined with uniquely modern materials, the company offers a finished product that is both beautiful and functuional.</span></p>', ''),
(757, 1, 'Nova Kool Mfg. Inc', 'novakool@novakool.com', '1578 Hartley Ave., Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.novakool.com ', '(604) 523-6515', '(604) 523-6674', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nova Kool manufactures more than 25 quality refrigeration products for mobile and off-power grid applications such as Marine, RV and Trucking. Nova Kool products include DC and AC/DC models of refrigerators and freezers in single door, two door, side by side and upright configurations. Sizes range from 0.8 to 9.1 cubic feet.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Nova Kool continues to focus our product offering to the mobile and off power grid applications. Innovation has helped us expand our product offering to include more than 20 distinctive models, many of these models are a direct result of our customers feedback. The current offering includes single door units from 0.8 cu.ft. to 5.8 cu.ft., double door units from 4.2 cu.ft. upto 9.1 cu.ft. and also our LT series of icebox conversion kits. Nova Kool prides itself on being the easiest in the industry to do business with, continually providing our customers with timely information, products and services.&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(758, 1, 'NSC Minerals Ltd.', 'nsc@nscminerals.com', '2241 Speers Ave, Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, Canada', 'www.nscminerals.com ', '(306) 934-6477', '(306) 242-0178', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NSC Minerals Ltd is a leading supplier of industrial mineral products specializing in bulk and packaged rock salt.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NSC Minerals was established in 1988. The company\'s growth is a result of 3 key factors: (1) the ever-expanding spectrum of products offered (2) a stead-fast commitment to providing a high quality product at a competitive price and (3) strategically located bulk storage facilities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">NSC Minerals Ltd has two modern operating plants with a daily production capacity in excess of 6,000 tonnes of salt crystals, located at Rocanville and Vanscoy, SK Canada. The Rocanville Plant is located in southeast Saskatchewan near the Manitoba border and the Vanscoy Plant is located in central Saskatchewan approximately 40 kilometers southwest of Saskatoon.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our bulk products are used for a variety of applications such as: Highway De-icing, Livestock Feed Supplements, Hide Curing, Drilling Muds, Water Softening, Road Stabilization, and Industrial Applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our packaged ice melter products are used in a variety of consumer and industrial applications.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(759, 1, 'Nu-Way Kitchens Limited', 'harvey@nuwaykitchens.com', '1328 Topsail Rd., Paradise, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', 'www.nuwaykitchens.com ', '(709) 782-1711', '(709) 782-4710', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nuway Kitchens limited was founded in 1967 by harvey short sr. the initiative to focus on custom-built cabinetry that was durable, artistic and reasonably priced, has resulted in an outstanding and proven reputation in both renovation and new home construction.</p>', ''),
(760, 1, 'NWP Industries Inc.', 'debdeb@nwp.ca', '4017 60th Ave, Innisfail, Alberta, Canada', 'www.nwp.ca ', '(403) 885-4656', '(403) 885-4841', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Like many businesses in the Western Canadian oil patch,&nbsp;&nbsp; NWP, grew out of the dream and ambition of a dirt poor Saskatchewan boy, who wanted nothing more than to become a millionaire.&nbsp; After all,&nbsp;&nbsp; when you are young and picking up old batteries and scrap metal for a few bucks in small town Saskatchewan, you already have the beginnings of the entrepreneurial spirit that&rsquo;s required to create a successful venture into the Western Canadian Oil patch.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, NWP Industries Inc. employs over 100 exceptional people who know the values of hard work, customer service and quality.&nbsp; We still have our roots in Blackfalds, with store distribution, rentals and yes, used pipe, but we have also grown into one of the most respected manufacturing companies in the patch. NWP has the honour of building and distributing equipment for some of the world&rsquo;s most prestigious oil and gas companies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(761, 1, 'Nygard International Ltd.', 'sharon.clarke@nygard.com', '1771 Inkster Blvd., Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.nygard.com ', '(204) 982-5000', '(204) 697-1254', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Woman\'s Fashion Designer, Importer, Manufacturer , Wholesaler and Retailer&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(762, 1, 'Oakrun Farm Bakery Ltd.', 'customerservice@oakrun.com', '58 Carluke Rd W, ANCASTER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oakrun.com ', '(905) 648-1818', '(905) 648-8252', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">When we say farm we literally mean it. When we say country goodness we deliver on that too!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Located in the farming heartland of Ancaster, Ontario, one hour from the U.S. border, our bakery was founded in 1979 by John and Ellie Voortman. It all started with a great idea to supply the local community with preservative-free baked goods in a 2,000 square foot bakery attached to the Voortman&rsquo;s horse stables.&nbsp; The bakery grew at such an accelerated pace that the stable was soon shut down to allow the bakery to expand.&nbsp; And expand we did.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, with over 237,000 square feet dedicated to our bakery operation and over 30,000 square feet of onsite freezer space, we boast over 11 production lines and bake over 400 high quality and consistently produced fresh and frozen products for our in-store and food service clients across North America. Our bakery is Kosher certified as well as organic through the OCCP.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a first rank high volume and highly efficient bakery that specializes in key product categories.&nbsp; We are pioneers in proportioned frozen batters (muffins, cookies, scones, tea biscuits), and we are experts in what believe are the best tasting, quality English muffins and crumpets in the marketplace.&nbsp; In fact, Oakrun Farm Bakery branded English muffins and crumpets are the #1 brand in Ontario. We also specialize in delicious sweet muffins, bagels, angel food cake, traditional and premium loaf and pound cakes and artisan Danish.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are very proud of the partnerships we have developed over time and how we have progressed as a company.&nbsp; We continue to invest in our facility, our people and how we go to market. For our Ontario based in-store retail bakery clients we offer direct store delivery for our fresh made baked goods.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(763, 1, 'Oakwood Air Limited', 'gloria@heatwave-hvac.com', 'B-387 Carlingview Dr, Etobicoke, Ontario, Canada', 'www.heatwave-hvac.com ', '(416) 675-2233', '(416) 675-8896', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1963 Oakwood Air Ltd. has been active in the heating, ventilation and air conditioning business. First serving the multi family housing business as a mechanical contractor providing service and installation to the condominium and apartment sector. As the company expanded Oakwood Air Ltd. changed direction and began manufacturing air conditioning equipment under the brand name HEATWAVE Air Conditioning. The first efforts where focused on manufacturing air conditioning equipment that was no longer distributed by the original manufacturer. Today, manufacturing air conditioning equipment for the Commercial and Residential market is Oakwood Air Ltd. primary business. Providing the HVAC industry with quality manufactured air conditioning &amp; heat pump equipment at a competitive price is our company goal.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Oakwood Air Ltd. manufactures air conditioning equipment at our factory in Toronto, Ontario. Our assembly staff are qualified with many years of refrigeration and air conditioning experience. Our design engineer\'s oversee ever stage of our production ensuring the highest level of quality standards. Prior to shipping, every unit is run tested in the factory test lab. The units are tested for leaks, secure electrical connections and quality assemble. All performance ratings are gauge checked to ensure capacities are being achieved in our test lab. Heat pump units are run tested in heating and cooling mode operation.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(764, 1, 'Objectif Lune Inc.', 'info@ca.objectiflune.com', '500-2030 Pie-IX Blvd, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.objectiflune.com ', '(514) 875-5863', '(514) 342-5294', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Objectif Lune&rsquo;s mission is to free customers from legacy mentality by creating elegant software tools to help our customers communicate more effectively with their customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Design, distribution, management and/or re-engineering of data driven communications, all parts are covered, independent of hardware compatibility considerations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(765, 1, 'Ocean Case Co. Limited', 'sales@oceancase.com', '252 Aerotech Dr., Enfield, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.oceancase.com ', '(902) 873-3045', '(902) 873-3046', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ocean Case Company Limited is a leading manufacturer of reusable shipping cases and containers. We are based in the Aerotech Business Park at Halifax Robert L. Stanfield International Airport, Canada. Ocean Case is strategically located to ship custom cases worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our specialty is in manufacturing short runs of cases in quantities of 25 to 200 pieces at a time. We are set up to inventory and expedite cases worldwide to customers who require just in time shipments on a regular basis. We can put in place a weekly or monthly delivery schedule for any number of cases needed. Please email your inquiry to sales@oceancase.com. A company representative will contact you to discuss your requirements.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our manufacturing facility uses the latest in computer controlled machinery. Our panel processing department utilizes a CNC panel saw and a CNC machining center. Precise cutting of extrusions is achieved using numerically controlled measuring systems. Riveting is performed using the best in hand held and automatic machinery. A modern well equipped facility coupled with the desire to provide complete customer satisfaction makes Ocean Case your number one choice for reusable shipping case products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(766, 1, 'OCEANAIR CARGO INC', 'operations@oacargo.com', '5770 Highway 7 2nd floor, Woodbridge, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 850-2696', '(905) 265-2146', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Oceanair Cargo Inc are Freight Forwarders based in Canada.Oceanair Cargo\'s network of agents throughout the world allow you the opportunity, with one phone call, to coordinate airfreight shipments worldwide for the most safe, timely, seamless and cost effective manner possible. At Oceanair Cargo, we have been meeting our customers\' air freight needs ever since our establishment with fast, efficient service and an on-time performance record that has been impeccable. Our customer commitment is as strong as ever. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From dangerous goods to general cargo to perishables, Oceanair Cargo handles all airfreight shipments in the most professional, reliable and expeditious means possible using the world\'s scheduled airlines and all cargo fleets offering thousands of flights daily on which to move freight to any location around the world. Whether you\'re flying the smallest or largest consignments to any part of the world, Oceanair Cargo is there for you and your customers needs. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We select the most appropriate carrier for your shipment that gives you a head start over any other air freight forwarder. Taking into account the variations in summer and winter timetables and the impact of size and weight restrictions will help you avoid unnecessary costs and delays in shipping your freight around the world.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(792, 1, 'Ouellet Doors & Mouldings Inc.', 'commande@pmouellet.com', '1906, rue Boyer, Baie Comeau, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pmouellet.com ', '(418) 652-1422', '(418) 652-3633', '', '<p>&nbsp;Pr&eacute;moul&eacute; is the North American industry leader in postformed countertops and custom cabinet doors and accessories.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>More than ten HPL Postformed countertops profiles are offered in over 500 stocked colours and finishes. Our thermoplastic doors and components program is the most complete customized program in the industry. Additional accessories, wood doors, polyester doors and quartz countertops complement our offering.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>At Pr&eacute;moul&eacute;, we do not simply follow trends and technological developments. We create them!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We operate six plants in eastern Canada, which positions us well to deliver our products throughout North America. In addition, thanks to an impressive network of cutting centers, Pr&eacute;moul&eacute; is present and responds quickly and efficiently to our customer&rsquo;s needs.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our markets include cutting centers, kitchen designers, woodworkers, specialized distributors, closet furniture manufacturers, furniture and component manufacturer of all types, designers and architects.</div>', ''),
(768, 1, 'Odotech Inc', 'info@odotech.com', '3333, ch. Queen-Mary Bureau 301, Montreal, Quebec, Canad', 'www.odotech.com', '(514) 340-5250', '(514) 340-5211', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Odotech&rsquo;s mission is to provide communities and industry with sophisticated tools to see, track and control odor generated by odor producing sites. Working with governments, businesses, community groups, and neighbours, Odotech provides real-time odor tracking information for the benefit of all stakeholders in communities across the globe.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Odotech is an environmental company with a patented electronic nose specializing in the measurement and monitoring of odors at waste water treatment plants, composting sites, landfills, rendering plants and industrial odor producing plants. The system alerts operators when odors begin to reach threshold values, enabling them to proactively respond before an odor problem occurs. As the population grows and is moving closer to odor emitting sites, the need for odor management is growing exponentially.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Odotech also provides odor audit &amp; studies, dispersion modelling reports and consulting.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With offices in North America, Chile and France, Odotech is the leader in odor monitoring with over 80 installations worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(769, 1, 'OES, Inc', 'oes@oes-inc.com', '4056 Blakie Rd., London, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oes-inc.com ', '(519) 652-5833', '(519) 652-3795', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OES provides innovative technology solutions for a diverse range of applications and markets through three business divisions &ndash; OES Technologies, OES Scoreboards, and OES Electronic Manufacturing &amp; Design Services (EMDS).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OES&rsquo;s core engineering capabilities in electrical, electronic, mechanical design, and software development combined with extensive application experience contribute to the successful commercialization of new products and technologies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OES&rsquo;s process engineering experience supports world class in-house automated manufacturing, assembly, and test processes. This experience contributes to a consistent level of production, quality product, and time to market. OES&rsquo;s Quality Management System is an integral part of the entire organization<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OES&rsquo;s founding principles based on customer relationship and customer service form the vital cornerstone of our corporate business philosophy.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(770, 1, 'Offshore Interiors Inc', 'mail@offshoreinteriors.ca', '8-31272 Peardonville Rd, Abbotsford, British Columbia, Canada', 'offshoreinteriors.ca ', '(604) 309-4995', '(604) 557-1164', '', '<p>&nbsp;Offshore Interiors Inc. is a company that provides the services of design, fabrication, and installation of yacht interior millwork. We cater to private boat owners as well as the needs of the yacht manufacturing and retrofit industry. Our crew has the knowledge and experience to assist you from the initial design stages through to final installation. Past projects have included everything from one of a kind custom furniture pieces to complete yacht interiors.</p>', ''),
(771, 1, 'OHM Industrial Designers Inc.', 'kmosna@ohm.ca', '210-270 Sherman Ave N, Hamilton, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ohm.ca ', '(905) 527-4064', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;OHM provides an intensive product design package incorporating in-depth research, innovative design, engineering, graphics and manufacturing assistance. This integrated approach enables OHM\'s clients to get to market quicker with greater impact. The goal at OHM is to understand and anticipate the needs of the consumer through research, observation and practical experience. At OHM, we help develop new products that improve the quality of people&rsquo;s lives.</p>', ''),
(772, 1, 'Okanagan Precision Machine Ltd.', 'opm@opmachine.com', '1-230 Lougheed Rd, Kelowna, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.opmachine.com ', '(250) 765-1611', '(250) 765-6711', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OP Machine is a full service machine shop offering a complete range of custom precision machining and turnkey manufacturing solutions. Our dedicated staff can offer a variety of machining options in both milling and turning with the capacity to handle prototype batch sizes up to full production quantities. Our welding/fabrication and assembly departments give our customers added flexibility in project management, keeping more processes in-house, adding value and cost effectiveness to even the most complex jobs. Dedicated to providing the highest level of quality, OP Machine is certified and registered with the ISO 9001:2008 quality management system. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to our full service shop capabilities, OP Machine also offers a design and drafting department utilizing the latest 3D CAD software. Manufacture drawings can be created in-house from customer supplied solid models or we can take your sketch or idea and provide full design support in bringing it to realization. With our comprehensive experience and trusted reliability you can be confident in choosing OP Machine for your next project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(773, 1, 'OLEOTEK inc.', 'info@oleotek.org', '835, rue Mooney O, Thetford Mines, Quebec, Canada', 'www.oleotek.org ', '(418) 338-1318', '(418) 338-1338', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Oleochemistry deals with the physico-chemical transformation of fats and oils from animals and vegetables. First used in the fabrication of soaps, oleochemistry is now part of our daily lives where it is found in a wide variety of sectors: food, cosmetics, pharmaceutical and industrial.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The raw materials of the oleochemical sector are:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vegetable oils such as rapeseed oil as well as those derived from soybean, sunflower, safflower, corn, peanut, palm, coco, castor, etc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fats and oils from animals like rendered fats, tallow, lard, fish oil, etc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Recycled fats and oils like grease from restaurants, used frying oils, trap greases, etc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To offer quality services to businesses in applied research and technical assistance, to elaborate and complete technological innovation projects, to spread information and integrate continual training in the industrial oleochemistry sector in order to actively and distinctly contribute to the implementation and the maintaining of a regional hub of excellence in this sector.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Of Excellence: By constantly looking to improve its services and by being at the forefront of its area of expertise while continuing on the path of improvement and innovation in its personnel and its own operations<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(774, 1, 'Olympic Plastic Bags (1983) Limited', 'mail@olympicplastic.com', '35 Mid-Dominion Acres, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.olympicplastic.com ', '(416) 299-0536', '(416) 299-9034', '', '<p>&nbsp;Olympic Plastic Bags Ltd., a family owned and operated business; has stood at the forefront of the polyethylene packaging industry for more than 23 years. Olympic Plastic Bags is recognized as one of Canada&rsquo;s leading manufacturers of plastic bags, specialty products and solutions in flexible packaging, with one of the largest packaging inventories in the country consisting of hundreds of items in stock. Olympic Plastic Bag provides complete, end-to-end solutions to the largest distributors of packaging materials in Ontario, Canada. At Olympic Plastic Bags, we pride ourselves with wholesale factory- direct pricing that will save you time and money.</p>', ''),
(775, 1, 'Omcan Inc.', 'general@omcan.com', '3115 Pepper Mill Crt., Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.omcan.com ', '(905) 828-0234', '(905) 607-0234', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">Over the last 60 years, Omcan Inc. has grown to become a leading supplier to the food service industry in Canada and the USA. Our success over these many years is directly attributed to our established relationships with all of our valued customers and through providing them with Diverse, Dependable and Proven products. Omcan continues to help our customers remain competitive.</span><br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">With associates in North America, Europe, and Asia, our global footprint continues to expand and we hold to the principle that clients benefit from the accessibility and familiarity of sales teams. In 2012 as our geography and brand recognition continued to grow, we changed to one name Omcan Food Machinery.</span><br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">In over 200,000 sq ft of warehouse space we stock over 2,000 quality food equipment and supplies for the food preparation market. Our friendly sales, customer service and product service teams are always available to quickly provide you with the information you need.</span><br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">Omcan will continue its mission of supporting the food service industry by providing our customers with the peace of mind they get from our process excellence and quality products, we deliver.</span></p>', ''),
(776, 1, 'On Track Manufacturing Corp.', 'info@ontrackcorp.com', '800-15355 24th Ave Dept. 570, Surrey, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.ontrackcorp.com ', '(604) 538-7362', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">World\'s largest manufacturer of automotive anti-radar and anti-laser accessories. We have been in business since 1993. We export to 43 countries.&nbsp; ON TRACK Manufacturing Corp. is a highly established firm, in business since 1993. In that time, we have quickly grown into the world\'s largest manufacturer of passive anti-radar and anti-laser automotive products. We have operations in both Canada and the USA<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ON TRACK manufactures every product you see on our web site, and sells to dealers and distributors on a world-wide basis.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PROVEN OVER TIME: Our most popular selling product, the Protector, has now been on the market since 1996 and in over 43 countries to which ON TRACK now exports.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VOLUME DISCOUNTS: Dealers, distributors, and importers are able to buy directly from the manufacturer at large volume discounts. We also work with agents.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">DEALER SUPPORT: ON TRACK has a strong dealer support program. We provide our wholesale customers with the tools to become greatly successful with our products.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(777, 1, 'OneCAD Solutions Ltd.', 'info@onecad.com', '202-325 Renfrew Dr., Markham, Ontario, Canada', 'www.onecad.com', '(905) 943-7667', '(905) 943-7411', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OneCAD Solutions Ltd. provides mechanical engineering contract design services, 3D CAD &amp; 2D drafting, FEA &amp; CFD analysis and reverse engineering.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OneCAD is authorized by the Association of Professional Engineers of Ontario to offer professional engineering services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We work with engineering and manufacturing companies on a project basis. Typically our clients call us when they have extra work on but it&rsquo;s not enough to be hiring on more full time staff or they need a small team to help but only for a short period of time.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In many cases they have us work on the 3D modeling or the detail drafting so that their own staff can concentrate on getting the design engineering done in order to meet their deadlines.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(778, 1, 'Open Seas Instrumentation Inc.', 'openseas@openseas.com', '124 Petpeswick Rd W, MUSQUODOBOIT HARBOUR, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.openseas.com ', '(902) 889-3339', '(902) 889-3313', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We manufacture oceanographic equipment for the international scientific community. Open Seas is a manufacturer of equipment for physical oceanographers and marine biologists. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Marine Biology products are various types of fully instrumented zooplankton sampling systems. These are multiple net, with propietary datalogger and deck operating software. They include the Bioness, &nbsp;Mininess, RMT and Tucker Trawls. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company also specializes in highly stable mooring systems for oceanographic instrumentation. The SUBS line is a system used for mooring current meters, ADCP\'s, acoustic and and optical instruments. By using patented streamlined buoys, the moorings are kept very stable, vortex shedding is virtually eliminating which substantially reduces mooring oscillation, and instrument data is significantly enhanced.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Open Seas provides trawl resistant bottom mounts for <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">instrumentation (primarily ADCPs and ADPs), significantly reducing fishing gear depredation. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Subs streamlined buoys have been configured as Sidescan tow bodies which allow sidescan sonar operators to work and obtain good data in sea states that were previously impossible. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company has recently introduced a line of low torque oceanographic swivels. These are primarily used on instrumented moorings. They are ball bearing, oil-filled, pressure compensated and low maintenence. Presently available in 1 tonne SWL, stainless 316 construction.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(779, 1, 'OpenText Inc', 'info@opentext.com', '75, rue Queen Bureau 4400, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.opentext.com', '(514) 908-5406', '(514) 908-5407', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OpenText is the leader in Enterprise Information Management (EIM).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our EIM products enable businesses to grow faster, lower operational costs, and reduce information governance and security risks by improving business insight, impact and process speed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OpenText welcomes you to our ever growing community. Engage with us in your conversations. Tell us what is on your mind. Engage with your OpenText peers and peers around the world to come up with the best solutions to your challenges.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(780, 1, 'Opsal Steel Limited', 'sales@opsalsteel.com', '19388 Enterprise Way, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.opsalsteel.com ', '(604) 533-5555', '(604) 533-8680', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Opsal Steel Limited, owned and operated by British Columbian people, is a company founded on a tradition of excellence; excellence in product and excellence in customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&quot;The provision of crafted products for industrial uses... coupled with personalized customer service, will always be the motto of Opsal Steel Limited and of every Opsal employee.&quot; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">These company goals were set by Opsal Steel Limited at the inception of the company. for 80 years Opsal Steel Limited equipment has been known throughout the forest, mining, construction and fishing industries for its\'strength, dependablity, precise machine work, careful fitting and assembly. Over the years we\'ve prided ourselves in manufacturing practical, quality equipment that gives you an excellent retrun on your investment. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our trademark &quot;OSCO&quot; has come to be recognized as a hallmark of quality. we are vitally concerned that our equipment give better-than-average satisfaction. In keeping with this policy, we are constantly introducing imporovements and new designs. While we take pride in supplying new equipment of the most modern type, we deen it of equal importance that our customers get one hundred per cent service out of our equipment already in use. We are in a position to ship promptly from stock at all times; not only the newer type of equipment, but also parts required for many of our older designs no longer being manufactured.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We want you to know that our interest in the &quot;OSCO&quot; equipment which you purchase does not end with the bookkeeping transaction. We back up every sale with as much service as possible. Please feel free to call on us for information and advice.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(781, 1, 'Opta Minerals Inc.', 'info@optaminerals.com', '47 Morton Ave E, Brantford, Ontario, Canada', 'www.optaminerals.com ', '(905) 689-6661', '(905) 689-0485', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Opta Minerals is North America&rsquo;s leading integrated processor/distributor/seller of industrial minerals. From our roots providing sand to a local foundry in the 1880s, Opta has grown to an international group of companies in Canada, the United States and Europe, all committed to delivering optimal results for our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We source, process and distribute a wide range of products and services, from traditional copper and coal blasting slag to patented silica-free abrasives, construction-grade and golf course sand, water filtration media and jet cutting garnets, all used in a variety of industries and applications.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(782, 1, 'Optima Telecom, Inc', 'info@optimatele.com', '4-20 Cachet Woods Crt, Markham, Ontario, Canada', 'www.optimatele.com ', '(905) 477-0987', '(905) 477-5579', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Optima we are pioneering the merger of network technologies, applications and architectures.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is to bring together the latest in data communication and telecom applications. We custom build leading-edge data transport and management products. And we do not stop until we have a a tailor-made solution for each of our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">It is our belief that by working together we can help, optimizing our product line to fit the most demanding application. Optima Telecom is about making the connection, expanding your reach and enhancing your scope.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Building sustainable networks using the latest in clean-technologies has long been our goal. We embedded all our products with green DNA. Right from our beginning more than a decade ago. Long before it became fashionable to flaunt energy consumption ratings at every opportunity. And we did not stop there. Reducing our environmental impact is an ongoing effort and we are proud of our record to date. Optima. Greener by design.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(783, 1, 'Optimum Production Services Inc.', 'louis@optimumprod.com', '1490 South Sheridan Way, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.optimumprod.com ', '(905) 278-2125', '(905) 271-8687', '', '<p>&nbsp;OPTIMUM PRODUCTION SERVICES INC. produces the best foreign (dubbed) versions in over 45 languages. Based in Mississauga (Toronto), Ontario with production offices in Montr&eacute;al, Qu&eacute;bec, and Mexico City, we benefit from a vast pool of performers.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(784, 1, 'Orbit Manufacturing Inc.', 'orbit@telus.net', '104-3070 Norland Ave, Burnaby, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.orbithydraulics.com ', '(604) 293-0063', '(604) 293-0064', '', '<p>&nbsp;Orbit Manufacturing Inc. has over 30 successful years of hydraulic industry experience in North America. Most of this time has been spent in the servicing and manufacturing of hydraulic pumps, cylinders, and jacks. During this time we found that the most common problems with the industry standard steel hydraulic jacks is their tendency to corrode as well as the fact that these steel jacks are very heavy and difficult to handle.</p>', ''),
(785, 1, 'Ordan Thermal Products Ltd.', 'info@optimatele.com', '9-21 Amber St , Markham, Ontario, Canada', 'www.OrdanThermal.com ', '(905) 475-9292', '(905) 475-3286', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ordan Thermal designs, builds, and services industrial heating systems (including combustion controls, burners, flame safeguards, regulators/governors, mixers, valves, motors, blowers) and many other parts used in the manufacture of combustion heat processing systems. With a primary focus on Industrial Food Processors; namely industrial and wholesale bakeries, Ordan Thermal is able to offer complete turn-key custom combustion solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ordan Thermal is a producer of CSA approved and design certified to ANSI Z21.20 Automatic Gas Ignition Controls and related components. The microprocessor controls are designed for use in many heating applications such as industrial and commercial gas burners, gas furnaces, boilers, water heaters, gas fireplaces, infra-red and radiant heaters, commercial cooking equipment, commercial dryers and virtually all other types of low temperature heat processing applications. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are also a certified Distributor of CHAIN GUARD Industrial Lubricants brand of special synthetic food grade lubricants. Including; lubricants for oven, proofer and cooler chains for the Baking Industry formulated to operate in high temperature and extreme environment applications. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As suppliers of complete heat processing systems, our goal is to fit each job to the customer\'s specifications. We specialize in food processing industries and mainly in the baking industry. Ordan Thermal supplies combustion systems and designs for various industrial and commercial combustion heat-processing applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Endurance is the word best fit to describe the combustion heat process equipment supplied by Ordan Thermal. Over the years, we have gained a growing reputation for the supply of solid, age enduring, efficient, and trustworthy equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">An innovative and versatile approach to process heating allows Ordan Thermal to operate as problem solving partners with your specific applications. The common belief of matching every product to the client\'s specific requirements, and not simply to act as order takers or salespeople, is echoed throughout Ordan Thermal\'s entire staff. The services offered by Ordan\'s team of professionals continue after the product has been delivered. At Ordan Thermal, pride is taken in looking out for the customer. This level of honest service - the foundation of Ordan Thermal Products - will continue to be the cornerstone of the company well into the future.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As the existing and potential applications for industrial and commercial heat processing are virtually unlimited, at Ordan Thermal our job is to put your needs first, and ensure a quality solution to your combustion heat processing application.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(786, 1, 'Original Foods ltd.', 'service@originalfoods.com', '701 Broad St E, Dunnville, Ontario, Canada', 'www.originalfoods.com ', '(905) 701-7010', '(905) 701-7015', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Original Foods was founded in 1947, and has since been producing and selling food products under its own brand name as well as private labels for some of the largest national retailers. Boasting 3 production plants operated by 150 employees, Original Foods is one of the few enterprises specializing in seasonal confectionery. Caramels and marshmallow-based treats are examples of products that made it an industry leader for more than 65 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With its state-of-the art production facilities and team of experts in sweet and salty products, Original Foods can quickly adapt to the growing needs and expectations of its many clients and consumers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Original Foods serves various food markets, and can adapt to the unique needs of its many different clients. Whether serving retailers in Qu&eacute;bec, Canada or the United-States, distributors or wholesalers in the restaurant business, or baking and pastry specialists, Original Foods will develop the product that you want in a size and package that meets your needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(787, 1, 'Orion Health Ltd', 'michael.craig@orionhealth.com', '1900 - 10020 - 101A Ave, Edmonton, Alberta, Canada', 'www.orionhealth.com ', '(780) 969-0200', '(780) 420-9959', '', '<p>&nbsp;Orion Health is a global, independently owned eHealth software company with proven experience in delivering interoperable, connected solutions for healthcare facilities, organisations and regions.</p>', ''),
(788, 1, 'Oscardo Inc.', 'amigo@oscardo.com', '14-1145 Bellamy Rd N, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oscardo.com ', '(416) 785-8618', '(416) 785-4531', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">scardo has a long illustrious history as a supplier of high quality products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our story begins in 1987, when the Lulka brothers acquired a neckwear company established in 1959. Oscardo\'s winning collections of elegant neckwear and associated products have since been a staple at men\'s wear establishments and have been customized for many private label and corporate programs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Atlas Umbrellas, established in 1932 and acquired by Oscardo in 1995 , has a worldwide reputation for high quality and superb style. Atlas flourishes as part of Oscardo, and continues to provide the world with the most beautiful umbrellas.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Skemo, established in 1956 and acquired by Oscardo in 1997, provided Oscardo\'s entr&eacute;e into the Canadian gift and souvenir business. The tradition continues as Oscardo distributes unique souvenirs designed by Native Artists and featuring stunning Canadian and North American images.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Oscardo products can be found in the smallest family-owned boutiques and the largest department stores. Our customers include museums, public and private art galleries, National Parks and Government agencies. We export to over a dozen countries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is to establish a mutually profitable relationship with every customer. We are proud of our reputation for excellent design, high quality products, and for quick turnaround and accurate deliveries.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(789, 1, 'Origin BioMed Inc.', 'info@originbiomed.com', '1K-102 Chain Lake Dr, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.originbiomed.com ', '(902) 423-5745', '(902) 492-0013', '', '<p>&nbsp;Origin BioMed manufacturers products with the highest quality active ingredients at therapeutic levels, with the science or clinical evidence of their effectiveness. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(790, 1, 'Orillia Woodworking Inc.', 'info@owwinc.com', '11 Progress Dr., Orilla, Ontario, Canada', 'www.owwinc.com ', '(705) 327-0700', '(705) 327-7998', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Orillia Woodworking has been in business since 1988. Our employees are very involved and dedicated to meeting customers&rsquo; expectations in a courteous and timely manner. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">What began as a pallet-making plant has evolved and expanded to include 24,000 square feet of manufacturing space at two locations with modern equipment and a dedicated team of employees.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We produce both stock and custom trim, moulding, flooring and siding which are sold to retail outlets and directly to builders and contractors. The pallet operation continues in a separate location.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(791, 1, 'Otman Associates', 'info@otmanassociates.com', '1801-1 Yonge St, Toronta, Ontario, Canada', 'www.otmanassociates.com ', '(647) 931-4017', '(647) 931-4016', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a marketing firm based in the Greater Toronto Area. We specialize is PPC marketing (Facebook, Google Ad Words, etc.), search engine marketing and affiliate marketing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">What makes us different from most other marketing companies is that we do all the work ourselves. We don&rsquo;t outsource so with don&rsquo;t have the added overheads and expenses that don&rsquo;t benefit you. This means you are getting the same results or better as the larger agencies without the added costs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">You see, hiring a marketing company like Otman Associates, is much like hiring a mechanic for your car, there are a lot of things going on behind the scenes that are outside of your expertise and that you can&rsquo;t see, this means you need to find a company that you will have confidence in.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Otman Associates is a professional online eCommerce marketing and specialist search engine optimization company based in the Greater Toronto Area. We are involved in affiliate marketing and also provide affordable local seo services for small business. We are seo experts in local listings, lead generation and organic natural search engine optimization services.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(793, 1, 'Outdoor Outfits', 'info@outdooroutfits.com', '400-372 Richmond St W, Toronto, Ontario, Canada', 'www.outdooroutfits.com', '(416) 598-4111', '(416) 598-4626', '', '<p>&nbsp;Outdoor Outfits is a manufacturer of uniform outerwear since 1945. We are recognized for our attention to detail, selection of styles and colours, on-time delivery, and flexibility in meeting customer specifications. The company manufacturers in its own production facility with state-of-the-art machinery and a quality workforce. Our extensive line of protective outerwear for public safety; includes duty jackets, cargo trousers, leather jackets and rainwear. Our certifications include HI VISIBILITY (CSA-Z96 and ANSI-107), protection from viral contaminants (NFPA-1999) and quality assurance (ISO-9002). We are currently the holder of multiple PCPG/BPS contracts. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(794, 1, 'Overhead Management Group Inc', 'paulchateau@shaw.ca', '4916 Batchelor Cres NW, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'overheadmanagementgroup.com', '(403) 730-4419', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Energy efficiency is one of the best long-term investments property owners can make to save money, ensure protection from rising power prices, and protect the environment.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Investment in energy efficient lighting is an intelligent business decision. The correct lighting implemented in your building has many benefits.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>OMG provides products and consulting services aimed towards reducing overhead costs, with little to no capital expenditure, using energy efficient strategies and products. We offer product management services for implementation of said strategies. Examples of products available are environmentally friendly fuel enhancers/additives, energy efficient lighting solutions, and overal energy efficient consulting.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(795, 1, 'Owen Oil Tools', 'austin.obermeyer@corelab.com', '2100 - 125 - 9th Ave SE, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.owentools.com ', '(403) 571-2400', '(403) 571-1635', '', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Owen Canada is a manufacturer and supplier of completions,&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">perforating and abandonment systems to the oil &amp; gas industry. We&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">have been in operation for 17 years, with employees worldwide,&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">and are listed on the NYSE under the trading symbol CLB.&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(796, 1, 'Estonian Expo Center', 'info@estonianexpocenter.com', 'Tallinn Airport, Gate-3, Tallinn, Ta, Estonia', 'www.estonianexpocenter.com', '+372-605-8120', '+372-605-8120', '', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bring your company to the heart of Tallinn Airport!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\">The most visible way to market globally!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For three years our permanent business fair near Gate 3 has been making it possible for different companies to use the large target group to market and brand their products and services. Our goal is to help companies to get noticed by the potential business partners and clients all over the world. Through active promotion and personal approach the trained staff of Estonian Expo Center creates the first contact with the representative of the field you are interested in. Whether you sell products or services, import or export, whether your business field is in textile or in metal &ndash; no industry has been left unnoticed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date: <span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>May 02, 2011</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">End Date: <span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Jan 24, 2016</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(797, 1, 'Best International Exhibition Organization', 'bestguangzhou@vip.163.com', 'Xingang East Road, Guangzhou, HK, Hong Kong', 'www.84t.cn/en/index.asp', '+86-20-8961 7099', '+86-20-8961 7161', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Best International Exhibition organization was founded in 2001 and became one of the largest and most influential exhibition organizations in China. There were three fully owned companies. Hong Kong Best Exhibition Group, Guangzhou Best Exhibition Co. Ltd. and Guangzhou Yifa Exhibition Co., Ltd. Scope of business involved exhibition organization and planning, conference marketing, brand consulting, planning activities and media information. Since its establishment, Best had been successfully held dozens of large and medium-sized international exhibitions</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Benefiting from the rapid development of China Exhibition Economy, Best International Exhibition focus on the Chinese market, organized more than 10 large-scale exhibitions in Guangzhou, Beijing, Shenzhen and other places each year. Relates to vehicle air conditioning, forklift, logistics equipment, RFID, medical instrument, outdoor &amp; leisure industry, engineering machinery, auto parts, food industry, pharmaceutical machinery, financial management, etc. And automotive air-conditioning exhibition, forklift &amp; logistics equipment exhibition have become the leading brand in the same exhibition project. After 12 years of development, Best International Exhibition Group has become the backbone of China\'s private exhibition industry</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start Date: <span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Mar 12, 2015</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">End Date: <span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Mar 14, 2015</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(798, 1, 'Bangkok International Trade Fair 2015', 'info@bigandbih.com', '44/100 Nonthaburi 1 Road, Bang Kra Sor, Nonthaburi , Thailand', 'www.bigandbih.com', '+66-819-2606', '+66-819-2606', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Bangkok International Gifts and Bangkok International Houseware Fair (BIG + BIH), jointly organized by The Department of International Trade Promotion of the Ministry of Commerce and the Thai Lifestyle Products Association is by far a stage that offers an opportunity for business operators to present their ultimate quality design and lifestyle products to the whole world. This important regional exhibition bring together thousands of buyers from all over the world, its operated twice a year (April and October).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Venue - Bangkok International Trade and Exhibition Centre (BITEC), Bangna, Bangkok, Thailand<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Organizer - Department of International Trade Promotion, Ministry of Commerce, Royal Thai Government Of&amp;#64257;ce of Export Promotion Activities<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">44/100 Nonthaburi 1 Road, Bang Kra Sor, Nonthaburi 11000, Thailand<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date: April 19, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">End date: April 23, 2015</span></p>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(799, 1, 'SIAL Canada', 'apedreira@expocanadafrance.com', '2120 Sherbrooke East, suite 901, Montreal , Qc, Canada', 'www.sialcanada.com', '+1 514-289-9669', '+1 514-289-1034', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">SIAL Canada 2015 will be the country\'s most important agri-food industry event.</span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">SIAL Canada is the only event of its size in the country, bringing together more than 800 national and international exhibitors from 45 countries, all while welcoming more than 14,000 buyers from Canada, the United States and 64 other countries.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">In addition, SIAL Canada is the only domestic show offering up a complete range of food products, all under the same roof, and in so doing, meeting the needs of your clients &ndash; whether they\'re inretail, food service or food processing &ndash; that are on the lookout for new innovative, specialty, ethnic or regional products&hellip; from right here, or from across the globe.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start Date:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space: pre;\">	</span>Apr 28, 2015</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">End Date:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Apr 30, 2015</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Expected in 2015:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">14,000 professional visitors<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">800 exhibitors from 45 countries, including Canada<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">240,000 sq/ft of exhibiting space (+ 10% compared to 2013 in Toronto)<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(800, 1, 'The 15th China International Food Exhibition', 'gzyfzl@163.com', 'Room 201-219, Yanling Road, Tianhe District, Guangzhou, China', 'www.ifechina.com', '+86-20-29188293', '+86-20-6108-9459', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">China Import &amp;Export Fair Complex covers 700 thousand square metres, the largest exhibition centre in Asia, with the most advanced facilities, highest level, can satisfy the large international commodities fair, large trading exhibition which demand the exhibition centre to be Multi-function, comprehensive, multifunctional, high standards, High-technology, intelligent, perfect ecological. China Import and Export Fair Complex is the landmark building of the new image and is one of the tourism scenic spots<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">China Import and Export Fair Complex has convenient transportation, the exhibition hall was set up with the subway platform, and all the urban main road go through these area from all directions. It just take 2 minutes walking from the Pazhou Station in line 8 to 14.2-16.2 halls in C area<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date: June 04, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">End date: June 06, 2015</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(801, 1, 'The 9th China Guangzhou Int\'l Billiards Exhibition', 'sales7@grandeurhk.com', 'Third Street of Kehui, No.100, Science City, Guangzhou, China', 'www.gbechina.com/index_en.html', '(+86-020&#65289;2831', '(+86-020) 82579220', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">As one of the biggest international billiard exhibitions in the world, GBE has already become the must-attend exhibition for the world billiard industry. Despite the weak economy around the world, GBE2014 was successfully concluded in Guangzhou in April, 2014. The success of previous sessions ensures this show as one of the most attractive trade fairs in Billiard field worldwide, and ensures it as a better platform for professionals and specialists in this field to get together</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">Although the global economic situation is not very well and billiard industry is influenced, GBE2014 still attracted top billiard suppliers both at home and abroad, including Shender, Yalin, Wiraka, Rasson, Predator Group (USA), Iwan Simonis S.A. (Belgium), Longoni Cues Italy, McDermott Cues (USA), Hainsworth Cloth (England), Aramith Ball (Belgium), Dynamic Billiards(Germany), Palko Pty Ltd (Australia), Master Cues, Fury Cues, etc. Furthermore, there is an increasing number of international brands express that they will choose GBE as their premier business platform to exhibit their products</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">GBE2015 - The most Influential Worldwide billiard Pageant</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">GBE2015, supported by over 50 international professional associations and more than 60 professional media, will be staged in the Import and Export Fair Pazhou Complex during May 9th - 11th, 2015. GBE is the best platform for worldwide billiards enterprises to improve brand valuation, showcase the latest products and technology as well as a pageant for professional buyers to seek top-notch suppliers</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">For more detailed information about GBE, please visit www.gbechina.com. We are looking forward to meeting you at GBE2015 and to celebrating the feast together</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Start Date:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>May 09, 2015</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">End Date:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>May 11, 2015</p>', ''),
(802, 1, 'THAIFEX World of Food 2015', 'thaifex@ditp.go.th', '563 Nonthaburi 1 Road, Bang Kra Sor, Nonthaburi , Thailand', 'www.thailandfoodfair.com', '+662 507 8359', '+662 547 4268', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hall occupancy</span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Challenger 1, 2, 3 + IMPACT Forum Hall 9</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Construction and dismantling periods:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Build up : 18-19 May, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Dismantling : 25 May, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Target groups Exhibitors: Producer and Manufacturer, Exporters<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Visitors: Hotels, Restaurants and Bars, Supermarkets, Grocery and Convenience Stores, Departmental Stores, Food Catering, Importers, Distributors, Wholesalers and Retailers, Food Manufacturers, Fast Food, Food Service, Bakeries, Airlines, Clubs and Resorts, Packaging and Distribution Centers, Institutional and Commercial<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Entrance fee: Free of charge<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">2014 Facts and Figures&nbsp;&nbsp;  <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">No. of Exhibitors: 1,463&nbsp; exhibiting companies<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">No. of Countries represented: 35 (Algeria, Argentina, Australia, Bangladesh, Belgium, Brazil, Cambodia, Chile, China, Denmark, Ethiopia, Germany, Hong Kong, India, Indonesia, Italy, Japan, Laos, Malaysia, Mexico, Myanmar, Peru, Philippines, Singapore, South Korea, Spain, Switzerland, Taiwan, Thailand, The Netherlands, Turkey, USA, United Arab Emirates, United Kingdom and Vietnam)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date (Trade): May 20, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date (Public): May 23, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">End Date: May 24, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(803, 1, 'China International Coffee Industry Expo 2015', 'info@coffeexpo.org', 'No. 25-27, Yanling Road, Tianhe, Guangzhou, China', 'www.coffeexpo.org', '+86-20-6108-9279', '+86-20-61089459', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"text-align: justify;\">China (Guangzhou) International Coffee Industry Expo 2015(ICE2015) which was organized by Coffee Branch of China Fruit Marketing Association and China National Food Industry Association will be held on June 4-6. Coffeexpo2015 focus on assisting oversea companies to find the distributors and agents to expand the coffee market in China, there are exhibitors and visitors from more than 30 countries paticipate in the exhibition. We provide the toppest tradeshow platform, don\'t hesitate to seize the opportunity, and create your brilliant business in China! Sincerely looking forward to meeting you in ICE2015!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Exhibition profile:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-18.0pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">&middot;<span style=\"font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]-->Exhibition space of IFE China covers 5 halls at 50,000 sqm, one special hall for coffee industry is about 10000 sq. m. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-18.0pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">&middot;<span style=\"font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]-->192 coffee exhibitors come from 15 different countries and regions, including 7 country pavilions<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-18.0pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">&middot;<span style=\"font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]-->10280 coffee industry professional visitors come from 20 different countries and regions<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-18.0pt;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">&middot;<span style=\"font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]-->309 representatives attended in our exhibition, 196 from domestic area and 113 from abroad.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Start Date: June 04, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">End Date: June 06, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(804, 1, 'Wine & Gourmet Taipei', 'info@winegourmettaipei.com', '8F -3, No. 9, Dehuei Street, Taipei, Taipei, Taiwan', 'www.winegourmettaipei.com', '(+886)  2259-5421', '(+886)  2595-5726', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Integrates The Entire Supply Chain Of The Wine Industry<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">covering both local and international wine agents, wineries, professional wine cellars, and International high-end wine glasses, etc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wine &amp; Gourmet Taipei is the only professional exhibition in Taiwan that integrates the entire supply chain of the wine industry, covering both local and international wine agents, wineries, professional wine cellaret and high-quality accessories. WGT also includes a variety of gourmets, master classes and extensive programs. This is the only professional major sourcing platform in Taiwan, which makes the interaction possible between wine importers, industry-related parties, professional buyers, and consumers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date: June 26, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">End Date: &nbsp;June 28, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(805, 1, 'Bangkok Electric & Electronics', 'tiditp@ditp.go.th', '563 Nonthaburi 1 Road, Bang Kra Sor, Nonthaburi , Thailand', 'www.bangkok-electricfair.com', '(+66) 2 507-8374 - 7', '(+66) 2 547 4282', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Thailand is one of the world&rsquo;s major exporters of electrical goods and electronic products to the world markets including Japan, China, USA, Hong Kong, Singapore, the Netherlands, Germany, Malaysia, Australia, South Korea and UAEIn 2015 Bangkok E&amp;E expects to draw trade visitors from Asian countries, South Asia, Japan, China, India, Egypt, USA, the Middle East and EU</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Bangkok E&amp;E 2015 will showcase the latest energy-saving innovations and eco-friendly technologies from Thailand and other leading producing countries including Japan, Korea, Taiwan, Hong Kong, China, Singapore, Malaysia, India, USA and Europe&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Start Date: Aug 14, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">End Date: Aug 16, 2015<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(806, 1, 'OXAND Canada', 'contact.ca@oxand.com', '2500-1155 Rene-Levesque St W, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.oxand.com', '(514) 313-6058', '(514) 286-6078', '', '<p>&nbsp;Oxand is an international consulting and solutions provider with proven capabilities, knowledge and tools for capital intensive assets. As an independent company, we deliver risk-informed decision support information that improves returns across the life cycle of our clients&rsquo; assets. Our worldwide clients are investors, owners, contractors and managers in Energy (Nuclear, Oil &amp; Gas, Renewables), Transport (Railways, Roads &amp; Waterways) and Public/Private Properties (Public Infrastructures, Private &amp; Industrial assets).&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(807, 1, 'Oxbury Group Incorporated', 'rlavigne@oxburygroup.com', '949 Deer Valley Dr., Oshawa, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oxburygroup.com ', '(416) 949-5573', '', '', '<div>Oxbury Group is an Canadian based IT solution provider with commitment to servicing SMB\'s. Oxbury Group provides a variety of IT services focusing on IT Alignment within your business.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Oxbury Group is a Canadian based IT service provider. Our technology services range from consulting, technical support, outsourcing, web and software development and fully managed IT service solutions. We have experience in many industry sectors but our focus is on small to medium sized businesses. After years of dealing with enterprise companies our team of professionals prefers to deal in the fast paced SMB segment.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We find that SMB&rsquo;s are friendly and know what they want. We enjoy being part of your business team as apposed to just another numbered vendor in a long list of service providers working for the fortune 500&rsquo;s. Oxbury Group collaborates with its clients to help them achieve their business goals and execute their long term strategies. We want to become part of your team working with you to succeed. We can only be successful if you are successful.</div>', ''),
(808, 1, 'Oxford & Ewing Engineering Inc.', 'gewing@oeeng.com', '585 Riverview Dr., Chatham, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oeeng.com   ', '(519) 355-0959', '(519) 355-0961', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Oxford &amp; Ewing Engineering Inc. is an controls engineering firm <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">providing professional engineering, project leadership, construction management and support services to help its clients achieve higher levels of efficiency through proper application of control system technologies. With over thirty five years combined experience in the automotive manufacturing, food &amp; beverage and energy industries, the company offers an extensive portfolio of services to suit the clients&rsquo; specific requirements. These services range from expert technical support, process evaluations and enhancements to complete design, build, commissioning and continuing support for automated plant floor production processes, factory wide data networks and SCADA applications. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;We work in partnership with our clients to help them evolve their process by applying innovative methods and the appropriate technology, ultimately to achieve the most cost effective, reliable solution with optimal performance and minimum business risks. Our services can be rendered as a standalone project or as part of the client&rsquo;s lean manufacturing program. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Quality is the cornerstone of Oxford &amp; Ewing Engineering&rsquo;s commitment to provide services and solutions that fully meet its clients&rsquo; needs and expectations. Oxford &amp; Ewing Engineering is currently implementing ISO 9001. This strong focus on quality, together with our dedication to client satisfaction and industry expertise, assures our clients of receiving the very best in professional services from concept through to final product. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Oxford &amp; Ewing Engineering sets high standards of excellence in delivering its services. From the initial conceptual and development phases through to the final product, we are diligent in providing the progress reporting, documentation and training necessary for successful completion. Our success indicators are the client&rsquo;s satisfaction with the end product and the quality of our services.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(809, 1, 'OYG Consulting Inc', 'info@oyginc.com', '38 Sapphire Cres., Brampton, Ontario, Canada', 'www.oyginc.com ', '(416) 731-9356', '(905) 846-9777', '', '<p>&nbsp;OYG is in business to help people and teams solve problems and deal with change. Through a unique strategic process that utilizes creative problem-solving tools, we help give you and your people the tools that they need to solve their problems in real time. We provide measurable, customized career management and talent development solutions to help both people and organizations deal with change and become top performers.</p>', ''),
(810, 1, 'Ozocan Corporation', 'info@ozocan.com', '12-690 Progress Ave, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ozocan.com ', '(416) 439-7860', '(416) 439-6806', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozocan Corporation has been supplying complete ozone generating systems since 1954. Ozocan generators have been used primarily for bottled water, municipal drinking water plants, waste water, odor reduction applications and cooling tower water.&nbsp; Ozocan has also supplied ozone to laminating plants to speed up the application of PE (polyethylene) to paper.&nbsp; Ozocan laboratory facilities provide determination of ozone demand and bromide conversion to bromate studies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We manufacture and supply:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone generators (Oxygen &amp; Air fed)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone contactors (contact chambers)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone destructors (to destroy excess ozone after process)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone analysers (OzoMeter ozone analyzer)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone is a form of oxygen whose highly unstable nature (due to its extra oxygen atom) makes it an excellent oxidizing agent; 1.5 times greater than chlorine. Ozone is a benign, non-persistent molecule with a very short half-life in water. It is used extensively in bottled water and frequently for municipal potable tap water.&nbsp; Ozone does not produce halogenated compounds such as Trihalomethanes, which are strongly suspected to be carcinogenic, and is the most effective treatment for Cyryptosporidium. All of these elements support The Ozone Advantage over conventional, chemical water treatment practices in North America.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozocan Corporation is a leading manufacturer of Ozone Generators and Purifiers.&nbsp; Our Ozone Generators are used world wide in commercial, industrial, and institutional applications.&nbsp; The Ozocan group has provided technology and service for nearly 50 years and continues to meet the needs of our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Mission: TO PROVIDE SOLUTIONS TO THE WATER AND WASTEWATER PROBLEMS OF OUR CUSTOMERS.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(811, 1, 'Ogden Granite Ltd.', 'info@ogdengranite.com', '3140 Griffin Rd., Ogden, Quebec, Canada', 'www.ogdengranite.com', '(819) 876-2424', '(819) 876-7359', '', '<p>&nbsp;Ogden Granite Ltd. was founded in 1981 as a family business. The founder\'s were third generation granite worker\'s (today we are fourth generation). We started as a small company with one fulltime employee and over the years have grown to well over thirty employees. We have also added and expanded our buildings several times during the same period. We are a supplier specialized in granite monuments. Ogden Granite Ltd. employ\'s some of the finest memorial worker\'s in North America. They crafted and designed some of the most beautiful granite funeral monuments in North America. On this website you will be able to see some of the incredible work our employees have produced for different projects like the Blood Spalding project the York University (commemorative for their opening) and the Prince Arthur project in Toronto. On this site you will also be able to see a sample of monuments and urns that we can customize at the families request. We have lots of beautiful designs of memorials and carvings to give tribute to your loved ones. Our craftsmen can facilitate you in customizing and designing you memorial and are ready to help you with all your needs. Over the years our customers have given us a huge amount of thanks for the quality of work and the excellent service we offer.</p>', ''),
(812, 1, 'Oilfield Directory Publications Inc.', 'sales@oilfielddirectory.com', '7500-10301 104 St NW, Edmonton, Alberta, Canada', 'www.oilfielddirectory.com ', '(780) 701-7282', '(780) 701-7282', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a global technology company providing technology expertise, hardware, software development, including website and e-commerce development for the petroleum industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The # 1 Petroleum Domain name registry on the NET - Register yourname.com, .net, .org, .info, .biz. The easiest, most affordable way to register and manage your domain!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(813, 1, 'Ojibway Designs', 'hughart@onlink.net', 'Temagami First Nation Lot #118 Lake Temagami, Bear Island, Ontario, Canada', 'www.hughmckenzie.com', '(705) 569-2881', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canadian Ojibway Native Artist,with 45 years experience. bulk orders art of art-cards, prints, posters and consignment of Original art work. Forty five years experience: Original artwork, art-cards, prints, posters, and consignment work. special artwork for social services, Corporate Company\'s designs. I have Logos for Social Workers across North Eastern Ontario call, It Shouldn\'t Hurt to be a Child. Aboriginal Ojibway Artist, Prints, Art-cards, Originals. Also diploma: Substance Abuse Counsellor. Healing with Art and Music. Cultural: Seven Grandfather Teachings<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(814, 1, 'P&H Fabrication Inc.', 'blhagey@rogers.com', '3-652 Bishop St N, Cambridge, Ontario, Canada', '', '(519) 653-0503', '(519) 653-0796', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Material Handling Equipment Manufacturing,</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Conveyors, Automation, Fabrications, Work Stations.</span></p>', ''),
(815, 1, 'P.J. Wallbank Manufacturing Company Ltd', 'general@wallbank.com', 'Oxford County Rd. 8, Plattsville, Ontario, Canada', 'www.wallbank.com ', '(519) 684-7423', '(519) 684-6939', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wallbank is a North American company with ISO/TS Registration providing bolts, springs and wire formings to Automotive, Agricultural and Industrial companies. We produce high quality custom bolts and springs, have flexible production runs and can operate on short lead times.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wallbank Manufacturing was established in 1955 by Phil Wallbank and is an approved Supplier to most Automotive OEM and 1st Tier companies, also supplying springs to high profile Industrial Customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With the experience of several decades of spring making and an ideal location in the heart of Southern Ontario, Canada, P.J. Wallbank Manufacturing is in close proximity to Buffalo, New York and Detroit, Michigan and is well known for its quick response to customer needs whether in the United States or Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Utilizing the latest technology in conjunction with extensive employee training and involvement programs, our staff is unsurpassed in their dedication to quality and productivity, particularly our engineers who work closely with our customers from design and development to prototype and production.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Using the latest EDI and Internet technology, Wallbank Manufacturing has the capability to receive up-to-the-minute quality reports and automatic releases from our customers. We translate that data into realistic product scheduling and Just-In-Time manufacturing methods throughout our facility. When blended with old world craftsmanship, we provide our customers with the modernization and pride of workmanship they have come to expect from a world class manufacturer.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(816, 1, 'P.E.I. Fish Fertilizers Ltd.', 'peifish@eastlink.ca', 'P.O. Box 308, Souris, Prince Edward Island, Canada', '', '(902) 687-2829', '(902) 687-4141', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">P.E.I. Fish Fertilizers was incorporated in 1991 and is located in Souris, Prince Edward Island. The Company has a most modern process facility to convert fish wastes into a liquid fertilizer that is sold in various size containers under the trade name Gardener\'s Dream.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A key benefit of the product is that it is a value added item, turning fish wastes into a very usable product. Development work is presently being conducted to also incorporate lobster, crab shells, fish bone and seaweed into their formulations.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">P.E.I. Fish Fertilizers Limited collects fish wastes from seafood processing establishments in the surrounding area and brings the fish wastes to the company owned processing facility where with the addition of acids, the fish wastes becomes liquefied. The resulting liquid fertilizer is suitable for both indoor and outdoor use by plant and garden hobbyists and commercial growers. Its formulation meets the requirements set out by the Organic Crop Improvement Association, the certifying body for the organically grown fruits and vegetables.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(817, 1, 'P.L. Light Systems Canada Inc.', 'info@pllight.com', '4800 Hinan Dr. R.R. 1, Beamsville, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pllight.com', '(905) 563-4133', '(905) 563-0445', '', '<p>&nbsp;PL Light Systems develops and manufactures supplemental lighting systems for the horticultural industry. We offer a complete range of innovative fixtures, lamps and reflectors for optimized light distribution in a variety of technologies including LED, High Pressure Sodium (HPS), Metal Halide (MH), and Hybrid Systems. For each lighting solution, we provide a comprehensive light plan to ensure optimized crop growth through adequate light penetration and uniformity into the crop. Through our parent company Hortilux Schr&eacute;der, we are constantly involved in research, new developments and improvements to our lighting solutions so we can stay at the fore-front of innovation and technology in the grow lighting sector. Hortilux&rsquo;s strength lies in how it translates growers&rsquo; requirements and new insights into cultivation techniques, transforming technical possibilities into reliable products.</p>', ''),
(818, 1, 'P.W.I. Industries Inc.', 'info@pwi-industries.com', '8000, av. Duplessis, SAINT-HYACINTHE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pwi-industries.com ', '(450) 796-1770', '(450) 796-2188', '', '<p>&nbsp;The company was founded in 1950 by Henri M. Samson, father of the current president of the company, Pierre J. Samson, and grandfather of Jean Marc, Marie Jos&eacute;e and Bertrand who also participate actively in the company.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>P.W.I. Industries Inc. is a company who operates in the market of transforming carefully selected wood wastes into sawdust and woodflour of various sizes for its customers\' needs. Some of the applications include fur dressing, meat &amp; fish smoking, binding agent in thermoset plastics, insecticides and glue, bedding for laboratory animals and many more.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Over the years, the company has continuously improved the efficiency of its operations by installing the latest technology in electronic equipement, and today it has become one of the most technologically advanced in its field.</div>', ''),
(819, 1, 'P1 International Inc', 'info@p1international.ca', '4796 Dayfoot Dr., Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.p1international.ca ', '(905) 607-8468', '(905) 607-8879', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are here to to bridge the gap between the West and the East in the business world. Our role is to find and supply industrial raw materials and consumables to our valuable customers at the most competitive pricing combined with prompt shipment. Are you an OEM or a Manufacturer? Then you have come to the right place. Please let us know your requirements. We can source and supply &nbsp;through our &nbsp;associated offices and consultants &nbsp;located worldwide.</p>', ''),
(820, 1, 'Pac West Properties, Inc', 'gordie@pacwestproperties.ca', '408-318 21st St E, Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, Canada', 'www.pacwestproperties.ca ', '(604) 999-9688', '(604) 288-5155', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Pac West Properties specializes in providing our clients with integrated accommodation strategies<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our ability to service remote, rural and urban locations enables us to support your company&rsquo;s needs, where and when you need them across North America.&nbsp; As an Aboriginal company, we are committed to upholding our legacy of providing services and supplies to the discoveries and development in Western Canada where our history influences our future.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(821, 1, 'Pacific Basket Company', 'order@pacificbasketco.com', '23-91 Golden Dr., Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.pacificbasketco.com ', '(604) 552-0249', '(604) 677-5997', '', '<p>&nbsp;Pacific Basket Company, based in Vancouver, BC, is a leading Canadian online store for gifts and gift baskets shipped anywhere in Vancouver, the rest of Canada and the USA. For more than a decade, we\'ve been designing unique gift baskets and offering the latest in innovative gifts. With a variety of award winning designs combined with affordable pricing, our gifts and gift baskets are sure to leave a lasting impression.</p>\r\n<div>Our superb Holiday, corporate, gourmet, baby and theme product selection, one of a kind gift ideas, first-class delivery service and outstanding customer service will prove that we are your absolute choice for gift baskets in Canada and the United States. We offer creative gift solutions for a variety of occasions and themes including: gourmet food gift baskets, baby gift baskets, picnic baskets canada, fruit baskets in Vancouver, father\'s day gift baskets, mother\'s day gift baskets, corporate gifts, thank you gift baskets, birthday gift baskets, thank you gift baskets, newborn gift baskets, sympathy gift baskets, congratulations gift baskets, corporate gifts, personalized gift baskets, custom gift baskets canada, Christmas gift baskets, secretary\'s day gift baskets, summer gifts, graduation gift baskets, gifts for her and Mother\'s day gift baskets Canada.</div>\r\n<div>We specialize in unique gourmet gift baskets Canada, birthday gift baskets, gourmet gift baskets Canada, baby gift baskets, picnic baskets, corporate gift baskets Canada, mothers day gift baskets, Valentine\'s day gifts, Christmas gift baskets Vancouver, spa gift baskets, housewarming gift baskets, fruit baskets Vancouver, thank you gift baskets and wedding gifts.</div>\r\n<div>We use a variety of containers including bamboo, wicker, wood, metal, paperboard, faux leather as well as environmentally friendly containers and the latest trends in home decor.</div>', ''),
(822, 1, 'Paige Logistics Ltd', 'info@paigelogistics.com', '18781 74th Ave, Surrey, British Columbia, Canad', 'www.paigelogistics.com ', '(604) 800-1480', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Paige Logistics\' Transportation Services includes Over the Road Freight Shipping, with Logistics Management and Support, International Shipping Services, Intermodal Freight, major USA and Canada trucking routes, LTL, FTL Trucking, as well as Import/Export Documentation Assistance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We Strive to Get You the Best Rates in Transportation and Logistics Services from a Single Pallet to a Full Truck Load.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We Service Manufacturers, Retailers, Contractors, Distributors, Wholesalers of Produce, Forestry, Equipment and Machinery, Construction Projects, Oil Sands Projects, and Pipeline Projects.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Paige Logistics\' Transportation Services includes Over the Road Freight Shipping, with Logistics Management and Support, International Shipping Services, Intermodal Freight, major USA and Canada trucking routes, LTL, FTL.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Trucking, as well as Import/Export Documentation Assistance.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(823, 1, 'Paramount Windows Inc', 'customersupport@paramountwindows.com', '105 Panet Rd, Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.paramountwindows.com ', '(204) 233-4966', '(800) 665-7006', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Paramount Windows, our beginnings are the foundation on which we build our company\'s reputation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1948, when we started as a small family homebuilder and custom millwork shop, Paramount Windows has crafted quality windows and doors, making us a leader in our field. And while the technology and innovations from the past sixty years have advanced our craftsmanship, our family tradition of excellence and product integrity remains proudly unchanged. This means providing our customers with quality windows and doors, while remaining innovative in our manufacturing processes and maintaining integrity when it comes to the sales and service of our products. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Paramount windows and doors allow you to experience the world around you with the quality and beauty that has come to define our products over the past six decades. Whether it&rsquo;s our Signature Series Clad and All Wood windows, our Phoenix Series of composite windows, or the Freedom Series PVC windows, there&rsquo;s a window to fit your budget and lifestyle. Our doors also provide an abundance of options to enhance your home, with swinging and sliding patio doors, insulated entry doors, and aluminum storm doors. It&rsquo;s your world &ndash; experience it with windows and doors from Paramount.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(824, 1, 'PBA Industrial Supplies Limited', 'sales@pbaindustrial.com', '84 Clyde Ave, MountPearl, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', 'www.pbaindustrial.com ', '(709) 368-9800', '(709) 368-9814', '', '<p>&nbsp;P.B.A. Industrial Supplies Ltd. has been supplying industrial mechanical equipment to the Canadian marketplace for almost 20 years. P.B.A. Industrial Supplies Ltd. is a distributor of quality industrial products with our product main lines consisting of industrial hose, industrial couplings and clamps, hydraulic hose and fittings as well as an extensive line plastic modular conveyor belting.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As the Canadian manufacturer of plastic modular belting, we offer a extensive selection of conveyor belt solutions. We can provide conveyor belt solutions in a variety of shapes, sizes, materials and functions to support companies in various manufacturing environments. Whether your business is bottling, fruits and vegetables, meat poultry, seafood or another industry we will have a conveyor belt solution to suit your needs.</div>', ''),
(825, 1, 'PC Woodworking', 'info@communityconnectionsinc.com', '701 Water St W, Summerside, Prince Edward Island, Canada', '', '9024364274', '(902) 436-424', '', '<p><font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">PC Industries Inc. is a manufacturer of quality wood products. One half of our manufacturing is to supply the wholesale gift and juvenile products market. We emphasize traditional Canadian heirloom products - two prominent lines are &quot;Smiley the Pony&quot; line of rocking horses and infant cradles - all solid pine construction. Current market penetration is Canada wide.</span></font></p>\r\n<p><font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><br />\r\n</span></font></p>\r\n<p><font face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">The other half of our manufacturing is custom woodworking and millwork in the areas of office and church furnishings, furniture reproductions - solid pine and hardwoods construction. Current market penetration is the Atlantic provinces - Canada.</span></font></p>', ''),
(826, 1, 'PCL Industrial Constructors Inc', 'IndFabShopInquiries@pcl.com', '2107 4th St, Nisku, Alberta, Canada', 'www.pcl.com', '(780) 979-6300', '(780) 979-6363', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PCL is a group of independent construction companies owned by employee shareholders across the United States, Canada, and Australia. As a diversified general contractor, PCL celebrates the past and builds for the future.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The PCL family of companies has a century-long tradition of excellence, hard work, and a can-do attitude when providing construction services in the commercial, civil infrastructure, and heavy industrial markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This family of independent construction companies forms one of the largest general construction contracting organization in North America.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(827, 1, 'PDi-Pharmaceuticals, Inc.', 'Mail@PDi.ca', '16401 Dufferin St , Kongcity, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pdi.ca ', '(905) 886-7886', '(905) 886-7886', '', '<p>&nbsp;Our mission is to provide the best quality, cost effective solutions to our clients in the areas of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients, Regulatory Services and Finished Dosage products as well as Reference Standards.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>PDi was founded in the year 1978 and today counts among the top respected pharmaceutical distribution and Regulatory Service companies in Canada. PDi is a subsidiary of Heste Corporation, a diversified group with interests in Pharmaceuticals and Equine products, Thoroughbred and American Quarter Horse Breeding &amp; Race Horse Training Facilities. We have a successful record of being &Acirc;&lsquo;behind the scenes&Acirc;&rsquo; of several pharmaceutical product launches in Canada.</div>', ''),
(828, 1, 'PDK Projects, Inc.', 'dmalley@pdkprojects.com', '5072 Vista View Cres., Nanimo, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.pdkprojects.com ', '(250) 751-8890', '(250) 751-8225', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our vision is that rapid analytical tools based on near-infrared spectroscopy are widely used for decision making in agriculture and the environment, for the betterment of quality of life and environmental health.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mission: Meeting client needs in monitoring and protecting environmental quality through new and innovative applications of near-infrared spectroscopy and assisting in the evaluation and effective application of the technology to other needs. Offering customized education and consulting.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company is flexible, innovative, forward-looking, and well-connected to the global NIRS community. Company principals have more than five decades of varied experience in NIRS (including many first-time applications), agricultural product quality, aquatic science, fisheries science, sustainable development, and global environmental issues.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PDK Projects, Inc. was incorporated in Manitoba, Canada in December 1997 and registered in British Columbia in July 1999. PDK Projects, Inc. is an equal opportunity employer and an employer of youth.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(829, 1, 'PE INTERNATIONAL Canada Inc.', 'info@fivewinds.com', '203-1339 Wellington St, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pe-international.com', '(613) 722-6629', '(613) 722-0574', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sustainability Performance is now firmly on the agenda of all large and progressive companies. Increased profitability reduced operating costs and enhanced brand reputation together with growing consumer demand for sustainable products and government legislation are driving the adoption of sustainable business practices in every industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PE INTERNATIONAL provides conscientious companies with cutting-edge tools, in-depth knowledge and an unparalleled spectrum of experience in making both corporate operations and products more sustainable. Applied methods include implementing management systems, developing sustainability indicators, life cycle assessment (LCA), carbon footprint, design for environment (DfE) and environmental product declarations (EPD), technology benchmarking, or eco-efficiency analysis, emissions management, clean development mechanism projects and strategic CSR consulting.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(830, 1, 'Peerless Electric Co. Ltd.', 'info@peerless-electric.com', '9145 Boivin St, Lasalle, Quebec, Canada', 'www.peerless-electric.com ', '(514) 595-1671', '(514) 595-4411', '', '<p>&nbsp;Peerless Electric is a leading Canadian lighting solutions provider specializing in the manufacture and supply of lighting fixtures for the commercial, industrial, institutional and residential markets.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Peerless products are specified by Architects and Engineers across North America and Peerless luminaires have been chosen for some of the most prestigious projects in Canada and abroad.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Peerless Electric Company Ltd., with modern production facilities in Montreal, Toronto, and Calgary has been manufacturing and supplying lighting fixtures for the North American market since 1939. Led by a dynamic management team, Peerless has continuously adapted to meet the needs of its customers and to apply the latest technologies.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The export marketing team of Peerless welcomes inquires for luminaries that meet regional or country specific requirements.</div>', ''),
(831, 1, 'Pega Medical Inc.', 'info@pegamedical.com', '1111 Chomedey Hwy (A13), Laval, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pegamedical.com ', '(450) 688-5144', '(450) 688-1977', '', '<p>&nbsp;Today, Pega Medical is known for its dedication to pediatric orthopedics. This niche was born in 1997 out of a growing demand from surgeons who wanted to be able to treat children as distinct individuals with their own complexities and needs, and not as small adults. The first two pediatric products that initiated this trend towards maintaining the normal growth of the child while correcting the deformity consisted on a non-fusion spinal device for the correction of idiopathic scoliosis and a telescopic rod for correcting bone deformities in OI (known today as the Fassier-Duval telescopic IM system).</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Pega Medical has continued to assist surgeons in solving surgical issues and focusing on new and improved devices especially designed and developed for the paediatric patient. Today, Pega Medical is recognized not only as a innovator with distinct devices reaching children with orthopedics conditions in over 50 countries around the world (a small international company with a brain), but also as company who puts the care of patients and the assistance to the surgeons as its first priority wherever they live (a small international company with a heart).</div>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(832, 1, 'Penmar Automation Inc.', 'mark@penmarautomation.com', '18-1151 Gorham St, Newmarket, Ontario, Canada', 'www.penmarautomation.com   ', '(905) 836-8103', '(905) 895-0364', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Penmar Automation Inc. is a provider of technical services and proper safety upgrades to the wider Automation Industry.&nbsp; Whether you require us to help bring your equipment up to current safety standards, build panels for your equipment, or provide on site assistance, we can fulfill all of your needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Penmar Automation Inc. is a provider of technical services and safety upgrades to the Automation Industry. Whether you require a complete safety upgrade, electrical control panel, rewiring or turnkey installation, we can offer the right solution to meet all your automation needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(833, 1, 'Pentco Industries Inc.', 'pentco@pentco.com', '9274, 194th St, Surrey, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.pentco.com ', '(800) 663-7915', '(888) 663-7915', '', '<p>&nbsp;As one of the largest cabinet door manufactures and distributors in Western Canada, Pentco Industries Inc. has been producing industry leading products for single/multi residential developments, commercial and institutional projects since 1979. Quality controlled for efficiency and excellence, Pentco&rsquo;s 80,000 square foot plant facility is equipped with the most advanced machinery and green manufacturing processes available. Consistently delivering top quality products and ensuring complete customer satisfaction, Pentco has earned the respect of a world wide range of clients. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(834, 1, 'PFS Logistics Inc.', 'sales@privatefleetsales.com', '368 Bussel Cres., Milton, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 876-3524', '(905) 875-3097', '', '<p>PFS INC. has been serving the needs of its customers on freight shipments between the united states and canada for the past twenty three years. Any shipments 1000 lbs. and up which are currently being handled by common carriers will be handled more efficiently and more rate competitive - references upon request.</p>\r\n<p>Our Company was established with the mandate to provide high-quality personalized service at very competitive rates. This remains the fundamental principle driving our company. We take a proactive approach to our clients&rsquo; needs. When you succeed, we succeed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Our strengths include providing LTL and full truck loads in Canada and the USA; on all types of equipment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We have the people, the equipment and the technology to exceed your expectations. Using our on-line database, we can match loads to trucks anywhere at anytime in North America. PFS provides the broadest possible range of services to meet your needs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We offer satellite tracking, so that all freight movement is fully traceable from pick up to delivery, the same truck that picks up your freight will deliver it to it&rsquo;s final destination, reducing transit time and damage claims.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Whether you are transporting one skid to truckload, PFS is prepared to get your freight moving. Our experience has shown us that customers require consistent personal attention to their shipments. From the point of pick up through to the final delivery our staff monitors every detail of your freight movement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We handle many diverse industries and understand the importance of proper handling of your freight from clean and odour-free trailers to any exceptional equipment needed.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(835, 1, 'Pfalzgraf Canada Inc.', 'bernds@pfalzgraf-patisserie.com', '90 Saunders Rd Units 4-5-6, Barrie, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pfalzgraf-patisserie.com ', '(705) 739-8980', '(705) 739-8981', '', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie offers more than 50 different kinds of premium quality cakes, from a truly decadent Chocolate Devotion Cake and Carrot Cake to delicious classics such as Black Forest, Chocolate Truffle Tortes and rich creamy Cheesecakes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The finest quality ingredients, master-baker techniques and our use of only traditional \'time proven recipes\' ensures our authentic European style cakes. Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie uses real cream in the making of many of our cakes. Real cream is fresh and natural. Its rich, creamy texture and full bodied colour makes it a perfect complement to our cakes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Throughout our entire BRC Certified process, controls are in place to ensure a safe and consistent product and our high quality standards are maintained.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie bakers are specially trained in old-world techniques of cake making. This attention to detail and the use of the freshest ingredients guarantee a product that is consistent and of the highest quality.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">At Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie we offer uncompromised service to our customers. By using carefully approved distributors as well as our own fleet of refrigerated trucks we are able to faithfully serve customers throughout Canada and the United States.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Ease in handling, timesaving, flexible inventory and superior freshness are Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie\'s unbeatable advantages.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">For the cake connoisseur, we offer the freshest and finest specialty cakes available. From simple to extravagant, Pfalzgraf P&acirc;tisserie frozen cakes offer you an unlimited variety of dining possibilities.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(836, 1, 'PG Hardwood Flooring Inc.', 'boispg@pgmodel.com', '2424 Principale St, SAINT-EDOUARD-DE-LOTBINIERE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pgmodel.com ', '(418) 796-2328', '(418) 796-3021', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PG manufactures flooring boards ready for factory finishing or varnishing on the premises after installation. Moreover, PG manufactures factory-finished flooring boards under the name, Model&reg;. All told, PG offers a range of more than 5000 distinct products. As a flooring manufacturer, PG Hardwood Flooring is renowned for the exceptional quality of its products and a solid reputation backed by more than 30 years of experience.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The PG acronym consists of the first letters of the last names of Julien Par&eacute; and Richard Garneau, co-founders in 1979 of PG Hardwood Flooring Inc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are proud of our membership in the most respectable organizations in our industry. All environmental and quality standards applied at PG are inspired by the regulations of our member associations. We are committed to offering the latest products available on the market in compliance with the most stringent environmental standards in effect.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">You are unique, and so are we!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(837, 1, 'PG Tex Inc', 'info@pgtex.com', '940 INDUSTRIEL BLVD, Terrebonne, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pgtex.com ', '(450) 434-0123', '(450) 434-1411', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;PG Tex is a complete promotional item and clothing distributor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We offer printing, embroidery and silk-screening among others as&nbsp;well as a complete line of promotional items.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1862, 217, 'TURRESS CORPORATION LIMITED', 'info@turresscorp.com', NULL, 'www.turresscorp.com', '1-289-925-2775', '', 'We offer prime quality products with competitive prices available on the worldwide market.', 'TURRESS CORPORATION LIMITED is a Toronto based import and export company, with well established connections in the UK, Dubai and Lagos providing an international platform on the worldwide market.Our operations are worldwide, dealing with manufacturers, suppliers, farmers and distrubutors globally  \r\n\r\nWith warehousing facilities and well-established connections across the globe, our products cater to a wider consumer base', 'import, export, grains, construction'),
(838, 1, 'PH Technologies Inc.', 'mcarpanzano@p-h-tech.com', '5887 ch. Saint-Francois, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.p-h-tech.com ', '(514) 334-7100', '(514) 334-8556', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To work in confidence with all our partners by presenting solutions and ideas for mutual profitable growth and success. Our goal is to understand our clients needs and present solutions that make us their premier partner.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We resolve to conduct our business with honesty, to avoid all deception and to deal fairly with all our partners and competitors. We are respectful our co-workers and to put our combined efforts upon our business.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(839, 1, 'Phantom Couriers', 'info@phantomcouriers.com', 'B301-325 Howe St., VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.phantomcouriers.com ', '(604) 899-5447', '(604) 899-7904', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Why us? Well, plain and simple we are good, hands down. Our customer retention level is astronomical, when clients come on board with us, they stay. Some of our clients even laugh at salespeople that come in and try to get them to switch, those always make for great stories.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are 100% locally owned and operated and we have no investors, we do it all ourselves, we are extremely proud that we need no outside help. Our owner is also the dispatcher, meaning he is hands on, knows what&rsquo;s going on all the time, constant communication is the keystone to our success with customer service and quality of service as the support, so to say.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(840, 1, 'PHD Medical Inc.', 'jeremy.brouillette@phdmedical.com', '100-500 Morgan Blvd., BAIE-D\'URFÉ, Quebec, Canada', 'www.phdmedical.com', '(514) 694-0367', '(514) 694-4280', '', '<p>&nbsp;PHD Medical Works closely with several sectors of the health system to design products and services to meet specific needs of the home diagnostic and telemedicine markets. With our technical and clinical expertise we offer complete solutions to the market that improve the treatment and well-being of patients. Each of our core product offerings focus on a distinctive segment of a typical healthcare encounter &ndash; Consultation, Diagnosis, and Care Management. &nbsp;We are specialists in migrating traditionally hospital based services to remote clinics and the home.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>PHD Medical leverages advancements in technology and applies it towards unique solutions that allows individuals and professionals to have better access and reach to care. Each solution seeks to eliminate constraints based on distance, cost, and expertise while maintaining high clinical standards.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All of our solutions are web based which allows medical information (data, audio, video, etc.) to be transferred effortlessly and securely regardless of location. This assures that individuals get quality care in a timely fashion &ndash; even from rural and remote locations. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(841, 1, 'Picard Ovens Inc.', 'info@picardovens.com', '1325 Notre-Dame St E, VICTORIAVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.picardovens.com ', '(819) 758-1883', '(819) 758-1465', '', '<p>&nbsp;Founded in 1957 Picard Ovens is the maker of the popular Revolution revolving oven. Its ovens are known for their compact size, versatility and economical cost of usage. The company\'s mission is to help their clients succeed in today\'s aggressive marketplace. &nbsp;Picard Ovens currently serves customers in the food service and bakery industries worldwide. It has won numerous awards for its innovative design and sustainability.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Always looking to offer you equipment which meets your high&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>standards of quality in regards to materials, design and&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>construction. We take all the necessary steps in order to&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>satisfy your expectations. We manufacture custom-made equipment&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>to suit your specific needs.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are sure that our products and our experience will be&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>profitable in the bakery industry in all the world.&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(842, 1, 'Pioneer Transformers Ltd.', 'rhaddad@pioneertransformers.com', '612 Bernard St, Granby, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pioneertransformers.com ', '(450) 378-9018', '(450) 378-0626', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Pioneer Transformers Ltd., designs and manufactures high quality/energy efficient liquid filled transformer up to 25 MVA at 69 kV (350 kV BIL). The head office and manufacturing plant has been located in Granby Quebec since 1965. We also have a sales/quotation office in the Greater Toronto area.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Pioneer Transformers Ltd., was purchased on March 1st 1995 from Group Schneider/Federal Pioneer. Since the acquisition, Pioneer has been through a few changes and investments which have elevated it into a high quality, reliable supplier to the electrical industry. We supply transformers for utilities, industrial and commercial customers, wind and solar farms and we have extensive experience with retrofit transformers.</p>', ''),
(843, 1, 'PJJ productions inc.', 'info@pjjproductions.com', '8 Saint-Francois St, VICTORIAVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pjjproductions.com ', '(819) 758-4000', '(819) 758-0619', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1985, PJJ Productions has delighted in helping Canadian companies project a more distinctive image. We are known for developing effective, reliable, easy-to-use sensory marketing products and services that meet our clients&rsquo; specific needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our specialties: On-hold messaging, Voice prompts, Background music and corporate radio, Digital signage<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We like to keep things friendly and simple. We are passionate about what we do and thoroughly enjoy the people we work with. We go all out to develop cooperative, candid, strong client partnerships, creating positive synergy that fosters bold, creative action that exceeds all expectations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This media broadcasting system created by PJJ Productions uses a unique platform with updates delivered through a secure Internet connection: Impeccable broadcasting quality, Easy to install, Low cost service, No parabolic antenna or other equipment required other than an in-store sound system, Content regularly renewed, No action required by personnel to operate the system, Music royalties included in monthly fees, And we manage everything remotely.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At PJJ Productions, we keep it simple.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(844, 1, 'PKL Technologies Inc.', 'pkain@pkltechnologies.com', '18911, 72 Ave NW, Edmonton, Alberta, Canada', 'pkltechnologies.com ', '(780) 486-9564', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PKL Technologies Inc. manufactures tunable diode laser (TDLAS) based gas detectors and monitors. Spectra-1 open path gas sensors are used in a variety of environmental and safety remote sensing applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PKL Technologies Inc. manufactures tunable diode laser (TDLAS) based gas detectors and monitors. Spectra-1 open path gas sensors are used in a variety of environmental and safety remote sensing applications. Spectra-1 gas sensors have been designed in a compact, easy to use, robust and portable format. Spectra-1 has been developed using proprietary hardware and software, to produce a low cost alternative for open path gas monitoring. Spectra-1 can operate from a 1 to 1000 meter path length. Spectra-1 units are available in hydrogen fluoride (HF), ammonia (NH3), carbon dioxide (CO2), Carbon monoxide (CO), methane (CH4), acetylene (C2H2), ethylene (C2H4), and others. Spectra-1 is used for: portable gas detection, open path gas detection, landfill gas detection, continuous emission monitoring, emission reduction, ambient air monitoring, carbon dioxide monitoring, methane monitoring, HF monitoring, leak detection, fugitive emissions, gas monitoring and others.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(845, 1, 'Placage Unique Inc.', 'jamie@placage.com', '35, rue St-Jean-Baptiste O, Rigaud, Quebec, Canada', 'www.placage.com', 'Placage Unique Inc', '(450) 451-4546', '', '<p>Manufacturer of spliced hardwood veneer faces (layons).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>Faces in all North American hardwood species.&nbsp;Offering veneer faces to manufacturers of Hardwood Plywood,&nbsp;Doors, Kitchen Cabinets and Furniture.&nbsp;Member of HPVA (Hardwood Plywood and Veneer Association)&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Member of CHPA (Canadian Hardwood Plywood Association) &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Specializing in the design and development of innovative&nbsp;manufacturing technologies and processes specific to splicing of&nbsp;veneer. Modern technological facilites and equipment. Leader&nbsp;in manufacturing quality.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Manufacturer of Spliced Hardwood Veneer. Species of veneer&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>include, Plain Sliced (PS) Cherry, PS Maple, PS Red Oak, PS&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>White Oak, PS White Ash, PS Walnut, PS Aromatic Cedar, PS&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Mahogany, PS Beech and specialties upon request..</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(846, 1, 'Pioneer Log Furniture', 'info@pioneerlogfurniture.com', '25080 RD26 N, GRUNTHAL, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.pioneerlogfurniture.com ', '(204) 434-6789', '(204) 434-9431', '', '<p>&nbsp;A family owned and operated business from Manitoba, Canada that has been building high quality heirloom furniture for nearly 25 years. Since 1980 we\'ve been crafting unique, one of a kind log furniture made from trembling aspen and knotty white pine. Initially it was for family and friends close to home and now includes individuals, families, corporations and businesses around the world.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We anticipate you will find what you are looking for and if not please call us at our toll free number listed above.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Looking forward to working with you and that you will not only become a customer but also a friend.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Pioneer Log Furniture is a family owned and operated business and has been building handcrafted log furniture for nearly a quarter of a century. Starting about 1980 we began in our basement building for neighbors and friends, and today have over 5000 square feet of shop area and ship around the world to the USA, Germany and Japan.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our family consist of myself, Daniel, my wife Della and our five children, Johanna, Deborah, Rebekah, Amos and Andrew. They are all a big help: peeling logs, sanding, drilling, packaging, answering phones, doing shows and a 1,000 other things. It is nice to be able to work together (and somethimes scrap) as a family and be able to instill in them the values, traditions and principles that will make them a valuable asset to their generation. We believe in putting God first in all things and in having the principles of honesty and integrity being reflected in our life whether it is at home, in our work or at play.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our master craftsmen include Jonathan who can design and build anything. Harry and Danny both born in South America brought many skills with them when they joined the team at Pioneer Log Furniture. Lester is our experienced cabinet and case goods professional with over 25 years in the industry. Vera is our very efficient and competent office manager who usually takes your calls and gets you the information and answers you are looking for.</div>', ''),
(847, 1, 'PIONEER STEEL MANUFACTURERS LIMITED', 'contact@pioneersteel.com', '1137 Lorimar Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pioneersteel.com', '(905) 564-1301', '(905) 564-1304', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Pioneer Steel Manufacturers Ltd. A name that is today synonymous with clear span, trussless, self-supporting arch style steel buildings. Pioneer Steel is a leading edge manufacturer and worldwide exporter of dependable, steel building solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1980, our premium quality, preengineered steel buildings have been in use for a wide range of agricultural, industrial, commercial, residential and recreational applications. Specialized in-house engineering facilities and our years of experience and expertise enable us to successfully design and create steel buildings for virtually any application quickly, efficiently and cost-effectively.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Pioneer Steel takes great pride in their reputation for providing steel building solutions for residential and commercial applications across North America and worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our ownership, senior executives, engineers, management, and senior factory personnel, are proud to have well over 200 years of collective experience and expertise in the manufacture, design and distribution of arch style steel buildings.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(848, 1, 'Plantech Control Systems Inc.', 'plantech@plantech.ca', '3466 South Service Rd., VINELAND STATION, Ontario, Canada', 'www.plantech.ca', '(905) 562-7345', '(905) 562-5958', '', '<p>&nbsp;Plantech Control Systems, for over 35 years, has been a leader in the area of greenhouse electrical, controls and automation. Our commitment to the greenhouse industry has provided us recognition not only locally but throughout North America as experts in our field.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Plantech is primarily an electrical contractor, licensed and trained to provide complete electrical installation and service. We are also the first and the largest full service dealer of Priva NA. Our expertise has allowed us to participate in the success of Priva NA throughout North America as well as overseas.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Plantech Control Systems is a CSA approved panel manufacturer. All controls panels are designed, manufactured and CSA approved at our facility, fully tested and supplied with CAD produced schematics and connection documents. We can provide complete installation or provide expert direction for your installer. Our staff is available around the clock for technical help or troubleshooting.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our product line also includes grow lights, EMI Circulation Fans, Javo Soil Handling Equipment, Aweta Vegetable Graders, and WanJet Spray Robots.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for the opportunity to present our products to you. Feel free to contact our sales staff or view our web site for a full description of our products and services.</div>', ''),
(849, 1, 'PM SYSTEMS', 'sales@pmsystems.ca', '6890 Davand Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pmsystems.ca ', '(905) 564-2955', '(905) 564-2966', '', '<p>&nbsp;PMSYSTEMS has long been the supplier of choice for most major oil companies and many other companies. Providing Liquid loading&nbsp;solutions, safe access and fall protection equipment.</p>', ''),
(850, 1, 'PMG Technologies Inc.', 'marketing@pmgtest.com', '100, rue du Landais, BLAINVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pmgtest.com/', '(450) 430-7981', '(450) 430-2318', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We continue to gain knowledge and expertise, in our quest for increasingly innovative solutions that continuously push the limit of existing technology providing our clients with results that surpass their expectations<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We strive to obtain accurate, repeatable and reliable measurements through the:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Development of clearly documented laboratory test procedures.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Development of strict quality control measures.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Establishment of automated report generation to assure accurate and expeditious results.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Major improvements to the facility were completed as a result of investments by Transport Canada to improve capacity and the repeatability of results. These improvements included upgrades to the:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Control of the propulsion system in the crash laboratory<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Environmental chambers through the introduction of CFC-free refrigerants<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The improvements also included the acquisition of<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">An instrumented load cell;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Two new prototype WorldSID dummies;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A servo-controlled acceleration sled;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">An automated steering controller;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Specialized high intensity lighting for the crash area.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(851, 1, 'PNH SOLUTIONS', 'abertrand@pnh.ca', '1985 Hymus Blvd, DORVAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.pnh.ca', '(514) 683-3279', '(514) 683-5820', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PNH &ndash; Large format printing specialists for event marketing, retail marketing and trade show design<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PNH Solutions provides you with exceptional service and quality. Our complete in-house operation takes your project from start to finish &ndash; from project management and colour management for large-format digital-inkjet printing or large-format dye sublimation, to your every retail marketing or event marketing need.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Backlit displays, banners and sign hardware. Vehicle wraps, custom tents and promotional flags. Window decals,&nbsp; building wraps and much more!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">High-quality printing and unmatched production capacity allow us to offer you a wide variety of solutions to showcase your brand. We provide the right product, technology, advice and service. When you need it, wherever you need it!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since its founding in 1989, PNH has partnered with leading and forward-thinking marketing professionals, merchandisers, agencies, large corporations, business owners, governments and organizations from Canada, the USA and around the world to help promote and display their brands, both indoors and out, using a vast array of digital print services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PNH partners with customers by listening, understanding and anticipating their requirements in order to consistently meet and exceed their expectations of product design, quality and colour management as well as timely delivery and responsive service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We promise that each order &ndash; large or small &ndash; will be treated with the same degree of diligence, hard work, integrity and reliability.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(852, 1, 'POC Communications Inc.', 'info@poc.ca', '6217, rue Saint-Andre, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.poc.ca ', '(514) 270-7651', '(514) 270-7526', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Accr&eacute;dit&eacute;e ISO 9001, POC Communications est une entreprise <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">int&eacute;gr&eacute;e de communication-marketing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(853, 1, 'Point Click Media Inc.', 'info@pointclickmedia.ca', '205-108 High St, MONCTON, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.pointclickmedia.ca ', '(506) 855-3591', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fusebox is an incredibly creative and innovative design company located in Moncton, New Brunswick, specializing in creating visually and independently strong web design, graphic design and branding. Our talented group is exceptionally passionate about working with businesses that are eager to develop their brand awareness with high quality production across any medium including, web, print, and brand identity.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether your business is brand new or been servicing loyal clients for years, we will establish or enhance an identity for your company that will help captivate your demographic.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(854, 1, 'Poklik Solutions', 'info@poklik.com', '6268A 9ieme Ave, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.poklik.com ', '(514) 593-8558', '(514) 593-1210', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nous &eacute;valuons vos besoins afin de vous proposer un syst&egrave;me qui vous conviendrait &agrave; souhait.Nous vous expliquons en d&eacute;tail les possibilit&eacute;s offertes avec chaque p&eacute;riph&eacute;rique. Si vous n\'&ecirc;tes pas familier avec les composantes de l\'ordinateur, la solution id&eacute;ale serait de venir rencontrer l\'un de nos conseillers qui se <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">fera un plaisir de vous guider judicieusement dans vos choix afin qu\'ils r&eacute;pondent exactement &agrave; vos besoins pr&eacute;sents et futurs.Si le syst&egrave;me propos&eacute; vous convient, nos techniciens exp&eacute;riment&eacute;s s\'occuperont du montage de votre syst&egrave;me et le mettront sur le banc des tests pour quelques heures afin d\'en v&eacute;rifier toutes les fonctionnalit&eacute;s; tant au niveau mat&eacute;riel que celui du syst&egrave;me d\'exploitation.Le processus complet du montage et de la configuration vous sera remis avec votre nouveau syst&egrave;me.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Avoir une vitrine sur le monde et non seulement sur un coin de rue est un avantage qui n\'est pas &agrave; n&eacute;gliger. Nous vous offrons la possibilit&eacute; d\'avoir votre propre espace Web r&eacute;serv&eacute; pour votre commerce ou votre usage personnel. Libre &agrave; vous de faire usage de votre cr&eacute;ativit&eacute; et de votre savoir-faire.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(855, 1, 'Polar Bear Productions Ltd.', 'cds@polarbearltd.com', '335 - 23 - 845 Dakota St, Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.polarbearltd.com ', '888-775-5206', '(204) 775-5202', '', '<p>Polar Bear is a reliable and economical CD and DVD manufacturing service for independent artists and businesses. We\'re print specialists who can provide cost-effective solutions for the budget-minded, right up to high-end specialty packaging for those aiming for the best our industry has to offer.</p>\r\n<p>Concerned about the environment? Be rest assured that you&rsquo;re at the right place. All of our print and boardpaks contain post consumer product printed with vegetable dye inks. Our Digipaks and cardboard products can be upgraded to 100% recycled material at no additional cost.</p>\r\n<p>Because of our diverse nature, we are able to offer a range of products to suit everyone. If your project is only in the concept stage, our experience in custom print and packaging will be a huge asset. At Polar Bear, we stand behind our work, therefore can guarantee you the best in the industry.Polar Bear has been serving Canadian and US customers since 1992.</p>\r\n<p>CD &amp; DVD duplication, replication &amp; manufacturing. Packaging and printing, fulfillment and project management. Website creation and graphic design services, DVD authoring and multimedia content developement. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(856, 1, 'Polaris Inflatable Boats (Canada) Ltd.', 'polaris@polarisboats.com', '8-5684 Landmark Way, Surrey, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.polarisboats.com', '(604) 534-5585', '(604) 534-2329', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Here at Polaris Inflatable Boats we build new and make replacement parts for high quality watercraft. Whether you are looking for a durable river boat to charge rapids or are law enforcement agencies looking for a perfect rescue boat, we make exactly what you&rsquo;re looking for. Located in Canada, we are a custom boat builder.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We pride ourselves on using state of the art high quality materials; along with exceptional craftsmanship on everything we build. We have a full line of products to meet your needs and a custom unit can be designed and built to your individual requirements. Whether it is new boats, replacement parts or much needed repairs, we are your one stop shop.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Located in Canada, we are surrounded by many different sources of open water and understand the need for diverse products that can survive in unique environments. Riding tough rapids and rocky waters requires a strong inflatable boat. Our Aluminum inflatable boats can compensate and withstand rough surroundings while keeping passengers safe. We have many different sizes to accommodate tours, guiding, search &amp; rescue and many other commercial uses.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fulfilling the needs of Law Enforcement agencies can be extremely challenging, especially on water. Here at Polaris Inflatable Boats we manufacture boats that are fit to keep the United States and Canada safe and sound. Whether it is foldable inflatable boats for discrete operations or aluminum inflatable boats made to patrol waters, we are there to help protect and serve.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Canadian zodiac type style inflatable boats are built to order and your boat will be one of a kind. We specialize in custom accessorizing Polaris Ribs to meet your needs and expectations. Or, if you are looking for inflatable boat accessories, we have many available. Feel free to visit us or contact us for more information on the services and products we provide.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(857, 1, 'Portes Laforge Doors Ltd./Ltee', 'laforged@nb.aibn.com', '62, ch. Saint-Andre, SAINT-ANDRE, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.laforgedoors.com ', '(506) 473-4034', '(506) 473-4283', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laforge Doors Ltd. is a 100,000 sq. ft. plant located in Grand Falls, New Brunswick, Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company began manufacturing wooden overhead doors in 1981 for residential, commercial and industrial markets. In 1986, because of a growing demand, aluminum and steel overhead doors were introduced to the production line.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laforge Doors products are distributed throughout the world via the intermediary of distributors and dealers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We know that when you order a Laforge Door, you want it delivered on time and in one piece. That is why we operate our own fleet of delivery trucks. Our experienced team of drivers understand the importance of delivering doors to you promptly and undamaged.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We deliver in the Maritimes, Quebec and Ontario to owners and dealers</p>', ''),
(858, 1, 'Positron Inc.', 'info@positronpower.com', '220-5101 Buchan St, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.positronpower.com   ', '(514) 345-2220', '(514) 345-2271', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established in 1970, Positron Inc. is a holding and operating company that develops and manufactures telecommunications equipment for high reliability, critical service applications including communications protection for high voltage environments and SONET fiber optic transmission equipment. Positron invests 16% of revenues into research and development. Over the last 39 years the company has built a reputation for delivering superior technology, reliability and value.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With headquarters in Montreal and offices throughout North America, Positron\'s global footprint extends from the United States and Canada through Europe, Africa, Latin America, Australia, Asia and the South Pacific. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company is a recipient of the Canada Export Award and has received awards for leadership in developing new technologies from the Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers (IEEE), as well as the Award of Excellence from the City of Montreal. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Positron Inc. has several high technology operating subsidiaries in the telecom domain, including Positron Power, Positron Access Solutions and Positron Telecommunications Systems. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Positron engineers and manufactures high voltage isolation products to protect telecommunications circuits entering substations, power generating plants, and any high voltage area that is susceptible to the effects of Ground Potential Rise (GPR). For over 40 years, Positron has been the market leader in providing high quality, reliable wireline isolation equipment that meets the highest industry standards. Worldwide, there are more Positron isolator circuits deployed than any other vendor. With the availability of the TeleLite product line (a fiber optics based isolation/protection solution), Positron became the first and only equipment vendor in the market to offer a complete line of copper (Teleline) and fiber based (TeleLite) high-voltage isolation/protection solutions. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Positron manufactures carrier-class bonded copper solutions that enable carriers to deploy Ethernet and DS3 services faster while obtaining fiber-like bandwidth on a copper budget. Positron also produces carrier-class metro optical transmission equipment for SONET/SDH and packet-based networks as well as Ethernet-over-copper solutions. Its products are used in applications including Metro-area Ethernet and transport networks where they provide access, edge traffic aggregation, wireless and triple-play backhaul, and thin-route access transport. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Positron Telecommunications Systems (PTS) develops and markets high reliability VoIP equipment for SMB and enterprise communication. PTS products integrate VoIP and traditional telephony in stand-alone systems that combine ease of use with powerful functionality. Its new generation IP PBX systems are video enabled and include integrated firewall &lsquo;anti-hacking&rsquo;, unlimited extensions (no license fees), auto-provisioning, wizard configuration tools, remote diagnostics and configuration and unlimited IVR&rsquo;s.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(859, 1, 'Powder Designs', 'powderdesigns@shaw.ca', '313 Schooner Cove NW, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', '', '(403) 547-5780', '(403) 241-7516', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Design and manufacture custom backpacks and bags for the&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">surveying industry (Global Positioning Systems equipment).&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Manufacturing back packs, radio harness, GPS packs, custom bags&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">etc... &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(861, 1, 'Q\'Max Solutions Inc.', 'rnorthcott@qmaxsolutions.com', '1700-407 2nd St SW, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.qmaxsolutions.com ', '(403) 269-2242', '(403) 269-2251', '', '<p>&nbsp;Q&rsquo;Max Solutions Inc. is an independent, privately-owned oilfield services company that has grown from five original partners, located in Western Canada in 1993, to a multi-national company serving the oil and gas industry today.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The vision of the original founding partners was to provide drilling fluids product and technical services with a focus on value. They called it &ldquo;growth partnering&rdquo;, and it meant that Q&rsquo;Max intended to work as a partner, focused on helping customers&rsquo; achieve success in their projects at lowest total cost. Most other business models of the day were based on a customer-vendor relationship which tended to be adversarial due to the pursuit of lowest perceived cost.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The approach has been successful. Today, Q&rsquo;Max employs almost 1,400 people within 9 countries, each country represents a fully equipped and self-sufficient independent business unit. Each business unit enjoys a significant amount of autonomy, which allows for rapid responses to business and customer needs, while enjoying the advantages of accessing the technical, logistical, purchasing, financial and operational expertise of the company, as a whole.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>What really makes the company successful is the application of experience, knowledge, technologies, research and product development to help our customers achieve their goals, through the people who work throughout the Q&rsquo;Max organization. The culture of the company encourages and rewards innovative thinking and customer focus. This attitude helps us to attain our objectives including being viewed as the supplier of choice, and the employer of choice, for our industry. Our objective is to be the &ldquo;Go To&rdquo; company. Our mission is to make a difference in the drilling process.</div>', ''),
(862, 1, 'Q-Line Trucking Ltd.', 'quote@qlinetrucking.com', 'Box 110B R.R. 4 , SASKATOON, Saskatchewan, Canada', 'www.qlinetrucking.com ', '(306) 651-3540', '(306) 651-3541', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With more than 330 trucks and 550 trailers, Q-Line Trucking is a very aggressive company that fully understands what is required to move all types of equipment in a safe and efficient manner. If your business is construction, oil and gas, fabrication, manufacturing, agriculture, mining, forestry or distribution, we understand your specific needs and how important it is to have a carrier that can move your equipment and materials as quickly as possible. At Q-Line Trucking, drivers, office staff and management are always ready for the next challenge.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our fleets are satellite equipped to provide professional, tracked, on time delivery, and our web portal allows customers to track their shipments without calling in. As customer satisfaction is our number one priority, we create a personal relationship with each of you. If there is any additional service that we could provide to facilitate and comfort you in your work, we will find a pragmatic way to adapt our business to your needs. Q-Line Trucking is ISO certified.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(863, 1, 'Q & R Trading Inc.', 'info@qrtradinginc.com', '6-855 Alness St, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.qrtradinginc.com ', '(416) 222-8988', '(416) 222-8908', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">IMPORT CHINESE WOODWORKING, METALWORKING CUTTING TOOLS (SAW BLADES, ROUTER BITS, WOOD TURNING TOOLS, DRILL BITS, ETC.) AND OTHER GLASS/TILE CUTTING TOOLS, WOOD/TILE HOLE SAWS, CABINET ACCESSORIES (HINGES &amp; SLIDES) AND OTHER INDUSTRIAL PRODUCTS FOR SALE. &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(864, 1, 'Q2 Management Inc.', 'tsdscott@q2management.com', '4-250 Harry Walker Pky N, NEWMARKET, Ontario, Canada', 'www.q2management.com ', '(888) 510-0664', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Q2 Management Inc. was created by senior Quality professionals with extensive experience in all facets of the automotive quality assurance field.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From Containment and Crisis Management through to Program Launch, APQP, and Supplier Development, our collective knowledge translates each and every time into effective solutions for the most challenging customers&rsquo; needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Initially benchmarking against competitors in Canada and the US allowed us to identify opportunities as well as develop a business model which maximizes the ratio of value-added-services versus infrastructure and operating costs, all viewed from our customers&rsquo; perspective.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Q2 Management Inc . provides a total commitment to excellence in quality management services.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(865, 1, 'QB Marketing Inc', 'info@qbmarketing.com', '38 Anahid Crt, BEDFORD, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.qbmarketing.com ', '(902) 431-9629', '(888) 812-6292', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We\'ve been privileged to quarterback some fascinating marketing assignments since our start in the early part of 2000.&nbsp; From marketing thought leadership to complex custom website content management system implementations, our clients have continued to challenge us to think creatively about how they communicate with their customers and to lead them with vision and passion on the field of business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">While some exciting new projects are underway right now, we\'re retooling our website to give a new glimpse of the direction we\'re taking as a company - integrating our modern approach to communications challenges, new ways of thinking, new means of delivering a powerful message and the new technologies that help us get there.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite our field being under renovation, our team is as active as ever, tackling web marketing, packaging design, trade graphics, advertising and ecommerce projects, to name just a few.&nbsp; If you currently face a communications challenge and you feel you could use help quarterbacking your vision<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(866, 1, 'QBD Cooling Systems Inc.', 'info@qbd.com', '31 Bramsteele Rd, BRAMPTON, Ontario , Canada', 'www.qbd.com ', '(905) 459-0709', '(905) 459-1478', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">QBD COOLING SYSTEMS MANUFACTURES GLASS DOOR UPRIGHT VISI COOLERS.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are the largest manufacturers of commercial refrigerators in Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">QBD MODULAR SYSTEMS INC. MANUFACTURES DISPLAY CASES FOR THE FOODSERVICE INDUSTRY.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We also manufacture Undercounter refrigerators, walk-in-coolers / freezers and refrigerated / heated / dry display cases<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
