(940, 1, 'RMV Electronics Inc.', 'customer@rmv.com', '300-3665 Kingsway, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.rmv.com', '(604) 299-5173', '(604) 299-5174', '', '<p>&nbsp;RMV Motion is a Vancouver based company that produces all of its hardware and software in Canada. Our main area of focus is motion control (BLDC, Stepper,Linear) we provide &nbsp;a completed solution &nbsp;for those motors as well technical support and customized firmware and hardware design. We are very excited to introduce our upcoming new technologies and products.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>What makes RMV Motion unique is the trusted relationships we develop by working collaboratively with our customers and focusing on delivering results. We always operate with the highest standards of integrity. One of our major goals is to listen and understand our customer needs, provide insightful consultation throughout the project to improve the product and the development process.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>RMV Motion provides expert development services and technology for a wide motor control<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>and embedded wireless products with automation ready protocols. Our engineering team has a high percentage of senior level developers and architects that know how to avoid the pitfalls of device development and deliver solutions that will outperform the competition. No matter your operating system or hardware platform, our engineers have the range of experience and depth of expertise to help achieve your project goals. Our extensive experience in developing motion control leading Linux, Android, Embedded Windows, IOs based embedded products.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(941, 1, 'S & C Clark Transport Inc', 'scclark@bellnet.ca', '111 Pine St, WINGHAM, Ontario, Canada', 'scclarktrans.com ', '(519) 357-3346', '(519) 357-1459', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 20 years we have been providing professional and efficient transportation services throughout North America.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our company was started by Steve Clark, who has extensive experience working in the trucking industry. His parents owned and operated a successful transportation company and truck repair business. From a young age Steve worked with trucks, and at 18 exposed himself to the business side of the industry &ndash;from ownership of one truck to running a multi-functional transport company.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, S &amp; C Clark Transport has grown to include Full Load and LTL services as well as Cross Docking, Logistics, Short term storage, and refrigerated/heated transportation services. What started as a small trucking company has become a full-service operation serving the entire continent of North America!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(942, 1, 'S.G. Smallwood Inc.', 'gord@sgsmallwood.com', '699 Wabanaki Dr., KITCHENER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sgsmallwood.com ', '(519) 894-2280', '(519) 894-0007', '', '<p>&nbsp;S.G. Smallwood Inc. specializes in the design, manufacture and distribution of transformer and inductor components to exactly suit your circuit and product applications.</p>\r\n<div>We offer a full complement of manufacturing capabilities: computer assisted design, toroidal winding, bobbin and layer winding, vacuum epoxy encapsulation, varnish impregnation, fabrication of specialized custom parts and comprehensive computerized product testing. Our Products are available in Custom, Standard and Equivalent designs. Available configurations include toroidal, ferrite, C-Core, and laminated EI UI core styles for 50/60Hz, 500Hz and higher frequency applications to 1 MHz.</div>\r\n<div>Supplier of custom transformers and inductors under the Controlled Goods Program, registration number 24504, an industrial security program authorized by the Defence Production Act.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As a service to our customers, we offer fast prototyping, design assistance, rush delivery, assembly / build services, and stocking options. Our Quality System is an ISO 9001:2008 system registered by Certech Registration Inc.</div>\r\n<div>We are located in Kitchener Ontario as part of the Golden Technology Triangle (Kitchener-Waterloo-Cambridge). The Company was founded by Stanley G. Smallwood in 1945, originally manufacturing radio and television coils.</div>', ''),
(943, 1, 'Sabic Innovative Plastics', 'dns.admin@sabic-ip.com ', '44 Normar Rd, COBOURG, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sabic-ip.com ', '(905) 372-6801', '(905) 373-3994', '', '<p>&nbsp;Since SABIC&rsquo;s founding, its employees have exhibited a remarkable ability to do what others said couldn&rsquo;t be done.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Ranked among the world&rsquo;s largest petrochemicals manufacturers, SABIC is a public company based in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. 70% of the Company&rsquo;s shares are owned by the Saudi Arabian government, with the remaining 30% held by private investors in Saudi Arabia and other countries of the Gulf Cooperation Council.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>SABIC began in 1976 by Royal decree and its growth has been nothing short of miraculous. Today, the company has operations in over 40 countries with a global workforce of over 40,000 talented individuals.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To find out how SABIC was created, and how it achieved its current success, please see the Corporate Profile pages. Or, for an idea of our size and capacity, see the Facts and Figures page.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>ORGANIZATION</div>\r\n<div>SABIC is composed of six business units, each headed by an Executive Vice President. These are: Chemicals, Polymers, Performance Chemicals, Fertilizers, Metals and Innovative Plastics. These six operating units make four distinctly different kinds of products:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Chemicals &ndash; Chemicals and Performance Chemicals</div>\r\n<div>Plastics &ndash; Polymers and Innovative Plastics</div>\r\n<div>Fertilizers</div>\r\n<div>Metals</div>\r\n<div>LOCATION</div>\r\n<div>SABIC&rsquo;s principle corporate offices and headquarters are in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia with major industrial operations in the industrial city of Al-Jubail on the Arabian Gulf, as well as in Yanbu on the Red Sea.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>SABIC&rsquo;s global presence continues to grow rapidly. Our ambitious plans for expansion are matched by the development of an infrastructure of manufacturing plants, distribution centers, offices and storage facilities worldwide. This enables us to respond efficiently to the needs of our customers in key markets around the world.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company&rsquo;s manufacturing , sales, technology and innovation facilities are located throughout the globe and are managed by four regional offices: the Middle East and Africa, Asia, the Americas and Europe. To find out more about our operations please see the worldwide section.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>INNOVATION</div>\r\n<div>Because we are constantly looking to the future, we invest heavily in Technology and Innovation (T&amp;I). Our T&amp;I facilities are spread across the globe with hundreds of dedicated scientists contributing to the ongoing development of new patents and certifications.</div>', ''),
(944, 1, 'Sager Food Products Inc.', 'info@sagerfoods.com', '6755 Henri-Bourassa Blvd W, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.sagerfoods.com ', '(514) 643-4887', '(514) 643-3424', '', '<p>&nbsp;Sager Foods is a family-owned and operated food company based in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. Sager is the leading packager of vegetable oils in Canada and serves all of the major Canadian grocery chains.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The Company\'s principle products include a full range of vegetable oils including Canola, Soya, Corn, Olive, Sunflower, Peanut, Safflower and various blends including Canola &amp; Olive oil.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Sager was established in 1983 by Santo Fata Sr. as a packager of vegetable oil products primarily for grocery chains and foodservice distributors. In the early 1980s, Canadian grocery chains began introducing private label products in their own stores to compete with the established national brands. Sager was among the first suppliers to this market segment which has and continues to grow at a strong rate. Many of our client relationships date back many years and we are very proud to have the privilege of serving Canada\'s leading grocery chains.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In addition to our private label business, Sager packs a number of products under national brands. These co-packing clients represent an important part of both our retail and foodservice businesses. In addition, since its inception, Sager has also developed its own brands including La Perla, Cantalia and Regina. La Perla, Cantalia and Regina products can be found throughout Canada. Recently, Sager has broadened its product offering to include organic oils and a wide assortment of sauces.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Sager currently operates two plants, both in the Montreal area. In our main plant, we package all types of vegetable oils in containers ranging in size from 375 ML bottles to 16L pails to 45 gallon drums. Our Akita plant produces some of our specialty oils such as our Stir-Fry oil and our Spicy and Aromatic oil products. In addition, all of our sauces are produced at our Akita plant.</div>', ''),
(945, 1, 'SBM Industries', 'service@sbmwoodblind.com', '8320, Place Lorraine, ANJOU, Quebec, Canada', 'www.sbmwoodblind.com ', '(514) 353-3339', '(514) 353-8483', '', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 1995, SBM industries rapidly became a leader of the Canadian window coverings industry. SBM&rsquo;s values rely on expertise, passion and a constant desire to offer its clients the best available solution for their window covering needs. At SBM, purchasing policy has always been to select Canadian suppliers first, therefore keeping our national workforce healthy. Cautious of the environment, SBM also made the choice in the early years to work with suppliers offering ecofriendly solutions. Always looking for new trends, SBM will keep positioning itself ahead of the competition in order to give its partners the finest products.</p>', ''),
(946, 1, 'Scaffold Gold Inc.', 'general@scaffoldgold.com', '9606, 40 St SE, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', 'www.scaffoldgold.com ', '(403) 663-1380', '(403) 663-1739', '', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 2006, Scaffold Gold specializes in developing scaffolding, manufacturing scaffolding and supplying factory direct formwork and scaffold systems.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All Scaffold Gold Formwork &amp; scaffolding products are developed in Canada to the highest standards and up to date specifications. Scaffold Gold heavily invests in product research and development to assure full certification of our people and scaffold products.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Scaffold Gold is a member of SIA, SIAC, ISN Network and we are ISO 9001 certified. All our scaffold products are designed to exceed the CSA and OSHA requirements.</div>', ''),
(947, 1, 'Scotty Ltd', 'scotty@scotty.com', '2065 Henry Ave W, SIDNEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.scotty.com ', '(250) 656-8102', '(250) 656-8126', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1952 Blayney and his wife Almeda Scott started a small company in Victoria, British Columbia, Canada that pioneered the use of plastics in the manufacturing of salmon fishing lures and other marine products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From humble beginnings, Scott Plastics Ltd. has evolved to produce thousands of products under the Scotty Trademark which are sold into the fishing, marine, outdoor and firefighting industries worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In this time the Scotty trademark has become recognized to mean one thing - product excellence.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The total commitment to quality, fair pricing and unmatched service means our customers everywhere can expect reliability and satisfaction from every product that carries the Scotty name.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Here you will find Scotty products to fit your fishing and boating needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(948, 1, 'SDI Aviation', 'jyoung@sdi-aviation.com', '56 Pinder Rd Nackawic Industrial Park, NACKAWIC, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.sdi-aviation.com ', '(506) 575-2218', '(506) 575-2766', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SDI AVIATION designs, manufactures, distributes and supports<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">the SUPERIOR&reg; line of aviation ground support equipment (GSE). SUPERIOR&reg;, a well-known brand name associated with GSE &ndash; and more specifically aircraft ground deicers - was purchased by privately held Nackawic Mechanical Ltd. (NML) in August of 1992. The intellectual property and physical assets of the<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">former U.S. company were transferred to NML\'s modern manufacturing facility at Nackawic, New Brunswick, Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 1973 by journeyman machinist David A. Young, NML has long been a leader in the structural steel fabrication; material handling and transportation industries. Serving the pulp &amp; paper; mining and aggregate industries throughout North America, NML has earned an excellent reputation for its superb<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">workmanship and dedicated customer service. While the manufacturing of aviation equipment has, in recent years, become its core activity NML continues to serve the needs of the aforementioned industries. NML\'s diversity has allowed it to remain strong during often difficult, industry-specific periods.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1992, SDI AVIATION has manufactured in excess of 150 deicer units. And, we continue to support the more than 400 deicers built by our predecessors. Now in its fifteenth year of manufacturing ground support equipment, SDI AVIATION has built a customer base that spans the globe. We continuously strive to improve our product line with innovative features that provide the industry with reliable, efficient and affordable GSE. Customers include major and regional airlines; ground services providers; aircraft manufactures; couriers; FBO\'s and airport authorities. Military customers include the United States Army,<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">United States Air National Guard and the UK Royal Air Force.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(949, 1, 'Seanautic Marine Inc.', 'infomtl@seanauticmarine.com', '201-20 Saint-Paul St W, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.seanauticmarine.com ', '(514) 287-1812', '(514) 287-9202', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Seanautic Marine Inc. is an International Sea Transport Agency established in 1983 specializing in shipping cargo to over 130 ports in the Caribbean, Central/South America, Mediterranean, Middle East, Africa, Pacific and Indian Ocean.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We provide fast and efficient quality logistics and transportation services including Full Container Load (FCL) and Less Than Container Load (LCL), Roll-On/Roll-Off (Ro/Ro), and Break Bulk (B/B). View our Routes and Destinations for sailing days and Container Equipment Specifications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Seanautic Marine head office is located in the heart of Vieux-Montreal with a regional office in Toronto, Ontario.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(950, 1, 'Security Mirror Industries Ltd.', 'smi@securitymirror.com', '69 Densley Ave., NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.securitymirror.com ', '(416) 244-3393', '(416) 244-8994', '', '<p>&nbsp;We hope you find what you\'re looking for. We\'ve worked hard on providing you with a site that is easy to navigate and full of valuable information you can use.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Security Mirror has been in business now for over 40 years, with a combined employee work experience of over 175 years!</div>\r\n<div>We value our employees - as well as our customers and suppliers very much!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We\'re very proud to be a Canadian manufacturer offering quality products for the framed mirror markets and beyond.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We offer a growing product line ready to meet your mirror, glass and stainless steel needs. Along with our revamped custom metal fabrication capabilities, inhouse custom silvering and experienced staff, we are confident we can meet your requirements.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We look forward to meeting you and discussing how we might be of service to you.</div>', ''),
(951, 1, 'Seven Star Sports', 'info@sevenstarsports.com', '65 Lancing Dr., HAMILTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sevenstarsports.com ', '(905) 574-9270', '(905) 574-7082', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;929641 Ontario Inc., Operating as Seven Star Sports is an Ontario registered company in Canada and is privately owned. The name Seven Star Sports was chosen because of the seven brothers in the family that make up Seven Star Sports. In the early 1990\'s after researching the sporting good industry, the company concluded that health and fitness is increasing in its market size and that more people are being involved in health and fitness. Due to the rapid growth of health and fitness, accidents relating to sports also sharply increased. After this research Seven Star Sports commenced R&amp;D to develop a new line of safety helmets for the cycling and inline skating industry. Early 1994 seen the design and completion of 4 helmet lines that had been developed. All the regulatory approvals CSA, ANSI and ASTM have been received and commercial production commenced February 1995. The company was now a 100% dedicated to manufacturing &amp; distribution of helmets. Subsequently other lines were added such as sports gloves, protective wear, ball items (soccer balls, basketballs, footballs) and skateboards. Seven Star Sports started its helmet production in Burlington, Ontario and moved to Hamilton, Ontario in early 1998. Our headquarters are in Hamilton, Ontario, Canada. We sell direct to mass merchants, specialty stores, grocery chains, drug store chains and small independents. Seven Star Sports has established itself as a quality manufacturer and supplier. We also produce private label products. We have produced products under many different brands to meet the needs of the customer. Our extensive list of customers in the non-profit sector include; Federal, Provincial, State, Municipal Governments, Universities, Colleges, Hospitals, Police Departments, Fire Departments and more.</p>', ''),
(952, 1, 'SFT (Snap Film Technologies)', 'mail@snapopen.com', '25 Monkstown Rd, ST. JOHN\'S, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', 'snapopen.com ', '(709) 726-3951', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SFT is an Intellectual-Property company, presently holding (for out-licensing) technology patents for improved single-use plastic bags. SFT may License manufacturers, distributors, or corporate users to use the technology (as on snapopen.com or [=] easyopenbags.com). Our IP enables the manufacture of bags that open &quot;first time, every time&quot;. That reduces cost by reducing the waste (of time, of bags) that results from bags (as often happens with ordinary bags) that are difficult to open. Our primary focus is Canada and USA, but we hold IP elsewhere also.&nbsp; Bags often &quot;fight back&quot;. Hard to open. Stuck shut. Frustrating, time-wasting. The problem is so well-known that it is almost a joke (see Leslie Nielsen exploiting that joke in the first few minutes of the comedy \'Naked Gun 33 1/3\', battling with a supermarket produce bag).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The presence of the industry-wide problem creates latent demand for a better product. Interestingly, the demand is latent because most users currently accept hard-to-open bags as common enough to be considered normal unless they are very hard to open. At present customers are not demanding better bags, for one simple reason: they don\'t yet know that they exist. But now they do exist, and they are becoming known, and the latent demand is becoming expressed demand.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(953, 1, 'SGS Canada Inc.', 'richard.mcneil@sgs.com', '4092 Port Malcolm Rd, POINT TUPPER, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.sgs.com ', '(902) 625-3233', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wherever you are in the world, in whatever industry, you can rely on our international teams of experts to provide you with specialized business solutions to make your business faster, simpler and more efficient. We partner with you to offer independent services that will help you reduce risk, streamline your processes and operate in a more sustainable manner. You can find out more about how we can help you reach your objectives by viewing our corporate video.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SGS is the world&rsquo;s leading inspection, verification, testing and certification company. We are recognized as the global benchmark for quality and integrity. With more than 80,000 employees, we operate a network of more than 1,650 offices and laboratories around the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our core services can be divided into four categories:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Inspection: our comprehensive range of world-leading inspection and verification services, such as checking the condition and weight of traded goods at transshipment, help you to control quantity and quality, and meet all relevant regulatory requirements across different regions and markets<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Testing: our global network of testing facilities, staffed by knowledgeable and experienced personnel, enable you to reduce risks, shorten time to market and test the quality, safety and performance of your products against relevant health, safety and regulatory standards<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Certification: we enable you to demonstrate that your products, processes, systems or services are compliant with either national or international standards and regulations or customer defined standards, through certification<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Verification: we ensure that products and services comply with global standards and local regulations. Combining global coverage with local knowledge, unrivalled experience and expertise in virtually every industry, SGS covers the entire supply chain from raw materials to final consumption.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are constantly looking beyond customers&rsquo; and society&rsquo;s expectations in order to deliver market leading services wherever they are needed. As the leader in providing specialized business solutions that improve quality, safety and productivity and reduce risk, we help customers navigate an increasingly regulated world. Our independent services add significant value to our customers&rsquo; operations and ensure business sustainability.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As well as delivering services that promote sustainable development, our values also show a commitment to corporate sustainability. For us, sustainability is about managing a long-term profitable business while taking into account all the positive and negative environmental, social and economic effects we have on society. You can find out more about our sustainability policies and program in our Corporate Sustainability section.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(954, 1, 'Shades of Clay', 'wendy@shadesofclay.com', '428 Sherin Dr., OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.shadesofclay.com ', '(416) 452-5204', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Shades of Clay! .... a Canadian resource for mixed media and polymer artists. We stock an eclectic range of art and craft supplies and ship world wide; see our shipping page for more information.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We\'re searching for even more great finds in every department. If there is something that you can\'t live without, please&nbsp; get in touch and We\'ll see what we can do.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(955, 1, 'Siam Marine Canada Inc', 'peyman_7@yahoo.com', '112-125 19th St W, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(778) 987-2431', '(778) 340-2431', '', '<div>Siam Marine Canada Inc. is a high professional company in Construction, Engineering, Geo-Science, and Import/Export. &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(956, 1, 'Signal Weather Services', 'signalweather@shaw.ca', '49 Davis St., DRYDEN, Ontario, Canada', 'www.signalweather.ca ', '(807) 221-8722', '(807) 223-8408', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We specialize in finding innovative solutions to weather monitoring for industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Finding the best mix of durability, reliability and cost in weather instruments isn\'t always easy - put our 40 years experience to work for you!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(957, 1, 'SilverTip Marine Inc', 'info@silvertipmarine.com', 'Box 453 6362 Fraser St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.silvertipmarine.com ', '(604) 676-0304', '(604) 419-8561', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SilverTip Marine products, our ESP series of Boat Alarms, Boat and Yacht Security Systems, and remote monitoring systems actively fight boat and equipment theft and increase your chances of recovering your boat.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Every year tens of thousands of boats are stolen, with very few ever recovered. Boats are stolen from almost everywhere: from back yards, from front driveways, from marinas, from service yards, and even from motels on the way to or from vacation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">However, theft of the boat itself is not the only risk. Increasingly thieves are targeting equipment and electronics on boats in marinas. Outboards and tenders are favourite targets as they are easily transported and even if secured with chains or locks, are rarely monitored by security systems or boat alarms.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Theft is not the only event that can cause the loss of a boat. Every year boats sink where they are moored in marinas. A failed through hull fitting can eventually overpower a bilge pump or cause the bilge pump to drain the battery and sink the boat.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The solution is to use a security system for your boat that monitors not only entry points on the boat, but also important status points such as bilge water level, battery voltage and even temperature. A boat alarm is not enough. A two-way remote monitoring system will keep you informed<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more information contact SilverTip Marine today!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(958, 1, 'Sierra Wireless Inc.', 'info@sierrawireless.com', '13811 Wireless Way, RICHMOND, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.sierrawireless.com ', '(604) 231-1100', '(604) 231-1109', '', '<p>&nbsp;Sierra Wireless is the global leader in machine-to-machine (M2M) devices and cloud services, delivering intelligent wireless solutions that simplify the connected world. We offer the industry&rsquo;s most comprehensive portfolio of 2G, 3G and 4G embedded modules and gateways, seamlessly integrated with our secure M2M cloud services. Customers worldwide, including OEMs, enterprises, and mobile network operators, trust our innovative solutions to get their connected products and services to market faster.</p>', ''),
(959, 1, 'Signature Wood Systems', 'brad@signaturewoodsystems.ca', '7 Barrie Blvd, ST THOMAS,, Ontario, Canada', 'www.signaturewoodsystems.ca', '(519) 637-7023', '(519) 637-7024', '', '<p>&nbsp;Signature Wood has been providing customers with high quality craftsmanship. Signature Wood proudly waves the AWMAC flag to ensure that our first time clients know they are dealing with a reputable organization.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Mission at Signature Wood is to Manufacture, deliver and install a broad selection of high quality, competitively priced millwork through the innovative use of technology and materials by skilled and dedicated employee&rsquo;s.</div>', ''),
(960, 1, 'Signcraft', 'andy@signcraftcanada.com', '6 Ontario St, SUNDRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.signcraftcanada.com ', '(705) 384-7550', '(705) 384-7830', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SignCraft, established in 1985 was always a well known quality sign company owned and operated by Tom and Pat Crane. In 2011 Tom and Pat made the decision to sell the business to Dymond Design, previously located in Barrie Ontario for twenty years. At this time SignCraft was rebranded and strategically relocated into the heart of Sundridge to better serve customers. Since then SignCraft has expanded and worked hard to cater to the needs of local businesses and entrepreneurs and has grown to be an asset to the community.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Based on hard work, creativeness and dedication, our full-time talented staff works one-on-one with you to find creative solutions. By using the industries latest techniques, we guarantee to complete your project to your up-most satisfaction, as well as on time and on budget. SignCraft has completed a mass variety of signage within the area and we promise our expertise is second to none. Having produced signage for local businesses, large organizations and corporate identities, we guarantee that we can handle any project with great proficiency and professionalism. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We take tremendous pride in the quality of work we produce. We understand that the signage we provide not only reflects your businesses image, but more importantly your success. By being located in Sundridge Ontario, we strive to be a centeral hub for North Bay, Parry Sound and Hunsville Ontario. As well we serve small communities such as South River, Powassan, Trout Creek, Burks Falls, Kearney, Magnetewan and more. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To serve our clients best, we provide a variety of services to ensure quality products and upmost satisfaction. With our creative designers, experienced producers and the trade&rsquo;s best installers, we execute our projects from concept to completion.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(961, 1, 'Sky Teck Labs Inc.', 'info@skytecklabs.com', '3289B Lenworth Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.skytecklabs.com ', '(905) 602-8007', '(905) 602-8008', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sky Teck Labs Inc. is a distributor of leading industrial chemicals, machinery &amp; equipment. For over 25 years Sky Teck Labs has been committed to providing its customer\'s with problem solving products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Hand Cleaners | Industrial Cleaners | Lubricants | Coatings<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sky Teck Labs Inc. is a trusted supplier of industrial and municipal chemicals. We have a diverse portfolio of raw materials for manufacturing as well as products for maintenance and lubrication.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Turbine Parts &amp; Service | Welding Supplies | Pumps/Mixers | Ship Steel &amp; Materials<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sky Teck Labs Inc. is a trusted supplier of industrial and municipal equipment. We offer quality replacement parts and service for turbines. We carry industrial pumps as well as welding supplies, pipes &amp; fittings, and steel.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sky Teck Labs Inc. is a trusted supplier of industrial and municipal chemicals. We have a diverse portfolio of raw materials for manufacturing as well as products for maintenance and lubrication.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sky Teck Labs Inc. is a trusted supplier of industrial and municipal equipment. We offer quality replacement parts and service for turbines. We carry industrial pumps as well as welding supplies, pipes &amp; fittings, and steel.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(962, 1, 'Sligo Wear Inc', 'shawn@sligowear.com', '1-2283 Argentia Rd, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sligowear.com ', '(905) 997-7750', '', '', '<p>Sligo is the fusion between fashion and performance. Cutting edge fits, progressive styling and aggressive color ways define the golfer as an individual.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(963, 1, 'SMAG Industries Inc.', 'agrenon@smagindustries.com', '2275 De La Province St, LONGUEUIL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.smagindustries.com ', '(450) 651-2333', '(450) 651-3334', '', '<p>&nbsp;SMAG Industries is an equipment manufacturer. For the past 5 years, we have provided our customers with innovative and affordable solutions to improve their efficiency. All members of our team share our values based on respect, professionalism, expertise and dedication to quality.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We have the expertise and knowledge for designing and building industrial equipments for the ICF industry. SMAG Industries is the exclusive manufacturer of the Polycrete&reg; equipments.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our experts are also doing custom equipments based on your needs and specifications, following our SMAG Custom Engineering Methodology.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our multidisciplinary professionals offer a large variety of personalized services to our partners, like :</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Custom Equipments &amp; Engineering</div>\r\n<div>Training &amp; Technical Support</div>\r\n<div>Equipment Maintenance</div>\r\n<div>Business &amp; IT integration</div>', ''),
(964, 1, 'Smart Electronics Corp.', 'frank@smartco.net', '17-760 Pacific Rd, Oakville, Ontario, Canada', 'www.smartelectronics.ca ', '(905) 847-2598', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Smart Electronics both provides electronic engineering, programming and consulting services and manufactures a growing line of unique commercial and industrial electronic controls and devices. The pages of this site describe our products and services.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We have the tools and experience to develop electronic controls and devices for your machinery, equipment, vehicles, instruments and other products. We can design a custom electronic device for your application, and have it manufactured and delivered to you ready to install in your equipment. Our business is small but professional, and we work diligently to provide innovative and cost-effective electronic solutions for our customers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We sell a number of unique electronic products, including a new series of CAN/CANopen I/O modules, high density USB I/O modules for OEM applications, automatic door controls, rebar machinery controllers and software, water processing controllers, strain gauge interfaces and controllers, specialty conveyor controls.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Smart Electronics is also the Canadian sales and technical representative for ESD Electronics and its excellent line of CAN communication and other industrial electronic products.</div>', ''),
(965, 1, 'Szeto Technologies Incorporated', 'info@szeto.ca', '1881 Saint-Regis St, DOLLARD-DES-ORMEAUX, Quebec, Canada', 'www.szeto.ca ', '(514) 421-3737', '(514) 421-3700', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Szeto Technologies Inc. has been engineering and supplying telecommunication equipments to the TAS industries since 1986. The company was founded by Mr. Charles Szeto, a veteran in Communication, Telephone Switching, Voice and Data Processing. Collectively, our engineering team possesses over 150 years of experience in the Telecommunication and Computer Technology.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Szeto Technologies specializes in customizing its products to suit customers&rsquo; needs. The company designs, develops and manufactures both hardware and software for all of its product lines. Whether you are a small start-up company or a well established large scale operation, we have a solution for you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Szeto Technologies&rsquo; business approach is to continually grow with each individual customer, to support their on-going business needs with quality equipment utilizing the state-of-the-art technology.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(966, 1, 'Sytek Enterprises Inc.', 'info@sytek-ent.com', '100-55 Gostick Pl, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.sytek-ent.com ', '(604) 988-1125', '(604) 988-0299', '', '<p>A technology leader in Printed Electronics, Membrane Switches, Force Sensors, Graphic Overlays and Labels. Through years of innovation and experience, we deliver the impossible.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our goal is to provide our clients with the best design consultancy, custom production, and product manufacturing in the industry. Founded in 1982, Sytek has become a major supplier of custom-made membrane switches, overlays, and labels to international electronics, medical, industrial, automotive, and commercial markets.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Located in North Vancouver, on the scenic west coast of British Columbia, our 18,000-square-foot custom manufacturing plant boasts a clean-room environment for the following printing and assembly processes:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Digital colour matching</div>\r\n<div>Screen printing</div>\r\n<div>Roll-to-roll printing</div>\r\n<div>Lamination</div>\r\n<div>Die making</div>\r\n<div>Die cutting and embossing</div>\r\n<div>Laser cutting</div>\r\n<div>Assembly</div>\r\n<div>Pick-and-place technology</div>\r\n<div>3-Dimensional Modeling</div>\r\n<div>In-house CAD facilities</div>\r\n<div>Research and Development</div>', ''),
(967, 1, 'Syscor Controls & Automation Inc.', 'contact@syscor.com', '201-60 Bastion Sq., VICTORIA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.syscor.com ', '(250) 361-1681', '(250) 361-1682', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Syscor Controls &amp; Automation Inc. manufactures intelligent sensor solutions for accident prevention at petrochemical facilities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The risk of AST floating roof failures is increasing as the population of tanks throughout the world ages. The FR-Tracker&trade; system was developed in cooperation with the petroleum industry as an effective and economical tool for accident prevention through continuous monitoring of key AST parameters.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The FR-Tracker&trade; monitoring system consists of three main components: Multi-Sensors, Repeaters, and Base Stations. To minimize installation and maintenance costs, the Multi-Sensors and Repeaters are battery-operated wireless devices with battery life expectancy exceeding 10 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AST floating roofs exhibit specific behaviour patterns prior to failure.&nbsp; The FR-Tracker&trade; system can detect these patterns and alert the tank operators.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(968, 1, 'Synergy Marine Inc', 'merrill@synergymarine.com', '4553 Des Cageux St, PIERREFONDS, Quebec, Canada', 'www.synergymarine.com ', '(514) 867-7112', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;We offer a complete array of the brightest and longest lasting replacement MARINE GRADE 12V and 24V LED light bulbs. We can supply &nbsp;a drop-in replacement bulb for virtually any fixture on your sailboat, yacht, boat, RV, camper, caravan, or motorhome. You will love your new LEDs, and that\'s 100% guaranteed!</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our replacement fixtures and LED bulbs for boats are energy-efficient, run cooler, have great color rendering, and provide better brightness levels than any other competitive LED bulb on the market.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our LED bulbs are specifically designed to match the output and color of your existing 12V or 24V bulbs. They are manufactured in the smallest form to guarantee a perfect fit and make your conversion as easy as a drop-in replacement.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We specialize in replacement LED bulbs for boats. This means that all of our LED products, unless noted otherwise, have our on board DC/DC CONSTANT CURRENT converter chip. This way we obtain maximum output while taking into consideration the varying input voltages seen on yachts and other mobile DC applications with battery banks and multiple charging sources. This technology allows the bulbs to run on a constant 12V or 24V regardless of the fluctuations in the power source. &nbsp;Starting up your generator, connecting to shore power or starting your engine will no longer fry your LEDs. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(969, 1, 'Swedcan Lumican Plastics Inc.', 'swedcanplastics@on.aibn.com', '151 Whitehall Dr, MARKHAM,, Ontario, Canada', 'www.swedcanplastics.com ', '(905) 940-0500', '(905) 940-1500', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SWEDCAN LUMICAN PLASTICS INC. is rated amongst the leading plastic sheet distributors in CANADA. It has a significant share of the Sign, Display, Skylight, Glazing, Fabrication and Industrial markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SWEDCAN is best known for having introduced Continuous Cast Acrylic in the roll form in CANADA. It has over the years provided the plastic substrates for most, if not all, major corporate identification programmes including Shell, Esso, Texaco, B.P, Gulf, Bank of Montreal, CIBC, Canada Trust and Petro-Canada to name but a few. SWEDCAN supplied sheet for the pylon signs for the Shell corporate identification programme in Europe.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SWEDCAN created the acrylic sanitary-ware market in Canada. It introduced a cross linked grade of material and supplied the technology to manufacture plumbing fixtures such as bathtubs, whirlpools, shower enclosures, sinks and lavatories. SWEDCAN&rsquo;s LUMATECH plumbing fixture manufacturing plant with proprietary technology (fiberglass free &ldquo;GREEN&rdquo; products) and intellectual property was sold in January 2001 to Kohler Co., Kohler Wisconsin. Kohler is the largest sanitary-ware company in the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mr. Kendall has owned SWEDCAN LUMICAN PLASTICS since its inception. Prior to incorporating SWEDCAN LUMICAN PLASTICS INC. in 1980, Mr. Kendall was V.P. and general manager of Swedlow Plastics. He retained that position when the business was acquired by Montedison followed by USS Chemicals and Aristech. Des Kendall has been directly involved with a wide range of plastic sheet for over 30 years and has numerous patents to his credit.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SWEDCAN LUMICAN is also involved in the construction industry. It owns The Gracious Living Centre, which supplies high-end Kitchens, Baths and Custom Acrylic Furniture. The Gracious Living Centre has been in business since 1988 and has two showrooms one of which is in downtown, Toronto. The Gracious Living Centre has a proven record of completing upscale projects on time and within budget.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(970, 1, 'Svah Resources Inc.', 'richard@svahresources.com', '11322, 77 Ave, DELTA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.svahresources.com ', '(604) 897-8272', '(604) 594-2628', '', '<p>&nbsp;Being born and raised in Vancouver, British Columbia with an Asian heritage, Richard intuitively understands the business culture and needs in both Western and Eastern business styles. &nbsp;With 25 years of in-depth work experience as a business owner &nbsp;and trainer for Petro-Canada, a large national corporation, business growth and &nbsp;performance excellence is second nature to Richard. Being a top performer, Richard has been a provincial recipient for the &ldquo;Best in Class&rdquo; award as well as a multiple winner for &nbsp;the &ldquo;President&rsquo;s Award&rdquo; showing brilliance in business acumen, outstanding mentorship, pioneering leadership style, and record-breaking business growth.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Richard comes with vast experience and strengths in Business including:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thorough understanding of Retail Operations</div>\r\n<div>Financial Acumen</div>\r\n<div>Training and coaching skills</div>\r\n<div>Ability to co-ordinate activities through use of planning and organizational skills</div>\r\n<div>Excellent time management skills</div>\r\n<div>Self Discipline to set daily priorities and schedules</div>\r\n<div>Strong Non Authorative Leadership Skills (NAL) to influence and guide employees to meet goals and objectives</div>\r\n<div>Since the inception of Svah Resources Inc. the company has traded $20 million in product value internationally. With strong work ethics, loyalty, and trust, Richard has developed business relationships in the Philippines, India, China, and Africa to date with the demand for our services growing each day. To ensure product quality meets industry standards and mine site operations are functioning, we have personally visited each of the sites.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Svah Resources Inc. prides itself on a face-to-face business relationship and transparency. You can always meet us in person to discuss the product and delivery process. Client satisfaction is our pride and the key to success. Svah Resources&rsquo;s goal is to create an enterprise that is direct competitor to other import export companies and to offer cheaper iron ore prices among other.</div>', ''),
(971, 1, 'Sussex Telecom Inc.', 'sussex@sussexgroup.ca', '510-900 Greenbank Rd., NEPEAN, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sussexgroup.ca ', '(613) 274-0606', '(613) 727-3317', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We offer a wide range of products and services to meet the needs of almost any home or business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Managing your bottom line is important and we understand that. Sussex is always working very hard to keep your costs low so you can spend more time enjoying your services and not worrying about how much they cost.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Explore our website to find out more information about our service offerings, and how they can save you money; call with any questions - we are waiting to help.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sussex has always believed that our personalised customer service is one of our greatest strengths. Since we are a smaller company, we are able to tailor our services to better fit your needs. Our team is readily available waiting to help you with any questions or requests you may have.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With Sussex it is easy to customise your services so you can stop over-paying and start saving.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(972, 1, 'Surespan Construction Ltd.', 'bridges@surespan.com', '301-38 Fell Ave, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.surespan.com ', '(604) 998-1133', '(604) 998-1132', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 35 years Surespan Construction has designed, supplied and constructed high-quality steel and precast concrete structures all across the West Coast of Canada and the United States.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We started out as a forestry bridge builder back in 1977 on Vancouver Island. Since then, we have expanded nationally and increased our bridge supply and construction services to include everything from project management to precast parkade installation and beyond.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our success is due to our unmatched dedication to providing high-quality, durable structures to our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(973, 1, 'Superior Engineered Wood Products', 'bill@superwood.ca', '111 St. Arnaud, AMHERSTBURG, Ontario, Canada', 'www.superwood.ca', '(519) 736-0221', '(519) 736-3841', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Superior Engineered Wood Products was founded in 1999 by Windsor native Ken Harris. As a general contractor at the time, Ken recognized that local engineered wood product manufacturers lacked the most important aspects of structural wood components in their products; material quality and design accuracy.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A mandate of continuous process improvement combined with strategic investment in specialized industry leading equipment enables Superwood to uniquely offer competitive pricing while providing an unmatched premium product. This balance is maintained through a dedication to strict quality standards and quality control procedures. In addition to the benefits achieved by using a truss system versus the traditional stick-framing method, as a Superwood customer you will be provided superior customer service. Our design team is committed to working closely with you to ensure specific needs are met and unique design features are achieved. Typically, each project is site measured followed by a design process which includes internal checks and balances. Kiln dried lumber is then hand selected for the manufacturing process.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">These commitments to quality ensure problem-free installation, structural and design accuracy, and the highest level of strength and durability available in the engineered wood product industry.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(974, 1, 'StyroChem Canada Ltd.', 'sales@styrochem.ca', '19250 Clark-Graham Ave, BAIE-D\'URFE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.styrochem.com ', '(514) 457-3226', '(514) 457-4390', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 1975 as Expandable Technologies, StyroChem was one of the first manufacturers of EPS for food service applications. The business grew with the addition of two production facilities in Fort Worth, in 1979 and 1981 and manufacture of block and shape grade product lines.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1983 Expandable Technologies became Texstyrene. The company expanded further in 1984 when the Montreal facility came on line, providing capabilities to service the entire world market. Texstyrene was purchased by Scott Paper in 1988 and became Scott Polymers. A private holding company purchased Scott Polymers in 1996 to become what is know today as StyroChem.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The consolidation of the Fort Worth facilities into one streamlined production site took place in 2007. This right sizing of manufacturing assets has created a company ideally situated with a competitive cost structure to meet today&rsquo;s exacting market demands. StyroChem expanded its capacity at the Montreal site in late 2008 to include a separate production line for block and shape grade EPS, capable of an additional 80 million pounds per year.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">StyroChem is investing in the future by creating an extruded resin division to promote extruded specialty resins, including recycled resins. StyroChem has added a high capacity extrusion line and one specialized reactor for the manufacture of expandable engineered resins and recycled resin products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">StyroChem is a world renowned producer of Expandable Polystyrene (EPS) for food service, packaging, construction, casting and specialty applications. Over 38 years of experience dedicated to manufacturing EPS for a variety of applications results in the most consistent and highest quality EPS products in the world. Our strategically located sites in Montreal, QC Canada and Fort Worth, TX USA, makes StyroChem ideally positioned to service the North American and Global export EPS markets.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(975, 1, 'Strite Industries Limited', 'info@strite.com', '298 Shepherd Ave, CAMBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.strite.com ', '(519) 658-9361', '(519) 658-6925', '', '<p>Strite Industries was founded to assist companies that need superior machining skills to manufacture ultra-precision components. See the Strite advantages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Whether you are looking for an experienced ultra-precision manufacturer to fulfill your general machining needs or have specific high-end part requirements, Strite Industries will be your quality partner. See our quality.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We encourage you to talk to our staff about your manufacturing, tooling and prototype requirements. You will see why we have such a great reputation and you\'ll quickly understand why you should work with us. See the Strite advantages.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Strite provides engineering and prototyping services for the manufacturing, research &amp; scientific communities. We manufacture a wide range of ultra-precision machined products for the automotive, aerospace, defense, medical, orthodontic, and nuclear power industries. Strite products can be found in automotive turbochargers, Boeing, Airbus and Bombardier aircraft, IMAX cameras, CANDU nuclear reactors, telecommunication satellites, portable blood analyzers and orthodontic brackets. We also actively participate in product development, prototyping and complex assembly work.</div>', ''),
(976, 1, 'SRI Homes', 'inquiries@srihomes.com', '9500 Jim Bailey Rd, KELOWNA,, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.srihomes.com ', '(250) 766-0588', '(250) 766-0599', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The first SRI factory (Shelter Home Systems), located in Estevan, SK began building homes in 1978. In 1985, the second SRI factory (Regent Home Systems), in Lethbridge, AB was acquired. Rounding out the Western Canadian factories (Winfield Home Systems), the Kelowna factory began producing homes in 1992. To date, over 30,000 homes have been built between the three factories.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With over 65 acres of property and 300,000 sq. ft. of factory space, SRI&rsquo;s three Western Canadian factories are well poised to service customers from Vancouver Island to Ontario and from the US border north into the Yukon and Northwest Territories.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Building homes in a controlled factory environment and out of the weather has many advantages; no weather related damage and no delays due to inclement weather. Every phase of the home construction process can easily be inspected to ensure rigorous quality standards are met. Additionally, this building method offers significant cost savings by volume purchasing of building materials as well as reduced wastage.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(977, 1, 'SSI Micro', 'solutions@ssimicro.com', '356B Old Airport Rd, YELLOWKNIFE, Northwest Territories, Canada', 'www.ssimicro.com', '(867) 669-7500', '(867) 669-7510', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SSi Micro installs and maintains satellite networks in some of the world&rsquo;s most unworkable locations. In 1990, we started out as a small business selling and repairing computers in Fort Providence, Northwest Territories. Today, we are the North&rsquo;s largest Internet Service Provider headquartered in the NWT&rsquo;s capital city of Yellowknife.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Large urban areas are often connected by fibre-optic Internet networks, such as cable or DSL. But these physically connected networks are too expensive to install in rural and remote locations such as Northern Canada, as well as most of the world&rsquo;s developing countries. In these cases, satellite technology is the only cost-effective and reliable way to provide broadband Internet service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We&rsquo;re experts in making this technology work in the harshest conditions and the hardest-to-reach places. We&rsquo;ve deployed networks in Nunavik, Quebec, the Northern territories of Nunavut, the NWT, as well as in Africa, Indonesia and in the South-Pacific country of Kiribati (pronounced Keer-ih-bahs). We were also the first Canadian ISP to offer wireless Non-Line of Sight Internet access to its customers. In each situation, we designed and adapted existing software to meet the unique needs of remote locales.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Although we\'re Northern Canada\'s largest ISP, outside of Nunavut and the NWT, we might be the industry\'s best-kept secret. We like it that way. It\'s allowed us to remain firmly focused on developing our award-winning ideas while spending less time worrying about sales and marketing. Staying out of the spotlight also means we can do what we do best: design and deploy innovative satellite networks to bring the Internet to places nobody thought possible.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Recently, we designed a state-of-the-art private satellite network for the Government of Nunavut. Tomorrow, we might develop a new cellular network to serve the Far North. Or we may simply continue providing Internet communications solutions to remote corners of Canada and across the globe. Whatever we do, we will build on our reputation of being on the leading edge of wireless technologies.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(978, 1, 'SRB Technologies Canada Inc.', 'sales@betalight.com', '140-320 Boundary Rd E, PEMBROKE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.betalight.com', '(613) 732-0055', '(613) 732-0056', '', '<div>The specification of safety &amp; emergency lighting can be one of your most crucial decisions. People\'s lives depend on it.</div>\r\n<div>Betalight, Tritium Exit &amp; Safety Signs Are:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Self luminous</div>\r\n<div>Entirely self-powered</div>\r\n<div>Use no electricity, no batteries, no wiring, no maintenance &amp; no energy consumption</div>\r\n<div>From the original developers of the Betalight. The Betalight is an innovative self luminous light source used as an alternative to conventional electrical lighting products for safe, continuous, well illuminated emergency lighting.</div>', ''),
(979, 1, 'Squidink Communications', 'squidink@nl.rogers.com', '7 Walsh\'s Square, ST. JOHN\'S, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', '', '(709) 576-1312', '', '', '<p>A small firm, a big commitment. Squidink Communications provides professional print and web writing, research, editing and other communication services. From articles to annual reports; from brochures to background papers, company provides promotional copy, public education materials and corporate communications for public and private-sector clients. Experienced in a range of sectors and work, the company has a particular affinity for projects in the fields of sustainable development, environment, natural resources and cultural and natural heritage. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(980, 1, 'Sprague Foods Limited', 'info@spraguefoods.com', '385 College St. E, BELLEVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.spraguefoodslimited.com', '(613) 966-1200', '(613) 962-8600', '', '<p>Sprague Foods Limited is a BRC certified and HACCP recognized facility employing one of the most advanced in-container sterilization and cooking system in the world to optimize cooking quality while preserving nutritional qualities.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Organically certified, Sprague Foods produces private label products for both Canadian and US markets.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Specializing in all natural, healthy, vegetarian products including both natural and organic pureed, chunky and cream based soups, prepared bean products, re-fried beans and dips, puddings and a variety of meal builders. In addition to items in our product list we provide complete service including:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>- Product Development</div>\r\n<div>- Thermal Process Development</div>\r\n<div>- Nutritional Analysis</div>\r\n<div>- Label Compliance</div>\r\n<div>- Transportation to all Canadian &amp; US destinations</div>', ''),
(981, 1, 'A-1 Blasting Mats', 'a1blast@bellnet.ca', '325 Quesnel Rd, STURGEON FALLS, Ontario, Canada', 'www.a1blastingmats.com ', '(705) 753-5736', '(705) 753-5441', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A select group of highly-skilled craftspeople dedicated to:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Being a leading company in marketing a product and service of superior quality at a competitive price.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Marketing a product that meets or exceeds our customer&rsquo;s requirements and expectations, both nationally and internationally.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Striving towards continuous improvement, by implementing the latest developments in technology and combining them with our hands-on approach to ensure the best possible value for our clients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Promoting a progressive working environment for our employees, who are the key to our success.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company was founded in 1979 by Leo Arcand and was named Superior Blasting Mats. Superior Blasting Mats sold controlling shares and dissolved in 1984. In 1987, Denis Arcand (son of Leo Arcand) formed a new company called A1 Blasting Mats. In the early days, the company would produce 1 mat in a 10 hour work day. Today, the company now produces 5 to 6 mats in an 8 hour work day. Our objective is 8 mats per day. Member of the Ontario Tire Stewardship (OTS). Long standing employer in the local community.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(982, 1, 'A-R Business Machines Inc.', 'ar@a-rdistributors.com', '643 Railroad St W, MOUNT BRYDGES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.a-rdistributors.com', '(519) 452-1602', '(519) 452-3199', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Incorporated in 1987, A-R Business machines began distribution of &ldquo;ADLER-ROYAL&rdquo; calculators, typewriters and cash registers through a dealer network stretching from St. John&rsquo;s Newfoundland to Victoria, British Columbia.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1991 with the purchase of Assmann Dictation Systems of Canada Limited our endeavors into the field of dictation equipment began. Assmann is a well-known name in the Canadian marketplace for quality and mini cassette dictation systems since 1953.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">1992 brought expansion into the paper shredder market with the agreement to market Kobra Shredders exclusively in Canada. Kobra has grown to become one of our major product lines that we distribute. We have 12 models approved for sale to the Federal Government.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1993 brought further expansion to the products we distribute, with the addition of Muratec Multifunction copiers and facsimile machines. Muratec is a proven industry leader with more than 35 years as an innovator in the copier and facsimile field. Even some of the major players, such as Xerox, Sharp, Minolta, Konica, Okidata, Omnifax, Pitney Bowes, Monroe, just to name a few, have had Muratec manufacture machines for them. If you purchased a copier or a fax from one of these companies it is possible that it actually was a Muratec.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1997 we entered into an agreement with Grundig, an international electronics firm, to market their line of dictation products which include their Steno cassette, micro cassette and digital dictation systems.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2000, we entered into an agreement with Carolina Wholesale to market their line of Nakajima typewriters. We have both French and English models to distribute across Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our latest agreement is with Philips Dictation Systems a huge electronics firm. We are an MCDE distributor for their line of mini cassette and digital dictation systems across Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(983, 1, 'A & BB Rice Inc.', 'trade@abbrice.com', '209-1033 Bay St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.abbrice.com ', '(416) 929-7423', '(416) 929-7438', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 1994, A &amp; BB Rice Inc is a privately held Canadian corporation based in Toronto, Canada. The company&rsquo;s co-founder Mr. Ali Bilgen has been in the rice business since 1988. Unlike many other food brokerages in Canada, our company&rsquo;s focus has always been on the rice business. We firmly believe that we provide a value proposition to our customers by specializing in rice.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since its inception, A &amp; BB Rice Inc has been the exclusive broker/agent of Riceland Foods Inc of Arkansas and Farmers&rsquo; Rice Coop of California in the Canadian market.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A &amp; BB Rice Inc also works with selective mills from around the world in the area of specialty international rice varieties.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1996, A &amp; BB Rice Inc expanded its business into the area of conventional and certified organic dry edible beans, peas, lentils, chickpeas and other agricultural commodities.&nbsp; These products are complimentary to rice.&nbsp; Many customers asked for the high level of service they were receiving with rice, on these products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We contract directly with growers and processors to meet the exact requirements of our customers. Our strength lies in understanding our customers&rsquo; complex situations and finding the right solution. We are a customer service oriented company.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our experience in agricultural commodities combined with our understanding of the North American market has allowed A &amp; BB Rice Inc to become a leading rice brokerage and agricultural commodity trading company.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, our customer list includes many of the top retail, foodservice, industrial and re-packing customers in North America. Our conventional and organic food products are sold under many top brand names and private labels across the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our staff is highly experienced in agricultural commodities with extensive knowledge in conventional and organic rice, wild rice, dry edible beans, peas, lentils, chickpeas, barley, popcorn and other agricultural commodities.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(984, 1, 'A & L Computer Software Limited', 'postmaster@anl.com', '6-175 West Beaver Creek Rd, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, Canada', 'www.anl.com ', '(905) 886-8066', '(905) 886-6617', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A&amp;LComputer Software Limited has been in the computer software business since 1982. With the release of the A&amp;L Medical System in 1985, A&amp;L started directing its product line toward the medical market in Ontario, more specifically to medical offices and clinics. A&amp;L has worked closely with the Ontario Medical Association, medical laboratories and the Ontario Ministry of Health to ensure that its software applications align well to the specific needs of its clients. A&amp;L\'s president, Alex Yuan was granted the 1995 Entrepreneur Of The Year award from the Town of Richmond Hill, Ontario. In 1998 he also recieved the Entrepreneur Of The Year award from the Association of Chinese Canadian Entrepreneurs and the Outstanding Business Achievment Award from the Ontario Chamber of Commerce. In 1992, A&amp;L took over Medics, a competitor, helping to expand its presence throughout Ontario, and also leading to the development of a joint marketing venture with the University of Toronto the following year. This resulted in A&amp;L donating 33% of its software revenue to the University of Toronto and the Chinese Community Nursing Home for Greater Toronto.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1994, A&amp;L released its document imaging program, A&amp;L Document Console, expanding its potential client base beyond the medical community (and beyond Ontario) to include a variety of business venues. This software product allows all documents, whether they be text, photographs, charts, etc., to be stored and indexed on computer databases for immediate access. This can allow a business to run a virtually paperless office and to electronically route all documents anywhere in the world. In 1995, A&amp;L launched a joint venture with another Ontario company, HTN Incorporated, in order to develop and market the Healthcare Electronic Resources On-Line (HERO*) network for Ontario physicians. It provided the Ontario healthcare industry with its first comprehensive transactional network. A&amp;L HERO*, a Windows based application, provides electronic OHIP billing, scheduling and e-mail in addition to the capability for laboratory requisitions and prescription transmission in association with those laboratories and pharmacies who will eventually subscribe to the network. A&amp;L now has a 30% share of HTN Incorporated, and continues to develop and market the HERO* network through its Client Service Centers and business partners across Ontario. (\'HERO*\' is a registered trademark of HTN Incorporated.) In 1997, A&amp;L expanded into the United States by opening its first Dealership for A&amp;L Document Console in Fallbrook, California. For further information you may access their website.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A&amp;L also publishes a newsletter, Softwords, which can be viewed at this website by selecting the \'newsletter\' hot button on the menu. Please make sure to visit often to keep up with our latest developments.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(985, 1, 'A Bit of Home', 'sales@abitofhome.ca', '925 Rathburn Rd E Unit C10, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.abitofhome.ca ', '(905) 804-1731', '(905) 804-8959', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A Bit of Home is a Canadian independent retailer specializing in Irish and British consumer goods. Our mission is to provide the best selection of products to expatriots as well as others who seek the quality and uniqueness from back home.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our first sale was made in February 2002 when we launched our online store and carried a little over 100 items. In 2004 we opened our first retail location in Mississauga, Ontario when it became apparent that there were quite a number of people who preferred to shop in person as opposed to online.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today we stock well over 2,000 different items covering the most popular packaged food products from Ireland and Britain, Celtic Jewellery, DVDs, football memorabelia, books, souvenirs and giftware. A Bit of Home turned out to be the right name for our shop with the largest selection of all sorts of Irish and British goods.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(986, 1, 'CREATIVE CORPORATE GIFTS', 'acorpgifts@videotron.ca', '315 Brighton Dr, BEACONSFIELD, Quebec, Canada', 'www.acorporategifts.com ', '(514) 695-9001', '(514) 695-2360', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a DISTRIBUTOR of PROMOTIONAL PRODUCTS. We help you promote your Company by BRANDING your Company Name, Logo &amp; Sales Message on any of our 15,000 products which are put into your prospects\' environment to help you increase SALES OF YOUR PRODUCT OR SERVICE. Promotional Products are used for: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* TRADE SHOW GIVEAWAYS <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* SPONSORSHIP <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* CLIENT APPRECIATION <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* FUND-RAISING <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* CORPORATE GIFTS <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* EMPLOYEE RECOGNITION <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* INTRODUCTION OF A NEW PRODUCT OR FACILITY <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">* BRANDING YOUR PRODUCT OR NAME IN THE MARKET&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(987, 1, 'A.R.D. Industries Ltd.', 'iinf@ardindustries.com', '14-180 Sheldon Dr., CAMBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ardindustries.com ', '(519) 622-1652', '(519) 622-1358', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A.R.D. Industries Ltd. is a privately held Canadian company incorporated in 1975.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A.R.D. Industries produces friction welded components and does sub-contract friction welding of customer\'s goods, for a broad variety of manufacturers, including agricultural, automotive, electrical, forestry, mining, transportation and other related industries. A.R.D. Industries is Canada\'s only friction welding sub-contract manufacturer.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A.R.D. Industries operates nine (9) Direct Drive Friction Welders from (6) tons to one hundred fifteen (115) tons forge capacity (with orientation) and also does production cutting, CNC turning and induction heat treating of welded assemblies. A.R.D. Industries occupies 19,000 square feet in Cambridge, Ontario Canada, and employs 25 people. All machines have been retrofitted to add the capability of recording full weld data throughout the weld cycle for data collection, setup, archiving, retrieval and plotting. A.R.D. Industries has been successfully registered to ISO 9001:2008 since 1999.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A.R.D. Industries is centrally located to service Canada, the USA, Mexico and abroad.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(988, 1, 'A.T.F. Sports Inc.', 'orders@atfsports.com', '620 McCaffrey, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.atfsports.com ', '(514) 744-3621', '(514) 744-3083', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ATF Sports, manufacturers of some of the world\'s finest combat sports equipment (BOXING, MARTIAL ARTS, BOXERCISE, FITNESS) for home and GYM.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Boxing equipment, full line retail merchandised.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Boxercise or Aerobic boxing equipment for home and Gym.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Full line of martial arts equipment and apparel. ATF has developed a world wide reputation for quality products, for professionals and amateurs alike.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(989, 1, 'Aardcom Communications', 'mail@aardcom.net', '100-53 Summerfield Cres., ETOBICOKE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.aardcom.net ', '(416) 875-7543', '', '', '<p>Event Services and supplies for trade shows, conferences, and corporate meetings including on-site and advance registration, name badges, on-line registration, website design &amp; hosting, seminar tracking, session tracking, and electronic lead retrieval. We also lease computers by the week, month or year.</p>', ''),
(990, 1, 'AB Sciex LP, Division of MDS Inc.', 'gordon.logan@absciex.com', '71 Four Valley Dr., CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.absciex.com ', '(289) 982-2596', '(905) 660-2600', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">SCIEX was incorporated in 1974 by a group from the University of Toronto Institute of Aerospace Studies. In 1981 SCIEX was acquired by MDS Health Group Limited. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The key to SCIEX\'s success has been the innovative approach that it has taken to the development of instrumentation. In every product line, SCIEX has been the pioneer with the introduction of the first commercial mobile laboratories, triple quadruple mass spectrometers, inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometers, contraband detection systems, and electrospray based mass spectrometers. Many of these products are in the second and third generation stages. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The development of innovative products which meet the needs of niche markets have been critical to company\'s success. SCIEX has twice been awarded the Canada Award for Business Excellence, once in the category of spectrometry and secondly in the category of Innovation for the development of the API III system. SCIEX frequently works in partnership with our clients to develop new solutions to client problems. Joint venture partnerships have been a key component of the strategy to market products world wide, notably with Applied Biosystems Inc. and PerkinElmer Inc.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(991, 1, 'Abbott Boats Inc.', 'info@abbottboats.com', '1458 London Rd, SARNIA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.abbottboats.com ', '(519) 542-2771', '(519) 542-2324', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Recreational and competition boats by hand lay-up.</span></p>', ''),
(992, 1, 'ABC Tool & Die Ltd.', 'abctool@golden.net', '225 Toman Dr, WATERLOO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.abctool.on.ca ', '(519) 884-8453', '(519) 884-8436', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ABC Tool and Die Ltd. is a full service supplier of liquid filling nozzles, feed screws and change parts, dedicated to exceeding expectations in the shortest period of time.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In business since 1979, customers the world over benefit from the expertise and knowledge found only at ABC Tool and Die Ltd.&nbsp; From packaging automation to the maintenance of virtually every type of liquid filling nozzle to new equipment design, ABC Tool and Die Ltd. can equip you with the right solution.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Backed by a plant with over 5000 square feet of manufacturing space, our team of highly trained engineers can design and manufacture liquid filling nozzles, feed screws and change parts including customer specialty jobs. We distribute liquid filling nozzles and other change parts across Canada and the United States, and work with local businesses in the Tri-City area as well. Superior customer service and liquid filling nozzles that are second to none, are what make our customers repeat customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Located in Waterloo Ontario, ABC Tool and Die Ltd. proudly services clients across North America.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(993, 1, 'ABCO Group', 'mikea@abcogroup.ca', '1280 Eglinton Ave E, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.abcogroup.ca ', '(905) 629-2291', '(905) 629-2432', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1987, The ABCO Group has provided office furniture and moving solutions to thousands of Ontario businesses. With locations in Toronto, Mississauga, Concord, Pickering, Barrie and Kitchener, The ABCO Group offers over 160,000 square feet of new and pre-owned office furniture deals. The ABCO Group can also assist your business in many related areas, such as corporate relocation and moving services, refurbishing of existing furniture and servicing and repairing of almost all brands of office furniture. We also offer the benefits of a custom furniture division, a full service repainting shop and we can help re-design your space with computer assisted drawings.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2009, The ABCO Group acquired Addmore Office Furniture to become Ontario&rsquo;s largest independent office furniture retailer. With a strong focus on the ability to display quality new and pre-owned office furniture in a relaxed and inviting atmosphere, The ABCO Group has become a preferred supplier for most of Ontario&rsquo;s leading companies. The ABCO Group understands that the competitive nature of business in today&rsquo;s economic climate can create challenges for companies of all sizes. Through strategic alliances with our suppliers, The ABCO Group offers a wide range of new office furniture at very competitive prices, as well as re-markets the region&rsquo;s largest selection of quality, pre-owned office furniture that allows companies to save money on one of the most important requirements for successful businesses.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether your business needs to grow or move, The ABCO Group offers the services to assist in any transition. With a dedicated team of Consultants and the personnel and equipment to execute, we are truly &ldquo;big enough to manage and small enough to care!&rdquo; Drop into any of The ABCO Group&rsquo;s six locations today and see what&rsquo;s in store for you.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(994, 1, 'Abenaki Artworks', 'abart@mts.net', '730 Midland St N, PORTAGE LA PRAIRIE, Manitoba, Canada', '', '(204) 857-5945', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Artist Carmen Hathaway creates innovative original works in acrylic painting, art glass, clay and digital media.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Meshing style, technique and content of diverse media has resulted in increasingly focussed thematic structure and content. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Her digital online exhibition with Winnipeg\'s PLATFORM centre for photographic and digital arts debuts in the fall of 2009. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Guest artist instructor at the 2008 Hot Art Colony, Tougaloo College, Jackson, Mississippi&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(995, 1, 'ABS Manufacturing and Distributing Ltd.', 'sales@absmanufacturing.com', '185 Magill St, LIVELY, Ontario, Canada', 'www.absmanufacturing.com ', '(705) 692-5445', '(705) 692-1435', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ABS Manufacturing and Distributing is committed to providing high quality, cost effective products and services that will meet or exceed the requirements and expectations of our clients in the mining, aggregate and forestry industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ABS Manufacturing and Distributing believes that Safety, Progressiveness, Integrity and Quality are the key elements in creating overall synergy with our customers, employees, partners and the environment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are committed to providing a safe and fair working environment for our people. We aspire to exceed all government and industry safety and human rights standards. We ensure ongoing training for all personnel and fully support any and all efforts on behalf of our employees to further their education.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We at ABS Manufacturing and Distributing also understand that we have a responsibility to society and the environment. All of our dealings are done with integrity and to the highest moral standards. To do our part in protecting our natural surroundings, we ensure that we meet and exceed all government standards for environmental care in the manufacturing and distributing of all of our products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our objective is to provide products manufactured to the highest quality, distribute them at competitive prices and build solid relationships with all of our partners, customers and employees. Our mission is to continue building to make our name synonymous with top quality.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over two decades, ABS Manufacturing and Distributing Limited has been providing the mining, milling, and pulp and paper industries with fabrication, machining, rubber lining, rubber molding, plastics, gaskets, valves, pumps, conveyor belt parts, assembly, and repair services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our shops are totally integrated facilities with the ability to fabricate, machine, rubber line and mould all at one location. We maintain ISO 9001:2000 certification, CWB W47.1 registration, as well as high pressure welding certification through TSSA (Technical Standards and Safety Authority). We are also pleased to announce our TSSA certification for the repair and re-certification of Section I, IV and VIII pressure relief valves for fluid gas and steam.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(996, 1, 'Absolute Logistics', 'greg@absolutelogistics.ca', '1A3-48 Trider Cres, DARTMOUTH,, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.absolutelogistics.ca ', '(902) 468-4188', '(902) 468-5925', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are a full service freight forwarder worldwide providing feasible methods in air, ocean and trucking as well full documentation and customs.Cold storage and crossdock as well as one stop shopping for all your transportation requirements.Full service freight forwarding, Worldwide Importer and Exporter. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(997, 1, 'Acadian Glass Art', 'info@acadianglassart.com', '329 Main St, YARMOUTH, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.acadianglassart.com ', '(902) 742-4308', '(902) 742-5891', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established by business proprietor Brenda Doucette in the port city of Yarmouth, Acadian Glass Art is a design studio for the production of stained glass artwork.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Stained glass design is a detailed process that allows for the crafter to utilize varying combinations of color and shapes in the production of the final work that takes on a life of its own when completed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Within the Studio, produced artwork is placed on display for public viewing and purchase. Much of the works available have themes rooted in Acadian traditions that are strong in this region.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Along with works that are available on display, customized orders are also taken and produced based on the design and ideas of your choosing.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(998, 1, 'Access Mining Consultants Ltd.', 'mail@accessconsulting.ca', '151 Industrial Rd. 3 Calcite Business Center, WHITEHORSE, Yukon, Canada', 'www.accessconsulting.ca ', '(867) 668-6463', '(867) 633-4882', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Access was formed in March 1995 to provide locally experienced professional project management environmental services for development projects in Yukon, northern British Columbia, and Alaska. Since that time we have permitted many projects over a wide range of land and resource development in the north.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">What We Provide:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A Tailored Project Approach<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A Multidisciplinary Core Team with Recognized Specialists<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A Keen Understanding of the Local Environment, Government, and Stakeholders<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Access was established in 1995 , Purchased in 2006 by Alexco Resource Corp.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Access is now part of Alexco Environmental Group which is comprised of Access, Elsa Reclamation and Development Co. Ltd., and Alexco Resource U.S. Corp.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Operating as an independent Yukon based subsidiary of Alexco Resource Corp.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Providing comprehensive scientific and engineering solutions to challenges for projects \'Large &amp; Small\'<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Permitting and Licensing Specialists.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(999, 1, 'Accessible Media Inc.', 'info@ami.ca', '200-1090 Don Mills Rd, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ami.ca ', '(416) 422-4222', '(416) 422-1633', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Happy New Year! Time certainly flies, and as we welcome 2015 with open arms I&rsquo;m extremely proud to reflect on all that we have accomplished over the past year.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">2014 produced many milestones for AMI including two big firsts: the launch of AMI-t&eacute;l&eacute;, our third broadcast channel and the first French language channel with open described video, and the launch of the AMI-player, the first accessible online media player in North America. Both of these initiatives contribute significantly to our mandate of making accessible media for all Canadians and we&rsquo;re committed to their ongoing development in the coming year.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2014 we expanded our original programing line-up to provide a variety of unique and engaging content for our audience. That initiative continues into 2015 with all new episodes of the D.J. Demers Show and AMI Inside. Plus, Christine Ha and Carl Heinrich are back with a brand new season of Four Senses, and Kelly MacDonald&rsquo;s Blindsighted makes the big move to the small screen. In April, AMI-t&eacute;l&eacute; will launch their first original program, a magazine- style show exploring everything from health to personal finances, hosted by popular blind radio personality Luc Fortin. AMI original programming is available online using the AMI-player so you can watch your favourite programs at your convenience.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1001, 1, 'Accurate Fabricating Ltd.', 'ray@accuratefabricating.com', '12875-85th Ave, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.accuratefabricating.com ', '(778) 863-5451', '(604) 591-5875', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Accurate Fabricating we have been building and designing superior quality excavator attachments since 1994. Our large product line, experienced staff, and speed of service, are unsurpassed!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Be it a simple repair, our most popular excavator or backhoe attachment, or a highly complex custom design, Accurate products are built to last.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Accurate we provide on site fabrication and engineering by a fully qualified, innovative and dedicated staff who take pride in their work, and the products they manufacture.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All maintenance and repairs are handled professionally, promptly and efficiently, keeping costly down time to a minimum.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Accurate Fabricating ensures a high quality product at an affordable price.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1002, 1, 'Acme Fire and Safety Co Ltd', 'acmesales@acmefire.com', '7015 Curragh Ave, BURNABY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.acmefire.com ', '(604) 437-8555', '(604) 437-1301', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In March of 1972, Acme Fire and Safety Co. Ltd. was formed between Lino Tonolli and Bruce Buckner, and was located across the street from where the Joyce-Collingwood Sky Train Station was later built.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1974 Acme Fire purchased and moved into a building at 3427 Kingsway in Vancouver. In 1996 a new associate, Michael Tonolli, was brought on board, and in 2002 Michael became the sole owner of Acme Fire. After 32 years at our Kingsway location the business moved into a more progressive 12,000 square foot facility located at 7015 Curragh Avenue, in Burnaby.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1972 Acme Fire has grown from a two-person operation to over 40 employees. Our technicians average over 8 years of experience. This long-term commitment extends to our customers through dedication and knowledge of all kinds of fire safety services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our services range from sales, service and installation of pre-engineered and engineered fire suppression systems, fire extinguishers, fire alarms, ULC fire alarm and elevator monitoring, emergency lighting, sprinkler and back flow services, and fire safety plans. We have our own hydrostatic testing and recharging facilities. By providing all these services in house, we ensure quality and control. We have strategic alliances with professional engineers to assist or design specific projects when needed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a manufacturer&rsquo;s representative for several high quality product lines such as Notifier and Firelite fire alarm systems by Honeywell, Kidde Fire Systems, Ansul Fire Systems, Range Guard/Badger and Pyrochem suppression systems, Amerex and Ansul fire extinguishers, Redilite emergency lights, ZTS battery testers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In over 40 years of successful business and continued growth, our established customer base includes the likes of McDonalds Restaurants of Canada, Royal Arch Masonic Care homes, BC Ferries, A &amp; W Restaurants, White Spot Restaurants, Canada Safeway Limited, YVR Airport, Finning Inc., City of Vancouver Fire Department, UBC and Vancouver Hospitals&hellip; and many other commercial buildings, restaurants, and apartment complexes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are members of the National Association for Fire Equipment Distributors, the National Fire Protection Association, Canadian Fire Alarm Association, and the Fire Prevention Officer\'s Association.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Acme Fire is insured with a 5 million dollar insurance policy. All of our established technicians are manufacturer certified, as well as ASTTBC certified.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1003, 1, 'Acro Media Inc.', 'info@acromediainc.com', '103-2303 Leckie Rd., KELOWNA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.acromediainc.com ', '(250) 763-8884', '(250) 763-6936', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Acro Media Inc. is a design firm founded by designers and operated by designers. Our award-winning design, multimedia, technical, and content teams turn ideas into action.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">There\'s a binary split among the majority of web development companies - a given firm is strong in either the aesthetic or the technical. Acro Media is an exception to this rule, providing innovative internet solutions that are visually appealing. Our firm is based on teamwork, and each team member is at the forefront of his or her respective field.</span></p>', ''),
(1005, 1, 'ADL Products Inc.', 'sales@adl-electricmotors.com', '31023 Gardner Ave, ABBOTSFORD, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.adl-electricmotors.com ', '(604) 309-1177', '', '', '<p>Wholesaler of 3-phase electric motors.All ADL Electric motors hold a high efficient certification as tested by CSA. Looking for dealers in North America, also. &nbsp;</p>', '');
