(1027, 1, 'Arbell Electronics Inc', 'sales@arbell.com', '8-1175 Corporate Dr., BURLINGTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.arbell.com ', '(905) 332-7755', '(905) 332-0748', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Arbell is Canada&rsquo;s largest authorized distributor of production equipment and supplies. We have a national sales team of product knowledge experts dedicated to serving our industry customers with excellent pricing, technical support, inventory and leading brand name products. We welcome you to explore our selection of over 80 different manufacturers to find just what you are looking for.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Arbell is the largest industry distributor of production equipment and supplies in Canada. With over 10,000 parts stocked in inventory and access to thousands more through our network of 80+ industry leading manufacturers, Arbell offers our customers the best selection at competitive prices. We are an authorized distributor for the world&rsquo;s most trusted brands including 3M, Cookson, Hakko, Hammond, Lista, Loctite, Pace and Weller to name a few. At Arbell, we are continually expanding and improving our product line to bring you the latest technologies and products in the marketplace, delivered accurately and on time. Customer service is of paramount importance to us, and our national sales team is dedicated to ensuring that you will be satisfied with your shopping experience. We invite you to explore the products we sell online. Feel free to contact us for volume pricing, product demos or further industry support as necessary- we want to earn your business!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1028, 1, 'Arctic Fisheries Ltd.', 'aherring@eastlink.ca', '32 Hawthorne St, YARMOUTH, Nova Scotia, Canada', '', '(902) 742-9101', '(902) 742-1287', '', '<p>Consulting Services, oil and gas interaction with the fishing industry.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1029, 1, 'Argus Control Systems Ltd.', 'argus@arguscontrols.com', '1281 Johnston Rd, WHITE ROCK, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.arguscontrols.com ', '(604) 538-3531', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Argus provides automated control systems for horticulture, aquaculture, and related biotechnology industries. Our capabilities include facilities automation and specialty monitoring and control applications to support the needs of our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Argus is an automated control systems pioneer with over thirty years of leadership and innovation in control technology. We were among the first to use computers for integrating the control of greenhouse environments and irrigation systems. Today our systems are used in horticulture and biotechnology research facilities, universities, aquaculture and aquaponics, and many other custom control applications at sites throughout the world<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We understand that complex environments and engineered bio-production facilities require individually tailored&nbsp; strategies designed around the needs of the target activities. We also understand that greenhouses and other specialized facilities behave a lot differently than conventional buildings and often require much more complex equipment systems and backup contingencies to maintain optimal climates and growth processes.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Your Controls Partner: we provide complete monitoring and control solutions including all necessary hardware and software. We also provide the knowledge and experience necessary for safe, efficient integrated control of your facility. Whenever you need help, our service team will work with you to ensure you get the most out of your Argus control system.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We don&rsquo;t expect you to be an expert. We know firsthand that automated control is a complex subject and we try to make our systems as easy to understand as possible, while allowing you maximum latitude for making your own adjustments and modifications.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1030, 1, 'Arla Foods Inc.', 'marketing_canada@arlafoods.com', '675 Rivermede Rd., CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.arlafoods.ca ', '(905) 669-9393', '(800) 387-3699', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a 13,500-strong dairy farmer cooperative and a team of 19,000 engaged colleagues who love milk and all the possibilities it presents. We are an ambitious bunch, who strive to be responsible and open-minded to your needs and ideas. We aim to make the most out of milk to help you make the most out of life &ndash; throughout life.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A cooperative dairy company<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">You may not know this, but Arla Foods is a cooperative owned by dairy farmers. The cooperative ethos means we all work together to continuously create something stronger and better, for the benefit of our farm owners. This principle has always been at the heart of everything we do and it is why we are still here today, and going strong, over 100 years after Arla first started.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Know more about our cooperative<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Arla and sustainability<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We work hard to grow our business in a sustainable manner and can only do this in close collaboration with our dairy farmers and the many people and companies we do business with. And, very importantly, by listening to you. Meet us on our group Facebook page to ask questions and see updates on new products, our sustainable work and much more...<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Joyful dairy moments<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We want our dairy products to be good for you and give you joyful moments. We aim to bring a little health and inspiration into your life - wherever you are, whenever you feel like it and at every stage of your life. Get great ideas for joyful moments whenever the mood takes you:<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1031, 1, 'As You Like It Media Inc', 'sheila@asyoulikeitmedia.com', '1383 29th St E, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.asyoulikeitmedia.com', '(604) 986-5065', '(604) 986-5065', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As You Like It Media Inc. is based in Vancouver, BC, a magnificent city nestled in the wilderness of Canada&rsquo;s rugged West Coast. We draw upon this mixture of urban cosmopolitan energy and awe inspiring Pacific coastline to give a unique energy and style to our productions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Scott Alpen and Sheila Allan are principle partners and work with a great team of talented and creative people. If you have a message to deliver, a vision to share, a lesson to teach, a product to launch or an image to build, we are a vital asset your business needs for today&rsquo;s media.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With over two decades of production excellence we have experience in producing everything from multi-camera festivals to full-spectrum marketing graphics and video media for major corporate campaigns, documentaries, training, broadcast and the web. If you need a connection &ndash; we can make it.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We have International working agreements with partners in London, Tokyo, Dubai, Ottawa and Brazil and are always able to help with national and international production needs. Check us out, give us a call, let&rsquo;s connect.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1032, 1, 'ATA Medical International Inc.', 'info@atamedical.com', '30-70 East Beaver Creek Rd, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario , Canada ', 'www.atamedical.com ', '(905) 417-8756', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is to provide a better link between worldwide manufacturers and developing markets. ATA Medical International Inc is privately owned and is specialized in medical &amp; dental products as well as pharmaceuticals.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We help worldwide manufacturers target these market as effective as possible and save them substantial time &amp; money.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">If you are a manufacturer with at least CE approved products we would like to hear from you and explore the potentials of our cooperation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our expertise and over a decade experience in International markets complements your fine products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ATA Medical International Inc is a Canadian company with the goal to provide a better link between worldwide manufacturers and International Markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are specialized in medical &amp; dental products and pharmaceuticals. We have partner offices in select countries that serves our target market with a full team of local experts in the field.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our employees are experts with over 25 years of combined experience in their own fields and we have experience in their market for years.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1033, 1, 'Atlantic Star Uniforms (2009) inc', 'info@atluniforms.ca', '15 Miller Ave, EDMUNDSTON, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.atlanticstaruniforms.ca ', '(506) 735-1902', '(506) 735-1917', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As Canadian industry leader, Atlantic Star Uniforms give you the safest workwear on the market. If protection, durability and quality of superior product are the things you&rsquo;re looking for, Contact Atlantic Star Uniforms.&nbsp; Our team pledges to create a unique product made to your specifications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Atlantic Star Uniforms, For People Who Go Into Action.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1034, 1, 'Audiotelecom inc. - Orpheo Canada', 'info@orpheocanada.ca', '7556 De La Sarcelle St, CHARNY, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.orpheocanada.ca ', '(418) 832-7955', '(418) 832-5334', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Orph&eacute;o Canada (Audiot&eacute;l&eacute;com inc) has made a name for itself in the field of multimedia-based talking guides. Our projects stand out for their high value-added and cutting-edge features, the result of design quality, applicability, rigorously researched content, and user-friendly technology<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This Website has been designed to allow you to find out more about our company and its products and services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We hope to be talking to you soon. Enjoy your visit!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1035, 1, 'Autogas Propane Ltd.', 'service@autogaspropane.com', '10128 Nordel Crt, DELTA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.autogaspropane.com ', '(604) 433-4900', '(604) 433-9719', '', '<p>We provide clean, simple solutions to your propane needs with outstanding service. We take pride in the value added services provided by our friendly, knowledgable employees.</p>', ''),
(1036, 1, 'Automation Devices (Canada) Limited', 'sales@adlcan.com', '4700 Montrose Rd, NIAGARA FALLS, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.automationdeviceslimited.com', '(905) 354-3881', '(905) 354-4072', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 40 years Automation Devices have been creating machines that help our clients increase production and limit down time.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our mission is to exceed the expectations of our customers, whom we define as friends, partners, and fellow employees. We will accomplish this through teamwork, integrity, and a steadfast commitment to achieving the highest levels of customer satisfaction, with extraordinary emphasis on economical and innovative solutions. Quality and service are the heart of our business!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1037, 1, 'Avanti Aerospace & Engineering Inc.', 'awalls@avantirework.com', '4 - 8473 - 124th St, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.avantirework.com ', '(604) 590-8013', '(604) 590-8014', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Avantirework.com. We invite you to explore the many services that Avanti Aerospace and Engineering Inc. has to&nbsp; offer.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a full service repair and overhaul facility, holding both Transport Canada AMO (92-03) and EASA (145.7162) certifications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Avanti Aerospace, all personnel - from owners to every employee - work as a team to provide top tier quality, service and reliability to our customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In an extremely cost conscious marketplace, we strive to ensure our pricing is very competitive to assist our customers in achieving their financial objectives.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1038, 1, 'Award Marble Ltd.', 'mona@awardmarble.com', '147 De Baets St, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.awardmarble.com ', '(204) 661-6640', '(204) 663-7803', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are Manitoba\'s leading custom marble manufacturing facility. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Award Marble is a family company established in 1977. Our combined experience of over a century creating, and installing cultured marble bathrooms, showers, tub surrounds, finishes and other products provides peace of mind for our clients and allows the quality of our work to speak for itself.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The MARBLE FACTORY LTD. (TMF) is a private Canadian company founded in 1976. The initial owners were Ron and Dyanne Martin and current owner is Iksil Group Inc. TMF is a manufacturer of cast polymer Marble, Onyx, Granite bath and kitchen plumbing fixtures. TMF is a also the manufacturer of POLYSTONE solid surface counter tops. The company\'s head office and manufacturing plant are located in a new 13,000 square foot building they own at 51 Scurfield Blvd. in Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada. The company\'s full time staff of 12 to 15 experts is supplemented with part time and contract as required for project work.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PRODUCT MANUFACTURED: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Cast polymer MARBLE, ONYX and GRANITE bath and kitchen ware. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Vanity tops, standard and custom sizes <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Bath tubs and whirlpools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Whirlpool wall splashes, decking, steps and skirting <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Shower bases, wall panelling and tub surrounds <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Recessed and surface mounted soap dishes and shampoo shelves. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Toilet, low profile, one piece, 2.5 gal. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Fireplace fronts and hearths <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- POLYSTONE solid surface countertops, 3/4&quot; standard thickness. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Commerical counter tops for Banks, Restaurants, Hospitals, Retail and Office buildings <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Mausoleum crypt covers (interior only) <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Cremation urns <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Epoxy Laboratory counter tops (acid, chemical and heat resistant.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1039, 1, 'Axens Canada Specialty Aluminas Inc.', 'bmorin@axenscanada.com', '4000 Development Dr., BROCKVILLE, Ontario , Canada ', 'www.axens.net', '(613) 851-5092', '(613) 342-6943', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Axens is an international provider of advanced technologies (licensor), catalysts, adsorbents and services (technical assistance, consulting) to the refining, petrochemical, gas and alternative fuels industries. The main scope of Axens&rsquo; business is focused on the conversion of oil, gas, biomass and coal to fuels and major petrochemical intermediates.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OUR MISSION: Improving the performance of our clients and helping them to be more successful constitute our only mission. We are a non-aligned pure technology company. We do not sell motor fuels or chemicals and do not operate service stations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OUR AMBITIONS: Our ambition is to be the reference technology company for applications in refining, petrochemicals and gas processing. We are also active in industrial water treatment markets. Actively preparing for the future, we aim to be a leader in alternative fuels: conversion of renewable lipids to diesel and jet fuel, production of high-quality distillates from direct coal-liquefaction and the manufacture of liquid products through the conversion of synthesis gas from various feedstocks such as natural gas, biomass and coal.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OUR FOUNDATION: Axens, an IFP Energies nouvelles group company, was created in 2001 through the merger of Procatalyse with the Technology Licensing &amp; Service Division of IFP Energies nouvelles. This combination provides a single-source offering of technologies, products and services enabling us to respond more efficiently to customer needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1040, 1, 'AYA Kitchens and Baths Ltd.', 'info@ayakitchens.com', '1551 Caterpillar Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.AyAkitchens.com ', '(905) 848-1999', '(905) 848-5127', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Kitchen is today\'s living room - It\'s the heart of the home. At AyA we believe that a great kitchen starts with you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Every AyA kitchen is designed and made just for you. Unlike other kitchen manufacturers we don\'t assemble from stock, we produce a unique kitchen for each and every customer. With AyA\'s mass customization approach, you get the best of both worlds - the personalization of a custom kitchen with the value and quality that comes from a 150,000 sq. ft. state-of-the-art production facility.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AyA is committed to staying on the cutting edge of design and providing the best customer service experience possible. A lot of things have changed since AyA opened its doors back in 2001: technology, styles, materials, new locations and much more, but the one thing that never changes is our dedication to delivering exceptional value and customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">By combining old world craftsmanship and attention to detail with high tech manufacturing processes AyA offers innovative, quality cabinetry at competitive prices, incomparable selection of colours, styles and accessories to help you create your ultimate living space.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1041, 1, 'Azimuth Machinery Ltd', 'sales@azimuthpress.com', '6040, rte 132, SAINTE-CATHERINE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.azimuthpress.com ', '(450) 632-8080', '(450) 632-8081', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AZIMUTH MACHINERY LTD, is a leading manufacturing of air clutch, clinching presses and mechanical or custom build presses. AZIMUTH is renowned for the quality of its clinching, mechanical, and air clutch presses, its ability to supply custom built presses based on customers\'unique specifications, and its outstanding customer and after-sales services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All AZIMUTH air clutch, mechanical and clinching presses are manufactured in plant, increasing our competitiveness in offering the best possible quality at the best possible prices. AZIMUTH keeps a wide range of replacement parts in inventory for all AZIMUTH clinching and air clutch presses as well as for Taloc and Alceco presses allowing us to provide fast and efficient after-sale services.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1042, 1, 'Aztec Water Systems', 'aztecindustries@sasktel.net', '639 Park St, REGINA, Saskatchewan, Canada ', 'www.ruralwater.ca ', '(306) 721-2595', '(306) 721-2320', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Aztec Industries is a true leader in Rural Water Treatment ...<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We don\'t just dabble in Rural Water Treatment, we specialize exclusively in it, and have been leaders in the industry, throughout Western Canada, for over 30 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With more than 30 years of Rural Water Treatment experience and proven solutions, tens of thousands of satisfied customers, a written Product Performance Guarantee, and a 6-month Trial Offer ... you can be assured that there is absolutely NO RISK in trying an Aztec system to solve your water problems.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">There is no other company like Aztec, that specializes exclusively in Rural Water Treatment. Our systems are designed and built to last for over 20 years, and are all patented products, available only through us. We are truly the best at what we do, without exception!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Because all of our systems are installed on a 6-month trial basis, we won\'t install anything, unless we are confident that it will work.&nbsp; We have trained Rural Water Specialists, who carry portable labs, and will come out at your request, to do a full inspection of your water supply and perform multi-parameter tests.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">If we can help you, we will give you a written proposal and a quote for you to base a decision on. There is no charge for this service, so you have absolutely nothing to lose.&nbsp; Trust Aztec for the highest quality products and service ... if we can\'t fix your water problems, nobody can!<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
