(1043, 1, 'B-Con Engineering inc', 'sales@bconeng.com', '14 Capella Crt, NEPEAN, Ontario , Canada', 'www.bconeng.com ', '(613) 727-0021', '(613) 727-0493', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B-Con Engineering is a progressive optics manufacturing company producing aspheric, diamond turned, freeform, plastic optics, and using advanced metrology techniques to provide some of the world\'s most advanced optical components and optical systems. Cutting-Edge Optics, High Technology Applications, B-Con serves the optics design, prototyping and manufacturing needs of numerous high technology industries, including:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Aerospace<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Military<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Automotive<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Display Technology<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Biotechnology<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Acting as a sub-contractor to many of the world\'s leading companies in these industries, and with many links to the Academic community, B-Con works on the cutting edge of modern optics technology. B-Con components are currently being used on some very high profile projects, including:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Phoenix Mars Mission,optics within the light detection and ranging (LIDAR) instrumentation. The recently launched Phoenix will land on Mars in May 2008 to study the history of water on the planet in all its phases.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Global Imagination Magic Planet B-Con\'s optics comprise the projection lens system for Magic Planet\'s spherical format projection.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1044, 1, 'B I Logistics Services Inc.,', 'bilsicustoms@bilsi.com', '4050A Sladeview Cres., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.bilsi.com ', '(905) 606-2222', '(905) 606-2250', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">BILSI is a privately held licensed customs broker, freight forwarder and logistics provider. We firmly believe that we must provide the best in class service therefore we constantly strive to add value to the relationship with our clients. We are continually searching for ways to improve our efficiency and our service offering. The basic principles under which BILSI operates is as follows:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will work as a team to deliver the best possible solution and service<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will respect every client\'s confidentiality<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will ensure our clients and our company are in a compliance position<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will not compromise the financial position of our clients or our company<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will always have open communications<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will always deliver what we promise<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1045, 1, 'B&H Wholesalers Ltd.', 'bhwholesalers@eastlink.ca', '802 Main St, KINGSTON,, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.bhwholesalers.com ', '(902) 765-2272', '(902) 765-2552', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For All Your Industrial &amp; Safety Needs!\'<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Located at 1530 Bridge Street in Kingston, you will find the best little safety shop in the valley. Locally owned and operated since 1999, B &amp; H Wholesalers have been your &ldquo;One Stop Safety Shop&rdquo;&nbsp; for quality work wear and industrial supplies. B &amp; H not only services the Western Annapolis Valley and around the South Shore, we have customers all over the Atlantic Provinces.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B &amp; H pride ourselves in our exceptional customer service. We live by our #1 rule, &ldquo;If we don&rsquo;t take care of our customers, someone else will!&rdquo;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1046, 1, 'B.C. Greenhouse Builders Co. Ltd.', 'Inquiries@bcgreenhouses.com', 'A5 - 19327 - 94th Ave, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.bcgreenhouses.com ', '(604) 882-8408', '(604) 882-8491', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We understand that it can be challenging to see quality online when it comes to greenhouses. Many structures look similar. We are North American made, maintenance free and designed so that the average homeowner can build the greenhouse.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our structures are typically 30-50% heavier than our competition. Our aluminum extrusions are substantial and our corner posts and purlins are designed to withstand the heaviest winds and snow loads. You can put a 50 pound hanging basket on every roof bar! Simply put, this greenhouse will not blow over in the wind or degrade after only a few years. Our greenhouses are passed down through family members and we are proud of that.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a custom greenhouse manufacturer and that means if you need the greenhouse altered in any way, we can do it.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our standard greenhouses are rated for 85 mph winds and 30 psf for snow.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1047, 1, 'B.G. Roberts Chemicals Inc.', 'bgr@bgr.ca', '282 Southgate Dr., BEDFORD, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.bgr.ca ', '(902) 456-0530', '(902) 835-1525', '', '<p>Environmental Products and Services&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Industry sector market interests:</p>\r\n<p>Environment</p>\r\n<p>Manufacturing</p>\r\n<p>Medical/Biotechnology/Chemical</p>\r\n<p>Mining/Petroleum/Gas</p>\r\n<p>Service Industry</p>', ''),
(1048, 1, 'Babin Ironworks', 'service@babinironworks.com', '208 Margaret Dr., NORTH BAY, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.babinironworks.com ', '(705) 580-4766', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;We, at Babin Ironworks, understand that our work will be around for a very long time and examined by many. We are proud men of steel and also know that every piece of wrought iron we build has the potential to send new and repeat customers our way so we make sure we get it right. Steel is one of the most versatile and enduring materials in existence. Wroughtiron originally meant working iron and alloys into useful works. This was done by hand and required skill and imagination. Today wrought iron means a whole lot more; more materials to work with like aluminum and copper as examples; better tools (like CNC) and equipment, but one thing has remained and that is the ingenious craftsman and artist who brings basic metal shapes into wonderful craftsmenship construction that are strong, long lived while adding beauty and value. Wrought iron fences, fencing, fence, gates, gate operators, manual automatic, balconies, juliet (or juliette) balcony, railings, stair railing, rails, staircases, spiral staircase, gazebos, gazebo tops, arbours, arbors, arbour arbor, pergolas, pergola columns, posts, furniture (like beds, bed frames, headboard, footboard) are but a small list of common art installed in communities all over the world. We say art because a well designed wrought iron piece built with the right materials will draw comments and opinions for decades and even centuries. Give us a call today to discuss your project - 1-705-580-4766 (IRON) or toll free at 1-855-456-4766 (IRON). Whether you are a contractor, builder, architect, home owner, business owner, commercial, institutional or residential customer, we\'d love to hear from you. You can also email us at service@babinironworks.com - feel free to browse our site and check out our service area, about us, contact us and disclaimer pages for some information on steelwork (steel work) and to get inspired through our inspirational galleries.! Serving North Bay, Sturgeon Falls, Sudbury, Mattawa, South River, Muskoka, Gravenhurst, Bracebridge, Barrie, Vaughn, Mississauga, Toronto, Hamilton and all points in between.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1049, 1, 'Bakerview Forest Products Inc.', 'gkump@bvfp.com', '105-20120 Stewart Cres, MAPLE RIDGE, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.bvfp.com ', '(604) 460-6333', '(604) 460-6303', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Delivering customer expectations with honesty and integrity is the central precept of our company.&nbsp; We view our suppliers, customers and employees as long term partners and believe that our own company&rsquo;s success is founded in assisting them to be successful.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The origins of both Bakerview Forest Products Inc. and the former Pat Power Forest Products Corp. date back to 1980 when each company began their businesses in the wholesale of Western Red Cedar.Over the past 3 decades as the forest industry evolved, so did each respective company, to include the business functions of re-manufacturing and distribution, and additionally adding a variety of different wood species to the product line.&nbsp; While Western Red Cedar remains a focal point of the company we further specialize in a variety of softwood species (DFir, Yellow Cedar, Hemlock, Pine, SPF) and coastal hardwood&rsquo;s.In 2007 in response to changing coastal industry and the secession desires of their founders (Vern Friesen and Pat Power) Bakerview and Pat Power Forest merged to the company that now carries on as Bakerview Forest Products Inc.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1050, 1, 'Balo Industries', 'balonova1935@gmail.com', '1640, 31 Ave NW, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.baloindustries.ca ', '(403) 284-2353', '(403) 289-7191', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Balo Industries was formed in 1960 to manufacture high quality solid brass fishing spoons for the sport fishing markets in Canada and the United States. The fishing spoons feature a high lustre finish available in ten different designs and numerous colour combinations. In addition to the various spoons, Balo Industries manufactures and supplies a wide variety of other sport fishing tackle for game fish<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Currently, distribution is handled through wholesale distributors, jobbers and large volume buyers with sales in Japan, the United States, Australia, Norway, Sweden, and New Zealand. EU Countries<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Balo Industries is interested in establishing manufacturing, warehousing or distribution facilities in the United States and Europe. Balo Industries welcomes joint venture opportunities and foreign investment negotiations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1051, 1, 'Barbarian Rugby Wear Inc.', 'customerservice@barbarian.com', '575 Trillium Dr., KITCHENER, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.barbarian.com', '(519) 895-1932', '(519) 895-0988', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Barbarian Sports Wear, Inc. is a Canadian Manufacturer of Classic heavy weight cotton rugby jerseys and Casual light weight rugby jerseys. We also make PRO-fit performance rugby shirts and shorts and Sublimation rugby shirts and shorts for game play.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All of our cotton rugby jerseys and shorts and performance rugby shirts and shorts are made in Canada using US cotton and polyester.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">If you have a World Rugby Fan or a North American Rugby Player in your life you may be looking for rugby jerseys or rugby shorts to give as a gift. If you are looking for something different, Barbarian Rugby Wear, Inc. can suggest a number of fashion rugby apparel gift ideas. Check out our store for Men&rsquo;s and Women&rsquo;s Rugby apparel gift suggestions.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1052, 1, 'BarretteWood Inc.', 'benoit.barrette@ebarrette.com', '583 Du Grand Bernier Rd N, SAINT-JEAN-SUR-RICHELIEU, Quebec, Canada', 'www.builtbybarrette.com ', '(450) 357-7000', '(450) 357-7050', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Barrette has been led by the same family for three generations. Started in 1963 from a sawmill in Chapais and lumber yard in Laval, both in Quebec, it is one of the largest manufacturers of wood and vinyl products for the construction industry and the Outdoor Living Products customers in North America. Doing what others pretend impossible, enjoying pushing limits and confronting every challenge with ingenuity. Committed people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is Barrette.</p>', ''),
(1053, 1, 'Bay City Marine Limited', 'sales@baycitymarine.ca', '136 Hester St., HAMILTON, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.baycitymarine.ca ', '(905) 574-1222', '(905) 574-4803', '', '<p>Here at Bay City Marine we are dedicated to great customer service! Family owned and operated since 1968 we can offer the expertise and products that will make your boating experience fantastic.</p>\r\n<p>With your choice of outboard and the best fishing boats by Lund or Triton your package can be made to order.</p>', ''),
(1054, 1, 'BB Impex', 'info@bbimpex.com', '507-15 Wertheim Crt, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.bbimpex.com ', '(905) 886-3373', '(905) 886-3353', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are in the diamond jewelry business for over 10 years and bring with us a vast amount of professional expertise to the online world. Our operations span many countries of the world and our products have been well accepted with our customers. This year we have brought our range of products to the internet world and are working hard to make it a preferred destination for online buyers by providing them be best shopping experience.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Customer Service team will always be available to help you before or after the purchase. You can always contact us by sending us an email by clicking the contact Us link at the bottom. Click here to meet BB Impex staff.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Philosophy:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our motto is to provide jewelry and services to our customers and achieve 100% customer satisfaction. Anything less than 100% will not satisfy us. We wish to provide our customers a risk-free shopping experience and will gladly take back any order within 30 days of purchase Please see our Returns policy for more details.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We strive hard to build trust with our customers. And that trust can only be built by delivering more than we promise. Our intention is to provide as much information about our products as necessary to enable you to make an informed purchase decision.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Product:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We take pride in selecting contemporary designs for our product range. We import the best of designs from around the world and often get the jewelry made to our designs and are thus able to offer you the cream of the crop. We strive to bring designer jewelry at value prices.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We do not sell gold plate, all designs are made in fine quality real 10K, 14 K or 18K gold (yellow or white). We do not sell imitation jewelry. We use good quality diamonds which are great value for money. Full specifications of each item on this site is provided so that you can take an informed purchase decision.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1055, 1, 'BCIT - School of Transportation', 'mary_jane_stenberg@bcit.ca', '3700 Willingdon Ave, BURNABY, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.bcit.ca/transportation', '(604) 432-8543', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">BCIT\'s School of Transportation is a North American leader in transportation training, producing the high quality, job ready graduates in demand by the Aerospace, Marine, Motive and Rail sectors. Strategically located directly at the Asia Pacific Gateway, the School of Transportation delivers accredited and globally recognized programs tailored to meet the human capital needs of the transportation industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether you are planning your future as a commercial pilot or a ship\'s officer, an auto service technician or a commercial transport mechanic, BCIT\'s School of Transportation is your best choice. For a career in the Transportation Industry, BCIT works!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1056, 1, 'BDC Aero Industrie Inc.', 'humberto@puma-aircraft.com', '496 De L\'Aeroparc Blvd , LACHUTE,, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.puma-aircraft.com ', '(514) 581-5577', '(514) 227-5089', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Are you looking for an airplane that allows real cross country flights in comfort? Do you want to operate from short fields with confidence?<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The PUMA will fulfill your expectations!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The PUMA is made by composite and aluminum material. The fuselage has a unique design, its interior has plenty of room and the ergonomic dashboard makes it really stand out, not to mention the aircraft&rsquo;s large doors and high clearance under the wings.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Attention to detail and flowing body lines give this airplane an excellent performance in its category.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Safe, easy and pleasant to fly, a real trainer, simple to maintain and to build, high quality at competitive cost: these qualities make the PUMA a great aircraft.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Recognized for being ideal for recreational flying as well as flight training, the PUMA is designed with three very important factors in mind: safety, comfort, and performance. Be amazed by flying in a PUMA!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Order your Puma Today!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Puma Ready to Fly<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">(call for a details quote)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Standard Puma features:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Rotax 912 80hp UL <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Electric Flap<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Electric trim elevator<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In dash VHF Radio ICOM 210<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Standard 90L gas tank.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Upholstery in Super Leather and ergonomic seat<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Matco USA wheels and brakes - toe or hand operated<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Aeronautical tires<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All metal surfaces are primed inside out, and where is possible, powdered for an extreme weather durability.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Rear seats baggage compartment with foldable seats system.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1057, 1, 'Beach Point Processing Co.', 'info@beachpoint.ca', '2144 Hwy. 330, CLARKS HARBOUR, Nova Scotia, Canada', '', '(902) 745-3159', '(902) 745-1753', '', '<p>Seafood Product Preparation &amp; Packaging</p>\r\n<div>Fish, Salted and/or Dried&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1058, 1, 'Bear Woods Supply Co. Inc.', 'info@woodparts.ca', '139 Bonaventure St, CORNWALLIS, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.woodparts.ca ', '(902) 638-8622', '(902) 638-8637', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">WEED PARTS<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We supply a wide range of wooden dowels and rods, fluted dowel pins, wood toy wheels, toy parts and game pieces, toy car plans, Shaker pegs, wood ball knobs and turned knobs, furniture spindles and finials, wood mushroom buttons and plugs, round and split balls, blocks and squares, beads and spools, wood hearts and star cut-outs, wood candle cups and much more<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CLOCK PARTS<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mini quartz clock movements and fit-ups, pendulum and chime clock movements, tide movements, clock dials and faces, clock inserts sizes ranging from 1-7/16&quot; to 8-1/2&quot;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">HARDWARE<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Lazy Susan bearings, box hinges, scroll saw blades, sanding belts and discs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">PICTURE HANGERS<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Strap picture hangers, d-ring picture hangers, sawtooth picture hangers, nailess picture hangers, plastic coated stainless steel picture wire, screweyes and cup hooks.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ERGONOMIC COMPUTER FURNITURE HARDWARE<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Underdesk Compx ErgonomX computer keyboard arms, computer keyboard trays, computer CPU holders and monitor arms.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1059, 1, 'Beaver Plastics Ltd.', 'techsupport@beaverplastics.com', '7 - 26318 Township Rd 531 A, ACHESON, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.beaverplastics.com', '(780) 962-4433', '(780) 962-4640', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our front line service starts with our telephone reception that has real people on between 8:30 AM and 4:30 PM MST. Our customers tell us that our telephone reception and personal customer services are second to none.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We service our clients from our own plants in Canada and Mexico, along with our affiliated EPS producers, distributors and agents, manufacturing and supplying products from the Atlantic to the Pacific.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Have a look around our website; there are some exciting things happening here at Beaver Plastics! We look forward to answering your questions and perhaps working together on your product development project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
