(1083, 1, 'Bradshaw Iron Works Ltd.', 'Biwaccounting@gmail.com', '14255 McKenney Rd., WELLAND, Ontario, Canada', 'www.bradshawiron.com ', '(905) 384-9138', '(905) 384-2344', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hello and welcome to Bradshaw Iron Works. Here you will find information about us and the work that we do. You will also find links to other sites and pictures of past and current projects that we are working on.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1084, 1, 'Brendan Wood International', 'mail@brendanwood.com', '15 Prince Arthur Ave, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.brendanwood.com ', '(416) 924-8110', '(416) 924-2293', '', '<p>&nbsp;Brendan Wood International (BWI) is a leading provider of strategic intelligence to financial institutions and corporations active in the capital markets. Headquartered in Toronto Canada, BWI covers the global markets and has pioneered a forensic investigative technique to examine capital market transactions and relationships in a conclusive deal by deal, client by client methodology. BWI has been providing its clients with specialized capital market expertise through reports and customized consulting services since 1970.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1085, 1, 'BSF International Inc', 'info@bsfinc.ca', '297 Labrosse Ave, POINTE-CLAIRE, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.bsfinc.ca ', '(514) 428-1234', '(514) 428-1230', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canadian Distributor of Portable Cooling Units designed for use where conventional air conditioning is cost prohibitive, not feasible, impractical, or unavailable. B.S.F.Inc. is a distributor of bolts,screws,studs,nuts,valves, bushings,sleeves,pins and a complete range of machined componets for the aerospace,defence and electronics industries. B.S.F. Inc. also distributes a range of non-ferrous alloys in sheet,plate,tubing,pipe and bar.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1086, 1, 'Buchner Manufacturing Inc.', 'info@buchnermfg.com', '30004 Highway 48, PEFFERLAW, Ontario , Canada', 'www.buchnermfg.com ', '(705) 437-1734', '(705) 437-4476', '', '<p>&nbsp;We manufacture aluminum eavestrough (gutters), downspouts, soffit, fascia, aluminum coils, and sell vinyl siding, caulking, fasteners, rollforming machinery, brake presses. Many of these products are also available in steel. Canada\'s most complete line of aluminum building products.</p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br />\r\n</span></div>', ''),
(1087, 1, 'Buffalo Jump Consulting', 'danbeavon@rogers.com', '6099 Rivercrest Dr., ORLEANS, Ontario, Canada', '', '(613) 841-1983', '', '', '<p>The company specializes in demographic and statistical data analysis, research, program evaluation, and training. The principal focus is on Aboriginal issues within Canada.</p>', ''),
(1088, 1, 'Building Professionals Inc', 'rdalgleish@buildingprofessionals.com', '410-250 McDermont Ave, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.buildingprofessionals.com', '(204) 956-5888', '(204) 956-5819', '', '<p>&nbsp;At Building Professionals, we&rsquo;re committed to helping builders build a better world. We do this by providing technical expertise, advice and consulting services to the building and construction industries. So while we may not physically raise the beams or pour the concrete, we can supply the tools to improve every aspect of how our clients operate.</p>\r\n<p>We Build Confidence: By developing and managing industry and manufacturer based site quality assurance programs and developing standards</p>\r\n<p>We Build Professionals: By developing and managing certification, credentialing and accreditation programs</p>\r\n<p>We Build Industries: By supplying high quality management and administration services for trade associations</p>\r\n<p>We Build Value: By providing expert consulting and industry support services fostering research, better building codes and technology transfer</p>\r\n<p>Our services include:</p>\r\n<p>Quality assurance program design, development and delivery</p>\r\n<p>Personnel certification implementation and delivery</p>\r\n<p>Standards and specifications development</p>\r\n<p>Project management for industry research</p>\r\n<p>Building Code consulting</p>\r\n<p>Warranty programs design, development, implementation and delivery</p>\r\n<p>Contractor and manufacturer accreditation and credentialing design, development and delivery</p>\r\n<p>Management of field audits programs</p>\r\n<p>Association consulting</p>\r\n<p>Association management</p>\r\n<p>Association marketing services</p>\r\n<p>To download further information on our full services available, please click on the document below.</p>\r\n<p>Building Professionals &ndash; Helping You Build Your Industry</p>', ''),
(1089, 1, 'Burleigh Bros. Seafood Ltd.', 'tom@burleigh.pe.ca', '224 Burleigh Rd, ELLERSLIE, Prince Edward Island, Canada', 'www.burleigh.pe.ca ', '(902) 831-2349', '(902) 831-3072', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Seafood Product Preparation and Packaging</span></p>', ''),
(1090, 1, 'Burrard Wood Manufacturing Ltd.', 'burrardwood@shaw.ca', '382 Esplanade E., NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.burrard.info ', '(604) 987-1718', '(604) 987-6588', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are the leading manufacturer of Solid Wood awards in Western Canada. We produce a full line of stock, catalog items, including Walnut, Oak, &amp; Maple: Plaques, trophies, cupbases, clocks , &amp; desk accessories.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We also are able to manufacture a wide variety of custom items in either solid wood, or MDF (Fiberboard). We use high-tech equipment including CNC routering, and pride ourselves in being able to manufacture a quality product, at a reasonable price, on time, all the time. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1091, 1, 'Burton Food Safety Solutions', 'sales1@burtonsoftware.com', '6255 Jade Crt, RICHMOND, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.burtonsoftware.com ', '(604) 231-1650', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Burton Software specializes in building software applications to automate business processes. Burton Software was founded in 1999 by Steven Burton, and is based in Richmond, BC. The company has grown steadily over the years and earned a reputation for product quality and service excellence across a broad range of industries. Burton Software has developed applications for large and small organizations in the energy, finance, education, business intelligence, and marketing sectors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Icicle is the award-winning food safety management system that makes it easy to create and manage internationally compliant HACCP food safety programs, reducing costs by up to 50%.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Icicle ensures your food safety program meets current legislation requirements and is being implemented consistently across multiple facilities while keeping your documentation safe, centralized, and up to date. You will always be ready for audits, even unannounced ones. Audit outcomes will be much improved too, reducing the risk of recalls and penalty charges. Having a high quality, internationally recognized food safety program in place will give you a competitive edge and facilitate expansion into new markets<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1092, 1, 'Business Round Table', 'rick@businessroundtable.ca', '37 Chandler Cres., MONCTON, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.businessroundtable.ca ', '(506) 857-8177', '(506) 387-7701', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Entrepreneurs and small business owners join Business Round Table where they are placed in a group with about 10 others, carefully selected so there are no conflicts of interest. They sign a Confidentiality Contract promising never to disclose anything discussed within their group. Each group meets once a month for about three hours, following a structured format, and using the collective wisdom of the group, the members help each other solve problems, prevent mistakes and maximize their opportunities. They act as each other&rsquo;s Personal Board of Directors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Business Round Table started in Moncton twenty-three years ago. At present there are more than 100 members. There are 6 BRT groups in Moncton and 4 in Vancouver. Expansion plans are to take BRT right across Canada and throughout the USA. Franchises have been established in British Columbia and others are available. Expansion into the U.S.A. is now ready to roll-out. Membership is open to entrepreneurs (those who have a financial interest in a business and are involved in the management of it).<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1093, 1, 'Butler Buildings (Canada)', 'CARegion@butlermfg.com', '21-3070 Mainway Dr., BURLINGTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.butlermfg.com ', '(905) 332-7786', '(905) 332-6260', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: MuseoSlab500, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px;\">Butler Manufacturing&trade; is a building-solutions company providing the design, manufacture, and marketing of metal building systems for commercial construction. Our systems play a part in buildings within the commercial, community, industrial, and agricultural markets. And with services such as BlueScope Construction, Butler goes beyond the manufacture of steel building systems by offering full-service turnkey construction solutions.</span></p>', ''),
(1094, 1, 'Buy Canadian First', 'info@buycanadianfirst.ca', '19 Aumais St, NOTRE-DAME-DE-L\'ILE-PERROT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.buycanadianfirst.ca ', '(514) 425-5999', '(514) 425-3999', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Launched in 2008, our mission is to promote Canadian companies, their services and the products they make right here at home. We are not an online store and no purchases can be made on the site. We simply direct consumers to points-of-purchase (either online or in brick-and-mortar stores) where they can find Canadian-made products and services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This current version of the website was launched in June 2014 and is still in BETA mode while we pretty it up. :-)<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1095, 1, 'BVL Controls Ltd.', 'salesrep@bvlcontrols.com', '661, rue de la Sabliere, BOIS-DES-FILION, Quebec, Canada', 'www.bvlcontrols.com ', '(450) 965-0502', '(450) 965-8751', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established for 30 years in beverage control systems and the manufacture of cooling units.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B.V.L. Controls stands out by the range of products it offers, after-sales service and the constant evolution to remain at the forefront of technology.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B.V.L. Controls promote its products with distributors across Canada, the United States and Mexico.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical support is offered to our clients by the visit of a technician or by phone call.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Our quality service and our satisfied customers make us a company you can trust.</span></p>', ''),
(1096, 1, 'BW Manufacturing', 'bwmfg@bellnet.ca', '37 Mill St, ELMIRA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(519) 669-4719', '(519) 669-0730', '', '<p>&nbsp;BW Manufacturing is a custom metal fabrication shop. We specialize in shearing, forming, machining, milling and welding of mild steel and stainless steel.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1097, 1, 'Bystat International Inc', 'static@bystat.com', '2630 Sabourin St, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.bystat.com ', '(514) 333-8880', '(450) 218-2825', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 1983, Bystat had the mission to become a major player in the ESD world. Today we offer an extensive range of products which form your front line defence in the war against ESD.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Bystat is recognized for its flexibility, its innovation and its capability to find or develop your most discriminating demands. Our line of products is one of the most complete in the marketplace. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">It is split in ten families of products as follows: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Personal Protection: Wrist straps, Heel grounders and Conductive garments <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Workstation products: Mats &amp; runners, Floor antifatigue mats, Grounding accessories, PVC &amp; rubber mats <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Chemicals Products: Paint, Floor Maintenace, Cleaners and Hand lotion <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Packaging: Sheilding Bags, Films &amp; tubings, Shipping containers, Conductive &amp; dissipative foams <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Flooring: Conductive &amp; dissipative tiles and sheeting, Clean room floor, Conductive glue <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Office: Binders, Page protectors, Dissipative papers, Tape &amp; Labels <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Handling &amp; Storage: Cabinets, Bins, PCB handling, Tote boxes, Storage box <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Ionization: Guns, blowers &amp; bars for electronics &amp; clean room application, Industrial guns &amp; bars <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Test &amp; Measurement Equipment: Grounding testers, Audit kits, Field &amp; Resistance testers, Monitoring &amp; Simulators <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">- Ergonomic Equipment: Workbenches, ESD chairs, Carts &amp; Cabinets, Vacuum sealers&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1098, 1, 'Byte Craft Limited', 'info@bytecraft.com', '213-55 Northfield Dr E , WATERLOO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.bytecraft.com ', '5198849660', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Byte Craft Limited specializes in embedded system software development tools for single-chip microcontrollers. We provide innovative solutions for developers, consultants, and manufacturers around the world. Our main products are C cross-compilers targeted to a variety of microcontroller families.</p>', ''),
(1099, 1, 'Bytown Consulting', 'rostum@bytownconsulting.com', '94 Maple Lane, OTTAWA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.bytownconsulting.com ', '(613) 749-8629', '(613) 749-4045', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Bytown Consulting is a management consulting firm based in Ottawa and registered in Ontario, Canada. Our management team, together with our partners, offer national and international multilingual services for clients in public sector and private organizations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a full-service firm, offering innovative solutions to meet our clients\' needs, from front-end planning to policy and program implementation and review.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We have been privileged to lead interesting projects for over twenty years. For questions about our services and capabilities, please send us a message or call us.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1100, 1, 'Busque et Laflamme inc.', 'genevieve.gagne@boisch.com', '52, route du Lac-Poulin , SAINT-BENOIT-LABREda, Quebec, Canadaa', '', '(418) 484-2888', '(418) 484-5659', '', '<p>&nbsp;Saw Mills</p>', ''),
(1101, 1, 'C\'est Danine Designs', 'danine123@hotmail.com', '3228 Winchester Rd, REGINA, Saskatchewan, Canada', 'www.cestdaninedesigns.com ', '(306) 352-6430', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Danine Schlosser graduated from the renowned, Academie des arts et du design in Montreal, Quebec and returned to her hometown, Regina, Saskatchewan to establish her own label, C\'est Danine Designs. Danine Schlosser with her Mom, Marie, designs and creates elegant one-of-a-kind gowns for brides, mother-of-the bride, graduations or any special occasion.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">C\'est Danine Designs provides individualized service that includes generation of the design, cutting of the pattern, and selection of the fabric; stages leading to the creation of the exquisite and unique gowns her clients envisioned for that special occasion. Travels for Danine, are an opportunity to find the right fabric to make her clients\' dream dress come to life.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1102, 1, 'C-I-L Explosives', 'reception@cilexplosives.com', '533 D\'Argenteuil Ave, LACHUTE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.cilexplosives.com ', '(450) 566-0655', '(450) 566-0677', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">C-I-L has served industry with explosives for 140 years. The tradition continues with specialty explosives for every need. Police, military, industry and even entertainment people trust our products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Suspension on the use of C-I-L Classic Snowlaunchers lifted as of Sept 2014-09-1.We recuperate and recycle track torpedoes. We recuperate and recycle marine signals. We recuperate and recycle highway flares.Our team is specialized in explosives and we have several years of experience in that area. We offer consulting services for your custom applications.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1103, 1, 'C&C Aviation', 'ccaviation@shaw.ca', '42212 Keith Wilson Rd, CHILLIWACK, British Columbia, Canada', 'members.shaw.ca', '(604) 795-0911', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">QUALITY ASSURANCE <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We develop your Quality Assurance program to meet your specific operation, with custom audit sheets . <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AUDITS <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Being knowledgeable in the Canadian Aviation regulations allows us to perform Independent, confidential Approved Maintenance Organization (AMO) and Air Operator (AO) audits, surveillances while understanding the operational requirements of your company. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MD-M SERVICES <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ministerial Delegation by Transport Canada to issue certificates of Airworthiness for the import and export of aircraft. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Full import and export services for your Aircraft or Helicopter. With our prepared package we can make it a seamless operation for the most inexperienced importer. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">MANUALS <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether you want a new AMO or just need an independent review of your existing manual we can do it all, from an amendment to complete package with all the forms and documents you need and training if required to cement it all together. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TRANSPORTATION and LOGISTICS <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are fully equipped with tools, support equipment, storage facility, cargo nets A-Frames, Trucks with either open soft ride flat decks open or enclosed trailers ranging for 16&rsquo; to 35&rsquo;. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AVIATION CONSULTING <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Movies - supplying parts and knowledge <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Financial Institutions - asset disposal and receivership contracts <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Insurance Companies &ndash; aircraft recovery, technical witness <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Educational Institutes &ndash; long standing supplier to colleges <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Aviation consultant in aircraft maintenance and maintenance policys manuals <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Rotary and Fixed wing&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1104, 1, 'C.C. Industries Ltd.', 'ccindustries.c@shawbiz.ca', '2229 Knell Rd E, PRINCE GEORGE, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.ccindustries.net ', '(250) 962-9683', '(250) 962-5042', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">C.C. Industries, for the past 30 years, has been serving British Columbia and Alberta Pulp Mills, Sawmills, and Mining Industries with our various metal fabricating services<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">C.C. Industries manufacturing plant of over 25,000 sq. ft. is the largest sheet metal shop north of Vancouver BC.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We pride ourselves on the quality workmanship in making all our aluminum Truck Accessories<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1105, 1, 'C.H. Robinson Project Logistics Ltd.', 'bruce.jantzie@chrobinson.com', '102-6715 8th St NE, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', 'www.chrprojectlogistics.com ', '(403) 295-1505', '(403) 444-9365', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our reliable staff specializes in complex logistics for global project freight forwarding. We\'re experts in transporting cargo for the oil and gas, mining, energy, North American wind farm, EPCM and high value, over dimensional machinery industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ur people, processes, and technology improve the world\'s transportation and supply chains, delivering exceptional value to our customers and suppliers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With today\'s global sourcing options, you may be transporting multiple orders from many origins to the site. Deep transportation knowledge can preempt problems that could cause delays and costly fines.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We really can move just about anything. But don\'t take our word for it. Look at some of the project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1106, 1, 'C.V. Logistic Inc.', 'dispatch@cvlog.com', '208-399 de la Grande Cote Rd, ROSEMERE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.cvlog.com ', '(450) 965-1045', '(450) 621-2092', '', '<p>We reduce the logistics cost associated with material purchases in their supply chain.</p>\r\n<p>We help companies cost-compare buying opportunities by designing and pricing out delivery solutions for both International and Domestic shipments.</p>', ''),
(1107, 1, 'C2 Imaging LLC.', 'mark.stahr@c2imaging.com', '14291 Burrows Rd, RICHMOND, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.c2imaging.com ', '(604) 270-4000', '(604) 270-8517', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Vomela. Let&rsquo;s talk possibilities!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For printing companies, there&rsquo;s a fine line between being too big and too small. One is impersonal, the other simply can&rsquo;t handle much. Vomela is the best of both worlds. We are large enough to handle jobs of any size&mdash;anywhere, anytime&mdash;with the speed and price you need. But we&rsquo;re local enough to remember your name, get personally invested in solving your challenges, and break into huge smiles when you love your finished product. Vomela is an industry-leading print conglomerate, with some of the most advanced capabilities around. But what we really are is all about you. We speak your language and help you reach your goals.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1108, 1, 'C2C Uniforms', 'vince@c2cuniforms.com', '2450 Cohen St , SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.c2cuniforms.com ', '(514) 745-3384', '(514) 664-5966', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">C2C Uniforms was founded in 2011 via a consolidated group of uniform companies.&nbsp; Recognized as one of Canada\'s leading manufacturers, distributors and importers of uniform apparel, we provide uniform solutions for: police, security, paramedics, corporate wear clients and most recently QSR uniforms, hotel and hospitality apparel and work wear.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our expert management team with over thirty years experience are well equipped and knowledgeable in leading industry standards of design and development, manufacturing, sales and logistics.&nbsp; We are always on hand to discuss your uniform requirements by providing you with tailor made options that meet your budget and offer complete satisfaction.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our customized programs range from tactical wear to corporate wear- the options are endless.&nbsp; Your company&rsquo;s image is extremely important to us. Our clients range from publicly traded companies, non-profit organizations to small and mid-size companies North American wide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We insist on quality products with competitive pricing and provide this by combining overseas production with domestic manufacturing to control cost and always meet our client&rsquo;s demand.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1109, 1, 'Cabco West Limited', 'info@cabcowest.com', '8684 Lochside Dr., NORTH SAANICH, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.cabcowest.com ', '(250) 655-3831', '(250) 655-1610', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1980 CABCO WEST LIMITED started to make cable assemblies for people who needed quality, serviceability, a solid guarantee, and products that meet their exact requirements. Many years and 1,200 different configurations later, our mission hasn&rsquo;t changed. We&rsquo;ve made assemblies from the very commonplace to the strange, weird and almost unbelievable. But that&rsquo;s what makes our customers happy, and makes us look forward to the next challenge.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We Design and Manufacture special assemblies geared to unique and unusual applications. Not only cables, but switch-boxes, patch panels and other custom hardware. We also assemble and do inter-cabinet harnessing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our Reputation springs from CABCO in-house expertise and quality products linked to specific customer needs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1110, 1, 'Cabinetmart Inc.', 'info@cabinetmart.com', '790 Little Grey St, London, Ontario, Canada', 'www.cabinetmart.com ', '(519) 679-1297', '(519) 679-2410', '', '<p>&nbsp;Distributor of cabinet hardware, kitchen cabinets, cabinet accessories and woodworking supplies to cabinetmakers, custom woodworkers, carpenters, renovators, do-it-yourselfers. Internet sales across North America. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1111, 1, 'Cabrelli Inc.', 'bags@cabrelli.net', '300-9200 Meilleur St, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.cabrelli.ca ', '(514) 384-4750', '(514) 382-9551', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether you choose an Olivia + Joy handbag; a wallet or briefcase from Cabrelli &amp; Co.; a travel organizer from Koltov; you are assured of quality and reliability backed by Cabrelli Inc., a trusted company since 1940.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cabrelli has remained committed to offering looks that emulate the sophistication and class associated with their brands, not just according to what\'s in vogue this season, but what will appeal to you throughout the years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Each collection stands on its own.&nbsp; The brands together represents the spectrum of fashion, each directed to a specific segment of the fashion market, always keeping in mind the ultimate user and their desire for fashion at a price.Cabrelli Inc. established in 1940 as a manufacturer of better quality non-leather handbags, has grown into an internationally recognized and respected distributor/wholesaler of fashion handbags, wallets and accessories. Cabrelli, always evolving with the changing times, expanded their product selection to include imported handbags. Today, all Cabrelli products are imported.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cabrelli products can be found in major fashion department stores, shoe chains, ready to wear stores and independent boutiques across Canada. Cabrelli Inc.&rsquo;s branded product lines include: CABRELLI &amp; CO. FASHION EXECUTIVES, CABRELLI &amp; CO. ACCESSORIES, KOLTOV, MULTISAC, OLIVIA + JOY, ZIPIT and our newest additions,C&amp;CO. and IMOSHION.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cabrelli Inc.\'s collections are made from synthetic materials, natural fibers and leather. Products range from everyday handbags and backpacks, to evening bags and lunch bags. Our products cover a wide range of price points; one that will surely satisfy you.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1112, 1, 'Cadex Electronics Inc.', 'info@cadex.com', '22000 Fraserwood Way, RICHMOND, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.cadex.com ', '(604) 231-7777', '(604) 231-7755', '', '<p>&nbsp;Cadex Electronics specializes in the design and manufacture of battery chargers and analyzers, as well as advanced rapid-test and monitoring systems. Cadex products are known for robust design, reliable service and long product life. Skilled engineers evaluate OEM opportunities, suggest possible simplifications by enabling new technology and offer competitive pricing. &ldquo;We built our products with one goal in mind &ndash; to get the most out of a battery,&rdquo; says CEO and founder Isidor Buchmann. The company accomplishes this with 30 years of experience and several patents on battery rapid-test technologies.</p>', ''),
(1113, 1, 'CAI Logistics', 'info@caigroup.ca', '1-50 Driscoll Cres , MONCTON, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.caigroup.ca ', '(506) 858-9963', '(506) 858-9903', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CAI Group is dedicated in offering our customers the best transportation service available because we know the importance of providing superior service. Our professional employees know the sense of urgency to deliver prompt services for your freight no matter how big or small.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From Domestic to International freight the CAI Group team of professionals are experts in providing creative and effective solutions in logistics, compliance and trade data management.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1114, 1, 'Canada West Shoe Manufacturing Inc.', 'info@canadawestboots.com', '1250 Fife St, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.canadawestboots.com ', '(204) 632-4110', '(204) 694-3831', '', '<p>&nbsp;Welt construction footwear- workboots, western boots and uniform footwear. Goodyear West construction -workboots and safety footwear (branded Canada West Boots) -Western Boots (branded Brahma and Bullrider) Goodyear Dept. Construction Uniform Boots for military, police, fire, paramedic and prison guards etc.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1115, 1, 'Canadex laboratories inc', 'fayez@canadexlabs.com', '707-725 Fortier Place, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.canadexlabs.com ', '(514) 978-4466', '(514) 747-7550', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canadex Laboratories was founded in 1990 in Quebec- Canada. Over the years the company has grown and became an important supplier of over-the-counter (OTC) medicines and vitamins supplements for large and small wholesalers and distributors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our ongoing mission has been to manufacture and market the best quality drugs and vitamins supplements by seeking to constantly innovate in terms of infrastructures and expertise, and providing excellent services to our customers by ensuring ongoing improvement, reliability and performance. The products we offer today have grown to cover most OTC and natural health products line, including our market leading VITADAY&reg; brands.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our pursuit of the best quality products is driven by the strictest manufacturing processes which meet or exceed all requirements as defined by Health Canada. We are focused on developing new speciality therapeutics that significantly improve patients outcomes.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1116, 1, 'Canadian Velvet Textiles', 'maha@superpufft.com', '880 Gana Crt., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.canadianvelvet.com', '(905) 564-1550', '(905) 564-1638', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">WE ARE MANUFACTURERS OF WARP KNITTED VELVET AND WOVEN JACQUARD VELVET USED FOR HOME FURNISHINGS AND CONTRACTS. WE ALSO CONVERT FLOCK VELVET INTO A VARIETY OF DESIGNS AND PRINTS. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">OUR PRIME MARKETS INCLUDE: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-EASTERN EUROPE, <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-MIDDLE EAST <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-SOUTH AMERICA. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">WE ARE OPEN TO NEW ALLIANCES FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1117, 1, 'Canfab Packaging Inc.', 'info@canfab.ca', '2740 Saint-Patrick St, Montreal, Quebec, Canada', 'www.canfabpkg.com ', '(514) 935-5265', '(514) 935-1074', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canfab Packaging Inc., established in 1936, is one of North America\'s largest specialty composite can manufacturers. Canfab has an outstanding reputation for quality products at competitive prices<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canfab&rsquo;s Sales staff is determined to help you find the right packaging product, designed and manufactured for your individual needs and specifications, complimenting your valuable product and thereby enhancing your sales<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Equipped with our own pressroom, we have the flexibility and comprehensive knowledge to manufacture numerous closures, ends, and custom made parts uniquely suited to satisfy you and the image you are projecting<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We, at Canfab will do everything within our means to ensure you receive the full benefit of our vast experience and exceptional customer service, from your first inquiry, through the design phase, to the delivery of your custom made composite can.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1118, 1, 'Caniwi Design', 'info@caniwi.net', '13 Welch Cres., OKOTOKS, Alberta, Canada', 'www.caniwi.net ', '(403) 774-9289', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Caniwi Design specializes in creating unique, interactive sites that promote your presence online. Strong branding, interest and ease of use are key factors that will make your website stand out. Let us know your wish list, design ideas and site requirements and we\'ll get back to you with options to meet your needs, wants and budget. We moved to New Zealand in the early 90s and spent almost 12 years enjoying the South Pacific before deciding to go back home to Okotoks in 2007. After 6 years in Canada, we are now back for good in Auckland because New Zealand is home for us!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are committed to working with you to ensure your website truly reflects who you are and what you can offer your clients. Caniwi will handle the technical side to ensure your site is quick to load, user friendly, code compliant, search engine accessible and works on a variety of platforms. Caniwi Design welcomes any enquiries into how our company can assist you with your Internet Presence. Please contact us for a FREE Initial Consultation to discuss your website requirements and design ideas. We are committed to customer service and want to make sure you are happy with all aspects of our service from start to finish.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1119, 1, 'Canmedical (Canada)', 'info@canmedical.ca', '173 Milsap Rd, YARKER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.canmedical.ca ', '(613) 358-5658', '(613) 358-5655', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From the minds of the decade&rsquo;s leading designers, Uno is a giant leap forward for veterinary small animal and equine digital radiography. A new starting point is needed. A fresh, new start at square one. That&rsquo;s why we invented Uno.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to canmedical.ca.&nbsp; For almost 25 years we have faithfully served the Canadian Veterinary community and are dedicated to what we do.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We specialize in digital ultrasound and radiography and feel quality products are of&nbsp;&nbsp; utmost importance.&nbsp; We supply cuattro DR systems for equine and small animals, as well as, Allpro Imaging CR systems.&nbsp; We are an authorized Tuttnauer sterilizer distributor.&nbsp; For platform scales, lift and operating tables we have chosen Technodyne for its&rsquo; superior performance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Service and support is top priority for us.&nbsp; Our service tech has over 30 years of experience and is factory trained on our ultrasound products.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1120, 1, 'Canus Plastics Inc.', 'info@canusplastics.com', '107-3030 Conroy Rd, OTTAWA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.canusplastics.com ', '(613) 232-2657', '(613) 232-6214', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canus has been manufacturing and selling quality plastic products in the Ottawa area for over 55 years. In fact, Canus was the first plastics company in the Ottawa area, and we continue to be a major player in the region&rsquo;s plastics industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We continue to evolve to meet the needs of the current market, and are well known for creating our own innovative custom products, such as bio-boxes and podiums. With so much experience in the plastics field, we are able to design and build almost any product that you can think of.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our staff is knowledgeable and experienced and will work with you from the original design through to the end result. We work hard to make sure your product meets your needs and exceeds your expectations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1121, 1, 'Canusa Wood Products Limited', 'canusa@canusawoodproducts.com', '203-1281 Georgia St W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.canusawoodproducts.com ', '(604) 687-2254', '(604) 682-4691', '', '<p>&nbsp;Originally Canusa Wood Products was the exclusive agent for four corporately related plywood and lumber mills in Malaysia and the Philippines. Today, the Vancouver based company has grown into one of North America&rsquo;s major importers of hardwood plywood, MDF and machined-to-pattern woods. With a current supply base of over 50 mills, Canusa has the global resources to supply a wide range of high quality materials for interior, exterior, marine and industrial applications. We have invested a significant amount of time working with suppliers and customers to acquire the specific knowledge of their relative businesses so that we can put it to work for you.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With a team that combines veteran experience and youthful enthusiasm, Canusa is able to offer the benefits of extensive knowledge and collective experience. Our ability to truly help our customers is a result of our relationships and product knowledge, and our ability to identify the appropriate specifications for the required application. It is important to us that we continue in our efforts to support our customers with great products that will fully satisfy their customers.</div>', ''),
(1122, 1, 'Canwest Aerospace Inc', 'info@canwestaerospace.com', '5225 216th St Hangar 10, LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.canwestaerospace.com ', '(604) 532-0322', '(604) 539-5592', '', '<p>CanWest Aerospace is a premiere independent aviation maintenance, repair and overhaul (MRO) provider in North America, successfully supporting helicopter and fixed-wing operators around the globe. With more than a decade of MRO experience, CanWest Aerospace holds approvals from Transport Canada (TC) and the European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) as an approved MRO provider; specializing in both helicopters and fixed-wing aircraft. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1123, 1, 'Caribou Clothes Ltd.', 'uibeljr@attglobal.net', 'Waterton Parks Hwy, MOUNTAIN VIEW, Alberta, Canada', 'www.caribouclothes.com ', '(403) 653-2353', '(403) 653-2974', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Caribou Clothes is located in the small hamlet of Mountain View, nestled in the foothills of Southern Alberta, Canada. From this hamlet comes distinctively unique, supple sheepskin accessories.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Each Caribou Clothes accessory, hand-tailored by skilled artisans, reflects our rustic area and has been styled for use in the &quot;now&quot; of today. The Caribou Clothes name is synonymous with top quality and value. Our handmade accessories are warm, long lasting and attractive&mdash;they make you look and feel your best.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1124, 1, 'Carmel Products Inc', 'info@carmelproducts.com', '10 Mount-Vernon Ave, LACHINE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.carmelproducts.com ', '(514) 489-7505', '(514) 489-7506', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Carmel Products Inc. is Canada\'s leading manufacturer and supplier of quality metal plant stands and bathroom accessories, and is based in Montreal, Quebec, Canada,. In addition to affordable plant stands, we also manufacture occasional furniture, giftware, and custom made stands and display racks. All of our products are 100% Canadian made, and all plant stands are welded and one piece with no assembly required.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established in 1957, Carmel Products was originally started as a small family business which has grown and expanded tremendously and can now 3 generations later, draw on over 50 years of experience in the industry in order to provide new innovative designs and a solid background. We have earned our strong reputation for the high quality and value of our merchandise and for servicing our customers and their specific needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Carmel Products currently sells to major chains as well as independents florists, nurseries, garden centers, and gift and variety stores throughout Canada, providing the public with a Canadian option to imports. We provide all of our clientele with the same high level of customer service. All of our products are made with top quality components and in accordance to our rigorous standards, ensuring their durability.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are always on the lookout to expand our horizons and client base and, with the advent of the technology, can now offer to service customers directly when our products are not available in local stores. We are also hoping to reach into new, untapped markets both in Canada and abroad and always welcome dealer inquiries as well as dynamic sales representatives to join our team and dealer network.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1125, 1, 'Cascade Aerospace Inc.', 'info@cascadeaerospace.com', '1337 Townline Rd, ABBOTSFORD, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.cascadeaerospace.com ', '(604) 850-7372', '(604) 557-2655', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cascade Aerospace Inc. began as a vision to build a world-class airplane repair station. The dream that inspired the vision began with Barry Marsden, Cascade\'s founder who got his pilot\'s license at 17 and thus began a life-long relationship with machines that fly. Marsden\'s love of flying led him to co-found Conair Group, a specialty aviation services firm, in 1969.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Conair\'s initial focus was aerial forest fire control. The experience acquired in developing specialty aviation products and operating and maintaining a fleet of 90 aircraft gave Conair the expertise required to offer third-party maintenance and modifications. That expertise inspired a more expansive vision. By 1993, Marsden, forward thinking about aviation - envisioned a new enterprise dedicated to providing third-party maintenance. That vision became a reality when Conair moved into a new, state-of-the-art, 230,000-square-foot facility in December 2000. In spring 2001, the third-party maintenance division became a separate company with a new name: Cascade Aerospace.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The passion and foresight that the founders brought to Cascade attracted other skilled and dedicated people to the company. The leadership team continued to diversify the company - entering into the military realm in 2005 when the company won its first contract with Canada\'s Department of National Defence for the total fleet management of Canada\'s fleet of C-130 Hercules tactical airlift aircraft.&nbsp; Today, Cascade Aerospace offers its services and products to aircraft operators around the world, and is partnered with some of the most respected OEMs in the global aerospace business.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1126, 1, 'Cascadia Metals', 'jamiem@cmetals.com', 'Eastern Access Rd and 33rd St E, BRANDON, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.cascadiametalsmb.com ', '(204) 728-9484', '(204) 727-3026', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cascadia Metals is a distribution centre with branches in Brandon and Winnipeg Manitoba. We offer a wide range of metal and steel products for the manufacturing industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We have direct contact with several steel mills, and offer very competitive pricing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Shipments can be made to your door via pre-arranged trucking or via our own trucks which deliver within a 200 mile radius of Brandon.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1127, 1, 'Cascadia Sport Systems Inc.', 'cascadia@direct.ca', '3012C Murray St, PORT MOODY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.cascadiasport.com ', '(604) 461-5208', '(604) 469-7278', '', '<p>Cascadia specialty contractor / supplier for sport and entertainment facilities. We offer support from design stage through to installation. Cascadia specializes in supply of products to gymnasium and arenas. Cascadia\'s two partners both offer over 30 years experience in the construction field. We have assembled the finest products and services available in our industry today.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1128, 1, 'Case-Tech Leather Inc.', 'sales@case-tech.com', '6-1100 Invicta Dr., OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.case-tech.com ', '(905) 842-8294', '(905) 842-7065', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a manufacturer of cases, straps and accessories for Land Mobile Portable Radios and similar carry cases for business and industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Because of our need for quality materials, we have complete leather finishing capabilities. We also do contract leather finishing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our special heavy duty stitching and cutting equipment is used for the manufacture of Police Duty gear.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1129, 1, 'CaseWare International Inc.', 'maureen.naughton@caseware.com', '469 King St W 2nd Floor, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.caseware.com ', '(416) 867-9504', '(416) 867-1906', '', '<p>&nbsp;Accountants and auditors in practices large and small, in corporations, and government recognize CaseWare International as the premier creator of assurance, reporting and analysis tools. CaseWare\'s family of products includes CaseWare Working Papers, CaseWare IDEA and CaseWare Time. These products are sold in over 60 countries with in excess of 200,000 users.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(1130, 1, 'CAST Safety Systems', 'castsafety@gmail.com', '362 Moffatt St, CARLETON PLACE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.castsafety.com/ ', '(613) 219-5129', '(613) 257-8395', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CAST Safety Systems (CAST) has been pioneering extraordinary innovations in Safety and Emergency Management Systems since 1988. CAST\'s clients are armed with the tools and confidence to perform to the highest standards. CAST\'s 1988 launch marked the creation and delivery of a specialized training program for municipal fire fighters whose area of responsibility included airports. CAST reshaped conventional wisdom by originating a revolutionary program designed to meet this crucial safety need, not only more economically, but also more efficiently, by employing existing municipal structural fire fighting personnel, equipment, expertise and experience. CAST its growth through developing, auditing and reviewing emergency and security plans for airlines, airports, corporations, and governments across Canada and worldwide. All plans, exercises and audits have been tailored to meet the unique requirements of individual clients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">When the U.S. government introduced legislation which required all airlines to submit plans under the Aviation Disaster Family Assistance Act (1996) and the Foreign Air Carrier Family Support Act (1997), CAST developed comprehensive plans to align its client airlines with their obligations to keep pace with evolving American regulations.&nbsp; And CAST pioneered the concept of gathering under one umbrella the expanding array of services that airlines and other organizations are increasingly expected to marshal, while preparing for or responding to incidents. In accordance with heightening expectations of both regulators and the public, CAST fashioned unprecedented response programs designed to harness and coordinate all aspects of crisis response plans and procedures.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">It was during this development phase that CAST, together with Rural/Metro Corporation of Arizona, founded the Emergency Measures Inquiry Center (EMIC) in Scottsdale which led to the partnership\'s development of the world\'s first major transportation emergency operation to combine under one contract the three definitive components of complete emergency response: preparedness, response, and long-term repatriation and disposition of personal effects. This original EMIC prototype became the acknowledged standard for other large-scale, worldwide systems, which were to follow (In 2000, Rural/Metro acquired full ownership of EMIC while CAST intensified its focus on further development of innovative safety and security capabilities.).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CAST answered the call from Bombardier Aerospace to provide project safety management for the mammoth 2002 World Youth Day and 2003 SAR&rsquo;s benefit concert events held at the company\'s Downsview airfield in Toronto. These were 2 of the largest events of their kind in the world with the World Youth Day hosting almost a million participants from around the globe. It was CAST\'s responsibility to guide and coordinate such diverse tasks as keeping the work of on-site construction crews in accordance with Canada\'s Civil Aviation Regulations, red-flagging potential safety and logistical hot spots during the event, and ensuring that post-event cleanup and repairs returned the airfield promptly and safely to its normal functions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Most recently CAST has pioneered the development of a practical approach to aviation Safety Management Systems. Based on extensive hands-on experience in a variety of safety critical environments&nbsp; including developing SMS philosophies, policies, procedures and practices for international airlines and other complex organizations,&nbsp; CAST&rsquo;s approach to SMS is providing clients with a simple, efficient and cost effective means of managing&nbsp; today&rsquo;s evolving safety and emergency management environment.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1131, 1, 'Canada Pet Products Ltd.', 'cppth@telus.net', '6069, 172nd St, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'cpp.jp.net ', '(778) 883-6872', '(604) 576-6822', '', '<p>&nbsp;We at Canada Pet Products Ltd. just had a booth&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>(Booth No.: 510) at the AQUARAMA 2013 (The 13th International Ornamental Fish and Accessories Exhibition)(www.aquarama.com.sg)&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>at the Sands Expo and Convention Center, Marina Bay Sands, Singapore, during 30 May to 2 June, 2013.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>AQUARAMA 2013 is co-located with PET ASIA 2013&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>(The 4th International Pet &amp; Accessories Exhibition), which made the show with exhibitors and visitors from both aquarium and pet industry this year.</div>\r\n<div>The show was another big success. Our hit products, such as AIR-BREEDER (handy manual air pump), OXYGEN STONE, AQUARIUM THERMOMETER (HOOK), PET MILK REPLACER (for Puppies and for Kittens) and CANNED CAT FOOD, attracted high attention and received a great inquiry/response from the exhibitors and visitors from various countries/areas, such as: Singapore, Australia, France, Sweden, Brazil, Colombia, South Africa, Malaysia, Brunei, Thailand, Indonesia, Philippine, Vietnam, India, Sri Lanka, Korea, Taiwan, Hong Kong and China. Furthermore, due to the breakthrough characteristics of the products, and as a new fresh vigor to the industry, media from Australia and China also came to interview and photo our products for their magazines.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our AIR-BREEDER (handy manual air pump) and OXYGEN STONE, which supply the oxygen for aquarium fish with NO NEED of PWR, are our original products with totally new concepts and completely unique functions. You can use them conveniently anytime and anywhere, e.g., when there is an electricity failure, when you take the fish from the aquarium to home and vice versa, or when you go fishing.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All of the products, together with our AQUARIUM THERMOMETER (HOOK) PET MILK REPLACER (for Puppies and for Kittens) and CANNED CAT FOOD, with their high quality and rich functions, have received a good reputation in the industry and in the market.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Distributors/wholesalers/dealers who are interested in becoming our products&rsquo; country/area agent, are welcomed to contact us (cppth@telus.net) for details.</div>', ''),
(1132, 1, 'CanTorque Inc.', 'info@cantorque.com', '14635, 119 Ave NW, Edmonton, Alberta, Canada', 'www.cantorque.com ', '(780) 436-2000', '(780) 732-0905', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CanTorque&trade; specializes in the sale, rental, calibration and servicing of industrial torque and assembly equipment. We are factory representatives for:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TorcUP Hydraulic &amp; Pneumatic Bolting Tools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CanTorque Stud Tensioners <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Equalizer International Flange Spreading and Allignment Tools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CDI Torque Products-Mechanical and Dial Torque Wrenches <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Dakota Ultrasonics Bolting Extensometers &amp; Gagues <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Gray Hand Tools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">ATP Pneumatic Tools and Replacement Parts <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wayne Tool Company Reamers &amp; Cutting Tools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our mission: To prevent and solve any problem related to any bolted connection. We will develop mutually beneficial and long lasting partnerships with our customers, employees and suppliers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To achieve this we will:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sell and rent only world-class equipment <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Service what we sell <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Stock replacement equipment and parts whenever possible to minimize downtime <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure our staff are factory trained and continue to develop both professionally and personally.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1133, 1, 'Canwest Bedding Ltd.', 'benjamin.kay@serta-wpg.com', '60 Bunting St, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', '', '(204) 667-3782', '(204) 775-4116', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Manufacturers of mattresses and boxsprings under the Serta&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Mattress label, private label, and contract maufacturing. &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1134, 1, 'Canworld Foods Ltd.', 'trade@canworld.com', '2-10 Shorncliffe Rd., ETOBICOKE, Ontario , Canada ', 'www.canworld.com ', '(416) 233-1900', '(416) 233-1915', '', '<p>An international food tradinghouse, founded in 1976, serving processors, retailers, wholesalers, and the the food service industry in Canada and worldwide with fresh, frozen and processed meat products. All aspects of international trading are utilized including documentation, international freight rates, currency exchange and letters of credit. We strive to be an innovative tradinghouse engaging in ethical&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">international trade for the mutual benefit of our customers, suppliers and employees.&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1135, 1, 'Canyon.TV Incorporated', 'warren@canyon.tv', '101-270 Shawville Way SE, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.canyon.tv ', '(403) 604-8528', '(403) 475-7986', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Media broadcasting, telecommunications and technology.</span></p>', ''),
(1136, 1, 'Caterpillar Mining Canada ULC', 'dan.brabant@cat.com', '3-2555 Maley Dr., SUDBURY, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.mining.cat.com ', '(705) 524-5000', '(705) 524-5111', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wherever you go in the mining world, you\'ll find Caterpillar. From underground coal mines in China to surface gold mines in Mali to the oil sands of Canada, our products are hard at work. And our people are right there, too&mdash;building and supporting products, training operators, helping our customers mine more profitability, conducting research and development, and working with schools, organizations and communities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Caterpillar serves the worldwide mining community through its Caterpillar Global Mining organization, headquartered in Oak Creek, Wis. Global Mining is the single point of contact for global mineral producers and the primary link to the Caterpillar extended mining enterprise. We provide mine-specific product and service solutions that help our customers enhance safety, improve efficiency, increase productivity and reduce cost per ton.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">About Caterpillar Inc: Caterpillar is the world\'s leading manufacturer of construction and mining equipment, diesel and natural gas engines, industrial gas turbines and diesel-electric locomotives. The company also is a leading services provider through Caterpillar Financial Services, Caterpillar Remanufacturing Services and Progress Rail Services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Cat&reg; equipment product line currently consists of more than 300 machines used in dozens of industries. In addition to tractors, trucks, graders, excavators, scrapers and other heavy machinery used in the construction, mining and forestry industries, Caterpillar also makes diesel and gas engines used in Cat machinery, electric power generation equipment, locomotives and other industrial equipment. With 50 production facilities in the United States and another 60 overseas, Caterpillar does about 44 percent of its business within the United States and 56 percent abroad. Through Caterpillar Financial Services Corporation and other subsidiaries, the company offers financing and insurance for its customers and dealers. The company employs over 100,000 people; of those, about 4,000 are employed by the Caterpillar Global Mining organization.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1137, 1, 'CatnRose Jewelry', 'serge@catnrose.com', '175 Third Ave, LAKEVIEW, Nova Scotia, Canada ', 'www.catnrose.com', '(902) 860-0243', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CatnRose Jewelry is a blend of tradition and exotic, creating unique, elegant, handmade one of kind necklaces, bracelets, earrings and more. Traditional freshwater pearls, combined with exotic gemstones, crystals, cloisonn&eacute; and unique findings are redefining jewellery. CatnRose creates a line of jewellery that is traditional, unique and exotic at the same time.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Rose Valade is the owner and designer of CatnRose Jewelry. Her passion for jewellery was rivalled only by her desire to redesign the pieces that she had purchased during her time traveling and living throughout Europe and the Orient. When people started noticing her redesigned pieces the idea of starting her own line of jewellery began to form.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Rose originally looked at working with vintage stones, redesigning them into original modern pieces. A trip to the Orient in February of 2003 soon changed Rose&rsquo;s mind. For many year&rsquo;s she had been fascinated and mesmerized by the natural visual experience of visiting the Orient. Her home, filled with treasures from her travels, along with her trip to Hong Kong soon convinced Rose that combining her two loves of jewellery and beautiful gemstones was the key to developing CatnRose Jewelry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Inspiration has never been a problem for Rose. She spends hours everyday testing and playing with combinations of gemstones evaluating them for brilliance, size, patterns and colour. These combinations allow the line of jewellery to appeal to people of all ages. All customers can enjoy the high aesthetic quality of her designs, which reflects her attention to details, standards and style.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1138, 1, 'Cats in the Bag design', 'info@catsinthebag.com', '1436 Fullum St, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.catsinthebag.com ', '(438) 838-1145', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cats in the Bag design, we are creative and curious cats!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The bag is where we go to incubate your project, goals, objectives and target audience. Knowledge and understanding are the creative fuel for the best strategic solution which makes everyone fall in love with your business!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">When the project is complete the &ldquo;cat is out of the bag&rdquo;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Strategic creative design and illustration!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1139, 1, 'CCI Thermal Technologies Inc.', 'info@ccithermal.com', '2721 Plymouth Dr., OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.ccithermal.com ', '(905) 829-4422', '(905) 829-4430', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CCI Thermal Technologies Inc. is a world leader in the development and production of advanced heating and filtration solutions for industrial and hazardous area applications. The diversity of our six brands - Cata-Dyne&trade;, Ruffneck&trade;, Caloritech&trade;, Norseman&trade;, DriQuik&trade; and 3L Filters&trade; - represents the broadest based industry expertise, and the range of our technologies enables their application in virtually any environment. Our product lines feature a wide array of heating and filtration solutions, including infrared gas catalytic heating, heavy-duty explosion-proof heating, electric process heating, automated product curing and finishing systems, and custom engineered heating and filtration packages.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We maintain four strategic manufacturing locations across North America. Our corporate head office in Edmonton, Alberta is also home to our Western Canadian manufacturing operation. Our two plants in the province of Ontario, including a newly renovated state of the art facility in Oakville, house our Eastern Canadian manufacturing. Finally, our United States manufacturing is located in Greensburg, Indiana in the center of America&rsquo;s industrial heartland.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CCI Thermal is very honoured to be recognized as one of Canada&rsquo;s 50 Best Managed Companies by Canada&rsquo;s leading business awards program for the sixth time running. Our strong commitment to research, product development and excellence in manufacturing has made our products the industry standard. Our dedication to superior customer service guarantees our continued success.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1140, 1, 'CCW Energy Systems', 'ltilby@ccwenergysystems.com', '8011 Davies Rd NW, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.ccwenergysystems.com ', '(780) 435-2284', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CCW Energy Systems produces high-quality, custom-designed, energy efficiency motor drive systems and generative motor drive systems for the oil and gas industry. Among the leaders in the field for control systems for ESP, Pump Jacks, PCP and horizontal pumping systems, CCW Energy Systems continuously introduces innovation and advanced technology to our entire range of products and services. CCW Energy Systems provides world class solutions to our clients for product selection, customization, installation expertise, oil field application assistance and warranty services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All our oil field energy efficiency products are designed and manufactured by professionals with years of combined experience and expertise in the oil and gas industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our dedicated team works closely with every customer to tailor the best solution based on individual requirements. We coordinate with various Electricity Service Providers to obtain net-metering applications for the clients\' regenerative pump jack drives. CCW Energy Systems provides assistance with obtaining these permits, and to start saving money on your field electric bills. In other words, CCW Energy Systems is the first truly dedicated oil field energy efficiency company.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1141, 1, 'CD Industrial Group Inc.', 'info@carldyke.com', '7-7875 48 Ave, RED DEER, Alberta, Canada', 'www.carldyke.com ', '(403) 358-3238', '(403) 358-3240', '', '<p>&nbsp;CD Industrial Group Inc. is an established industrial training provider.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We specialize in media-rich training tools that bring your equipment alive, such as our revolutionary Live Schematics.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We\'re a uniquely qualified team of consultants, educators, tradesmen, writers, programmers, and artists &mdash; all with industrial experience.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We work extensively with internationally recognized industry partners in manufacturing, mining, oilfield services and forest products.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our mandate is to provide exceptional training and support to heavy industrial maintenance and operations groups, and machinery manufacturers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To that end, our hydraulic maintenance consulting, customized Live Schematics, and Ten Step Troubleshooting Process have been recognized for their excellence, garnering stellar testimonials.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are based out of Alberta, Canada, and deliver our instructor-led training and consulting throughout North America, with online training available worldwide.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>What We Do</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>CD Industrial Group Inc. offers a wide range of training programs, ranging from industrial operations training for maintenance and troubleshooting, hydraulic and electrical fundamentals, and leadership training. Take a look at our training courses.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We use a reliability-centered approach to maintenance and a systems-based approach to troubleshooting. We provide the coaching to help your team think differently about the problems they encounter in the industrial environment.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We also offer the most specialized, equipment-specific training on the market. Our development team will work with you to craft rigorous custom training content using our unique interactive animations, supplemented with workbooks, tests, and documentation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The ultimate goal is to help develop root level competencies, essential skills, and best practices in your maintenance team and tradespeople.</div>', ''),
(1142, 1, 'CDI College Business, Technology, and Health Care', 'joe@diamondinstitute.ca', '100-100 Westney Rd S, AJAX, Ontario, Canada', 'www.cdicollege.ca ', '(604) 915-7288', '(905) 427-2558', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more than 40 years, CDI College has been one of the leading career training institutions in Canada, thanks to its commitment to quality education and the success of its students. Our rich history includes an alumni of thousands of successful graduates. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether you&rsquo;re training for a career in healthcare, business or technology, our programs will prepare you to use the most current methods, practices and tools utilized by professionals on the job. Academic knowledge will also be put to the test during practicum placements, which are part of many of the programs offered at CDI.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Emphasizing hands-on training with practical projects, you&rsquo;ll learn from savvy instructors with years of field experience. Our programs are developed based on input from industry specialists to meet the needs of a fast-paced and demanding job market. With the skills and knowledge you&rsquo;ll earn at CDI College, you&rsquo;ll be well prepared to launch your dream career in a matter of months.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With more than 50 diploma and certificate programs being offered at campus locations across the country, CDI College gives students the opportunity to live, work and study close to home. CDI College prides itself on changing lives; let us help you achieve your personal and academic goals today!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1143, 1, 'CE3 Electronics Inc.', 'raymond.kaps@ce3electronics.com', 'Dieppe Industrial Park 541 Ferdinand Blvd, Dieppe , New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.ce3electronics.com ', '(506) 858-7817', '(506) 877-0730', '', '<p>&nbsp;Nothing sells like face-to-face contact, even in global markets. That\'s how CE3, a Moncton-based contract electronics manufacturing firm, has made its mark with the &quot;big players.&quot; By focusing on customer service and international networking, this company has achieved significant growth, nearly doubling its number of employees in less than five years.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>So what exactly does a contract electronics manufacturer produce? In this award-winning company\'s case the products, which are targeted to niche markets, range from miniature electronic components to large power transformers. Specialties include:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Full turnkey electronic manufacturing services, individualized to meet any customers\' manufacturing needs;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Printed circuit board assembly using state of the art, lead-free SMT and quality assurance programs that will ensure fast turn-around with high reliability;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Cable and wire harness assembly using innovative technology paired with consistent and professional workmanship; and</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Custom-wound magnetic components used in a range of applications, from lighting and electronic signage to industrial control and medical electronics.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Since its 1985 start-up, CE3 has earned a solid reputation for providing reliable, quality products and services with on-time delivery. In 1994, the company received the Greater Moncton Business Excellence Award for Innovation. Then three years later it was hailed as one of the 10 best contract electronics manufacturers in Canada by Electronic Buyers\' News, the worldwide industry newspaper for purchasing and business management. More recently, the company successfully implemented the requirements to have its Quality Management System registered to ISO 9001:2008 and AS9100C. The new quality system will become a model for continuous improvement.</div>', ''),
(1144, 1, 'Cedarview Manufacturing Inc', 'info@cedarviewmfg.com', '1-17358 104A Ave, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.cedarviewmfg.com ', '(604) 582-0608', '(604) 582-0606', '', '<p>Manufacturer and supplier of pre-fabricated Hot tub Gazebos, Spa Enclosures and other cedar sheds shelters.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1145, 1, 'CEI Architecture', 'frontdesk@ceiarchitecture.com', '500-1500 W Georgia St , VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.ceiarchitecture.com ', '(604) 687-1898', '(604) 682-5398', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">David N. Spearing Architectural Group provides architectural design services with ancillary engineering services for a wide range of building types, urban design and major project development consulting.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Through association with experts in most specialty fields of building the Spearing Group provides in depth services, analysing needs from basic principles and translating those needs to built form.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Spearing Group is particularly known for understanding and interpreting into built form the specific needs of clients. As well the Group has established a reputation in Urban Design through the rejuvenation of Urban Cores and Heritage Structures and through the planning and design of residential communities and buildings on mountain slopes as well as ski and equestrian resorts, hotels, prisons, police stations, embassies, community centers, arenas, swimming pools, churches, office buildings, colleges and projects for First Nation and ethnic minorities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Current Geographic Marketing Activity <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Spearing\'s interests extend through Japan, South East Asia, the Indian Subcontinent, Peru, Mexico, Guatemala, Guyana, Poland, Russia, the Philippines and Bolivia. Projects are welcomed from any part of the world. Many projects form prototypes for trends to follow.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1146, 1, 'Celco Controls Ltd.', 'mhinman@cpc.ca', '110-1525 Broadway St, PORT COQUITLAM, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.cpc.ca ', '(604) 461-4547', '(604) 554-0135', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Canadian Process &amp; Control Ltd. designs, manufactures, installs and commissions process control systems for the resource, refining, chemical, municipal, manufacturing, high technology, and OEM industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Each of our clients is unique with different process control requirements. CPC will provide a complete turnkey solution, or, alternatively, is pleased to work as a team member to augment your in-house expertise. Whatever the exact role of CPC, it is our goal to provide and install accurate, cost-effective control systems that optimize your processes to maximize your competitive advantage.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Our services:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Design<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Purchase<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">System Integration<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">PLC Programming<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Motor Control<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Control Panels &amp; Kiosks<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Instrumentation Calibration<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Instrumentation Installation<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Startup and Commissioning<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">CSA &amp; Union Labels<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Pneumatic, Hydraulic &amp; Lubrication Tubing</span></p>', ''),
(1147, 1, 'Centaur Floor Machines Ltd.', 'info@centaurmachines.com', '103 Denison St., MARKHAM, Ontario , Canada', 'www.centaurmachines.com ', '(905) 475-5640', '(905) 474-9921', '', '<p>&nbsp;Commercial and Service Industry Machinery Manufacturing</p>', ''),
(1148, 1, 'CFM Air Equipment', 'cfmair@cfmair.com', '3647 Blackburn Rd SE, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.cfmair.com ', '(403) 252-1177', '(403) 252-1275', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Optimal Energy (2002) inc. was incorporated in Alberta on September 10, 2002 and operates under the trade name of CFM Air Equipment (&quot;CFM Air&quot;). CFM Air Equipment was established in Calgary and has been operational since 1965. In 2015 we will be celebrating 50 years of service in the Calgary and surrounding area. On March 7th 2009 a second office was opened in West St Paul (Winnipeg) Manitoba. CFM Air Equipment currently employs 11 personnel in Calgary and 2 in West St Paul.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CFM Air Equipment markets compressors, pumps, blowers, dryers, compressed air piping, replacement parts, instrument air packages, air end rebuilds, equipment rentals and provides 24/7 service on all makes/models of compressed air equipment. CFM Air Equipment services over 1,400 customers from an 18,000 square foot facility in Calgary and a 2,500 square foot facility in West St Paul. The markets served are primarily the provinces of British Columbia, Alberta, Saskatchewan, Manitoba, and north west Ontario. Industries serviced include oil and gas, mining, hydro, agriculture, building maintenance, government, fertilizer and power.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1149, 1, 'CGC Inc.', 'gtylor@usg.com', '11105 Bridge Rd., SURREY, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.cgcinc.com ', '(604) 580-2606', '(604) 580-1377', '', '<p>&nbsp;CGC Inc. is a leading marketer, manufacturer and distributor of gypsum wallboard products, interior finishing materials and suspended acoustical ceilings in Canada. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1150, 1, 'Chain Reference Inc.', 'info@chainreference.com', '133 Ellenville Cres., ARISS, Ontario, Canada', 'www.chainreference.com', '(519) 763-9487', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Chain Reference specializes in helping people build the history of their things. Using ItemPath, an affordable and easy-to-use cloud software program, you will be able to track all your things, from simple asset tracking to lot tracking to complex combinations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">You can also ID your items with ItemPath, the world&rsquo;s very first cloud label printing app.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1151, 1, 'Ciment Quebec Inc.', 'amorissette@cqi.ca', '145, boul. du Centenaire, SAINT-BASILE, Quebec, Canada ', 'WWW.cimentquebec.com', '(418) 329-2100', '(418) 329-3436', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ciment Qu&eacute;bec Inc. (CQI) owns one of the most modern cement factories in North America. CQI makes many types of cement that it distributes in Quebec, Ontario, the Maritimes and the United States. CQI is vertically integrated into the ready-mixed concrete and aggregates sectors. Ciment Qu&eacute;bec Inc. employs more than 700 skilled and experienced people, who produce high-quality products. They provide services to clients, and are committed to upholding the company&rsquo;s reputation for excellence.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">It all began around the end of the forties, when cement was a rare commodity in Canada. Gustave Papillon and his father, Ernest-J. Papillon, started on this great adventure in cement production in 1947, after using cement for the first time to expand a farm building. Gustave Papillon became interested in cement-making, and over the next two years, he developed a plan to build a cement plant, perfect the chemistry of the process, and find the equipment required to produce cement in Canada and the United States.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Gifted in mechanics, he applied his abilities and in 1949 spoke about his plans to his father, Ernest J. Papillon, who was a real-estate broker, able to finance the project. After coming to a mutual agreement, the father and son started producing cement. The company was set up in their birthplace of Saint-Basile-de-Portneuf, noted for its quality limestone in quantities that could supply the business for a long time.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1152, 1, 'CJM Enterprises', 'cmdyprdcr@gmail.com', '49 Slidell Cres, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 699-1671', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Am a &quot;baby boomer aged&quot;, mature, empty nested, Milton based CLEAN comedian/Host/MC. since 2002 I\'ve been delivering &quot;the funny&quot; at corporate/government events/fundraisers/galas/balls, personal milestone celebrations throughout North/Central/South America primarily for the baby boomer aged audiences.... Am available for corporate/ marketing/events across Canada and possess a valid passport to 11/2016..I\'ve delivered &quot;the funny&quot; to Forces Canada/DND at bases in Ontario, and in Ottawa to both the &quot;troops &amp; suits&quot;.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1153, 1, 'CK Manufacturing / Industrial Concepts Inc.', 'rswan@ckconcepts.com', '1735 Sylvestre Dr., TECUMSEH, Ontario , Canada', 'www.ckconcepts.com ', '(519) 739-1614', '(519) 979-8599', '', '<p>&nbsp;CK Manufacturing offers engineering design, build and manufacturing of special purpose machines, military components and controls, electrical panel builds and programming.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>We utilize new and progressive business concepts which have evolved through many years of practical manufacturing and business experience. Our aim is to give our clients a cost effective way of doing business while generating profits and lasting relationships with their customers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our qualified team of controls experts, project managers, engineers and mechanical designers can provide the leadership and expertise in all areas of your manufacturing and industrial jobs efficiently, professionally and cost effectively.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Rapid changes in manufacturing applications and processes make it extremely difficult for companies to stay on top of all the innovative industry processes while remaining cost effective. CK Manufacturing couples their skill and drive with current industry innovations and strategies to keep your company at the top of the industry. By working as a team, we can make a difference in your bottom line.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To view our custom machine builds in action visit our Portfolio page for videos and photos of our Industrial and Military design build installations.</div>', ''),
(1154, 1, 'Claremont Communications', 'salesteam@claremont.ca', '400-303 Moodie Dr., Ottawa, Ontario, Canada', 'www.claremont.ca ', '(613) 863-0568', '(613) 863-0568', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Claremont Communications is a leader in the Global IT and Software Engineering Services field. Since 1995, we have been utilizing proven project management methodologies to achieve outcomes for your competitive advantage.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether your organization is large, medium or small, together with our partners, Claremont will consult with you to streamline requirements, derive efficient plans, implement effective solutions and assist your organization every step of the way. We have a proven track record we are proud of, including a working partnership with Public Works and Government Service Canada (PWGSC) for over 15 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We succeed by providing professional guidance and exacting implementations to go beyond the standards in attaining truly sustainable projects and bringing technological innovation to the forefront of today\'s development.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Claremont is pleased to announce our new dedicated Global IT and Software Engineering Services division to assist your organization with all your IT and software engineering needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are pleased to have worked with some of the most respected companies in the world in our endeavours with clients. We are adept at specifying the right tools for your needs and saving you money in the long run.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1155, 1, 'CM Associates', 'www.huntnewbiz.com ', '3108-41 Homewood Ave, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', '', '(416) 923-0877', 'cmassociates@sympati', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Big Game Hunting secures company-wide, ongoing assignments for niche firms who think globally.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Jungle Lesson #1: It&rsquo;s easier to look good when riding the wave. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Jungle Lesson #2: High-value transactions and enduring relationships can be built without face-to-face contact.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Jungle Lesson #3: Specialty knowledge-based businesses have no geographic limitations&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1156, 1, 'CNS Systems', 'sales-americas@cns.se', '210W-370 Torbay Rd, ST. JOHN\'S, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada ', 'www.cns.se', '(709) 754-0400', '(709) 754-0419', '', '<p>&nbsp;Based in St. John\'s, Newfoundland, Canada, CNS Systems develops, sells, and implements systems for Communication, Navigation and Surveillance for both the aviation and maritime market. The expertise and capability of CNS Systems covers a wide range of solutions from the delivery of complete system solutions to unit level solutions. The maritime solution includes complete systems for shore based, ship borne and airborne operation and the aviation offer includes communication and applications for air traffic management, airport and helicopter operation. The systems are based on and fully compliant with and certified to, the international standards AIS for the marine and VDL Mode 4 for the aviation market. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1157, 1, 'Coaldale Iron Products Ltd.', 'metalman@coaldaleiron.com', '12009 18 Ave, COALDALE, Alberta, Canada', 'www.coaldaleiron.com ', '(403) 345-3973', '(403) 345-6322', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Coaldale Iron Products is a family operated business serving Coaldale, Lethbridge and surrounding areas for the last 40 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We pride ourselves in delivering quality work, and understanding our customers&rsquo; needs and desires is always our highest priority!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our business is primarily customized manufacturing and we can fabricate just about anything you want.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Some of the things we do:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-wrought iron fencing / railing (interior &amp; exterior)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-pool fencing<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-flag poles<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-shelves<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-bed frames<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-pump houses<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-controller enclosures<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-gates of all sizes<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">-spiral staircases<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1158, 1, 'Commercial Aviation', 'info@commercialaviation.ca', '1 Airport Rd., HEARST, Ontario, Canada', 'www.commercialaviation.ca ', '(705) 362-8505', '(705) 362-7437', '', '<p>&nbsp;With over 25 years of experience serving clients in Ontario, Commercial Aviation is proud to introduce a modern fleet and professional two crew environment to suit your needs. Offering services from executive charters to medical transportation Commercial Aviation has a wide range of services guaranteed to me your needs.</p>', ''),
(1159, 1, 'CP Cases Inc.', 'salesna@cpcases.com', '3-450 Tapscott Rd, SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.cpcases.com ', '(416) 438-8803', '(416) 438-8849', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CP Cases offers a worldwide design and manufacturing service for high-performance, ruggedized cases and 19-inch racks used for transport, operation and storage of essential equipment for commercial and military applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our unique product range offers solutions to meet all your protective needs in any environment. All of our cases can be customized to suit any individual requirement with our wide selection of accessories, including climate control options, EMI/EMC shielding and your choice of internal fixtures, fittings and foam protection<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1160, 1, 'Company QuarterMaster Services Ltd', 'info@cqmsltd.com', '9 Railway Ave, Enilda, Alberta, Canada', 'www.cqmsltd.com ', '(780) 523-5311', '(780) 523-5328', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Retail new and used military surplus clothing and equipment. Provide new field uniforms to Army Cadet League and First Nations Cadets Corps. Tactical Ballistic Plates&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1161, 1, 'Crane Management Consultants Ltd.', 'debiasio@craneconsult.com', '1763, 3rd Ave E, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada ', '', '(604) 688-1245', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;P<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">rovide management consulting services in the environmental, natural resources and economic development fields &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1162, 1, 'CSR Cosmetic Solutions Inc.', 'info@csrcs.ca', '149 Victoria St, Barrie, Ontario, Canada', 'www.csrcs.ca ', '(705) 728-5917', '(705) 728-8262', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CSR is a proven leader in formulating, manufacturing and filling of personal care and colour cosmetic products<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 60 years, we have helped build successful consumer brands for some of the industry&rsquo;s most reputable companies. Our focus on consistency, performance and reliability in the context of strict cGMP guidelines makes CSR the right choice for North American and international companies looking for a complete range of product innovation, manufacturing and filling solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1163, 1, 'CT logics Inc', 'sinisa@telusplanet.net', '2-26318 Township Road 531A, ACHESON,, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.fluid-design.ca ', '(780) 960-8848', '(780) 960-8877', '', '<p>&nbsp;Oilfield drilling equipment manufacturer. Products range from variety of Top Drives, Coil Tubing Injectors, Make/Brake Units to pipehandling units, snubbing units, blocs, drawworks.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1164, 1, 'Current Equipment Inc.', 'info@currentequipment.com', '2410 39th Ave NE, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.currentequipment.com ', '(403) 248-1455', '(403) 248-1499', '', '<p>We are a Canadian based provider of quality geophysical acquisition products and services, backed with an industry leading level of integrity.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We support the Geophysical Industry with repair, maintenance, supply, rental of product and parts keeping your seismic crew moving forward.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our experience dates back to 1976, we opened in spring of 2006 and have over 80 years of combined experience.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With year round staff and state of the art testing equipment, we can maintain and / or supplement your equipment maintenance program.</div>', ''),
(1165, 1, 'CVR Inc.', 'cvr@istar.ca', '1586 Russett Dr., ARNPRIOR, Ontario, Canada', 'www.cvrproducts.com ', '(613) 623-8064', '(613) 623-5972', '', '<p>&nbsp;Motor Vehicle Electrical and Electronic Equipment Manufacturing</p>', ''),
(1166, 1, 'D & V Electronics Ltd.', 'sales@dvelectronics.com', '130 Zenway Blvd, WOODBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.dvelectronics.com ', '(905) 264-7646', '(905) 264-0502', '', '<p>&nbsp;D&amp;V Electronics of Toronto, Canada designs and manufactures test equipment for the testing of HV/EV motors and inverters/controllers, as well as alternators and starters. From endurance/durability to performance/laboratory to automated end-of-line production testing, D&amp;V is providing leading edge testers for the automotive industry worldwide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>D&amp;V&rsquo;s alternator and starter testers are proven state of the art machines sold throughout the world to Tier One manufacturers including Remy, Bosch, Valeo and Denso. State of the art component testers include testers for: starter solenoids, alternator voltage regulators, rectifiers, diodes and batteries. Special testers include: starter endurance testers with engine simulator, starter and alternator laboratory &amp; endurance testers with thermal chambers.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>D&amp;V&rsquo;s beginnings as a supplier to the alternator and starter remanufacturing industry have resulted in our leading the industry as we continue to develop new products for this industry worldwide. D&amp;V is now producing its newest tester, the JBT-1, a desktop alternator and starter tester with BSS and LIN capabilities for warehouses, distributors and small remanufacturers&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The D&amp;V EPT test stands are based on 14 years of automotive testing innovation and research, with our goal of providing the HV/EV industry with the best products ahead of the curve. By leveraging our long standing e-motor testing experience with strong electrical engineering expertise, D&amp;V develops products to meet emerging test requirements and provides more cost effective integrated test systems for the rapidly expanding hybrid and EV markets.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Recent projects include inverter durability testers for a state of the art, triple-output inverter. This system included 3 motors with loads on each, thermal chambers and 5 channel liquid cooling to allow full simulation of vehicle drive cycles. These testers are being used to provide the longest and most severe drive schedules used currently in the industry.&nbsp;</div>', '');
