(1167, 1, 'D.B. Kenney Fisheries Ltd.', 'slombard@dbkenneyfisheries.com', '301 Water St., WESTPORT, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.dbkenneyfisheries.com ', '(902) 839-2023', '(902) 839-2070', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">D.B. Kenney Fisheries is a third generation, family owned and operated business. Pictured here is the way the plant looked in the early 1970\'s, when the operation was under the care of Mr. Daniel Kenney Sr., who took over the business from his father, the original D.B. Kenney. With a lot of hard work and knowledgeable direction, Mr. Kenney grew the business from its humble origins until he turned it over to his son Daniel B. Kenney the third.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In the years since he took over, the current president of D.B. Kenney Fisheries has guided the business to it\'s present day success, expanding the facilities to include a state of the art lobster pound, a fleet of trucks compromising D.B. Kenney Transport and a modernized fish production facility. The seafood business is an ever changing and demanding challenge, one which Mr. Kenney has met and excelled at, making the Brier Island brand of seafood a commodity recognized and respected throughout North America.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The head office is located right in the center of the action. High speed internet access keeps the staff in touch with world markets, custom brokers and our network of customers across North America. Utilizing the internet and Federal Express we are able to ship seafood to customers around in the world, usually in less than 24 hours. See our Online Order services for all the details and treat yourself to a taste of real Canadian seafood at its best.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1168, 1, 'D.W. Electrochemicals Ltd.', 'dwel@stabilant.com', '3-97 Newkirk Rd. N., RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, Canada', 'www.stabilant.com ', '(905) 508-7500', '(905) 508-7502', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The company was established in 1986. While it was begun in 1976, as Wright Electroacoustics, it was based on the R&amp;D work of Wm. M. D. Wright. After several years of field trials, the final product, STABILANT 22 was introduced as TWEEK&copy;, by Sumiko.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Stabilant was first tested for defense use in 1983 at The Canadian Forces Establishment, Cold Lake, Alberta and was issued a NATO number for use as a &quot;Contact enhancer &copy;&quot; NSCM - Cage Code/NATO Supplier Code - 38948<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1169, 1, 'D/V LogWorks', 'dvlogworks@sunshine.net', '8121 Frances Rd, HALFMOON BAY, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(604) 885-5322', '(604) 885-5322', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are a small company that gets involved in medium to large projects. We have manufactured residential and commercial timber/log structures and are very team focused. Our belief is that everyone should have access to living/working/recreating in largely wooden structures that afford the greatest exposure to our natural environment. We belong to the Timber Framers Guild of Canada and have an excellent reputation with the Provincial Parks System within the Province of British Columbia. We are very capable of Project Management or components thereof and haven\'t any qualms about being part of a bigger team of craftsmen. We look forward to any inquiries regarding these types of building systems. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1170, 1, 'Dacro Industries Inc.', 'boswald@dacro.com', '9325, 51st Ave, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.dacro.com ', '(780) 434-8900', '(780) 433-3138', '', '<p>&nbsp;Dacro Industries Inc. is a wholly Alberta owned company that has been in the Petroleum, Petrochemical, Pulp &amp; Paper &amp; Power arenas serving domestic &amp; foreign markets since 1974. Facilities include 7100 sq. meters of modern plant with an additional 3500 sq. meters serviced by overhead crane plus 780 sw. meters of modern office on&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">a site of approximately 3.6 hectares. Custom fabrication pressure vessels including process towers, columns, storage vessels, reactors, contractors, separators, treaters &amp; converters, de-barkers,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">rotary driers, combustors, accumulators &amp; large diameter structural steel such as ducting. Vessel size up to 9.75 meters in diameter, 90 meters long, &amp; 850 tons. Materials experience includes low alloy, stainless steel, nickel alloys &amp; clad materials. Complete in-house&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">engineering designs incorporate CAD &amp; Finite Element Analysis. &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1171, 1, 'Dairytown Products Ltd.', 'derek.roberts@dairytown.com', '49 Milk Board Rd, ROACHVILLE, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.dairytown.com ', '(506) 432-1950', '(506) 432-1940', '', '<p>&nbsp;Dairytown Processing Ltd. produces dairy products and ingredients for the retail, food service, further processing and institutional markets. Located in the dairy hub of New Brunswick, central to Moncton, Saint John and Fredericton, Dairytown receives milk from a collective of local dairy farmers. Fresh milk is received daily, allowing us to process and ship our products immediately. This process gives our products a distinct clean, pure taste. This is what we call the Dairytown Difference.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our main product lines include skim milk powder, instant skim milk powder, whey protein concentrate, and butter. Though all of our products are known for their exceptionally high quality and great taste, our vast array of butter products have become the industry-standard for uncompromising quality. The Dairytown brand of butter has won numerous awards including World&rsquo;s Best Butter from the World Butter &amp; Cheese Championship and Canada&rsquo;s Best Butter from the Royal Agricultural Winter Fair.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our products are available for contract manufacturing, private label retail and food service. We receive fresh milk 365 days a year, allowing for large and consistent product output. We are flexible with production and shipping specifications, and always do what we can to meet our customers&rsquo; requirements.</div>', ''),
(1172, 1, 'Dalton Pharma Services', 'chemist@dalton.com', '349 Wildcat Rd, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.dalton.com ', '(416) 661-2102', '(416) 661-2108', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalton Chemical Laboratories Inc., was initally established to bring the benefits of modern instrumentation and chemical expertise to the Chemistry Department at York University. Over the years, Dalton has been providing advice and consultation to many chemical, pharmaceutical and analytical establishments across North American chemical, pharmaceutical and biotechnology industries. We have grown into a company that has expertise in synthetic organic and peptide chemistry, process development, scale-up and cGMP manufacturing of active pharmaceutical ingredients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Dalton has been producing fine chemicals on a custom basis for research and for chemical supply houses over the eighteen years (viz. Sigma, Aldrich, Fluka, ICN, BDH). As part of our business effort, we have identified and supplied many new reagents for biological and commercial synthetic purposes. We have specialized in oligo-RNA and DNA synthesis as it has been a unique opportunity for low-volume, high value-added fine chemical production with strong growth potential. More recently we have identified pharmaceutical impurity and analog synthesis and drug discovery as areas of growing demand. For this reason we have developed our contract research capabilities. In 1996 Dalton established a cGMP manufacturing operation for production of Bulk Pharmaceuticals as we anticipate strong growth in this portion of the business.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1173, 1, 'Academy of Learning', 'elipschitz@academyoflearning.com', '400-100 York Blvd, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, Canada', 'www.academyoflearning.com ', '(905) 886-8973', '(905) 886-8591', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Academy of Learning College, we attribute the growth in our success to identifying the gap between the formal education available and the realities of the working world. We fulfill the needs of learners by developing customized programs for each student, while meeting the requirements for convenient and effective training at an affordable cost.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In today&rsquo;s business world, where quality training is not only important but essential to career success, Academy of Learning College stands out as a training provider relied on by students, employers and government agencies. No other private post-secondary college can match the variety of programs that Academy of Learning College offers. Students can choose from over 30 diploma and certificate programs offered at Academy of Learning College.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Academy of Learning College will always be recognized as Canada&rsquo;s most effective and respected college, providing career, business and computer skills.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1174, 1, 'B & B Environmental Services Ltd.', 'bbenviro@nb.sympatico.ca', '1102 Route 890, NEWTOWN, New Brunswick, Canada', '', '(506) 433-1030', '(506) 433-2506', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B &amp; B Environmental Services Ltd. (formerly B &amp; B Sludge Services Ltd.), based 11 km from Sussex, N.B., is a N.B. owned organic waste management company. Services provided are flotation units (dry and liquid), tanker fleets, by-product storage and treatment, composting facilities, site permitting and resource management. Clients in the Maritimes and the State of Maine are serviced through land application of various by-products, from industry, municipalities, agriculture and aquaculture. Custom-built equipment allows B &amp; B to apply products on the surface or sub-surface and inject to depths of 17 inches. Also, with high flotation abilities adverse conditions such as weather is not a factor.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B &amp; B also composts all by-products from pulp and paper industries into a high grade product aimed for international markets. After several years of research, B &amp; B has developed several recipes, specific to each market. These products are produced on our 70 ha. Facilities located 15 kms. From Sussex on the Oldfield Road. These products will be promoted by the brand name &quot;Oldfield Natural Organics&quot; at a later date. B &amp; B co-operates very closely with all municipal, provincial, and federal departments. The compost meets the highest federal standard for compost quality, ensuring that it can be used in agriculture operations. As operations, services and products expand, the company is heading toward ISO certification.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">B &amp; B Environmental Services Ltd. originated from the based company Crowevel Farms Ltd. As a diversification in 1991 with a herd size of 180 head. The company has investments in an import-export company, dental supply company serving all of Canada and several states and finally ownership in equipment rental renting anything from had tools to highway tractors.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1175, 1, 'Calmont Group', 'grant.bennett@calmont.ca', '14610 Yellowhead Trail NW, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.calmont.ca ', '(780) 409-3353', '(780) 482-5663', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Calmont Leasing Ltd. was incorporated in 1977 and is a Canadian Nationwide company with its head office located in Edmonton, Alberta. Calmont Leasing has branches in Edmonton, Calgary , Winnipeg and Saskatoon. Calmont Leasing Ltd. is a franchised dealer in Southern Alberta for Autocar heavy trucks and in Alberta and Manitoba for Kalmar (Ottawa) shunt trucks. Calmont Leasing Ltd. is also a franchised dealer for, SportChassis, , Hi-Tech Trailers and Odanah Custom Fabricating (OCF) Truck Dumper Inserts.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Calmont is engaged in finance leasing of trucks and cars, full service vehicle leasing, short-term vehicle leasing, daily rentals, vehicle sales, part sales and service repairs of both owned and non-owned vehicles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1992, Calmont Leasing Ltd. entered the NationaLease network. The National Truck Leasing System was formed in 1944 and today has over 120 independent truck leasing companies in the U.S.A. and Canada, with the group operating more than 400 franchised service facilities. Advantages include buying power, reciprocal road service, national advertising, market support and training.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1176, 1, 'Dewpoint Bottling Company Ltd.', 'sammy.mittelstadt@worldofwater.ca', '326 Keewatin St., WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.worldofwater.ca ', '(204) 774-7770', '(204) 772-5051', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1976 Gladys Reid had a small residential water distiller and produced pure distilled water in her garage in Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.&nbsp; After sampling her water many of her friends offered to pay for the product if she would continue to supply it to them.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Gradually, her customer list increased to the point that she was not able to keep up with the demand.&nbsp; She set up a second distillation system in another location to help supply her customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The demand for her distilled water continued to increase and she set up a third production plant. This was the birth of World of Water. Many years later, through many industry changes and increasing consumer demand, World of Water evolved into a company with a strong presence in Canada, supplying Dewdrop&reg; Distilled water to business and residential consumers. World of Water International Ltd. has been in business since 1976. During that time we have solidified our reputation as &quot;Pure Water Specialists&quot;.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are known for providing top quality products, competitive prices, and superior knowledge and service. World of Water is the leading bottled water company in Manitoba.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At the end of 2013 there were 13 franchise stores operating in designated areas throughout the province of Manitoba.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">There are 10 locations in Winnipeg, one in Brandon, one in Portage La Prairie and one in Selkirk. Located in prime residential areas, all World of Water stores produce Dewdrop&reg; brand distilled water on site.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Customers can choose to have Dewdrop&reg; delivered to their home or business, or they can visit any World of Water location to exchange or refill their bottles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to Dewdrop&reg; distilled water, all World of Water stores offer an extensive range of products, including our exclusive Tear Drop&reg; line of water treatment products, to help people address a wide variety of water concerns.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At World of Water, we are proud of our past accomplishments, and with strong customer service and exceptional value as our focus, we look forward to a prosperous future.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1177, 1, 'Eclipse Technologies Inc.', 'info@eclipsetechnologies.com', '3-4801 Wellington Rd, NANAIMO, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.eclipsetechnologies.com ', '(250) 758-5477', '(250) 758-5497', '', '<p>&nbsp;Founded in 1999, Eclipse Technologies Inc. is the exclusive manufacturer of AIRA &reg; Retractable Screen Systems for doors, windows, and other architectural openings. AIRA&reg; Retractable Screens are the core product line of Canadian manufacturer Eclipse Technologies Inc. Eclipse Technologies reflects its commitment to uncompromising quality as the only ISO-9001:2000 certified manufacturer of retractable screens and establishes itself as an industry leader with innovations such as &ldquo;no slam&rdquo; speed reducing technology and claw-proof pet mesh and now recently adding two exciting new products, SOLA&trade; Motorized Screens and SOLARA&trade; Retractable Awnings. Our dealer network is expanding rapidly and our quality, market-leading products are making conventional screens obsolete.At Eclipse Technologies Inc. we are proud to announce that we are actively seeking quality, and success-minded OEM&rsquo;s, Distributors, Dealers, and Installers to complement our highly motivated and talented Global team.</p>', ''),
(1178, 1, 'FRAN5', 'info@FRAN5.com', '1801-1 Yonge St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.FRAN5.com ', '(800) 432-1583', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">FRAN5.COM is a Toronto based franchise brokerage firm serving clients worldwide. We provide our clients free access to explore over 500 Franchise brands in our portfolio. Additional services include no charge consultations for qualified buyers and assistance in the procurement of financing and legal. FRAN5 is simply a better way to buy a franchise.&nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1179, 1, 'Goodwin & Mark LLP', 'gm@goodmark.ca', '217-713 Columbia St, NEW WESTMINSTER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.goodmark.ca', '(604) 522-9884', '(604) 526-8044', '', '<p>Lawyers and trademark agents. Full service law firm, including corporate &amp; commercial; real estate conveyancing &amp; development; mortgages; commercial leasing; trademarks &amp; franchising; wills, trusts &amp; estate probate; adoptions, divorces &amp; family law; criminal law; foreclosures; builders liens; wrongful dismissal; and all related litigation.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1180, 1, 'HUB International HKMB', 'hkmb@hubinternational.com', '900-595 Bay St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.hubinternational.com', '(416) 597-0008', '(416) 597-2313', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">HUB International Limited is a leading North American insurance brokerage and the largest middle market commercial insurance broker in Canada. It provides a broad array of property and casualty, life and health, employee benefits, reinsurance, investment and risk management products and services. HUB International is structured around large regional &ldquo;hubs&rdquo; with satellite offices strategically located throughout Canada and the U.S. HUB International HKMB is one such &ldquo;hub&rdquo;.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">When it comes to risk management, risk optimization and insurance, HUB HKMB clients know they will receive expert strategic guidance and the most current information.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">HUB HKMB provides seamless, multi-line service extending to every major commercial centre in the world. HUB HKMB&rsquo;s experience in the international arena allows us to handle placements of all sizes quickly and efficiently. &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1181, 1, 'Icon Advertising Inc.', 'info@iconadinc.com', '1500-701 Georgia St W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.iconadinc.com ', '(604) 726-4414', '(604) 726-3299', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Icon Advertising Inc. is a dynamic company based in Vancouver, Canada. We specialize in media buying services offering Research/ Planning, Buying, Maintenance and track company sustainability when buying online media. We offer media consulting services for start-up, medium to corporate businesses which is integral to optimize full market exposure whether you advertise local, national or international. Our copy and design team possess the talent , savvy and expertise in creating innovative campaigns for your type of product or service. Working in the field of advertising has enabled us to build and develop strategic alliances with media vendors in the industry enabling us to offer a wider variety of media vehicle selection for your campaigns. We offer assistance in product placement, program development (treatment), sponsorship, media relations, and assistance with distribution of market-ready productions for both film and television.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our objective is to provide a sophisticated and effective media buying service by ensuring the media meets your goals and budget media recommendations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1182, 1, 'J.D.Sweid Foods Ltd.', 'dbyrne@jdsweid.com', '9696, 199A St, LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.jdsweid.com ', '(604) 888-8662', '(604) 888-2523', '', '<p>&nbsp;Since our beginning back in 1917, our commitment to providing high quality products and service to our customers has been the core of our success.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>JD Sweid Foods is now one of the largest poultry and red meat further processors in Canada. We service both the retail and foodservice channels and offer high quality products that deliver on taste.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A privately owned Canadian company, JD Sweid Foods is successful due to our ability and commitment to working with and exceeding our customer&rsquo;s needs and expectations.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>At JD Sweid Foods, our commitment to quality comes through in all we do from our products to our people.</div>', ''),
(1183, 1, 'Keyin College Inc.', 'ralph@keyin.nf.net', '100 Brookfield Road, ST. JOHN\'S, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada', 'www.keyin.ca ', '(709) 753-2284', '(709) 753-2049', '', '<p>CHOOSING A CAREER PATH is one of the most important choices you will make. Explore all your options but follow the path that excites you and offers you the challenges that will continue to motivate you as you learn.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thank you for considering Keyin College as your pathway. Over the past 32 years, we have educated thousands of Newfoundlanders and Labradorians and proudly watched our graduates join the workplace across the world!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Keyin College believes in developing programs which broaden your technical and personal skills. We encourage our students to be community volunteers and supporters, to expand their network and increase self confidence. The real world can teach us so much!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our province is a wonderful place to live and work and there are so many opportunities for you right now. Choose wisely and ENJOY THE RIDE!</div>', ''),
(1184, 1, 'Learning English With Laughter Ltd', 'learning@efl-esl.com', '10-1030 Hulford St, VICTORIA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.esl-curriculum.ca ', '(250) 360-4098', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;We have a full line of ESL products that are in use in more than 70 countries. Our ESL Curriculum progresses from the English Alphabet to Modules for Beginners, High Beginners, Intermediate to Advanced. Each Module includes a Student Reader, Student Workbook and a Teacher\'s Guide. English vocabulary and grammar are introduced incrementally, the students participate in large and small group conversational activities.</p>', ''),
(1185, 1, 'Moneysworth & Best', 'admin@moneysworth-best.com', '120 Midair Crt., BRAMPTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.moneysworth-best.com ', '(905) 790-0650', '(905) 458-2480', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">M&amp;B Acquisition Incorporated operates two business platforms. The first is our shoe and foot care manufacturing and distribution business, and the second is our shoe repair business. The synergy of these two platforms is at the heart of our extraordinary success.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moneysworth &amp; Best develops, produces, distributes and markets over 750 shoe and foot care products to over 50,000 stores across North America and abroad. Our products are made of the finest quality materials sourced and used from around the world. Moneysworth &amp; Best products are initially tested and marketed in Moneysworth &amp; Best\'s own retail repair shops before being launched into the marketplace.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Moneysworth &amp; Best operates the largest franchised retail shoe repair chain in North America, offering a full range of shoe repair services, and shoe and foot care products. Our stores are located in high-traffic, high-visibility shopping centres, mixed-use properties, and stores-within-a-store in Loblaws Supercentres.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1186, 1, 'Ongoing Results Ltd.', 'sales@ongoingresults.com', '8-117 Ringwood Dr., STOUFFVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ongoingresults.com ', '(905) 642-3500', '(905) 642-3545', '', '<p>&nbsp;Ongoing Results&reg;, incorprated in 1983, is a 30 year old non franchised Canadian stocking distributor of popular commodity PC business application software packages specializes in the sale of high volume commodity PC software in both retail and OEM packages from the world\'s leading software publishers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company concentrates on business applications, including programming languages, database management products, antivirus solutions and internet and network application software.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Products stocked include current and superseded versions of many of the most popular business application software.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1187, 1, 'Pak Mail Pickering', 'pickering@pakmailcanada.com', '12-1064 Salk Rd, PICKERING, Ontario, Canada', 'www.pakmailcanada.com ', '(905) 837-2222', '(905) 837-8128', '', '<p>&nbsp;At PAK MAIL &quot;We Pack &amp; Ship Anything, Anywhere&quot;.</p>\r\n<div>Our network of over 500 one-stop retail centres in 5 countries provides custom packaging, crating &amp; fulfillment services plus domestic &amp; international shipping services to countless destinations.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We ship via major couriers, LTL carriers, air or sea cargo -- whatever meets the needs of our customers. We are perfectly positioned to handle the packaging &amp; shipping generated by internet auction site ecommerce transactions.</div>', ''),
(1188, 1, 'Rent A Box Moving Systems', 'info@movingstore.com', '222C Lesmill Rd, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.movingstore.com ', '(416) 789-4185', '(416) 789-0181', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Toronto\'s first moving supply one-stop-shop! Find all of your moving supplies here! From cardboard boxes, bubble wrap, peanuts, to the rental and sales of reusable plastic boxes, Rent a Boxx&trade; / The Moving Store&reg; has everything that you might need to move.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Unlike many of our competitors, all our products are guaranteed brand new-- we never accept old or used products back into our stock. We also offer a full-service experience, and are willing to go the extra mile to make sure you have a smoother move.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We\'ve moved recently to our new locaiton on Lesmill Road. Only 8 minutes north of our old location!<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1189, 1, 'SciCorp International Corp', 'info@scicorp.net', '15-220 Bayview Dr., Barrie, Ontario, Canada', 'www.scicorp.net ', '(705) 733-2626', '(705) 733-2618', '', '<p>&nbsp;SciCorp International Corp. was founded in 1989 to manufacture and distribute the a revolutionary Biologic line of wastewater treatment products and odor control products, developed originally by the principals. Biologic formulations of micronutrients facilitate the predominance of bacteria populations which are most desirable for biodegrading wastewater, sludge, and compost. Years of extensive testing by independent laboratories, U.S. and Canadian government agencies, and use in industrial applications have proven that SciCorp&rsquo;s unique, natural nutrient formulations solve a complete range of waste treatment problems. SciCorp products do not contaminate groundwater while they eliminate odors, accelerate natural processes, and dramatically increase the quality of wastewater, sludges, and compost. The Biologic family of products from SciCorp has established new standards in waste and wastewater treatment and has successfully been proven and marketed globally.</p>', ''),
(1190, 1, 'Superscope Media Inc', 'info@superscopemedia.com', '201-1262 Don Mills Rd , NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.superscopemedia.com ', '(416) 444-5456', '(416) 444-0253', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Superscope Media Inc. is a brand innovation company.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We create brands that have strong identities by providing innovative and original ideas. We then bring these brands to the forefront through inventive and creative processes, making them memorable and distinct. The end result is a brand that is a leader in its respected industry, well recognized, has a loyal following and can achieve higher profitability for a longer period of time.</p>', ''),
(1191, 1, 'Telpay Incorporated', 'sales@telpay.ca', '298 Garry St, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada ', 'www.telpay.ca ', '(204) 957-2800', '(204) 943-2261', '', '<p>&nbsp;For over 25 years, Canadian owned Telpay has delivered innovative, cost effective and secure electronic payment solutions that are an alternative to writing cheques to consumers, financial institutions and businesses. In 1985, Telpay was founded as a R&amp;D division of Comcheq Services, a payroll company started by W.H. (Bill) Loewen. From there, Telpay pioneered the first telephone bill payment service. Moving from telephones to computer and the Internet, Telpay has been constantly committed to improvement, Telpay has grown to be one of Canada\'s most trusted and largest independent electronic payment companies, processing over $24 billion in payments in 2013.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our flagship product, Telpay for Business was designed by accountants for accountants to move money electronically, as an alternative to writing a cheque. Compatible with all major accounting software, by using Telpay for Business, any business owner or accountant/bookkeeper can, right from their computer or personal electronic device, move money for:&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1192, 1, 'UView Ultraviolet Systems Inc.', 'sales@uview.com', '1324 Blundell Rd, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.uview.com ', '(905) 615-8620', '(905) 615-9745', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 23 years UView has been producing quality products that are built by technicians for technicians. UView designs, manufactures and delivers the most innovative and functional products in the automotive repair industry across North America and the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We manufacture products to solve problems. Our product engineering and design philosophy isn&rsquo;t about self-expression. It&rsquo;s about solving problems. UView products are winning awards because of their simplicity of purpose and impactful results.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UView has an extensive customer list under it&rsquo;s own brand and provides custom solutions on complete projects or any aspect of product research, design, manufacturing, calibration, testing to packaging for private label clients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The people that use our products are technicians and problem solvers; people who are incredibly tenacious at finding the source of a problem and then fixing them. Our award winning, internationally recognized products have revolutionized the automotive aftermarket industry by our ability to manufacture quality products at our ISO 9001-2008 certified manufacturing facility.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UView operates and manufactures out of Mississauga, Ontario, Canada allowing us to easily export product to customers throughout North America and the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UView and it\'s founders were recently profiled in The Canadian Business Journal.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1193, 1, 'Varty & Company', 'dvarty@smartt.com', '900-555 Burrard St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.vartylaw.ca ', '(604) 684-5356', '(604) 443-5001', '', '<p>&nbsp;We listen, gather information, and &nbsp;provide &nbsp;advice &nbsp;to &nbsp;meet your needs. Your success is enhanced &nbsp;by our &nbsp;hard &nbsp;work, preparation &nbsp;and &nbsp;imagination.</p>', ''),
(1194, 1, 'Web Site Advantage Inc.', 'office@wsadvantage.com', '5 MacAleer Dr, CHARLOTTETOWN, Prince Edward Island, Ca', 'www.wsadvantage.com ', '(902) 628-6229', '(902) 628-6938', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Web Site Advantage Inc. located in Charlottetown, PEI, is one of the most well-established website design and development companies in Prince Edward Island. In operation since 1997, we believe that the key to our continued success is simple: we put our clients first - always. From the initial website design consultation to the final launch of your customized website and beyond - we work with our clients from the very beginning, and every step along the way, to ensure that our finished design is just what you envisioned and that your custom website keeps working for you for years to come. We pride ourselves on our dedication to our clients and know that our work doesn&rsquo;t stop when the website is launched. And we think it shows - many of our current clients have been with us for over 10 years.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As a dynamic information technology company we are able to provide our clients with a solution for every web-based challenge they may face as a business. Our custom designed websites provide our clients with a wide-range of tools to make their day-to-day business as effortless as possible.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1195, 1, 'Xytera Electronics', 'info@xytera.com', '16 Daudet St, CANDIAC, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xytera.com ', '(450) 444-5441', '(450) 444-2798', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Xytera Electronics is a highly reputable broad line global component distributor specializing in highly allocated and obsolete products from integrated circuits to computer products. With a combined knowledge base of over 45 years of experience in electronics distribution (franchised &amp; non-franchised) and inventory management solutions, Xytera provides unmatched quality products and services to our customer base of OEMs, CEMs, brokers and distributors. Xytera currently manages inventory solutions for a wide range of clients from Fortune 500 companies to smaller manufacturers and distributors worldwide.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">One of Xytera\'s driving principles is to act as a trusted and reliable electronic distributor, world renowned for its customer service. Here at Xytera we understand the challenges buyers face when dealing with factory shortages to excess inventory. We have the necessary tools to develop customized solutions to fit your needs. We are considered one of the top Electronics Risk Management companies in the world. Xytera Electronics supplies both production quantity components as well as highly allocated and obsolete products. We are proud to say that we have maintained strong partnerships with over 2500 Manufacturers, Authorized Representatives, agents and distributors worldwide. We also offer customized inventory management solutions to OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) and CM (Contract Manufacturer) customers worldwide. Xytera works closely with manufacturers in numerous industries such as; Automotive, Communications, Aeronautics, Entertainment, Medical, Lighting, Security, Appliance and many more.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<br style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\" />\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Xytera has built a host of marketing intelligence tools in order to support our customers. This, coupled with services including contract procurement, quality assurance, inventory management, asset recovery/re-marketing, component testing and global logistics management provides our customers the benefit of Xytera\'s value added services. Xytera Electronics is an ISO 9001:2008 compliant company. &nbsp;</span></p>', ''),
(1196, 1, 'British Columbia Internet Association', 'admin@bcia.bc.ca', 'BCIT Technology Centre 3700 Willingdon Ave.,, Burnaby, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.bcit.ca', '(604)  434-8254', '(604)  436-0286', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The BCIA offers on-going advice, guidance, and support to individuals, small business, non-profit organizations, corporations, governments and institutions throughout the province. Monitoring and researching leading edge developments in the industry and sharing the information with our members and the general public puts the BCIA in the fast lane of the information highway.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Providing a forum for discussion among providers, developers, operators and carriers associated with the Internet through the hosting of two conferences per year is a key focus of the association.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1197, 1, 'Canadian Food Exporters Association', 'susanp@cfea.com', '885 Don Mills Road, Suite 301, Don Mills, Ontario , Canada', 'www.cfea.com', '(416)  445-3747', '(416)  510-8044', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CFEA is a voluntary non-profit industry association founded in September 1996 by a group of fourteen companies who felt the need for a resource focused on the enhancement of export efforts in the food and beverage industry, particularly (but not exclusively) on the part of small to medium-sized enterprises (SME\'s).&nbsp; The mission of the organization is to:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Increase the profitable export sales of food, beverage and ingredient products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Increase the number of small to medium-sized food, beverage and ingredient processors and manufacturers exporting.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Raise the international profile of Canadian food, beverage and ingredient products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The CFEA takes pride in offering programs and services that contributes to the success of our members and clients export initiatives. The CFEA makes every effort to ensure our members and clients participate only in programs in markets that hold potential for them. If you are unsure if a market is the right fit for your company please reach out to us for guidance. Your success is important to us!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To learn more about the association click on the links above or contact the association directly (click on the contact link to see the various ways to get in touch with us).<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1198, 1, 'CAMESE', 'ramshaw@camese.org', '101 - 345 Renfrew Drive, MARKHAM, Ontario, Canada', 'www.camese.org', '(905)  513-0046', '(905)  513-1834', '', '<p>&nbsp;The Canadian Association of Mining Equipment and Services for Export, is the national voice for Canada\'s mining equipment and service exporters. Its more than 250 corporate members across the country supply the entire mining industry spectrum including mineral exploration, mine development, mining, mineral processing, environmental monitoring, smelting and refining.</p>', ''),
(1199, 1, 'Canada Africa Business Council Inc.', 'cabci@connection.com', '24 Huddleston Court, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ccafrica.ca', '(416)  265-0081', '(416)  265-1776', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Canadian Council on Africa (CCAfrica) is the only Canadian organization dedicated to the economic development of Africa. It is a non-profit, membership-based organization established in 2002, the year of the Kananaskis G8 Summit, where the agenda included the development of a self-help plan for Africa.&nbsp; CCAfrica focuses on the future of African economy and the positive role that Canada can play in meeting some of the challenges in Africa.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CCAfrica&rsquo;s current members come from large, medium and small Canadian and African enterprises, education institutions such as universities and colleges, and agencies of the federal and provincial governments. With more than 150 active members in all sectors of the economy - infrastructure, education, legal, environmental, natural resources, energy, consulting engineering, construction, transportation, mining - and 4 offices across Canada- CCAfrica is essential when it comes to economic relations between Canada and Africa.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1200, 1, 'Canadian Manufacturers & Exporters', 'carolyn.conner@cme-mec.ca', '1 Nicholas St  Suite 1500 , Ottawa, Ontario, Canada', 'www.cme-mec.ca', '(613)  238-8888', '(613)  563-9218', '', '<p>&nbsp;Canadian Manufacturers and Exporters association represents almost the total of Canada\'s industrial output and export. CME offers networking opportunities, policy, advocacy, issue researches and conferences at national and provincial levels. Over the past seven years, CME members have been responsible for many of the new jobs created in the Canadian economy.</p>', ''),
(1201, 1, 'eCustoms', 'ahille@ecustoms.com', '2 Tippett Road, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'http://www.ecustoms.com/', '(416)  630-3000', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">eCustoms provides scalable Global Trade Management and Compliance solutions that enhance the speed, flexibility, visibility and assurance of global supply chains.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Long description: eCustoms&rsquo; solutions and services span the entire spectrum of trade compliance, including import documentation and ABI submissions (ABI certified and ACH capable), NAFTA certificates, export documentation (AES certified), Restricted and Denied Party Screening, DDTC/BIS Export License applications and management, as well as tariff classification (HS codes) and new initiatives such as the ACE (Automated Commercial Environment) program for U.S. importers.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1202, 1, 'Saadat Enterprises Inc.', 'bahram@globazaar.com', '#2811 Hialeah Court, Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(604)  941-3757', '(604)  941-3773', '', '<div><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, \'MS sans serif\'; font-size: 11px;\">Export/Import</span></div>', ''),
(1203, 1, 'Daniels Electronics Ltd.', 'lmrsales@codanradio.com', '43 Erie St., VICTORIA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.codanradio.com ', '(250) 382-8268', '(250) 382-6139', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Codan Radio Communications is a leading designer and manufacturer of premium communications equipment for High Frequency (HF) and Land Mobile Radio (LMR) applications. We&rsquo;ve built our reputation for reliability over 50 years in radio communications, in some of the toughest conditions on the planet.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Trusted by the world&rsquo;s largest mission critical security, military and humanitarian agencies, we relentlessly focus on high reliability, meaning you can count on us to not let you down.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our over-arching goal is absolute customer satisfaction, achieved through a unyielding focus on innovative design, product quality and global customer service which provides our customers the uncompromising reliability they need for their demanding missions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Codan Radio Communications offer a series of HF transceivers to meet any combination of portable, vehicular and base station requirements. When combined with our complete range of accessories, Codan&rsquo;s transceivers provide a wide range of advanced capabilities &ndash; from voice communications to data, email, fax, chat, GPS tracking, security and interoperability.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Codan Radio Communications, we pride ourselves on quality and reliability, giving you LMR analog and digital P25 radio systems that exceed industry standards and are renowned for their low power consumption, ruggedness and transportability, surviving in the harshest environments.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We make any Codan purchase an investment, rather than an expense, by innovating in ways that keep you current without increasing your cost. The Codan Envoy&trade; is the world&rsquo;s most advanced commercial HF radio and only HF radio that can future-proof your investment. With an upgradeable software defined architecture and broad suite of features (such as colour screen, USB Capability, and embedded modem), the Codan Envoy&trade; gives you what you need now, while we&rsquo;re working on what you&rsquo;ll need next.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From aid workers fighting famine to peacekeepers rebuilding lives, people all over the world count on Codan for communication.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1204, 1, 'DB International Logistics', 'info@dbdonyabar.com', '400-601 Broadway W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.dbdonyabar.com ', '(604) 675-6966', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">DB (Donya Bar) International Logistics Ltd, is a Canadian International Freight Forwarding and Shipping Agency company that provides worldwide freight services via air, ocean, truck and rail. We have internationally gained a fine reputation with our top quality service and unparalleled customer satisfaction.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With over 35 years of experience in the field of freight forwarding, DB has become a reliable solution for transportation. We provide globally integrated door to door services for our customers&rsquo; individual needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our team is dedicated and passionate about their work and we provide the following large range of services:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;- Project Freight Forwarding &amp; Logistics<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Heavy Haulage &amp; Over Dimensional Cargo<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Ocean/Barge/Air/Road/Rail Freight<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Route Surveys and Transport Planning<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Logistic Consultancy<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Vessel Chartering<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
