(1283, 1, 'F&R Steelcraft Industries Inc.', 'fredq@frsteelcraft.com', '3513F, 78 Ave SE, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.frsteelcraft.com ', '(403) 279-5133', '(403) 236-0623', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">F&amp;R Steelcraft Industries Inc. has been serving many different Industries since 1985, in areas of cryogenics, fabrication &amp; trailer services. During this period &ldquo;High Quality Workmanship&rdquo;, &ldquo;On Time Deliveries&rdquo; and &ldquo;Customer Satisfaction&rdquo; have been and will be the &ldquo;Top Priority&rdquo; of this company\'s management team.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more than 25 years, F&amp;R Steelcraft Industries Inc. has specialized in: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- cryogenic vessels and equipment (steel / stainless steel / aluminum); <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- metal fabrication (as above, plus copper / brass / galvanized metal) including milling, lathe work, welding, etc.; and <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- highway trailer (inspection / certification and repair). <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In the cryogenic arena, the Company holds an Alberta Boilers Safety Association (ABSA) Certificate of Authorization to: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- inspect / certify, repair / alter and construct pressure vessels in the shop (ASME Section VIII-1); and/or <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- construct, repair / alter ASME B31.1 and B31.3 pressure piping in the shop and field. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Such work invariably requires the use of &quot;B&quot; Pressure welding skills by our employees and F&amp;R has become a leading facility for the provision of complete cryogenic services to a variety of industries, including: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- industrial gas suppliers; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- oil and gas (producers and service providers, alike); <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- chemical producers <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- health care; and <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- food services.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Other Corporate qualifications include: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Transport Canada Certificate of Registration (as a facility for the manufacture, modification, assembly, repair, test / retest or inspection of highway tanks and portable tanks in accordance with CSA Standard B620; <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Federal Department of Transport (MV Safety Act Sec 4(2), MV Safety Regulations Sec 3(4) and Ministerial Authorization; as well as <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Commercial Vehicle Inspection (Alberta) --- &quot;CVIP&quot;. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To ensure that clients receive supperior quality service and products, the Company has designed and implemented a registered Quality Program and all activities are executed in accordance with the applicable codes (above and ASME Nondestructive Examinations Sec V).<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1284, 1, 'Fab-Form Industries Ltd.', 'info@fab-form.com', '19-1610 Derwent Way, DELTA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.fab-form.com', '(604) 596-3278', '', '', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.9999990463257px;\">Fab-Form Industries Ltd. is a manufacturer of fabric forms for concrete and accessories for the ICF (insulated concrete form) industries.</span></p>', ''),
(1285, 1, 'Fabco Plastics (Western) Ltd.', 'edmonton@fabcoplastics.com', '12938 148 St, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.fabcoplastics.com ', '(780) 451-0238', '(780) 455-4816', '', '<p>&nbsp;Fabco Plastics is a supplier of thermoplastic products designed for use in corrosion resistant fluid processing systems. &nbsp;Our product offering comes from some of the leading domestic and international manufacturers of industrial plastics. &nbsp;Our product line includes pipe, fittings, valves, pumps, tanks, sheet, tubing, fans, rod, ducting, filters, grating and other products. &nbsp;These products are available in PVC, CPVC, PP, PVDF, PE and other specialized plastic materials.</p>', ''),
(1286, 1, 'Fabricated Plastics Limited', 'info@fabricatedplastics.com', '2175 Teston Rd, MAPLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fabricatedplastics.com ', '(905) 832-8161', '(905) 832-2111', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fabricated Plastics is the Leader In Plastics through a continuing commitment to explore and test all new plastic materials, acquire state-of-the-art plastic processing equipment, sourcing of plastic commodities in the international marketplace and innovative engineering and utmost quality in manufacturing.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Founded in 1962 and headquartered in Maple (Toronto) Canada,Fabricated Plastics is one of the Denali Companies which include, Ershigs Inc., CSI Containment Solutions Inc. and Belco Manufacturing Co., Inc.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1287, 1, 'Fabrimet inc', 'technique@fabrimet.com', '4375 Saint-Joseph Blvd, DRUMMONDVILLE, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.fabrimet.com ', '(819) 472-1164', '(819) 478-1625', '', '<p>&nbsp;Fabrimet has become one of the most modern and efficient producers of steel structures in North America with a capacity of 45,000 metric tonnes of tower steel and an additional capacity for switchyard and foundation steel.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Since the early 1960 we have been producing steel structures for transmission lines and substations. Fabrimet was begun as a division of GENERAL MFG. Co. Ltd., a company founded in 1942. In 1978 the division became an independant &nbsp;company and has been operating under the name of FABRIMET inc. ever since. Fabrimet has specialized particularly in the fabrication of galvanized lattice steel towers for the electrical transmission industry.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Fabrimet has become one of the most modern and efficient producers of steel structures &nbsp;in North America with a capacity of 35,000 metric tonnes of tower steel and an additional capacity for switchyard and foundation steel.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Fabrimet name is recognized by utilities and engineering firms alike for our quality steel products, on time delivery and trouble-free field erection.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The meeting of excellence, the quality and the effectiveness of the products and services are the principal concern of FABRIMET Inc. Our vast experience in this field of activity has become our seal of excellence.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Fabrimet Inc. is a responsible company which guarantees to its customers a product which meets its specified quality and delivery requirements.</div>', ''),
(1288, 1, 'Factonics Inc.', 'destefan@isys.ca', '1936 Hunter St., SUDBURY, Ontario, Canada', '', '(705) 522-2606', '(705) 522-0824', '', '<p>&nbsp;Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Service.</p>', ''),
(1289, 1, 'Fazio Foods International Ltd.', 'fjlau@faziofoods.com', '1050 Glen Dr., VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.faziofoods.com ', '(604) 253-2668', '(604) 253-5535', '', '<p>&nbsp;Based in beautiful Vancouver, BC, Canada, Fazio Foods International Ltd. has been a trusted name in the food industry serving domestic and international customers for over 25 years. &nbsp;Fully Canadian owned and operated, we offer a full line of vegetable oils, mayonnaise, salad dressings, spreads, sauces and dips. &nbsp;And if you prefer a specific flavour profile, Fazio Foods has the capability to match or create a product to meet your specifications.</p>\r\n<div>We are fully committed to providing quality products and services to our customers. Fazio Foods realizes the importance of establishing a reputation built on integrity, reliability, and dependability with each customer and manufacturer in every market we service. &nbsp;We believe that customer service, competitive pricing and the ability to keep pace with the dynamic food industry are the necessary ingredients to ensure complete satisfaction.</div>\r\n<div>Our commitment to using only premium ingredients is evident in the quality and exceptional taste of our products.</div>\r\n<div>&ldquo;We are fully committed to helping you enhance the quality &ndash; &ndash; and success &ndash; &ndash; of your business.&rdquo;</div>', ''),
(1290, 1, 'FBI (Finance & Business Institute)', 'info@fbibusiness.com', '109-246 Roslyn Rd, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.fbibusiness.com ', '(204) 237-9878', '(204) 231-5583', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FBI (Finance &amp; Business Institute) was established 15 years ago to help businesses find the funding &amp; information they need to grow their business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Large, Small or home based businesses all need cash flow to function profitably.&nbsp; FBI can help with business financing of almost any kind.&nbsp; There are several funders with money waiting to finance the right business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The first and most important thing you must realize is no one will lend you money because you are a &quot;nice guy&quot; and have a &quot;great idea&quot; unless he knows you or has more money than he knows what to do with. There are millions or &quot;great ideas&quot; but they do not mean anything.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">You must have some way to pay them back.&nbsp; Just like any business, a lender has a product or service which in this case is lending money.&nbsp; They must get their money back plus interest or a return on their investment (ROI).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For that reason, you will have to show them how you will do that and your business must have a good business plan or history to show that it will be able to provide the returns expected. They will do their Due Diligence which will include verifying your credit report information and ther financial statements, before lending you money.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Dick Brown, in his article &quot;Mastering Due Diligence&quot; states:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&quot;So, before any entrepreneur approaches any potential investor, they need a full, complete plan for how they\'ll: turn their idea into reality; the reality into a highly profitable business: and, the highly profitable business into liquidly for all the participants and investors.&quot;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1291, 1, 'FBT Inc.', 'sales@fbtinc.ca', '413 Lakeshore Rd R.R. 6, ST CATHARINES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fbtinc.ca ', '(905) 937-3333', '(905) 937-1381', '', '<p>For over six decades FBT has focused on understanding customer needs in order to provide optimal manufacturing solutions. We use our proven engineering and technical capabilities to produce precision components, tooling and stampings. Our products and services combine traditional practices and modern techniques which are utilized by leading manufacturers around the world.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1292, 1, 'FCI Molded Products Inc.', 'sales@fcimoldedproducts.com', '550 Applewood Cres. Building 1, CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fcimoldedproducts.com ', '(905) 660-1784', '(905) 669-0261', '', '<p>&nbsp;For almost two decades FCI&rsquo;s knowledgeable staff have supplied Caps, Glides and Levelers on rapid turnaround to the furniture industry. Now the largest stocking distributer in Canada, our inventory is constantly expanding and we own the tooling for many of our plastic and nylon parts. Need something from scratch? We manufacture hundreds of custom parts for our customers in almost any colour. In-stock and on-time, FCI is committed to keeping your business moving.</p>', ''),
(1293, 1, 'FCV Technologies Ltd.', 'info@fcv.ca', '1800-121 King St W , TORONTO, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.fcv.ca ', '(604) 662-8407', '(604) 662-8409', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our roots go deep in technology. But our business has always been about people<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From our beginnings in travel and tourism, we\'ve become the largest independent digital agency in BC with our unique mix of characteristics: we&rsquo;re straightforward, smart and proactive.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Every day we set out to uncover new digital opportunities that make life better. We reveal insights that strengthen your core value proposition, delight your customers and grow your business. And we deliver this with our proven expertise in service design, experiences &amp; content and platforms and integration.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We\'re ready to seize every chance to elevate and differentiate our client brands with great digital service experiences.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At our disposal are smarter devices, seamless technologies and data beyond imagining. Let\'s use it all to surprise and delight our ever-more connected users.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1294, 1, 'FD Canada', 'info@fdcanada.ca', '201-2530 Wilfrid-Hamel Blvd., QUEBEC, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.fdcanada.ca', '(418) 840-0332', '(418) 626-3363', '', '<p>FD Canada a pour objectif d&rsquo;&ecirc;tre un leader mondial du stockage en ligne www.stocklii.com et ainsi donner au Canada sa place dans ce domaine. FD Canada poss&egrave;de &eacute;galement un service d\'h&eacute;bergement Web et une &eacute;quipe de conception Web : sites, boutique en ligne, intranet, extranet, identit&eacute; visuelle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Nos services d\'h&eacute;bergement (production et d&eacute;veloppement) et de stockage en ligne fonctionnent sur des serveurs DELL PowerEdge SC1435, des unit&eacute;s de stockage Sans Digital ER104CT EliteRAID et des disques durs GreenPower Technologie Western Digital WD20EADS Caviar Green.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Nos services, sites et logiciels Web sont d&eacute;velopp&eacute;s avec la suite Adobe Photoshop et fonctionnent gr&acirc;ce la technologie Apache, PHP/MySQL. Toutes nos applications sont d&eacute;velopp&eacute;es de mani&egrave;re &ecirc;tre utilisables sans installation/configuration et sont compatibles Windows, Mac et Linux.&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1295, 1, 'FD Plastics Canada Corp.', 'ekodis@fdplastics.com', '742 Renaud, DORVAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fdplastics.com ', '(514) 341-1414', '(514) 631-4938', '', '<p>&nbsp;FD Plastics Canada is a custom Additive and Color Concentrate manufacturer based in Montreal, Quebec. We distinguish ourselves by providing high value and quality service.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1296, 1, 'FEA Corp.', 'sales@feawater.com', '1647 Markham Rd, MONT-ROYAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.feawater.com ', '(514) 526-1490', ' (514) 526-0845', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Future Energy Alliance (FEA) is a water storage&nbsp; solution company, which Specializes in the design, supply and erection of pre_engineered sectional steel water tanks. FEA Water Tanks is a combination of the most up to date research, engineering and manufacturing practice, and use only premium materials to give our client a durable tank of the utmost quality<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our know_how to design and engineer water tank will enable us to supply and provide a custom detailed product and ensure that each and every requirement, no matter how specific, can be tackled. FEA Water Tanks are used in a wide<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FEA storage water tanks are continually developed in term of design and manufacturing to meet the highest market expectation. We are meeting demands and requirements of projects for some of the largest and top corporation around the world. We are committed to working with customers by supplying water tank turnkey solutions and providing them with a 10 year warranty<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FEA qualified team of engineers and technicians support the design, manufacturing, supply, installation and after sales support of our water tanks. We are proud as company to offer the best water conservation and storage system for all applications &amp; environments.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1297, 1, 'Feathercraft Products Ltd.', 'info@feathercraft.com', '4-1244 Cartwright St., VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.feathercraft.com ', '(604) 681-8437', '(604) 681-7282', '', '<p>&nbsp;A Feathercraft kayak is the sum of many talented people, the highest quality materials, and exceptional customer support. Each kayak is hand-made by individuals who take care and pride in their workmanship.</p>', ''),
(1298, 1, 'FF EXPRESS', 'dispatch@ffexpress.ca', '1-1370 Sandhill Dr., ANCASTER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ffexpress.ca ', '(905) 648-9300', '(905) 648-9301', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FF EXPRESS started in 1994 with one 5 ton truck working for a local courier company. Over the following years FFX grew to 6 straight trucks and obtained its own running authorities. We became completely independent in May 1999 and have obtained some very loyal, satisfied customers in LTL and emergency expedited freight. Within only a few years we become known as &quot;one of the best&quot; if not the best, in the trucking industry. This is because of the quality of our drivers and our no nonsense, honest approach.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In a highly competitive market place and with rising operation costs, the only way to succeed in this business is to rise above the&nbsp; rest. As in ANY service oriented operation, if the customers not satisfied with the service they go elsewhere. Everyone within our organization is well aware of this fact, unlike other companies; we will not make any unrealistic promises.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We understand that when you are booking your shipment with us we are representing you and your reputation. Your commitments to your customers become our commitments to you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In our operation department each dispatcher is responsible for their own specific vehicles and service areas. This allows the dispatcher to properly maintain available space and pick up / delivery requirements for each shipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All Our drivers are contracted owner / operators earning a percentage of the freight they move. They too understand the importance in doing what we say and following through with all promises made.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Each driver is equipped with a cell phone and satellite tracking. Our drivers are required to update us at each pick up / delivery and in turn, we will notify you via email and or direct phone call whatever fits your specific needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Relaying information from our drivers to you is critical with hourly check calls we always know where your freight is 24 hours&nbsp; a day. At FF Express our name is our future.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Delivering&nbsp; what we promise is essential in our day to day operations.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1299, 1, 'FF Soucy WB L.P.', 'jeanblais@ff.papierswhitebirch.com', '191, rue Delage, RIVIERE-DU-LOUP, Quebec, Canada', 'www.papierswhitebirch.com/en/p2.html ', '(418) 862-6941', '(418) 867-1134', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today BD White Birch Paper Investment LLC operates four pulp and paper mills under the White Birch Paper name; three in Canada and<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">one in the United States of America. Together, these mills produce more than<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">1.3 million tons of newsprint and directory paper with up to 50 percent recycled content.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Headquartered in Greenwich, Connecticut, White Birch Paper manufactures and ships paper products to customers in North America and all over the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1300, 1, 'FGL Precision Works Inc.', 'contact@fglmolds.com', '475 Fenmar Dr., NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fglmolds.com ', '(647) 288-1212', '(647) 288-1220', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With over 40 years of experience behind it, FGL has built a worldwide reputation, in the mold making community, as a leader in design and manufacturer of tooling for the plastics industry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Utilizing a full range of CAD/CAM and CNC equipment allows FGL to cater to all of its customers\' needs.</p>', ''),
(1301, 1, 'FGT Consultants in Management, Education and Technology Inc.', 'info@fgt.com', '1175 Tecumseh St, DOLLARD-DES-ORMEAUX, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fgt.com ', '(514) 285-1100', '(514) 421-4254', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FGT was founded in 1987, by the current President, Jean-Marie Fahmy, whose background in strategic planning, management by projects, administration, consulting, coaching, telecommunication implementing, guided the firm to amplify its expertise.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The FGT Team is personally dedicated to take you along your success. We support you in setting up a working approach, which aims to always meet your strategic demands as a team and projects. Through practical and active experience of its instructors, FGT will guide you, your team, your organization, to obtain fulfillment on your expected results, through a Training service, an escort by Coaching, or through a direct intervention and Consulting within your company.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our clients can all testify they encountered a significant improvement in productivity thanks to their partnership with FGT.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FGT\'s mission is to help clients achieve their strategic goals by allowing to tame and use its Management by project approach.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1302, 1, 'FH Studio', 'info@fh-studio.com', '1410 William St, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fh-studio.com ', '(514) 989-7763', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fh studio produces video and photography content for both blue-ship and emerging brands, from small domestic businesses to huge multi-national conglomerates.&nbsp; Whoever they are, we help them to tell their story whether on screen or on print.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">All your needs met in one place. We adapt to your project, offering creative solutions and an expert approach to reach your goals.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This is what we live for at FH Studio.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1303, 1, 'FI Oilfield Services Canada', 'halifax@ficanada.com', '20 Mount Hope Ave, DARTMOUTH, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.ficanada.com', '(902) 481-8880', '(902) 433-1553', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FI Canada is a leading supplier of complete casing and tubing running services: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Casing Power Tongs <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Tubing Power Tongs with Integral Back-ups <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Computer Torque Monitoring <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- FC-1 and FC-2 Fillup Tools <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Pick Up/Laydown Equipment <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Power Thread Washers <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Thread Protector Recycling <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">- Connection make-up supervision services<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1304, 1, 'Fibertec Window & Door Mfg', 'fibertec@fibertec.com', '280 Bowes Rd, CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fibertec.com ', '(905) 660-7102', '(905) 660-6581', '', '<p>&nbsp;Fibertec Fiberglass Windows and Doors Manufacturing is a recognized leader in the fiberglass windows and doors industry. We provide one of the most comprehensive lines of high performance energy efficient windows and doors in North America. Fibertec provides uncompromising quality fiberglass frames that offer energy efficiency and beauty combined, with a lifetime warranty to guarantee the quality of our products. Fibertec&rsquo;s fiberglass windows and doors provides durable, reliable, thermally efficient and cost-effective fiberglass windows and doors.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Fibertec\'s production headquarters for fiberglass window and door manufacturing is located in Concord (just outside of Toronto), Canada from which our fiberglass windows and doors are shipped internationally. To ensure that we manufacture only the highest performing windows and doors, our products are tested regularly to maintain the highest energy ratings that meet or exceed the standard requirements in the industry. Our in-house, IGMAC certified sealed unit glass manufacturing allows us to achieve top quality fiberglass windows that outperform all others.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With highly experienced technical support, Fibertec&rsquo;s windows and doors are recognized as the most energy efficient windows in the industry by meeting and exceeding Energy Star criteria and LEED requirements. Fibertec&rsquo;s high performance windows include the following styles: casement, awning, double hung tilt, bay and bow windows, single hung, picture(fixed) and custom styles. Energy efficient doors include: fiberglass patio doors, fiberglass sliding doors and fiberglass entrance doors.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>At Fibertec, we provide the most durable, reliable and thermal efficient windows and doors in North America. The pultruded fiberglass framing systems at Fibertec, preserve the overall performance of windows and doors by providing superior insulation in extreme environments (heat, cold or highly corrosive), high condensation resistance, superior strength to weight ratios and high glass to frame ratios. Fibertec is the only company within the fiberglass industry to manufacturer a solid fiberglass entrance door frame &amp; slab.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>From fabrication, to finish, to shipping, we develop high glass-to-resin content to ensure our windows and doors preserve strength, durability and performance. Whatever the weather, whatever the pressure, Fibertec offers a complete range of benefits that meet or exceed Energy Star and LEED criteria, and offer the strongest support and best insulation. Get the most energy efficient windows and doors in the industry with Fibertec.</div>', ''),
(1305, 1, 'FjordTech Industrie Inc.', 'joseeb@fjordtech.qc.ca', '2760, boul. Grande Baie N, LA BAIE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fjordtech.ca ', '(418) 544-7091', '(418) 544-3739', '', '<p>&nbsp;Fjordtech Industry is expanding. &nbsp;It designs, manufactures &nbsp;and installs welded parts for various types of industrial activities. &nbsp;Our whole workforce differentiates Fjortech from others and allows it to be the outright leader in our industrial field of expertise. &nbsp;Engineers, draughtsmen, welders and mechanics constantly demonstrate their compentence by giving the highest quality service. &nbsp;Passion! &nbsp;It is the heart and soul of our accomplishments!</p>', ''),
(1306, 1, 'Flagro Industries Limited', 'flagro@flagro.on.ca', '26 Benfield Dr., ST CATHARINES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.flagro.on.ca ', '(905) 685-4243', '(905) 685-0113', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Flagro Industries Limited has been manufacturing propane, natural gas, and oil fired temporary heating equipment in St.Catharines, Ontario, Canada for over 30 years. Founded by Bruce Watson in 1978, Flagro remains a privately owned company offering a wide spectrum of gas and oil related products to both business and consumers from their office and plant near the U.S. border.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The product line has expanded many times over the years to include a comprehensive array of propane, natural gas, and oil fired temporary heaters, liquid and vapour propane burners and torches, air movers and roofing and road maintenance equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Flagro manufactures the Silver Giant commercial gas grill product line for the hospitality and rental industries. Flagro also designs and manufactures specialty equipment and burner systems to specific customer applications. Every product manufactured by Flagro is tested by qualified technicians before it is shipped from the plant to ensure that it meets applicable regulatory and safety standards.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1307, 1, 'Flagship Automotive Inc', 'hollis@nbnet.nb.ca', '1899 Main St W, MONCTON, New Brunswick, Canada', 'www.flagshipauto.ca ', '(506) 389-8884', '(506) 389-3357', '', '<p>&nbsp;Our company is in the automotive industry manly export/import of all type off vehicles to from any country possible. We are a wholesale company with a very good reputation and are gold is to become one of New Brunswick best company one customer at the time.</p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br />\r\n</span></div>', ''),
(1308, 1, 'Fleetwood Metal Industries Inc', 'common@fleetwoodmetal.com', '1885 Blackacre Dr, OLDCASTLE, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.fleetwoodmetal.com ', '(519) 737-1919', '(519) 737-1690', '', '<p>&nbsp;Since its inception in 1938, Fleetwood Metal Industries has continued</p>\r\n<div>to evolve to meet and exceed the technological trends.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Fleetwood capabilities focus on state-of-the art metal stamping and welding technologies, controlled by highly trained operators. Fleetwood houses over 60 presses that range from 250 to 2,000 tons for blanking, forming and drawing. Our advanced robotic mig and spot welding capabilities ensure the kind of quality that exceeds industry standards.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>What\'s more, an integrated Quality Assurance department monitors quality levels, using the latest in precision-testing equipment. Our advancement in forming simulation and CATIA design is moving Fleetwood to the forefront of high strength material part production.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The bottom line is superb quality - the kind of quality that has earned Fleetwood ratings far better then the industry norms.</div>', ''),
(1309, 1, 'FMC Technologies Canada Ltd.', 'harman.dhaliwal@fmcti.com', '1000-333 11 Ave SW 10th floor, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', 'www.fmcti.com ', '(403) 262-4000', '(403) 237-9728', '', '<p>&nbsp;FMC Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: FTI) is the global market leader in subsea systems and a leading provider of technologies and services to the oil and gas industry. We help our customers overcome their most difficult challenges, such as improving shale operations and subsea production performance to reduce cost, maintain uptime, and maximize oil and gas recovery. Named by Forbes&reg; Magazine as one of the World&rsquo;s Most Innovative Companies in 2013, the company has more than 20,000 employees and operates 30 production facilities in 17 countries. Follow us on Twitter @FMC_Tech for more information.</p>\r\n<p>Our Innovative Technologies, proven reliability and customer support increase production and reduce the cost of offshore oilfields.</p>\r\n<p>Our technologies and worldwide service locations help operators boost well site performance, savings and safety.</p>\r\n<p>Our top performing equipment and integrated services respond to customers&rsquo; technical, economic and safety challenges.</p>', ''),
(1310, 1, 'FMS X-Ray Services', 'fmsxray@uniserve.com', '303 - 8352 - 130 St, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.fmsxray.com ', '(604) 664-7757', '(604) 581-4589', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are here to assist you with all your x-ray a radiography needs. We offer Digital x-ray equipment, ultrasound equipment and other cutting-edge x-ray systems.&nbsp; We also offer processors, chemistry, x-ray film and accessories at competitive prices. We have been serving Canada and British Columbia healthcare professionals for over three decades and have built a reputation for reliability and excellence in this complex and exacting field among&nbsp; Hospitals, doctor\'s offices, chiropractors and veterinarians.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FMS X-Ray is a BC owned organization that has been serving BC healthcare professionals for over three decades and has built a reputation for reliability and excellence in this complex and exacting field among Regional and District Hospitals, doctor\'s offices, chiropractors, dentists as well as veterinarian clinics / hospitals. Service contracts are provided with and without an associated equipment sale.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Incorporated in British Columbia, Canada since 1980, Originally known as Excel Medical Systems, FMS X-RAY (a division of Excel Professional Services, EPS) and its founder Fred J. Fischer, have dedicated over thirty years to sales, servicing, reconditioning, installing and calibrating medical diagnostic imaging equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FMS X-Ray has built a reputation for reliability and excellence in this complex and exacting field. From the onset, Mr. Fischer pioneered the concept of a highly focused, micro-corporation offering to the medical profession viable alternatives to the high cost of equipment purchases and service contracts in the specialized fields of medical diagnostic imaging equipment. At that time, virtually all contracts were handled by large firms such as Siemens, General Electric, Philips, and Picker. Such corporations, with their large infrastructures and overhead, had a significant negative impact on the scant financial resources available for the propagation of quality medical and diagnostic products and services. FMS X-Ray&rsquo;s vision was to provide cost-effective alternative solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Mr. Fischer broke this de facto monopoly by challenging the parts supply policies of the larger manufacturing firms, and by painstakingly establishing himself and his organization as a technically and operationally competent service organization.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to challenging the status quo in the industry, FMS X-Ray has diversified its client base among hospitals, doctors, veterinarians, dentists, physiotherapists and chiropractors, and has established a well deserved high reputation in both service and sales. Service contracts, which are provided both with and without an associated equipment sale, form a significant portion of Excel&rsquo;s business.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1311, 1, 'Foam Geometrix Inc', 'info@foamgeometrix.ca', '27 Terry Fox Dr., VANKLEEK HILL,, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.foamgeometrix.ca ', '(613) 678-5111', '(613) 678-5110', '', '<p>&nbsp;Foam Geometrix specializes in the design and manufacturing of EPS moulds for the refractory precast industry. Moulds and inserts are made for many precast shapes including burner blocks, deltas, runners, tundishes, lifters as well as elbow and duct inserts.</p>', ''),
(1312, 1, 'FoamPackaging', 'sales@foampackaging.ca', '2166 Scottscraig Dr., OSHAWA, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.foampackaging.ca ', '(905) 723-5532', '(905) 732-3781', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Expanded Polystyrene (EPS) packaging material is specifically designed and intended for use as an Economical and Quality Packaging solution.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Product Reliability: All EPS used in packaging fabrication is UL approved and has fire retardant additives incorporated at the time of manufacture. Many materials such as wood, paper, cloth, vinyl, etc., will ignite at much lower temperatures than EPS. Without a source of energy EPS will self extinguish.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Chemical Resolution: EPS is resistant to virtually all aqueous media, including dilute acids and alkalis, water soluble alcohols and silicones. There is limited resistance to paraffin oil, vegetable oils, diesel fuel and Vaseline. EPS must not be exposed to organic solvents such as hydrocarbons, chlorinated hydrocarbons, ketones and esters. Note: If EPS is placed in contact with materials or vapors of unknown composition, tests should be made to determine compatibility.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Toxicity: Laboratory combustible product test indicate EPS is no more toxic than wood and minimal ingestion is not considered harmful.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Bacterial Resistance: EPS without soilage will not support fungus and bacteria growth. It is also inert, odorless, non-irritating and non corrosive<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ozone Friendly: EPS contains no CFCs or HCFCs known to deplete the ozone layer.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Environment: The Canadian Environmental Protection Act excludes Polystyrene from regulations controlling Polyurethane and Other Foam Sector. Adequate Polystyrene recycling facilities are readily available.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1313, 1, 'Food Safety Solutions Canada Inc', 'nfo@fssc.bizi', '6123 Coxswain Cres., Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fssc.biz ', '(647) 523-7006', '(905) 997-7006', '', '<p>&nbsp;Food Safety Solutions Canada Inc is part of the Global Food Safety Consultants Alliance, with over 15 years of service to the food, packaging, personal care and pharmaceutical industries. We provide consulting, auditing, training, and outsourcing services that go beyond assurance of food safety and quality. Our mission is to assist organizations get certified to the GFSI benchmarked standards (SQF, BRC, FSSC/ ISO 22000) through reliable and user friendly programs that contribute to continual improvement and profitability. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1314, 1, 'FPC Flexible Packaging Corporation', 'rthangavelu@fpcflexible.com', '1891 Eglinton Ave E, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fpcflexible.com ', '(416) 288-3060', '(416) 288-0808', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FPC Flexible Packaging is an industry leader in the production and conversion of flexible packaging including laminated and printed multilayered substrates of paper, film and foil. We utilize high quality rotogravure and flexography printing<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We serve manufacturers and packagers of pharmaceutical &amp; healthcare, confectionery, food, dairy and tobacco products<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FPC has been serving its customers since 1922, and currently employs 80 people in a 250,000 square foot converting facility located on the east side of Toronto<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We at FPC are proud of our converting facility, and of our ongoing commitment to service and quality. We encourage our customers to visit our facility for a tour and discussion. It is also of particular benefit to have reciprocal plant personnel visits, which help us to better understand our customers\' requirements allowing us to better serve them with quality products.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1315, 1, 'FPS Fluid Power Solutions Inc.', 'sales@fluidpowersolutions.ca', '824 Crowley Ave, KELOWNA, British Columbia, Canada ', '', '(250) 763-4333', '(250) 763-4367', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are a complete fluid power company providing sales, service, repair, design and installation hydraulic, pneumatic and lubrication equipment and systems. We are a full line Parker authorized distributor for industrial products, mobile products and hose and fittings. We are also an authorized Graco warranty and repair center for industrial lubrication pumps, meters, reels and automated lube systems. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our business is to make your business more profitable through more productive, reliable systems. Higher production and less downtime. We have complete inhouse repair capabilities. We specialize in servo and proportional systems particularly Bosch/Rexroth products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">If your hydraulics are not performing to your satisfaction we will provide you with a solution. Sawmill, Plywood, Mining, Construction, Drilling systems to name a few of the industries we provide customized solutions for. Hot Press applications, Veneer Lathes, Setworks, Water Well Drilling, Hydro-Vacs, and more.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1316, 1, 'Fraco Products Ltd', 'fraco@fraco.com', '91, ch. des Patriotes, SAINT-MATHIAS-SUR-RICHELIEU, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fraco.com ', '(450) 658-0094', '(450) 658-8905', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fraco is a Canadian manufacturer of mast guided access equipment. Its range of products includes work platforms, construction elevators, industrial lifts, material only hoists and transport platforms.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established in 1991, Fraco is one of the early pioneers in the North American mast climbing industry. Those years of experience have led Fraco to develop a high level of flexible quality products and an expertise that exceeds our clients expectations throughout the marketplace. Constant innovation and close customer relationships have cemented Fraco&rsquo;s reputation as a leader in the North American mast climbing industry. Our manufacturing presence in other international markets expands this footprint to a global level.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Originally conceived with mason&rsquo;s needs in mind, Fraco&rsquo;s range of equipment has evolved and now finds itself key to numerous other sectors of the construction industry (residential, commercial, institutional, industrial, etc.). Other non-building sectors such as power generation, infrastructures, and mining are also targeted. Fraco&rsquo;s equipment is offered to general and specialized contractors through our broad distribution network.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">FRACO AT A GLANCE: located in St-Mathias-sur-Richelieu, Quebec (25 km south of Montreal), 125 employees, 62,000 feet 2 (5,760 m 2 ) of plant facility, Two branches in Canada (Montreal, QC - Toronto, ON) and three in United States (Baltimore, MD - Sacramento, CA - Detroit, MI). Six distributors in Canada and over 15 in United States. Also present in France, United Kingdom, Germany, Belgium, Netherland, Poland, India, Middle East, Ta&iuml;wan</span></p>', ''),
(1317, 1, 'Framecraft Ltd', 'framecraft@framecraftltd.com', '2485, First St Louth, ST CATHARINES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.framecraftltd.com ', '(905) 682-7044', '(905) 682-6140', '', '<p>&nbsp;Manufacturer of wooden picture frames, Certificate Frames, Frames for Awards and Recognition, Distributor of Neilsen Metal Mouldings, Bainbridge Matboards &amp; Peterboro Matboards</p>', ''),
(1318, 1, 'FSA Architectures Inc', 'info@fsa-arch.qc.ca', '550-1470 Peel St Tower A, MONTRÉAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.fsa-arch.qc.ca ', '(514) 849-1277', '(514) 849-1200', '', '<p>&nbsp;FSA ARCHITECTURE inc. is a Canadian company based in Montreal. Noted for its distinct experience in the realization of important projects, the firm offers full integrated services in planning, design and construction of a wide range of specialized projects. The AIRPORT, HEALTH and EDUCATION divisions brings together a team of architects and technicians working for 30 years in these specific sectors. These teams collaborate with many specialists using the latest technologies to meet the constantly evolving needs of a wide variety of clients. This continuous collaboration with recognized specialists allows us to offer our clients a wide range of services. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1319, 1, 'fSONA Networks Corp', 'info@fsona.com', '100-13200 Delf Place, RICHMOND, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.fsona.com   ', '(604) 273-6333', '(604) 273-6351', '', '<p>&nbsp;Intelligent innovation is at the core of fSONA\'s corporate mission. At our research and development headquarters in Richmond, BC we continue to push the boundaries of free space optics technology to develop the next generation of short-haul broadband communications solutions for a wide range of markets and applications.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>fSONA has assembled a superlative laser communications team, whose depth and breadth of knowledge is unrivalled in the private sector. Most of our senior engineering and management personnel have backgrounds in space-based and military optical communications systems, where extremely high reliability is an essential element of the overall product specification. This background is the foundation of our fundamental design philosophy, which places a strong emphasis on superior product reliability and quality, supported by a world-class engineering and manufacturing capability.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>fSONA has brought together a team of wireless, communications and optics industry experts that includes some of the world\'s leading laser communications professionals. Our experts chair or sit on many boards, including SPIE Free Space Laser Communication Technologies, the Free Space Optics Alliance and the IEC international laser safety standards committee. Our team collectively holds eight patents, with two more applications underway.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>This outstanding design and engineering capability is backed up by a global commitment to customer service. Whether you plan to build an entire mesh network or simply connect two locations, our network of partners and affiliates stand ready to tailor connectivity solutions for you - anywhere in the world. We offer complete on-site training, installation and service, ensuring immediate attention to your pressing networking needs.</div>', ''),
(1320, 1, 'FTG Aerospace', 'info@ftgcorp.com', '10 Commander Blvd, Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ftgcorp.com   ', '(416) 438-6076', '(416) 438-8065', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Firan Technology Group is a leading North American manufacturer of high technology printed circuit boards and precision illuminated display systems.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FTG has manufactured complex mil-spec and specialty printed circuit boards for the Telecom, Medical, Avionics, Military and Advanced Test markets for over three decades. Our commitment to innovation and one-on-one partnering assures you the level of service and quality you want, while quick-turn prototype and production runs guarantee on-time delivery.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With facilities in Canada, and representation in the U.S. and Europe, FTG provides a broad range of integrated design and manufacturing services in a one-stop-shop offering.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
INSERT INTO `profiles` (`id`, `user_id`, `company_name`, `company_email`, `address`, `site`, `phone`, `fax`, `short_description`, `description`, `key_word`) VALUES
(1321, 1, 'FTS', 'sales@ftsenvironmental.com', '1065 Henry Eng Pl., VICTORIA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.ftsenvironmental.com ', '(250) 478-5561', '(800) 905-7004', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FTS&mdash;Forest Technology Systems, Ltd.&mdash;is a leading manufacturer of remote environmental monitoring systems, instrumentation and communications technology. Our equipment forms the backbone of some of the world\'s most sophisticated and demanding environment monitoring networks.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 3 decades, FTS weather and water monitoring stations have proven themselves under the most demanding conditions...from the most remote northern regions of arctic Canada to the sun-beaten, wind-blown salt and sand of the Mexican coast, FTS technology is engineered rugged and is unparalleled in ease-of-use.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1322, 1, 'Fuel Industries Inc.', 'info@fuelindustries.com', '100-7 Hinton Ave N, OTTAWA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fuelyouth.com ', '(613) 224-6738', '(613) 224-6802', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From tweens to Millennials, youth culture is bound by one clear fact &ndash; they&rsquo;re connecting and playing in ways no other generation has before.&nbsp; They respect peer opinion more than brand loyalty.&nbsp; And they&rsquo;re always asking &lsquo;what have you done for me lately?&rsquo; We&rsquo;re all about helping you answer that question.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Fuel helps Fortune 500 global brands connect with Millennial and iGen audiences with deep, digital brand experiences that include immersive virtual worlds, mobile apps and social gaming, branded entertainment, interactive multi-screen experiences, interactive rich media advertising, and digital loyalty programs.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1323, 1, 'Fugro GeoSurveys', 'fgi-mail@fugro.com', '25 Pippy Place, ST. JOHN\'S, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada ', 'www.fugro.com ', '(709) 726-4252', '(709) 726-5007', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are the world&rsquo;s largest integrator of geotechnical, survey, subsea and geosciences services. Our services are specifically designed to support your engineering design and large structure building projects.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our vision is to be world leaders in data acquisition and interpretation. We strive to deliver world class innovations and solutions to support your infrastructure projects.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We create value by acquiring and interpreting earth and engineering data and by supporting you with the design, construction, installation, repair and maintenance of your infrastructure.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We work predominantly in energy and infrastructure markets offshore and onshore. Our mission is to be your preferred partner by safely and consistently delivering quality solutions with teams of employees that apply world class, innovative and often proprietary technology and that perform to the highest standards of professionalism and integrity.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our vision is to lead in every market in which we operate, thus generating growth and superior profits and returns for our shareholders.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1324, 1, 'FWS Group of Companies', 'gdepres@fwsgroup.com', '475 Dovercourt Dr., Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.fwsgroup.com', '(204) 487-2500', '(204) 487-2900', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Precision, professionalism, efficiency and quality - these are the principles upon which the FWS Group of Companies were founded and continue to operate. For over 60 years, planned growth and diversification has resulted in a group that now includes the following corporate entities:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canada\'s Best Managed Companies<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FWS Industrial Projects Canada Ltd.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FWS Western Ltd.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FWS Industrial Projects USA Inc.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">FWS Technologies Ltd.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Sunstone Resort Communities Corp.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Though based in the tradition of design-build construction, FWS&rsquo; evolution now involves pioneering a wide range of project development approaches that include various forms of Construction Management and real estate development agreements. We take great pride in our ability to tailor proposals to meet the varied needs and objectives of clients and prospects alike.The fully integrated FWS approach to construction and development unifies owner, consultants and contractor(s) into a results-oriented building team. The approach promotes single-source accountability, improved cost control, shortened time frames and a relationship that keeps clients coming back again and again.Today\'s satisfied customers are tomorrow\'s growth opportunities. FWS&rsquo; continued commitment to the customer, maintenance of our excellent reputation and the principles of precision, professionalism, efficiency and quality control are all hallmarks of our success.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1325, 1, 'Fybon Industries Limted', 'customerservice@fybon.com', '202 Fairbank Ave, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.fybon.com ', '(416) 787-0191', '(416) 787-2077', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With over 34 years experience, Fybon Industries Limited is an industry leader among manufacturers of industrial nonwoven textiles. We are a well-diversified company supplying high quality products to a vast number of industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The staff at Fybon are highly trained and committed to respond to every customer&rsquo;s specific needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Committed to excellence, Fybon sources the finest fibers from all around the world. Our state of the art production facility produces a consistent and uncompromising product unparalleled in the industry. Using either the spray bonded or thermal bonded process, Fybon manufactures a comprehensive line of highloft, densified and needle-punched nonwovens for a wide variety of applications, and is able to meet the most stringent specifications. Our ongoing commitment to research and development assures that the company will stay on the leading edge of innovation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Customers can count on Fybon to supply them with the product that will do the job for them now and in the future.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1326, 1, 'G & G Machine Knife Inc.', 'ggtool@ggmachineknife.ca', '1-1246 Lorimar Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ggmachineknife.ca ', '(905) 670-0599', '(905) 670-2723', '', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 1985, G &amp; G Machine Knife has built a solid reputation of manufacturing the highest quality, best performing machine knives in the industry, as acknowledged by our customers.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All of our knives and accessories are manufactured from the highest quality steel available. Our CNC machining and grinding equipment ensures that we meet the highest standard possible and OEM specifications.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We at G &amp; G Machine Knife believe in continuous improvement, investment in state of the art production equipment and employee training programs ensure that our reputation for high quality products, at competitive prices is maintained.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Quality, performance, service and price are only few of the reasons you should be dealing with G &amp; G Machine Knife.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1327, 1, 'G & W Group Limited', 'susanwrj@hotmail.com', '61 Shootfield Cres., Scarborough, Ontario, Canada', '', '(416) 909-7198', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;We provide casual wear garments with superior quality and competitive price. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br />\r\n</span></div>', ''),
(1328, 1, 'G.B. Book Plastics Ltd.', 'gbbook@nexicom.net', '415 Pido Rd, PETERBOROUGH,, Ontario, Canada', 'www.gbbookplastics.com', '(705) 745-0666', '(705) 745-5855', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In today\'s globally competitive environment, it can be costly when a supplier let\'s you down. It\'s also frustrating when you can\'t get the job you needed yesterday, or the quality you require.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As a custom supplier of precision plastic moulded parts, we understand the day to day demands you face. Over the past 34 years we\'ve built our business by turning manufacturing challenges into everyday solutions. We\'ve been able to prove our ability by consistently providing superior quality, competitive pricing and service excellence.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our customers include respected manufacturers in the aerospace,medical, electrical, electronics, telecommunications, appliance, office furniture, sporting goods, hardware and food service industries. They can attest that G.B. Book Plastics&nbsp; has the people, the technology and systems to deliver the solutions you need.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1976,&nbsp; Barry Book created a long term plan for his company that involved a progressive move toward robotics and computerized machinery designed to compete in the global marketplace. With this commitment in mind, we began successfully competing internationally for business. The quality components that G.B. Book Plastics produced, together with our dedication to service, turned first-time accounts into long-term customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Backed by a talented and knowledgeable staff, our family and employees have been committed to continuing G.B. Book Plastics\' tradition of excellence. Our state-of-the-art moulding machines and attention to detail give us an edge as a quality global manufacturer of custom plastic components.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1329, 1, 'G.H. Chemicals Ltd', 'pbailet@ghchemicals.com', '1550 Brouillette St, SAINT-HYACINTHE, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.ghchemicals.com   ', '(450) 774-9151', '(450) 771-0457', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our team of trained and dynamic employees enables G.H. Chemicals to fulfill its corporate mission: Consistent Quality, Consistent Service, Consistent Value and Security of Supply.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">G.H. Chemicals manufactures multiple grades of zinc oxide in order to supply such industries as tire, custom compound rubber and plastics, ceramics, agriculture, lube oil additives and specialty chemicals.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">G.H. Chemicals is the manufacturer of IRM 91 (ASTM) zinc oxide reference material for the world&rsquo;s rubber compounding industry. It can be ordered directly from G.H. by visiting our Contact Us section.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our unique production method allows G.H. Chemicals to manufacture one of the purest zinc oxides available to both the pharmaceutical and food industry (USP and FCC). G.H. Chemicals was recently granted the world&rsquo;s first government GMP License (Good Manufacturing Practice) to produce USP zinc oxide serving as an Active Pharmaceutical Ingredient (API). The license is also the equivalent to the ICH Q7 Certification and therefore allows the importation of G.H. Chemicals zinc oxide into Europe. Please visit the GMP section of our website for more information.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">World class accreditations such as C-TPAT (United States), REACH (Europe), GMP, and our packaging in UN registered bags for shipment from the nearby port of Montreal, all ensure that G.H. Chemicals zinc oxide can be exported anywhere on the planet.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1330, 1, 'G.K. Industries Ltd.', 'gki@gkindustries.com', '50 Precidio Crt, BRAMPTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.gkindustries.com ', '(905) 799-1972', '(905) 799-0852', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1972 G.K Industries Ltd. has been a leader in providing filtration solution to the North American market. All our products are designed and manufactured to meet or exceed OE specifications and supported by industry leading service. GKI offers high quality air, breather, cabin air, fuel, transmission and oil filters all at a competitive price.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As an indication of our commitment to quality GKI has been registered to the prestigious ISO 9001:2008 Quality Assurance Standard. ISO is the International Organization for standardization, headquartered in Geneva, Switzerland.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Improve your filter profits, increase your market share, shorten your lead times, reduce your inventory and ultimately exceed your customer&rsquo;s expectations, make GKI your complete filtration solutions provider.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1331, 1, 'G.T. Wood Co. Ltd.', 'sales@gtwood.com', '3354 Mavis Rd., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.gtwood.com ', '(905) 272-1696', '(905) 272-1425', '', '<p>&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space: pre;\">	</span></p>\r\n<div>Founded in 1948 and incorporated in 1972, G.T. Wood, a privately owned Canadian high-voltage electrical contractor, today occupies a highly respected position in the field. Our success and &nbsp;reputation are based on our willingness to listen to our clients\' needs, our ability to keep pace with leading edge technology and our &nbsp;flexibility in discovering ways to adapt and expand our service offerings to meet our clients\' needs consistently, reliably and &nbsp;cost-effectively.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our full and part-time employees include highly-trained field service technicians, engineers and certified electrical technicians with a &nbsp;wealth of experience. G.T. Wood has, through more than 40 years of operation, earned a reputation of reliability and quality service, 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>At G.T. Wood, quality service is the &nbsp;foundation on which we\'ve built our reputation. It\'s because of that &nbsp;strong foundation that our reputation continues to spread. To us, quality service is more than a philosophy - it is the way we do business.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Throughout our years of operation, as the high-voltage electrical field expanded &nbsp;and diversified, we\'ve kept pace with the changes. We\'ve developed our &nbsp;expertise and broadened our service delivery capabilities to accommodate the increasingly specialized needs of customers. We\'ve moved with the changing times. Today, our reputation is recognized throughout Canada, but primarily in the Greater Toronto Area, Mississauga and the Golden Horseshoe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>As the high-voltage electrical contracting industry changes in the &nbsp;coming years - and it will; as needs of our clients become more finely &nbsp;tuned, we will continue to broaden our delivery options as well as our &nbsp;highly developed technical expertise. It\'s what we\'ve always done in the past - and that will never change.</div>', ''),
(1332, 1, 'Gab Induspac Inc.', 'sales@induspac.com', '1805, 50 Ave, LACHINE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.induspac.com ', '(514) 636-1347', '(514) 636-9545', '', '<p>&nbsp;A leader in the design and manufacturing of customized industrial packaging in Canada, the Induspac Group regroups the Smith Packaging plants of Toronto and Ottawa, as well as the GAB Packaging plant of Candiac. &nbsp;In business for over 40 years, the group now boosts almost 200 employees and over 300 000 square feet of manufacturing facilities. &nbsp;We will help you reduce your packaging costs by:</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Giving you access to our team of experienced designers, who works with different recyclable materials to create lighter packaging that will be better adapted to your production lines and will avoid costly over-packaging;</div>\r\n<div>Using our plants&rsquo; large manufacturing capacity to quickly produce all the items you require;</div>\r\n<div>Taking advantage of our expertise to determine the optimal production quantities that will minimize your costs;</div>\r\n<div>Combining our on-line inventory management tools and our truck fleet to orchestrate just-in-time deliveries that will minimize the use of your precious square footage.</div>\r\n<div>Whether small businesses or large multinationals, our clients are active in all aspects of the manufacturing sector. &nbsp;See what they know and take advantage of our expertise!</div>', ''),
