(1518, 1, 'Tatra Safety Boots & Shoes Inc.', 'dezi@tatra.ca', '2-330 Ramsey Dr., DUNNVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.tatra.ca ', '(905) 774-7585', '(905) 774-7586', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Tatra Safety Boots &amp; Shoes Inc, manufactures and distributes steel toe safety footwear for men and women. Looking for a steel toe work boot built for comfort, durability and reliability at a completive price? You\'ve landed on one of the web\'s leading online Canadian footwear distribution stores. Tatra Safety Boots &amp; Shoes Inc is not just a distributor we are manufacturers of high quality footwear. We can provide workers with the highest level of protection, meeting or exceeding CSA and ASTM Standards.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We&rsquo;ve been servicing and custom designing footwear in Canada for the construction industry since 1932. If you are working in the construction industry you know how important it is to build something right. We at Tatra have the same philosophy, if you are going to manufacture a shoe you just don\'t want to develop it to fit the foot, you also want it comfortable, reliable and durable is our motto. We can accomplish this because we use the highest quality control standards.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">What type of steel toe work boot or shoe can you offer me?<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We can offer you the casual shoe, a dressy high boot or the more rugged looking construction work boot. Tatra manufactures High Heat Work Boots that are vulcanized nitrile rubber outsole heat, oil &amp; acid resistant lug pattern, with steel toe. Our other safety products include, Foundry Boots, Internal Metatarsal, and the External Metatarsal Protection. For those of you that want a little western class be sure to check out our Westerns &amp; Wellingtons series. We haven\'t forgot about the ladies, we have a sections for Ladies Steel Toe Work Shoes.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1519, 1, 'TB Vets', 'Kandys@tbvets.org', '1410 Kootenay St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.tbvets.org ', '(604) 874-5626', '(604) 874-7646', '', '<p>&nbsp;From the battlefields of World War 2 to fighting a war against respiratory illnesses upon their return, our Veterans understood the meaning of compassion and caring for one\'s fellow man. Their vision was humble - to help disabled and inflicted Veterans with meaningful employment while providing a community service to British Columbians.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This vision was accomplished through the creation of the TB Vets Key Tag return program and subsequently the TB Vets Charitable Foundation. Veterans and the disabled manufactured the key tags which were offered as a free community service. Over time as donations from the key tags increased, our Veterans reached further out into the community, and began supporting programs for respiratory wellness.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1520, 1, 'TBL Inc.', 'lynntuttle@tblinc.ca', 'Site 230 Comp 1 RR2 Stn Main, STONY PLAIN, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.tblinc.ca ', '(780) 968-5455', '(780) 968-5465', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:#454545;mso-fareast-language:EN-CA\">Le but de TBL T&eacute;l&eacute;com est d&rsquo;offrir &agrave; ses clients des solutions en communication unifi&eacute;e, sans-fil large bande, Wifi, inter-r&eacute;seautage et de c&acirc;blage structur&eacute;.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:#454545;mso-fareast-language:EN-CA\">Notre personnel qualifi&eacute; et accr&eacute;dit&eacute; offre des services professionnels de pr&eacute;vente, des &eacute;tudes de faisabilit&eacute;, des&nbsp; demandes de licences &agrave; Industrie Canada, la validation des infrastructures inter-r&eacute;seautages, la configuration de syst&egrave;me et le service de maintenance sur place.building<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:#454545;mso-fareast-language:EN-CA\">Avec plus de 15 ann&eacute;es d&rsquo;exp&eacute;rience, TBL T&eacute;l&eacute;com a r&eacute;alis&eacute; plusieurs projets d&rsquo;envergure au le Canada&nbsp; en ayant comme mission d&rsquo;offrir des solutions durables et fiables de type &laquo; carrier grade &raquo;. Toutes nos solutions sont soigneusement con&ccedil;ues avec des objectifs minimums de fiabilit&eacute; de 99,999 % gr&acirc;ce &agrave; des produits de partenaires reconnus par l&rsquo;industrie.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;\r\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:#454545;mso-fareast-language:EN-CA\">Pour une tranquillit&eacute; d&rsquo;esprit et une ex&eacute;cution professionnelle, faites comme nos 4 000 clients qui font confiance aux solutions et au service de TBL T&eacute;l&eacute;com inc.</span><o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1521, 1, 'TCA Technologies Inc.', 'sales@tca-tech.com', '38 Winer Rd, GUELPH, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.tca-tech.com ', '(519) 824-8711', '(519) 824-9053', '', '<p>&nbsp;TCA Technologies Inc. offers a variety of unique machine solutions designed to fit your specific application requirements.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Over 15 Years in Business!</div>\r\n<div>Our engineers work with you to properly determine your requirements then we develop a concept that meets these needs for maximum return on investment. One of our strengths is the ability to develop, fabricate, assemble, program, and test each system with our in-house staff.</div>\r\n<div>TCA Technologies Inc. approaches each project with a commitment to quality, performance and customer satisfaction. Our experienced staff provides installation, start-up, training and technical support to meet your needs on time and within budget.</div>\r\n<div>We invest heavily in research and development to stay up to date on the latest technologies so we can provide the best solutions to industry. To date we have well over 1,000 systems that are successfully installed and running in manufacturing plants around the world.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Over 1,000 Systems Developed and Installed!</div>\r\n<div>TCA Technologies Inc. has developed a wide range of automated systems including:</div>\r\n<div>Pick &amp; Place Transfers and Robots</div>\r\n<div>Component Part Assembly Systems</div>\r\n<div>Hydraulic and Pneumatic Presses</div>\r\n<div>Leak Test Stands and Tooling</div>\r\n<div>Metal Forming</div>\r\n<div>Rivet and Staking Systems</div>\r\n<div>Part Trimming</div>\r\n<div>Servo Punching and Part Forming</div>\r\n<div>Part Handling and Inspection</div>\r\n<div>Vision Systems</div>\r\n<div>Turnkey Production Lines</div>\r\n<div>Plastics &amp; Composites Forming &amp; Molding</div>\r\n<div>High Speed Web Handling with Perforating &amp; Die Cutting</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Manufacturing Operations Potentially Ripe for Automation Include Those Exhibiting any of the Following Attributes</div>\r\n<div>Poor quality and high scrap rates due to operator inconsistency.</div>\r\n<div>Processes requiring high-speed operations to meet production demands.</div>\r\n<div>Cutting and drilling operations.</div>\r\n<div>Labour shortage. Automation may be the only answer.</div>\r\n<div>Simple and repetitive operations. These are ideal for automation and boring for people; boredom can lead to careless work.</div>\r\n<div>Dangerous/unpleasant/fatiguing operations.</div>\r\n<div>Two to three shift working. It is easier to justify the cost of investment over multiple shifts.</div>\r\n<div>Critical handling. A part may be easily damaged or contaminated. Automation can be cleaner and more consistent.</div>\r\n<div>Labour-Intensive Operations</div>\r\n<div>Skills difficult to retain. Automated machinery can be programmed to supplement these skills.</div>\r\n<div>Operations with high labour turnover. The use of automation will avoid costs of recruitment and training.</div>\r\n<div>Process bottleneck operations.</div>\r\n<div>Poor uptime of sensitive machines, due to inconsistent loading by operators.</div>\r\n<div>Expensive floor space. An automated system might require less space.</div>\r\n<div>Products specifically designed with automation in mind - for example assembly operations.</div>\r\n<div>Gauging and testing operations. Automation will reduce operator inconsistency and time consuming setups. Results can automatically be fed in to an SPC system for statistical tracking.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Operations to Avoid Automation Exhibit the Following Characteristics</div>\r\n<div>Out of control processes. Automation will fail in an unstructured, poorly controlled environment; it cannot adapt to change like people can.</div>\r\n<div>Poor parts consistency. People are usually fairly successful at checking parts before assembling/processing them and &quot;making them fit&quot; if possible. To error proof the process you must be prepared to use a high number of sensors, or use a vision system, for parts checking (and create a very complex machine in the process). It is better to put the effort into finding and fixing the problem at the source and then consider the automation.</div>\r\n<div>Complex manipulative operations. Nothing yet competes with human manipulation and hand-eye co-ordination skills. Unless the operation can be broken down into a series of elementary stages, do not bother. Just admire the skill of a good worker.</div>\r\n<div>Low volume manufacture that requires human decision-making at some point in the process</div>', ''),
(1522, 1, 'TCH Sales Inc', 'info@tchweb.com', '40 Emblem Crt, SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.tchweb.com ', '(800) 465-6281', '(416) 299-3255', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TCH is a distributor of industrial components. The company supplies enclosure hardware, laminates, electronic components, foam inserts and speaker parts to North American manufacturers. TCH fulfills customer orders out of its warehouse facilities in Buffalo, Calgary, Dallas, Montr&eacute;al and Toronto.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Contact TCH at a specific warehouse location.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TCH started operating in 1976, primarily serving musicians and businesses in the entertainment industry. TCH hardware and laminates were used in the production of musicians\' ATA-cases, in DJ road-cases and in the construction of event stages. Over 30 years, the company built a reputation for fast order fulfilment, competitive pricing and ability to source custom components.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Today, the company supplies manufacturers in the medical, information technology, transport and defence industries. TCH distributes components via its teams of local account managers, its 5000 components print catalogue, ecommerce and B2B websites.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more news and information about TCH subscribe to get our updates via your own email, Facebook, Twitter, or Linked-In accounts.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TCH Acquires Rush<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TCH has recently acquired Rush Electronics Ltd., a Canadian distributor of electro-mechanical components and industrial hardware. In business since 1978, Rush Electronics has four distribution centres in Canada and represents over 30 manufacturers of electronic components, enclosure accessories and other industrial hardware. Rush Electronics is a proficient distributor for O.E.M. customers, their contract manufacturers and the diversified Canadian marketplace.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1523, 1, 'TD ARCHITECTURAL GROUP', 'jboule@td-architecturalgroup.com', '4079 Confederation Parkway, Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', '', '(289) 946-2061', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Interior Architecture<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">People are often convinced that Architects are only interested in the design of a building\'s exterior and related technical issues. In fact, architects are usually drawn to solving any design problem whether it is building-related, furniture or industrial design, siting and landscape issues but certainly including the creation of successful interior spaces. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Architectural design for interiors includes space planning, concept development, detailed design and the careful coordination of building services just as with the building shell. With interiors however, additional considerations must be brought to bear including interior construction and detailing, selection of finishes, colours and the integration of millwork, furniture systems, special equipment and technology. The design challenge remains the same for interior space as for the building itself - how to best create functional, flexible space with a distinctive, appropriate image and within the budget constraints of the project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1524, 1, 'TD Products', 'sblok@nrtco.net', '3285 Beachburg Rd, PEMBROKE, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.td-products.com ', '(613) 582-3867', '(613) 582-3866', '', '<p>&nbsp;TD products was founded in 1979 as a welding repair shop with our head office and shop located just outside of Beachburg, Ontario. We soon became known as the place to go for high quality non-ferrous fabrication and repairs.</p>', ''),
(1525, 1, 'TEAC Fiberglass Consulting Group Inc', 'tom.turbo.davis@gmail.com', '829 Niagara Pky, FORT ERIE, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 650-8719', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Fiberglass resin product mangement consulting service. Perform third party inspection services, project and construction mangement for medium to large size projects throughout the world. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1526, 1, 'Teach Away Inc.', 'info@teachaway.com', '147 Liberty St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.teachaway.com ', '(416) 628-1386', '(647) 477-2065', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Teach Away, headquartered in Toronto, Canada, was established in 2003 to help teachers find reputable employment overseas. The agency has offices in Vancouver, London, Edinburgh, New York and Brisbane.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since its inception, Teach Away has become one of the largest and most diverse teacher recruitment agencies in the world. Teach Away is comprised of compassionate, honest, fun-loving education professionals that have lived and worked internationally.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Each year, Teach Away places hundreds of teachers in countries around the world including the United Arab Emirates, Hong Kong, Japan, China, Thailand, Vietnam, Taiwan, Saudi Arabia, South Korea and many more. Teach Away\'s partners include a wide range of educational institutions including Elementary, Middle, and High Schools; International Schools; Public Schools; Businesses requiring English Language Instructors; Summer Camps; Adult Learning Centres; and Private English Schools.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1527, 1, 'TFG Global Insurance Solutions Ltd.', 'info@tfgglobal.com', '1500-701 West Georgia St W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.tfgglobal.com ', '(604) 628-0426', '(604) 913-1153', '', '<p>&nbsp;TFG Global Insurance Solutions Ltd. is a domestic and international insurance brokerage serving clients in Canada and around the world. We have offices in Greater Vancouver and in downtown Toronto. We specialize in providing international insurance solutions to companies, government and non-governmental organizations who operate on a global basis.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We can search the market for group or individual global medical insurance, expatriate life and disability insurance, special risk coverage for high risk zones and online travel insurance. Because we started in Canada offering group and individual insurance coverage, we can also source domestic plans. You can view brochure or corporate presentation online. You can learn more about why you should choose TFG Global by clicking HERE. Please view our international folding or corporate expat brochure online.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You are assured that your will enjoy the financial security of being protected by insurance companies of the highest financial ratings and superior service and coverage.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>TFG Global Insurance Solutions Ltd. offers prompt, courteous and informed service while delivering a complete solution to your life, health and disability insurance needs along with various offshore savings plans. We seek to provide quality insurance and financial products with a personal approach using the latest in communications, computer and Internet technology to serve customers world-wide. As brokers, we are not tied to using just one insurance company as we represent your interests first. We will try to source the large number of quality insurance companies that we source with your unique requirements. Check out www.expatfinancial.com if you require expatriate insurance services. You can download our international insurance brochure or special risk insurance brochure.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>TFG Global Insurance Solutions Ltd. is a member of the Better Business Bureau. Expat Financial is a division of TFG Global Insurance Solutions Ltd.</div>', ''),
(1528, 1, 'TFI Aerospace Corporation', 'tsquires@TFI-Aero.com', '625 Riddell Rd, ORANGEVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.TFI-Aero.com ', '(519) 940-9003', '(519) 940-0480', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Located in Orangeville, Ontario, a short drive to Toronto\'s Pearson International airport, TFI Aerospace manufactures product for world markets through a professional sales team and leading authorized aerospace fastener distributors.&nbsp; We are dedicated to continual improvement and staying at the leading edge of technology in the development and manufacture of high-end fasteners.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TFI Aerospace\'s 20,000 square feet (1860 square metre) facility is purpose built for the design and manufacture of mission-critical fastener solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We pride ourselves in our flexibility and reactivity to customer needs, allowing for short lead times, and with the capability of rapidly turning around both small and large volume fastener orders.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TFI Aerospace\'s end user client list includes such industry leaders as Boeing, Bombardier, Lockheed Martin, Rolls-Royce and NASA.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1529, 1, 'TG Industries Inc.', 'taban@tgindustries.com', '107, 3rd Ave E, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.tgindustries.com ', '(604) 872-6676', '(604) 872-6601', '', '<p>&nbsp;We manufacture and import promotional products.</p>', ''),
(1530, 1, 'TGDTrading.ca', 'tgd2011@shaw.ca', '201A - 11615 - 28 Ave, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.tgdtrading.ca', '(780) 907-2929', '(866) 686-2858', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Trans-Global Distributions is an established Power Equipment&nbsp; trading company in operation since 1995.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are active in making a contribution towards the procurement requirements of local and international clients&rsquo; need for electrical power generating equipment such as Power Plants, Generators,&nbsp; Turbines, Engines, and related electrical equipment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We also offer for sale a wide range of Used Industrial Plants and machinery for light and heavy industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our&nbsp; equipment offered for sale are in the following categories: they are either new or second user, unused or has never been fully commissioned, new or &ldquo;as new&rdquo; still stored in the factory, cancelled-orders, refurbished or overhauled, and decommission units.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TGD operates in the global market place and offers equipment for sale at competitive prices to customers in the developed and emerging markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We also assist plant owners in seeking buyers for their used plant and equipment that they may have available for sale.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">TGD&nbsp; is committed to providing strong consultation support and professional services for our clients and trading partners in all transactions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Should you be looking for a unit that is not advertised on our site, you may still inquire, we may have that unit in our data base or be able to help by sourcing them for you. Not all our inventory are listed or currently advertised.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our mission is to facilitate customer&rsquo;s needs and requirement to the best of our professional abilities towards a mutual and satisfactory outcome.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We welcome the opportunity to be of service to you and your organization.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1531, 1, 'Thabet Aereoplus', 'thabet@bellnet.ca', '607, 6e avenue de L\'Aéroport Bureau 110, QUÉBEC, Quebec, Canada', 'www.thabetaeroplus.ca ', '(418) 871-0047', '(418) 871-6937', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Thabet is in close contact with any parties liable to answer your needs; they are familiar with the market of new and used aircrafts sales, and put their international network to work for the benefit of both buyer and seller. Researching and presenting aircraft require an energetic and alert approach, focussed on the approach pertinent to the targeted promotional areas. Our access to advertising and marketing resources favour effective results.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition, we have direct and privileged access to various databases of new and used aircrafts for sale, giving us an even greater edge in reaching your goals. We can easily spot business opportunities that would likely go unnoticed by anyone from a less specialized field.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Are you in the market for an aircraft? We&rsquo;ll find it for you! Thabet will subject your needs to the most meticulous analysis so as to determine the type of aircraft best suited to your needs. We will take into account anticipated usage and expected workload, as well, of course, as your budgetary goals.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We will study the market&rsquo;s potential to satisfy the body of your personal or corporate needs, in budgetary and technical matters. With Thabet, you sidestep the tedious burden of shopping, and armed with judiciously and professionally targeted data, you will be afforded the opportunity to make a clear-headed decision.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
