(1572, 1, 'UberMedia', 'info@ubermediahd.com', '13500, rue du Blizzard, MIRABEL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.ubermediahd.com ', '(450) 508-4420', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Afin de maximiser votre potentiel de mise en march&eacute;, votre entreprise m&eacute;rite d&rsquo;avoir les meilleurs outils!<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Plus que jamais, la vid&eacute;o est le moyen le plus dynamique pour rendre justice &agrave; votre image. Gr&acirc;ce &agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;volution r&eacute;cente des technologies de vid&eacute;o num&eacute;rique, il existe maintenant une myriade de moyen pour diffuser votre image corporative efficacement et &agrave; tr&egrave;s peu de frais.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Laissez tomber vos pr&eacute;sentations PowerPoint statique et monotone et offrez-vous ce qu&rsquo;il y a de mieux : Une vid&eacute;o en haute definition! &Uuml;berMedia est une entreprise sp&eacute;cialis&eacute;e dans la production de vid&eacute;os corporatives professionnelles. Nous &eacute;laborons pour vous le sc&eacute;nario id&eacute;al pour pr&eacute;senter votre entreprise ou vos produits et m&ecirc;me pour couvrir vos &eacute;v&eacute;nements sp&eacute;ciaux tels que lancement de produits ou formations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Un outil aux multiples utilisations La diffusion est maintenant chose simple.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">La vid&eacute;o offre une multitude de possibilit&eacute;s d&rsquo;utilisations<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Projection sur &eacute;cran HD dans votre kiosque ou salle de montre<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vid&eacute;o en flash pour diffusion sur votre site web<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vid&eacute;o sur format CD ou DVD pour accompagner votre brochure<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Un outil de vente sans &eacute;gal sur les ordinateurs portatifs de vos repr&eacute;sentants<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1573, 1, 'UControl Marketing', 'info@ucontrol.ca', '210-5800 Ambler Dr., Mississauga, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ucontrol.ca ', '(800) 261-3189', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Venkat, our founder, is passionate about technology that can change the world for the better. With UControl Marketing, he made his passion his business. Today, UControl Marketing works with customers In Canada and plans to expand its services to the Caribbean, South America, Middle East, and Asia (2014-2015).<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is to be the leading, innovative mobile marketing strategies service provider in Canada, offering cutting-edge solutions in mobile marketing and serving small to large businesses alike from a wide range of industries.&#8203;&#8203;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1574, 1, 'UCS Global Limited', 'sales_global@ucsglobal.com', '7088 Financial Dr, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ucfp.com ', '(905) 593-9918', '(905) 814-0090', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are the Canadian division of UCS Forest Group which includes Sierra Forest Products in the United States and UCS Global internationally.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our global reach and regional knowledge combine to bring the best possible product and service solutions to our customers: Unparalleled Service, Express ship delivery, Custom milling, Global sourcing of lumber and plywood, Product research, Market information, State-of-the-art warehouses, Customer focused technology, Quality Products<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are relentless in our pursuit of finding the best products available. Our expertise in sourcing and wood consultation enables us to match suppliers with customers. We are committed to continually researching, evaluating, upgrading and adding new products.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are unwavering in our commitment to selling products that come from sources that meet the highest standards of environmental compliance and responsible forestry practices.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Extraordinary People:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our people are responsive, knowledgeable and committed to understanding your business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A key element of our philosophy is treating customers as business partners. Our goal is to provide a complete lumber management solution, by working with customers to determine exactly what they need, sourcing the product from a global network of high-quality suppliers and then delivering it on time, every time.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1575, 1, 'Udisco Business Computer Systems', 'computers@udisco.com', '4660 Decarie Blvd, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.udisco.com ', '(514) 481-8107', '(514) 487-5383', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Udisco Ltd. is Canada\'s largest hobby wholesaler, with two warehouses containing over 60,000 items in inventory.&nbsp; Founded in 1944, Udisco has been supplying Canada\'s hobby market for over 50 years. Based in Montreal, Quebec, Udisco sells everything from plastic models, electric trains, remote control planes, boats, cars, and helicopters, to premium balsa wood, figurines, puzzles, die cast, and more! Udisco also stocks a wide assortment of accessories, including paint, brushes, tools, and coverings. Our inventory includes both new and hard-to-find items, all at wholesale price.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We carry lines from over 600 international manufacturers, and represent companies such as Hirobo and Heljan exclusively in Canada.&nbsp;&nbsp; We also stock a wide variety of parts and fittings, and maintain an inventory of spare parts for almost everything we sell.&nbsp; If a part you\'re looking for is not in stock, or is no longer available from the manufacturer, our expert machinists may be able to custom produce the part if necessary in our machine shop.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our website is updated nightly from our inventory. However, items shown as in stock may no longer be available as they may be on reserve. Customers who have placed orders in advance will have priority on receipt and inventory will continue to be displayed unitl they have picked up their orders.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The manufacturers are producing products based on a specific number of orders received from the distributors by the order deadline. Therefore, a limited amount of product is created. If, for axample, we order 24 pieces of an item and from the time we have placed the order to the time we received it, we receive orders for more thean we have ordered, then orders will be filled on a first come, first served basis. Orders can only be guaranteed if they are received prior to our placing our order, or selling out the quantity we have ordered.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To assure we have the stock you want, make sure to order early (reserve the item) or email us to verify it is in stock and reserve it for you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Finally, Udisco maintains a well-equipped service deptartment&nbsp; that can service or repair almost anything we sell, including radios, engines, and other sophisticated parts.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1576, 1, 'Udutu Online Learning Systems Inc', 'info@udutu.com', '108-3550 Saanich Rd, VICTORIA, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.udutu.com ', '(250) 388-5003', '(250) 298-9291', '', '<p>&nbsp;Udutu is a lead innovator in &ldquo;Training Solutions That Work!&rdquo;. A completely FREE and unlimited hosted course authoring tool, custom course development services and hosted, customizable LMS solutions that can be activated in minutes for as little as $19/mth.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1577, 1, 'UFMS Inc.', 'ufms@ufmsinc.com', '39 Oakmoor Lane, MARKHAM, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ufmsinc.com ', '(905) 477-0081', '(905) 205-0023', '', '<p>&nbsp;UFMS Inc. was founded by Mr. Fred K. Wong in 1992 after 9 years of serving major industry leading companies as a software consultant.</p>\r\n<div>Since its inception UFMS has dedicated 100% of its resources to the development, integration and support of flexible and innovative distribution logistic solutions for a wide range of industries, large and small. &nbsp;UFMS-Pro, our flagship Transportation Management System (TMS), is the direct result of observing and learning from visiting, on average, more than 20 distribution centers of all sizes monthly for over 20 years. &nbsp;Our vision and the constant desire to deliver &lsquo;Better than Expected&rsquo; experience for our clients is evident in the products and services the company is providing today.</div>\r\n<div>The UFMS team is dedicated to making you more effective in your distribution environment. We are committed to the quality and integrity of our products and services, providing customers with complete distribution management solutions to ensure maximum return on their investment. Today, our TMS is implemented and performing successfully at hundreds of client sites throughout North America.</div>', ''),
(1578, 1, 'UHAISA Group', 'mustansir1@hotmail.com', '15-1310 Dundas St E Suite 113, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(416) 908-4518', '(866) 609-0788', '', '<p>&nbsp;UHAISA Group is an emerging used automobile dealership servicing the needs of its customers by providing them with a a quality vehicle of their choice at affordable prices. Based out of Ontario Canada within the geographical region of Greater Toronto Area our business models allows us access to large used vehicle inventory pools all over North America (anywhere in Canada and USA) so we always have the vehicle you are looking for. We deal in all kinds of consumer &amp; commerical models from imported to domestic (Toyota, Honda, Mazda, Nissan, Hyundai, Kia, Ford, GM, Chrysler, Audi, VW, BMW, Mercedez etc.)and export all types of vehicles (Clean, Damaged, Salvaged) to our customers all over the world. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1579, 1, 'ULA-Matic Inc.', 'sales@ulamatic.com', '335 Connie Cres., CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ulamatic.com ', '(905) 669-2302', '(905) 669-1848', '', '<p>&nbsp;ULA-Matic Inc was founded in 1996. Over the years, we have built a team of automation professionals with the desire to design and build automation equipment with exceptional innovation, value and quality. ULA-Matic has developed systems and processes that result in improved, more efficient machinery while reducing the time from concept to production ready. At the same time, improving functionality and increasing machine life.</p>', ''),
(1580, 1, 'Ultimate Manufactured Systems', 'sales@ultimatemfd.com', '4165 Walker Rd, WINDSOR, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ultimatemfd.com ', '(519) 250-5954', '(519) 250-5953', '', '<p>&nbsp;Utimate Manufactured Systems Inc is a privately held company established in 1999.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are a tier-II systems integrator working in support of large systems solutions providers.</div>', ''),
(1581, 1, 'Ultra Electronics TCS Inc.', 'info@ultra-tcs.com', '88 Hines Rd, KANATA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ultra-tcs.com', ' (613) 592-2288 ', '(613) 592-8855 ', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Part of the Ultra Electronics Group, TCS provides advanced C4ISR and EW systems for ground, airborne and naval applications around the globe. Ultra Electronics, TCS is headquartered in Montreal, Canada with facilities in Ottawa and the United States.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ultra Electronics, TCS supplies reliable and powerful communications and networking equipment for defence systems, security and public safety applications. Its integrated solutions play a major role in the C4ISR ecosystem offering communications, IP networking, C2 support and ISR network convergence. Ultra Electronics, TCS is proud to work with leading system integrators to provide communication systems and services that can be integrated within any military architecture and fielded in any deployment scenario in the world. The company&rsquo;s products meet or exceed military requirements to ensure reliable, effective and robust communications in the harshest environments.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ultra Electronics, TCS also specializes in the design, development and manufacture of integrated ISR and EW solutions for the international market. It has a worldwide reputation for supplying advanced, vertically integrated systems from its full breadth of EW capabilities and technology base.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ultra Electronics, TCS traces its roots to 1903 when the Marconi Wireless Telegraph Company of Canada Inc. was founded. In 1956, it became the first Canadian company to design a complete microwave radio relay system and began manufacturing the first digital radio relay equipment for US DoD in 1970. From 1953 to 2000, the company was known as Canadian Marconi Company (CMC). It was acquired by Ultra Electronics in 2002 and is Ultra\'s center of excellence for tactical communications and electronic warfare.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1582, 1, 'Ultra Marine ', 'heider@ultrafurl.com', '1551 Clearwater Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(905) 274-7439 ', '(905) 278-2965 ', '', '<p>&nbsp;Manufacturer of Yachting equipment for sail furlin</p>', ''),
(1583, 1, 'UM inc.', 'info@umallette.com', '145, boul. Saint-Rémi, SAINT-RÉMI, Quebec, Canada', 'www.umallette.com  ', '(450) 454-2493', '(450) 454-2477', '', '<p>&nbsp;Founded in 1976, Les Usinages Mallette Inc has been an industry pioneer by focusing on the synergy between the skills of our engineering team and the versatility of our manufacturing department at the leading edge of technologies. This structure allows us to offer very high quality products and an enormous variety of services in any specialized areas.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are committed to develop and maintain a growing association with our clients, by creating new and innovative products that improve the quality of their own machinery.</div>', ''),
(1584, 1, 'UM Marketing ', 'um@axionet.com', '303-873 Beatty St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(604) 893-8661', '(604) 893-8662', '', '<p>Manufacturer of all types of dry erase products.</p>\r\n<p>Advertising services on dry erase boards which are distributed to different markets.</p>', ''),
(1585, 1, 'Unalloy IWRC', 'montreal@unalloy-iwrc.com', '131 Barr St, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.unalloy-iwrc.com  ', '(514) 735-7504', '(514) 735-4011 ', '', '<p>&nbsp;Unalloy-IWRC is one of Canada&rsquo;s leading wire rope and rigging companies. We specialize in high performance solutions that lower customer operating costs and increase productivity. With full service locations located strategically across Canada and a team of industry leading specialists, we are uniquely positioned to support customer needs anywhere, anytime.</p>', ''),
(1586, 1, 'Underground Support Systems Inc. ', 'info@undergroundsupportsystems.com', '102 Bales Dr. E, NEWMARKET, Ontario, Canada', 'www.undergroundsupportsystems.com  ', '(905) 967-9004 ', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Underground Support Systems Inc. has been fabricating tunnel supports since 2004.&nbsp; We were born of necessity for the needs of a tunnel contracting company who were unable to obtain the consistency they required.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tunneling is where we started&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.Innovation is where we headed&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With the application of technology, our Tunnel Rib Support production process offers a fully automated, computer controlled, single pass system where lengths of material are cold rolled with constant arc measurements, cut and robotically transferred to a welding station where butt plates are attached by welding robots.&nbsp; This automated process is specifically designed to roll wide flange H-beams, I-beams, channels and permits reliable and consistent tolerances to be controlled to + 1/8&rdquo; on critical dimensions.&nbsp; All ribs are cold rolled, not pressed.&nbsp; All supports are designed for the requirements of each project.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With this equipment, changing sizes is easily and quickly effected, allowing us to take care of multiple customers for small orders.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We have also developed a proprietary, robotically manufactured Tunnel Segment Liner designed to provide a thrust platform to advance the tunneling machine, reinforcement for the excavated tunnel or shaft and is available with a water tight gasket.&nbsp; This offers the first viable, cost effective alternative to concrete segments for shorter tunnels or shafts.&nbsp; Flange sizes can be built to any thickness or dimension to minimize or eliminate internal supports such as ribs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Segment Liners can be built for erector arms or manual installation for any diameter or weight.&nbsp; Galvanizing is also available.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As our customer, the end result for you is value; a high quality product when you want it and a competitive price.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">INNOVATION<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Underground Support Systems has delivered a number of &ldquo;firsts&rdquo; to the North American tunneling industry:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Specifically designed robotic manufacturing cells for Rib Supports and our proprietary Segment Liners<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Cold rolled 3&Prime; I-beams Rib Supports for tunnels as small as 48&Prime; diameter, more than 40% lighter<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A proprietary steel Segment Liner that offers a practical alternative to concrete segments for shorter tunnels or shaft lengths, available with a water tight gasket, galvanizing<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A proprietary &ldquo;Rib Clip&rdquo; that eliminates the need for butt plates on Rib Supports<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1587, 1, 'Uneeda Wood Products', 'tjm@gillwood.ca', '6550 Unsworth Rd, CHILLIWACK, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.gillwood.ca ', '(604) 858-3431', '(604) 858-6347', '', '<p>&nbsp;Welcome to Gillwood Remanufacturing Inc. (formerly Uneeda Wood Products).</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company began operations as Uneeda Wood Products in 1965 in Burnaby, BC with two wood moulders and a rip saw providing value-added custom services to the lumber industry. &nbsp;In 1975 the company moved to Chilliwack, BC and added two additional moulders and 12 dry kilns.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In 1996 more improvements were made with two finger joint lines. &nbsp;A planer was added in 1999.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In 2011 the company was acquired by new owners and the name was changed to Gillwood Remanufacturing Inc. &nbsp;Although the Uneeda name has been retired the company continues the legacy of being a premier custom remanufacturing facility.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Situated on 33 acres (15 hectares) of company-owned land in the heart of the Fraser Valley just one hour&rsquo;s drive east from Vancouver, Gillwood has 160,000 square feet of dry storage, an experienced work force, a reputation for good service and quality control, able to ship and receive shipments by rail (BC Southern R/R) or truck, able to load containers, LISA &nbsp;inventory control system and is PEFC/SFI/CSA (Chain of Custody) certified. &nbsp;The Company has many long term customers which is a testament to its reputation of providing quality service at competitive prices over the years. &nbsp;Gillwood believes in adding value, not cost. &nbsp;Customer loyalty is its greatest asset.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We Specialize in taing rough sawn lumber &amp; Transforming it into Precision shaped, high quality products</div>', ''),
(1588, 1, 'United Oil & Gas Consulting Ltd', 'info@uogc.com', '910-396 11th Ave SW, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', 'www.uogc.com ', '(403) 265-0111', '(403) 294-9544', '', '<p>&nbsp;With a proven track record since 1991, United Oil &amp; Gas Consulting has experience with Canadian, US, and International projects.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Using SMART4D geo-models United Oil &amp; Gas Consulting integrates geology, petrophysical, seismic, and engineering data to make decision-making more effective. United&rsquo;s technologies have increased production, improved recoveries and reduced risk for numerous oil fields for successive years.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3D characterization and visualization are cornerstones of effective resource development practices. United excels in this field with studies of the geological environment, characterizing the variability in 3D. We assess the in-place volumes, identify sweetspots in 3D, and plan wells.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>SMART4D Geosteering allows you to align, anticipate, and act faster than other geosteering systems and services available today. This service helps you to mitigate well placement risk and optimize in zone placement, while reducing doglegs and tortuosity.</div>', ''),
(1589, 1, 'Uponor Infra Ltd.', 'NAinfra-customer.service@uponor.com', '6507 Mississauga Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.kwhpipe.ca ', '(905) 858-0206', '(905) 858-0208', '', '<p>&nbsp;As of 1 July 2013, we are a part of Uponor Infra Ltd, a joint venture between Uponor&rsquo;s and KWH Group&rsquo;s infrastructure solutions businesses. Uponor Infra will combine the best of both companies and will continue to play a strong role in the development of the infrastructure systems segment in our key markets.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company is majority-owned by Uponor (55.3%) and consolidated within Uponor Corporation as the segment, Uponor Infrastructure Solutions. KWH Group owns the remaining 44.7% of the shares.</div>', ''),
(1590, 1, 'Upside Wireless Inc.', 'info@upsidewireless.com', '1401-1211 Melville St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.upsidewireless.com ', '(604) 687-7433', '(604) 628-0105', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At Upside Wireless Inc. we make text messaging simple. Whether your needs are local or global, our easy-to-use mobile messaging solutions can help you integrate your communications for a variety of strategic activities such as marketing and advertising, communicating with sales people in the field, or increasing the level of your customer service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">With no software to download, getting a fully-integrated communications system can happen in a matter of hours. Our superior networking platform and established carrier relationships reduce your go-live time and drastically cut the costs of developing and launching your mobile messaging solutions. It is our mission to enable businesses of all sizes to use text messaging as an integral part of their communication strategies. We would love to be able to help you with yours.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to the ability to deliver messages to almost any mobile phone on the Planet, our service also provides two-way messaging using standard functionality built in all mobile phones in use today. Recipients of messages sent from our services need only to press the reply button on their handsets. These replies are then processed using our proprietary algorithm and stored in the original senders&rsquo; mailboxes. Two-way messaging encourages conversation and expands the use of our service to applications such as personal and enterprise collaboration, Instant Messaging and premium messaging. Furthermore, our service enables respondents to reply at local rates in many countries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the unique characteristics of Upside is our ability to provide true, two-way messaging to US and Canadian networks, with or without the use of Short Codes. Our established network infrastructure therefore plays a significant role in enabling our corporate customers to launch their mobile messaging services quickly, economically and without any technical constraints related to the differences in GSM and CDMA networks.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1591, 1, 'URAL Sidecar Motorcycles and CNC Machining', 'lutz@ural.ca', '1 Yankeetown Rd, HAMMONDS PLAINS, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.ural.ca ', '(902) 832-1629', '(902) 835-1484', '', '<p>&nbsp;Ural Motorcycles:</p>\r\n<div>We assemble, set up and test-drive new Ural sidecar motorcycles right out of the Russian crate.</div>\r\n<div>We are an Authorized Ural Service Facility providing service, repair and warranty work.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Motorcycle K-Tools:</div>\r\n<div>Quality K-Tools to remove and install the crank shaft</div>\r\n<div>Other specialized K-Tools for parts and assemblies</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Parts and Prototyping:</div>\r\n<div>In-house machined quality replacement parts</div>\r\n<div>New improved designs for Ural motorcycle parts</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Computer Integrated Manufacturing:</div>\r\n<div>Once a CIM project leader at a German automobile supplier, now practicing CIM at our own shop.</div>\r\n<div>Fine German engineering, made in Canada.</div>', ''),
(1592, 1, 'Urban & Environmental Management Inc.', 'reception@uemconsulting.com', '301-4701 Saint Clair Ave, NIAGARA FALLS, Ontario, Canada', 'www.uemconsulting.com ', '(905) 371-9764', '(905) 371-9763', '', '<p>&nbsp;We provide unique, innovative services that our competitors don&rsquo;t offer. &nbsp;What sets UEM apart from our competitors is our ability to complement traditional planning and engineering services with innovative expertise in specialized areas such as asset management, water resources, management systems, transportation, and waste management. We bring new ideas to projects, leading our clients to the next level of excellence.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We know our limitations. &nbsp;We routinely partner with other consulting firms or industry professionals where additional specialized experience is required for a project. &nbsp;We are honest and forthcoming about our Team&rsquo;s capabilities, and we operate our business with the utmost integrity and professionalism.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We bring experience and commitment to every project. &nbsp;We have a diverse team of professionals who have earned outstanding reputations in their respective industries. &nbsp;We believe in working alongside our clients to ensure a thorough understanding of projects and associated challenges so that we can provide the best possible solutions. &nbsp;Regardless of the project location, the magnitude of the budget, or the size of the client, we bring the same level of commitment to each and every project.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We are responsible, we are accountable, and we deliver. &nbsp;UEM has earned a reputation for providing practical solutions to project problems, on time and within budget. &nbsp;Our experienced Project Managers provide one-on-one communication with clients to ensure project progress, consistency with project schedules, and client satisfaction at all stages of a project.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The professional experience is first-rate. &nbsp;UEM offers a dynamic work environment with a constant stream of new and exciting challenges. &nbsp;Our scope of services extends beyond conventional planning and engineering: we also provide niche services that complement and enhance our projects. &nbsp;Members of the UEM Team are provided with opportunities to work in specialized fields such as transportation engineering, water resources, and asset management. &nbsp;Our staff regularly form interdisciplinary teams to tackle complex projects using unique approaches. &nbsp;At UEM, the learning never stops!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The work environment is flexible and welcoming. &nbsp;At UEM, we value a flexible work environment. &nbsp;We acknowledge that happy workers are productive workers, and our Management Team works to assist all employees in finding the right balance of professional and personal time. &nbsp;We have a diverse, multicultural team that includes young professionals and seasoned veterans from across the country and around the globe.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The benefits are competitive. &nbsp;UEM&rsquo;s benefits package is generous and includes a wide variety of coverages for both reparative and preventive care.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The opportunities are endless. &nbsp;Our Senior Professionals understand the importance of mentorship and have guided numerous staff members through processes of professional accreditation, skills development, and career planning. &nbsp;UEM&rsquo;s Management Team firmly believes in promotion-from-within and continually provides staff with career development opportunities.</div>', ''),
(1593, 1, 'Uscan Aviation Sales Limited', 'uscanltd@gmail.com', '4536 10th Sideroad, ALLISTON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.uscanaviation.com ', '(705) 435-4031', '(705) 435-4485', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">A sales, overhaul and major repair facility specializing in Bell Helicopters, began operations in 1978 and became fully licensed by Transport Canada as an Aircraft Maintenance Organization in 1979. USCAN is a Bell Helicopter service facility with certified airframe and tailboom fixtures for Bell 206, 205, 212 and 412 series allowing us to perform major airframe repairs for our customer. Our overhaul capabilities include all airframe dynamic components for the Bell 47, 204, 205, 206 and 212 series helicopters.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our services also include major modifications to aircraft and avionics installations. To assist us with more complex repairs and modifications we have a DAR available locally. We are experienced on civilian and military helicopters.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Although we are not a helicopter operator we do understand the importance of prompt quality workmanship. We are committed to giving our customers our undivided attention and service they need to support their Bell Helicopters.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whether you require a little help or a major overhaul, we would be happy to offer our services. With the current US dollar exchange rate, we are able to offer very competitive pricing and fixed flat rates on component Overhauls. We would be happy to discuss our rates with you. Our convenient location is close to the Toronto International Airport and major highway allows easy accessibility.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We would appreciate the opportunity to discuss your needs. Please do not hesitate to contact us.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1594, 1, 'Ustuntash', 'ustuntash@rogers.com', '795 Columbia Forest Blvd., WATERLOO, Ontario, Canada', '', '(519) 746-6681', '(519) 746-7781', '', '<p>&nbsp;Chemical (except Agricultural) and Allied Product Wholesaler-Distributors</p>', ''),
(1595, 1, 'UTC Aerospace Systems', 'frank.karakas@utas.utc.com', '1400 South Service Rd W, OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.utcaerospacesystems.com/ ', '(905) 827-7777', '(905) 825-1583', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems is one of the world&rsquo;s largest suppliers of technologically advanced aerospace and defense products. We design, manufacture and service systems and components and provide integrated solutions for commercial, regional, business and military aircraft, helicopters and other platforms. We are also a major supplier to international space programs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2012, UTC Aerospace Systems was formed by combining two industry leaders, Hamilton Sundstrand and Goodrich, creating an organization with key positions on a wide range of aircraft flying today and substantial content on various UAVs, satellites and ground and naval vehicles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our customers include original equipment manufacturers that build aircraft and helicopters, engine manufacturers, and airlines, as well as defense agencies and contractors. Our commitment is to help them develop and maintain safer, lighter, more reliable and more efficient aircraft and other platforms.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems is part of United Technologies (NYSE:UTX), a diversified company that provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the global aerospace and building systems industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems employs approximately 42,000 people worldwide with approximate annual sales of ~$14 billion.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1596, 1, 'UTS Consultants Inc.', 'info@utsconsultants.ca', '195 St David St S 3rd Floor, FERGUS, Ontario, Canada', 'www.utsconsultants.ca ', '(519) 787-1813', '(519) 787-1624', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems is one of the world&rsquo;s largest suppliers of technologically advanced aerospace and defense products. We design, manufacture and service systems and components and provide integrated solutions for commercial, regional, business and milOur reputation is based on our ability to bring comprehensive engineering skills to our projects that often lead to first time approvals from Municipalities and Power Utilities alike.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTS Consultants Inc. is an affiliate company of Oakville Hydro Corporation. It was founded in 1992 by Wayne Groves to fill a need for better solutions to the Telecommunications Industry&rsquo;s ongoing requirements for plant extension and modernization. With many years of experience working with Civil Engineering firms and Municipalities, UTS is comprised of Engineers and Technicians that are sensitive to the needs of both the network operator and the approving authority and understands the priorities of both. Few can boast an approval record equal to ours.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTS recognizes the importance of accurate fieldwork and the foundation it becomes for a complete engineering solution. UTS&rsquo; field technicians are fully capable of using standard manual measurement methods or with the latest Total Station/RTK Topographic Survey equipment to CAD base and final plans incorporating a variety of industry specific software.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our projects range from simple cable placing plans, to manhole rebuilds to full pole line engineering and re-engineering that is fully compliant with Ontario&rsquo;s latest ESA 22/04 and CSA requirements including non-linear calculations. We have become an industry leader in pole line structural engineering to meet the requirements of Ontario Regulation (ESA) 22/04 and we have successfully completed aerial projects in over 30 Hydro Distribution service areas.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our staff is complimented by technical and clerical resources with the expertise to suit individual project requirements. On multi-disciplined projects our experience includes building project teams by combining our talents with those of other Engineering Specialists whose specific area of competence best meets the needs of our clients. Longer term projects will have a dedicated project team with ongoing regular client reporting to ensure a &lsquo;no surprises&rsquo; solution. UTS will provide a single point of contact for all clients and all projects, no matter how large or small.itary aircraft, helicopters and other platforms. We are also a major supplier to international space programs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2012, UTC Aerospace Systems was formed by combining two industry leaders, Hamilton Sundstrand and Goodrich, creating an organization with key positions on a wide range of aircraft flying today and substantial content on various UAVs, satellites and ground and naval vehicles.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our customers include original equipment manufacturers that build aircraft and helicopters, engine manufacturers, and airlines, as well as defense agencies and contractors. Our commitment is to help them develop and maintain safer, lighter, more reliable and more efficient aircraft and other platforms.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems is part of United Technologies (NYSE:UTX), a diversified company that provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the global aerospace and building systems industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">UTC Aerospace Systems employs approximately 42,000 people worldwide with approximate annual sales of ~$14 billion.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1597, 1, 'UV Pure Technologies Inc.', 'info@uvpure.com', '6-60 Venture Dr., SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.uvpure.com', '(416) 208-9884', '(416) 208-5808', '', '<p>&nbsp;Our mission informs everything we design, make, or do: Pure safe water. Always.&reg;</p>\r\n<div>UV Pure&reg; Technologies develops and manufactures technically advanced UV water purification systems. The Canadian company recently was chosen by AlwaysOn as one of the 2012 GoingGreen Silicon Valley Global 200 winners. UV Pure also won two Frost and Sullivan&rsquo;s 2011 Best Practices Awards &ndash; as the leading water treatment technology, and the leading wastewater treatment technology for industrial and commercial use in North America. UV Pure has also been recognized by The Artemis Project as a top 50 emerging clean-tech company, globally and cited for best practices by the Ontario Centre for Advancement of Environmental Technologies in 2008 and 2010.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Since 1998, over 14,000 UV Pure systems have been installed in residential, commercial, industrial, public and municipal applications treating wastewater, reuse water, rainwater, and drinking water. An aerospace version of UV Pure&rsquo;s technology has been chosen by Boeing&reg; to purify water on its 21st century airplane, the new 787 Dreamliner&reg;.</div>\r\n<div>UV Pure&rsquo;s products are currently distributed and in use in North America, Australia and New Zealand, China, Malaysia, Singapore, Mexico and Brazil, Africa and Greece. Its customer base includes GE, Siemens, 3M Corporation, Premier Tech, Kinetico, Culligan, and a broad base of leading specifying engineering firms like Veolia, CH2M Hill, Eco-Tec and others.</div>', ''),
(1598, 1, 'UVDynamics Inc.', 'info@uvdynamics.com', '315 Neptune Cres., LONDON, Ontario, Canada', 'www.uvdynamics.com ', '(519) 452-7520', '(519) 452-1701', '', '<p>&nbsp;UV Dynamics designs and manufactures Ultraviolet (UV) water disinfection systems. UV water disinfection is a proven, affordable, environmentally friendly technology that can help you to ensure the safety of your water supply.</p>\r\n<div>Extreme weather, spring snow melts and run-off from intensive agriculture activities are all affecting the safety of our private water sources. Even municipal water can no longer be assumed to be safe with boil water advisories becoming more frequent. Compared to chemical disinfection, UV water disinfection can never overdose, has no effect on taste and odour, and no carcinogenic disinfection by-products are produced with UV water disinfection. UV water disinfection is considered effective against cryptosporidium and giardia, pathogens which are almost completely resistant to chlorine. UV water disinfection systems have low operating costs and no tools are required for maintenance or lamp replacement.</div>\r\n<div>All our models incorporate both audio and visual lamp failure indicators along with an annual lamp change reminder timer. Many models also incorporate an isolated low voltage solenoid drive circuit for an optional water shut-off solenoid valve.</div>', ''),
(1599, 1, 'Uxline Services Inc.', 'aida@uxline.com', '1748 2nd Ave W, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', '', '(604) 999-6524', '', '', '<p>Our mission is to provide services and products for all type of companies to improve the user&rsquo;s experience on their websites, software and other interactive applications. We provide unmoderated remote user testing and usability studies to graphic designers, marketing managers, enterpreneurs, website agencies, online marketing agencies and anyone who wants to improve the user experience in their websites or other applications. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1600, 1, 'V I F Mould and Plastics Industries Ltd.', 'info@vifplastics.com', '4000 Casavant Blvd W, SAINT-HYACINTHE, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.vifplastics.com ', '(450) 774-6953', '(450) 774-4970', '', '<div>An integrated product development program must include the capability to conceive and design an original product. Demand for conceptual and engineering services can come from a wide range of interests.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our staff at VIF has created, or co-developed with our clients, such diverse products as underwater photographic equipment, educational materials, ventilation system controls, security devices, medical equipment...You will find our personnel eager to understand your requirements, and disciplined in their procedure.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Nothing is left to chance!</div>', ''),
(1601, 1, 'V&F Gas Analysis Systems Inc.', 'rodney.resch@vandfna.com', 'PO Box 24022 RPO Bullfrog, GUELPH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vandf.com ', '(519) 766-7760', '(519) 766-7761', '', '<p>&nbsp;Innovative measuring instruments for gas phase analysis</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>It is V&amp;F\'s aim to help our clients to obtain results and solutions on which basis they can optimize their production processes, improve the quality of their products and minimize pollutants.</div>\r\n<div>Our instruments for online gas analysis focus on industrial customers and their needs for flexible, robust, fast and sensitive measurements.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Scientific work at several universities like Innsbruck (Austria), Boulder (USA), Southampton (UK), Paris (France), Greifswald (Germany), Trento (Italy) led to the development of instruments to simulate reactions of atoms and molecules in space (interstellar clouds).</div>\r\n<div>These research works were the prerequisites for the Ion-Molecule Reaktion Mass Spectrometry (IMR-MS) which is the core technology used for most of the V&amp;F Analyzers. Today IMR is one of the most sensitive techniques to detect impurities in gases.</div>', ''),
(1602, 1, 'V.P. Fabricant de Stores', 'info@ca.objectiflune.com', '2315, boul. des Entreprises Local 102, TERREBONNE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vpstores.ca ', '(450) 477-5223', '(450) 477-1033', '', '<p>&nbsp;Distributor of blinds and lace for window for many decorations stores in Canada. We produce any size of blinds and we got high quality lace for window.</p>', ''),
(1603, 1, 'Vac Aero International Inc.', 'vacaeroinfo@vacaero.com', '1371 Speers Rd, OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vacaero.com ', '(905) 827-4171', '(905) 827-0868', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO is a leading vacuum furnace manufacturer and metallurgical service provider to aerospace and high-tech industries worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO offers a complete line of heat treating and brazing furnaces, from small horizontal laboratory units to large, vertical models. All VAC AERO furnaces come equipped with the Honeywell HC-900 system &quot;hybrid process control system&quot;.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO furnaces operate worldwide in diverse applications in a variety of industries such as; turbine engine component manufacture and repair, medical bone implants, nuclear materials, tool and die manufacturing, research and other high-tech industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO specializes in vacuum heat treating and brazing of advanced materials and holds numerous customer and quality system approvals from prime manufacturers in aerospace and other high-tech industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO has the equipment and expertise to process a wide variety of materials including steels, superalloys, aluminum and titanium for such diverse applications as aircraft landing gear and structural parts, aero and land-based turbine engine components, nuclear components and a host of other specialized applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AC AERO offers a variety of coating processes for protection and restoration of both new and service-exposed components. Services to the aerospace and high-tech industries include; plasma and HVOF spray coatings, inorganic paint and pack coatings as well as grinding and shot and glass bead peening.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO operates two fully integrated state-of-the Art High Velocity Oxygen Fuel (HVOF) system based on a new generation Carbide Jet System. VAC AERO offers Coating services in three of it\'s plants in Boucherville, Quebec, Canada, Kalisz and Rzeszow, Poland.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VAC AERO is accredited to NADCAP and AS9100B standards for heat treating, welding and tensile testing and holds numerous customer approvals from major aerospace prime contractors. VAC AERO operates heat treating and coating facilities in Canada, Poland and India and has world-wide sales representation.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1604, 1, 'Valley Metal Ltd.', 'info@valleymetal.com', '2912, 11th St SE, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.valleymetal.com ', '(403) 243-7778', '(403) 243-1476', '', '<p>&nbsp;Valley Metal Ltd. produces abroad range of metal table bases, chairs, brass railings, stemware racks, custom plating, painting and architectural specialty metal works from its plant in Calgary, Alberta. The products have numerous applications in the hospitality, restaurant, contract office furnishings, institutional and architectural industry sectors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The majority of sales are to the contract office furnishing manufactures and distributors.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company is currently developing a quality control program for its manufacturing and plating operations in preparation for ISO 9000 certification.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Valley Metal Fabricators Ltd. has an established research and development department, as well the ability to produce its entire products from manufacturing to complete finishing all in one facility. The company also offers a computer design &quot;CAD&quot;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>service to its clients. With these key elements the company provides a complete manufacturing, design facility enabling it to produce an excellence of quality in its products and services. &nbsp;</div>', '');
