(1605, 1, 'Valmart Door Sales Ltd.', 'info@valmartdoors.com', '114 - 9644 - 192nd St, SURREY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.valmartdoors.com ', '(604) 888-6116', '(604) 888-8828', '', '<p>&nbsp;Val Mart Door Sales offers many services for the industrial and commercial door market. Doing professional installations as well as specialty work and offering 24-hour service is what has made Val Mart an industry leader since 1976. Val Mart offers installation and service on strip curtains, sectional (overhead) doors, glass doors, airport hangar doors, sliding doors, rolling doors, fire doors, truck doors, and many others; as well as doing repairs on dock levelers. Our experience and expertise makes us a company worth doing business with.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We operate in such areas as: Vancouver, Burnaby, West Vancouver, North Vancouver, Richmond, Port Moody, New Westminster, Coquitlam, Port Coquitlam, Maple Ridge, Pitt Meadows, Ladner, Tsawwassen, White Rock, Surrey, Delta, Langley, Abbotsford, Mission, Chilliwack, and beyond!</div>', ''),
(1606, 1, 'VBPLUS INC.', 'vbplus@vbplus.ca', '1000, rue de la Gauchetiere O Bureau 2400, 24e eta, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vbplus.ca ', '(514) 737-6279', '(514) 737-0428', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">An On-Site Training School and Specialized Publishing House under the same roof: an excellent strategy for balance and success.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Always focusing on the needs of its clients, VBPLUS INC. has a very personal approach and a great respect for others. The firm is highly creative and constantly strives to help people reach their personal and professional goals.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1607, 1, 'VCI Controls Inc.', 'vciott@vcicontrols.ca', ' D-1 Royal Gate Blvd, WOODBRIDGE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vcicontrols.ca ', '(905) 850-4464', '(905) 850-4474', '', '<p>&nbsp;For three decades VCI CONTROLS Inc. has been the envy of the industry. Our clients have come to expect and rely on our prompt, professional, and knowledgeable team that goes well beyond the basics, providing complete satisfaction and peace of mind.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VCI pioneering knowledge of controls, together with its expertise in mechanical service ensure one phone call accountability. We are focused on providing building technologies and services that improve comfort, safety and occupant productivity. And using the power of our Performance Monitoring offering, we can typically save between 5% and 15% of a buildings energy spend without capital improvement.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our service department is available 24/7. &nbsp;As part of our maintenance program, we document and provide you with a detailed report on existing problems and suggested improvements with your HVAC equipment and BAS system.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our service technicians and team employ a holistic approach to solving problems before they become critical and work with you to implement strategies and programs targeted to reduce operating and energy costs.</div>', ''),
(1608, 1, 'VCT Courier', 'dinhmccain@gmail.com', '101-306 Sixth St, NEW WESTMINSTER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.couriernewwestminsterbc.ca ', '(778) 859-8179', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;VCT Courier promises prompt and safe delivery of your packages as a reliable courier in New Westminster, BC.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If you need fast and trustworthy courier service at the most competitive price, VCT Courier delivers! Our courier service understands that any delay can be costly from a business standpoint, which is why we are proud to be able to provide package delivery services to the lower mainland within 3 hours of drop-off at our convenient location. In addition to same-day delivery services for the greater Vancouver area, by working with DHL and FedEx, our courier service is able to help your packages get from New Westminster to other parts of Canada, the US, and beyond. For the added convenience of our customers, we also offer money transfers to Vietnam and the Philippines from our business office as well as immigration services with free consultations, which include the following:&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>-Student Visa</div>\r\n<div>-Work Permit Visa</div>\r\n<div>-Investor Visa</div>\r\n<div>-Skilled Worker Visa&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>-The Provincial Nominee Program Visa&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>-Business Immigration Visa</div>\r\n<div>-Skilled Trades Workers Visa</div>\r\n<div>-PRC Renewal</div>\r\n<div>-Canadian Citizenship Application&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>When you need service you can count on at the absolute best price, you can count on VCT Courier in New Westminster, BC.</div>', ''),
(1609, 1, 'VDC Canada', 'dvalentini@vdccanada.com', '218 Martindale Rd, ST CATHARINES, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vdccanada.com ', '(905) 228-3178', '(416) 352-7502', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VDC Canada has grown to be one of the largest Canadian Liquidators that specializes in inventory acquisitions from many retailers, manufacturers, and distributors. We warehouse our inventory in our Liquidation Warehouse that is located in St. Catharines, Ontario, Canada. Our inventories can be customer returns, damaged products, freight damage, and end of season &amp; overstock goods.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Canadian Liquidation: Canadian Liquidation has increased tremendously over the years, and VDC Canada has been leading the way in sourcing and providing clients with exceptional deals since 1996.We carry over 400 pallets in our Liquidation Warehouse. This allows you the opportunity to come and see exactly what you\'re buying. No longer do you have to purchase sight unseen.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Liquidation Canada: Our product categories consist of but are not limited to; Apparel, Hardware, Sporting Goods, Toys, Electronics, Bed &amp; Bath, Tools, Luggage, Furniture, Baby Product, Seasonal Goods,and many one time opportunity buys that Canadian Liquidators stock in their Off Price stores and Liquidation warehouse. We are based at VDC Canada 218 Martindale Road, St. Catharines,, ONTARIO, L2R 6P9, Canada<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At VDC, honesty and integrity is our main focus to build long lasting relationships with every customer.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1610, 1, 'Vecima Networks Inc.', 'sales@vecima.com', '150 Cardinal Place, SASKATOON, Saskatchewan, Canada ', 'www.vecima.com ', '(306) 955-7075', '(306) 955-9919', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vecima designs, manufactures and sells products that enable broadband access to cable, wireless and telephony networks. Vecima&rsquo;s hardware products incorporate original embedded software to meet the complex requirements of next-generation, high-speed digital networks. Service providers use Vecima&rsquo;s solutions to deliver services to a converging worldwide broadband market, including what are commonly known as &ldquo;triple play&rdquo; (voice, video and data) and &ldquo;quadruple play&rdquo; (voice, video, data and wireless) services. Vecima&rsquo;s solutions allow service providers to bridge the final network segment that connects a system directly to end-users, commonly referred to as &ldquo;the last mile&rdquo;.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vecima&rsquo;s products incorporate sophisticated hardware and software developed within our research and development facilities. Our products are used for encryption, decryption, processing, converting and transporting all types of digital media within connected-device ecosystems.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1611, 1, 'Vector Construction Ltd.', 'winnipeg@vectorconstructionltd.com', '474 Dovercourt Dr., Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.vectorgroup.com ', '(204) 489-6300', '(204) 489-6033', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vector Construction is a concrete repair, protection and restoration company with offices throughout North America, including Canada and the U.S. We offer an extensive portfolio of solutions to extend the service life of concrete, masonry structures and facilities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Proudly providing solutions to assist our clients with all aspects of their concrete restoration, concrete repair and concrete protection needs for over 45 year.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vector is committed to:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Providing a safe work environment.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Building long term relationships with our clients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Developing our employees.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Being a leader in the concrete restoration industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From small repair projects to multi-faceted multi-million dollar full scale concrete restoration projects Vector can deliver on every phase including:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Assisting owners and engineers in problem identification.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Development of repair options and feasibility studies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Budget pricing of concrete repair options and delivery options to meet your facilities needs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Turn-key delivery and management of the complete repair process.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Delivery of completed project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1612, 1, 'VF Imagewear Canada Incorporated', 'kendra_derbyshire@vfc.com', '9146 Yellowhead Trail NW, EDMONTON, Alberta, Canada', 'www.imagewear.com ', '(780) 479-4444', '(780) 477-1718', '', '<p>&nbsp;ImageWear was established in 1996 as a division of The Walman Optical Company&mdash;the largest independent ophthalmic company in the United States with over 40 branch offices. The Walman Optical Company and all of its divisions are owned by the employees of the company through an employee stock ownership plan (ESOP).</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With the success of Structure, ImageWear&rsquo;s first private label collection, the company soon partnered with Hans Stepper in 2005 to distribute the world recognized Stepper Eyewear collection. The Stepper collection features quality materials such as TX5 Grilamid and Titanium and is well known for its high quality and superior fit. Stepper Eyewear continues to be one of ImageWear&rsquo;s bestselling collections today.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In 2010, ImageWear introduced the Callaway Eyewear collection for men. Soon to follow was Callaway Sunwear for both men and women featuring the NEOX Transitions Adaptive Sunwear lenses. Most recently in 2012, ImageWear introduced the London Fog eyewear collection for women.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Today ImageWear has over 50 representatives that sell directly to the Eye Care Professional. ImageWear representatives carry a wealth of products that include proprietary eyewear collections, I.Line Readers and Visionaries polarized sun clips.</div>', ''),
(1613, 1, 'VFI', 'mskinner@vegroup.net', '190 Don Hillock Dr, AURORA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.video-furn.com ', '(905) 946-1459', '(905) 751-1488', '', '<p>&nbsp;Makers of videoconference furniture, from roll-about monitor stands to boardroom tables</p>', ''),
(1614, 1, 'Vi-Lux Building Products Inc.', 'info@vi-lux.com', '105 Richmond Blvd, NAPANEE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vi-lux.com', '(613) 354-4830', '(613) 354-6589', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vi-Lux Building Products Inc. is a manufacturer of cellular PVC products located in Napanee, Ontario, Canada.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For more than 20 years, Vi-Lux Building Products Inc. has continued to focus on products for the building materials industry, as well as manufacturing components and custom profiles for the window and door industry.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As cellular PVC millwork continues to grow as the preferred alternative to wood in many building applications &ndash; because of its ability to resist the elements and its cost effectiveness &ndash; so do we.&nbsp; We are dedicated to delivering the best product and customer service at great prices, and our company is set for continued growth in this expanding market.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vi-Lux Building Products Inc. delivers consistent high-quality, a broad product variety and, working together with our customers, just-in-time delivery to meet all their needs.&nbsp; Customers count on our continuous product and process development to produce products consistent with ever-evolving consumer demands.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">So, welcome to the Vi-Lux world.&nbsp; We are building our company on the foundations of superior products and outstanding service so you can build your own enterprise with total confidence.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1615, 1, 'Via-Chem', 'info@via-chem.com', '353 McCaffrey St, SAINT-LAURENT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.via-chem.com ', '(514) 332-3533', '(514) 332-0773', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are a 35 year plus supplier of Cyanoacrylate (Superglue), Epoxy Adhesive, Cements, Stationary Adhesives, Nail Care Products, Adhesive Backed Decorative Hooks, and Super Klips Wire and Tool Management Fasteners.</p>\r\n<div>We are pleased to provide Retail Ready, Bulk, or Private Label products</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>About Our Products</div>\r\n<div>Our Retail &quot;Carded Product&quot; Division supplies Hardware, Discount, Convenience, Food &amp; Drug Stores as well as the Distributors who sell to these Retailers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Professional / Industrial / Hobby Division supplies Industrial Accounts with Professional Grade Adhesives, as well as our Super Klips Fastener Line. Finally, we are pleased to be supplying our Cyanoacrylate Adhesives to the Professional &quot;Finger Nail Glue&quot; Industry.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Via Bond Nail Enhancement Products / Rendez-Vous Nails division supplies key Nail Care product lines (Adhesives, Gel Polish, Acrylic Systems, Nail Polish, Top Coats, Accessories, Files &amp; Brushes)</div>', ''),
(1616, 1, 'VKG METAL INC.', 'info@vkgmetals.com', '1860 Bonhill Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', '', '(647) 830-5849', '(866) 897-8541', '', '<p>&nbsp;We believe our success lies and work along the success of our mandates, and clients. VKG Metal Inc., strives to meet the requirements of our vendors and customers. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1617, 1, 'VKI Technologies Inc.', 'customer.service@vkitech.com', '3200 2nd St, SAINT-HUBERT, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vkitech.com ', '(450) 676-0504', '(450) 676-9348', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Established in 1947, VKI Technologies is a world leader in the design, manufacture and distribution of advanced coffee systems based on diverse, fresh-brew technologies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1967, VKI developed the single-cup brewer that would eventually become one of the world\'s finest, the Vendking brewer. Today, the advanced version of this device continues to ensure the freshness and aroma of millions of beverages brewed to suit the taste of consumers around the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Attentive to the evolving tastes of the marketplace as well as the needs of its business partners, VKI increased its line of products and services, solidifying its position as a leader in the industry. The development of integrated and innovative products and services ensures its distinct competitive edge on the national and international markets.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Since 1998, VKI Technologies has adopted a first-class approach to ensure the continuous improvement of its corporate processes. Best business practices, increased customer satisfaction, process optimization and employees\' mobilization have been the keys to ensuring our unparalleled quality.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As an equipment manufacturer, VKI Technologies follows a very strict quality management process that has resulted in ISO 9001:2008 certification. This accreditation guarantees that every product designed by VKI adheres to a series of internationally recognized quality standards.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">VKI\'s quality system encompasses every operational aspect - research and design, purchasing, production, distribution, and customer service. VKI\'s commitment to quality is not limited to maintaining its ISO Certification through yearly audits. This system is vital to ensuring continuous improvement and increased customer satisfaction.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1618, 1, 'VL Communications', 'vlcom@vlcom.com', '3424 Industriel Blvd, LAVAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vlcom.com ', '(450) 963-8940', '(450) 963-8949', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Software manufacturer. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Software manufacturer for repair shop of the automotive industry.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1619, 1, 'VLM Foods Inc.', 'marcel@vlmfoods.com', '101-52 Himus Blvd , POINTE-CLAIRE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vlmfoods.com ', '(514) 426-4100', '(514) 426-5977', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Once rarely seen tropical fruits, Asian vegetables and unique varietals are now common staples to an increasing number of discerning consumers who have come to expect year round access to a wide range of top quality foodstuffs. From frozen fruit and vegetable program management to end product development, VLM has the supply chain oversight and qualified personnel to meet the needs of our quality conscious 24/7 365 food system. As a tropical fruit processor and global supplier of processed fruits and vegetables, VLM is committed to ensuring the quality and safety of the competitively priced foods we bring to market.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>From changing consumption patterns in mature markets to exciting opportunities in emerging markets, the international protein trade is truly dynamic in nature and global in scope. Leveraging our long standing relationships with key processing partners as well as in depth product knowledge and our recognized expertise in cold chain logistics, trade finance and regulatory compliance&hellip;.VLM is a vital supplier of beef, pork and poultry products to a truly global clientele. From primal cuts to offals, from national tenders to speciality items for further processing &ndash; VLM&rsquo;s team of dedicated international trade professionals stands ready to handle all your protein needs.</div>', ''),
(1620, 1, 'VMAC', 'vmac@vmac.ca', '1333 Kipp Rd, NANAIMO, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.vmacair.com ', '(250) 740-3200', '(250) 740-3201', '', '<p>&nbsp;VMAC is an award-winning, world-leader in the development of compact, powerful truck mounted mobile air compressor solutions used for service trucks, public works, utilities, highway/heavy construction, oil and mining.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VMAC engineers and manufactures systems featuring high-powered, rotary screw, air-on-demand technology including 70cfm/150cfm UNDERHOOD air compressors, 40cfm/60cfm PREDATAIR hydraulic-driven air compressors, 60cfm RAPTAIR stand-alone diesel drive air compressors and the RAPTAIR-MF Multifunction Diesel Drive.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VMAC&rsquo;s success comes from working with customers to determine their air compressor needs and then surpassing those needs with unparalleled quality, innovation and customer service. Regularly introducing new and innovative products ensures VMAC remains the leader in truck mounted mobile air compressor technology.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Facility</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VMAC, a Division of Mangonel Investments Corporation, is situated on almost 8 acres of land, in the middle of a lush Cedar tree forest approximately 8 kilometers (5 miles) south of Nanaimo, British Columbia, Canada.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The building space totals almost 33,000 square feet and houses departments focusing on Research &amp; Development, Engineering, Production, Inventory Management, Marketing, Sales and Finance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Team</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The VMAC team is lead by President, Jim Hogan and consists of an international Dealer Network and sales force, innovative engineering and design crew, manufacturing and service specialists, plus high caliber administration and management professionals. The rapid growth of VMAC has caused a workforce expansion to approximately 100 full and part-time employees, all highly trained in their important roles at VMAC.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Company History</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The company was founded in Kitchener, Ontario, when two school friends, Tony Menard and Jim Hogan, decided that their entrepreneurial ideas required additional working capital. So, they decided to open their own machine shop. On August 8, 1986, VMAC (Vehicle Mounted Air Compressors) was incorporated under the name of Mangonel Corporation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>By 1988, VMAC had become specialized in the manufacture of UNDERHOOD mounting brackets for truck-mounted air compressors. In 1990, Tony moved the company to his native hometown, Nanaimo, British Columbia. Jim had decided to stay in Ontario instead of moving with Tony but four years later, he rejoined the business.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>By 1996, the company had designed and introduced an electronic throttle control to complement its product range. VMAC Throttle Commander products are currently used on most popular light-duty work trucks for the construction, tire service truck, utility, emergency equipment, mining, forestry, and agriculture industries.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Beginning in 1997, Tony realized that reciprocating compressors UNDERHOOD would not be viable in future aerodynamic truck designs. In September 1997, VMAC introduced a new mobile air solution that would revolutionize the industry &ndash; the UNDERHOOD VR7000 (a.k.a. VR70) rotary screw air compressor system.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VMAC continued to expand its VR70 and Throttle Commander product base over the next few years. And in 2002, VMAC once again amazed the mobile compressed air industry by introducing the VR150, doubling the output of the VR70 while remaining UNDERHOOD. The power of this unit allowed VMAC to compete with tow-behind portable air compressors.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Several years ago Lincoln Electric, a leader in welding system manufacturing, approached VMAC to build a product that would compliment a welder application to meet the needs of its customers. After some initial evaluation, the Research and Design Department at VMAC took the project on and introduced a product that worked directly with the Lincoln system. The Air Vantage 500 combined the functions of a Welder, Generator and Air Compressor. This product design helped VMAC make advances in other product developments.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In 2004, VMAC set out on an aggressive customer-focused research campaign, to find its next great product line. Utilizing the knowledge gained from the research and experience gained from manufacturing UNDERHOOD Air Compressor systems for ten years, VMAC developed the world&rsquo;s lightest and smallest above deck hydraulic powered air compressor system. The powerful PREDATAIR60 Hydraulic Air Compressor System took VMAC from a niche supplier of UNDERHOOD Air Compressor Systems to a supplier in a mainstream market whereby many companies compete for market share. The launch in 2005 was one of the most exciting launches VMAC has ever seen.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In July 2010, VMAC was deeply saddened by the loss of president Tony Menard in an accident. Jim Hogan took over as president of the company, which rallied to carry on the founder&rsquo;s vision.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>About Our Company Founder</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>VMAC continues to deliver application solutions to a broad spectrum of the market and is encouraged that other manufactures are following their lead in the area of UNDERHOOD technology. With thousands of installations world-wide and the development of new and innovative products, VMAC will continue to lead the mobile compressed air industry into the future&hellip;</div>', ''),
(1621, 1, 'VMP Group', 'info@vmpgroup.com', '319 Charlotte St Third Floor, SYDNEY, Nova Scotia, Canada ', 'www.vmpgroup.com ', '(902) 562-8006', '(902) 562-4146', '', '<p>&nbsp;We\'re a &quot;Next-Generation&quot; digital marketing agency founded in 1995 and headquartered in Sydney, Nova Scotia. We separate ourselves from other service providers through our unique expertise in electronic media.</p>', ''),
(1622, 1, 'Vocantas Inc.', 'info@vocantas.com', '120-135 Michael Cowpland Dr., KANATA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.vocantas.com ', '(613) 271-8853', '(613) 271-8381', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vocantas was founded in 2003 with a mission to answer the call for intelligent and interactive voice response communication systems. The company, characterized by its talent for seamless integrations and complex, customized IVR solutions, has steadily increased over the past decade in flexibility, modality and intelligence. Each new customized solution allows Vocantas to exercise its capacity for innovation in the field of robust IVR systems that solve real world problems. Now boasting over 140 clients across a variety of industries, Vocantas continues to help companies attain meaningful customer service and intelligent customer communication.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">utility bill payment by phoneVocantas&rsquo; leading IVR solution for utilities, Utilities OnCall, fields and redirects hundreds of calls that utility companies receive every day, and provides valuable information in real time about current outages, payment history, and account status, while even allowing customers to make bill payments over the phone. Utilities OnCall does even more than that, however; the solution also handles all outbound communication, allowing utility companies to reach out to their customers and remind them of overdue payments, inform them of outages, and advise them of any weather conditions that may affect their service.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Many of the impressive features of Utilities OnCall and the IVR solutions that followed it are made possible through Vocantas&rsquo; numerous integrations with payment systems, customer databases, and other complex products and solutions, allowing Vocantas the flexibility to plug in to any system, anywhere. The company&rsquo;s commitment to integration and interoperability and its use of Microsoft technologies make Vocantas solutions some of the most flexible solutions today.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vocantas&rsquo; journey hit another milestone with the development of CallAssure, Vocantas&rsquo; IVR solution for healthcare. Designed with the help of hospital and healthcare professionals across Canada, CallAssure has become Vocantas&rsquo; most flexible system, providing solutions that speak tohealthcare patient follow up by phone specific needs for specific institutions in the field of medicine. From appointment reminder calls, to patient satisfaction and post-discharge inquiries, to nurse scheduling, CallAssure is constantly growing more intelligent and more robust to address new healthcare innovation requirements. Recently, Vocantas developed a new piece to add to CallAssure&rsquo;s impressive list of applications; the new Interactive Emergency Broadcast Notification System ensures that any healthcare institution can be confident that they will be able to recruit the staff they need quickly, through multiple modes of contact, in the event of a city, province, or statewide emergency.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Vocantas began as a company committed to telephone communication, but has kept up with technological innovations to consistently give the most expansive service available. Whatever their customers&rsquo; preferences in terms of contacting message recipients, Vocantas offers. Email, SMS messaging, and the traditional phone call are all supported by Vocantas&rsquo; IVR solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1623, 1, 'Vogo Hardware', 'info@rainbowprecision.com', '1541 Floradale Rd, ELMIRA, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.vogo.com ', '(519) 885-4755', '(519) 885-6249', '', '<p>&nbsp;VOGO Inc. Manufactures window hardware for PVC casement&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&amp; awning windows. Our current products are an airtight&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>handle lock plus accessories. Our hardware has features that are patented in the U.S. &amp; Canada. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1624, 1, 'VPL Enterprises Ltd.', 'primex@primex.ca', '20160 92A Ave, LANGLEY, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.vplenterprises.com', '(604) 881-7875', '(604) 881-7835', '', '<p>&nbsp;A Plastic Injection Moulding company manufacturing and custom design of unique products for the Telecom, Construction, HVAC and industrial market place.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On April 1st, 2013 VPL Enterprises Ltd., the parent company of Vanguard Plastics and Primex Manufacturing, changed its operating name to PRIMEX MANUFACTURING LTD.</p>\r\n<p>The name change is a strategic move to better reflect the Company&rsquo;s vision, streamline communications and strengthen our brand in the marketplace.</p>', ''),
(1625, 1, 'VRINDA Inc', 'info@glassessential.com', '33 Clairfields Dr. W, GUELPH, Ontario, Canada', 'www.GlassEssential.com ', '(519) 780-2527', '(888) 335-2104', '', '<p>&nbsp;We provide complete security solutions for your residence and your business. We specialize in physical barriers such as Window Security Bars, Sliding Grilles, Folding Gates, Rolling Shutters, Rolling Grilles, Access Control, Alarm Systems and CCTV and Wire Mesh Partitions.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Glass is an essential and critical part of almost all building and design projects. It stands to reason. Glass easily breaks and create a high possibility for break ins, smash and grab and robbery type of crime. It is worthy investment for securing people and property inside of building by securing the Glass Window and Doors.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our expert Security experts with top technical knowledge in physical Security, Barrier security, Visual security and Electronics security advises how to get reducing break and enter possibilities, forced entry protection, delay and deter thieves, leaving them empty handed and increasing the chance of capture and arrest. Our products have intense strength and will be perfectly engineered to provide home and business a fear less environment. We have a wide varied knowledge, experience and skill to give you highest possible security solution at most affordable price.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Whether your need is for Home, Industrial, Commercial, Retail Loss Prevention or Property Management Service Contracts you can trust GlassEssential to get the job done. We are based in Guelph, Ontario and provide services across Canada and USA so please browse our site for more information or contact us with any questions you may have.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>You want it done right and you want it done well. That is why everyone we hire is not only trained to get the job done; they are also trained in customer service. We promise that when you buy our products and hire services. You will be assured that professional service will be provided, and that you will be treated with a smile. No problem is too large or too small for us. Give us a call for a free estimate.</div>', ''),
(1626, 1, 'VRVANA INC', 'info@vrvana.com', '305-460 Sainte-Catherine W, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.vrvana.com ', '(514) 448-6831', '(514) 495-9988', '', '<p>&nbsp;Vrvana is the brainchild of gamer and engineer Bertrand Nepveu. Totem was designed with robust technology and user comfort in mind. Back in 2005, it all started as a personal quest to improve his video gaming experience. With an expanded team of software and hardware engineers and 5 prototype versions completed, they have a product that&rsquo;s ready for developers to begin using to create outstanding 3D VR experiences.</p>', ''),
