(1665, 1, 'WSP Canada Inc. (Automation Group)', 'jean.pierre.poirier@wspgroup.com', '2010 Powell St, JONQUIÈRE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.wspgroup.com ', '(418) 548-3060', '(418) 548-4191', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are a diverse group of individuals that include engineers, scientists, technicians, consultants and academics. We work together to provide the most effective and sustainable solutions for our clients. Our core values support this, and create an environment where our people can flourish.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Mission statement defines why we exist, and our vision clearly identifies what we aspire to become. Our core values are the priorities we set for our practices and daily activities.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>OUR MISSION:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Be a solution-driven advisor with outstanding expertise.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>OUR VISION:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Always be the first choice for clients, partners and employees.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>On October 31st, 2014, the transaction to acquire Parsons Brinckerhoff was closed. &nbsp;Long recognized as one of the world\'s leading transportation engineering firms, Parsons Brinckerhoff&rsquo;s expertise enhances WSP in providing comprehensive services for all types of infrastructure projects including power, buildings, water/wastewater, mining and community development. WSP, through its acquisition of Parsons Brinckerhoff, has approximately 32,000 employees, mainly engineers, technicians, scientists, architects, planners, surveyors, other design professionals, as well as various environmental experts, based in more than 500 offices, across 39 countries, on 5 continents. WSP, including Parsons Brinckerhoff, had pro forma revenues of $4.5 billion for the 12 months ended December 31, 2013.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>WSP also acquired Focus, Technip TPS and Winward, increasing its expertise in geomatics, in buildings and infrastructure engineering. &nbsp;The acquisitions grew our client base and our presence in Alberta, France, the U.S. and Australia.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>On January 1st, 2014, the Company reorganized its corporate structure to create a parent company named WSP Global Inc. and adopted a common brand, WSP, thus creating a united company with one strategy and one vision.</div>', ''),
(1666, 1, 'WT&C Enterprises', 'wtandc@shaw.ca', '5808 Dalkeith Hill NW, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada', '', '(403) 228-2135', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;WT&amp;C provides advanced waste water treatment systems and technologies to the Canadian natural resources industries, primarily:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1. Gold mining&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>2. Copper mining&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3. Uranium mining&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4. Oil &amp; Gas source and produced water&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Proven systems operating in other countries. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1667, 1, 'WT&T Inc', 'info@wttechnology.com', '04-277 Lakeshore Rd, POINTE-CLAIRE, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.wttechnology.com ', '(514) 804-0822', '(514) 551-6617', '', '<p>&nbsp;WT&amp;T Inc is a manufacturer of fiber-coupled, stabilized coherent (laser diodes) and broad-band (SLED, LED) semiconductor light sources, covering visible and near infra-red wavelength range for various applications, including spectroscopy, optical sensing, biology and metrology. Also WT&amp;T produces fiber-based components, including micro-lensed fiber, fiber probes, optical fiber reflectors, collimators and specialty patch-cords.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>Through continuous interaction with academy and research centers, WT&amp;T developed range of compact, customized, multi-functional optical fiber modules for research labs.</div>', ''),
(1668, 1, 'Wulftec / M.J. Maillis Group', 'wulftec@wulftec.com', '209 Wulftec St, AYER\'S CLIFF, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.wulftec.com ', '(819) 838-4232', '(819) 838-5539', '', '<p>&nbsp;Since 1990, Wulftec International has been synonymous with unbeatable strength and durability in the stretchwrapping industry. We are renowned for developing, manufacturing and distributing the industry&rsquo;s best-built stretchwrappers. Our unwavering focus on quality, service and innovation means Wulftec machines are designed to work flawlessly in any environment and under any condition, load after load.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Reasons for Success&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Why are Wulftec stretchwrappers considered to be the best? In addition to boasting unique patented features and European-influenced designs, every Wulftec stretchwrapper comes with the Wulftec Advantage, which includes all-steel structural designs, AC variable frequency drives and the best warranties available. Behind every meticulously handcrafted Wulftec machine are 200 highly skilled employees who work in a state-of-the-art 136,000 square-foot facility located just minutes from the Canadian-U.S. border and 75 miles from Montreal. We take pride in knowing that our commitment to excellence just can&rsquo;t be beat.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A Commitment to Customer Satisfaction&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In early 2002, Wulftec was acquired by M.J. Maillis Group, a leading Europe-based Group that designs, manufactures and distributes complete &ldquo;end of line&rdquo; packaging solutions, including strapping, stretchwrapping and shrinkwrapping materials and equipment. Present in more than 19 countries worldwide, the Group&rsquo;s global resources have strengthened Wulftec&rsquo;s competitive advantage and ability to provide superior solutions to meet the individual needs of clients. Our strong entrepreneurial spirit dictates that if we haven&rsquo;t built it yet, we&rsquo;ll work with clients to build it now. This commitment to customer satisfaction goes well beyond equipment design. We also give equal attention to installation and operations training, after-sales service and maintenance.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Thanks to the can-do approach of Wulftec&rsquo;s sales and service departments, along with our extensive network of Wulftec distributors, it&rsquo;s easy for clients to benefit from the exceptional value, reliability and productivity that only Wulftec can offer.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1669, 1, 'WVL Enterprises', 'info@abcinfonet.com', '655 Lakeshore Dr., NORTH BAY, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.abcinfonet.com ', '(705) 495-3556', '', '', '<div>\r\n<div>Internet Consulting and Internet Marketing, Web-Site Design, Proramming: HTML, Perl, Java, CGI, UNIX, Internet Publishing, Publishers of Canada\'s Northern Life Awards for NorthernLife: Top Choice for Most Innovative Canadian Site. The Canuck Site of the Day, 4Star Magellan. Top Business Site Award for B&amp;W Virtual Publishers Corporate Site. 18 TOP SHOPPING AWARDS for our clients, 1 Top Business Award of Client.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>All awards are for Web-Site-Design.&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1670, 1, 'www.logistrics.com', 'mail@littleservices.com', '601-255 Duncan Mill Rd, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.logistrics.com ', '(416) 792-2104', '(416) 331-8289', '', '<p>&nbsp;Logistrics is a proprietary offering of Little Services Gateway Inc., a Toronto (Canada) based M2M Company providing its solutions under a &ldquo;Software as a Service&rdquo; model. It serves the transportation sector with specific focus on Taxi Dispatch, Crew Management, Distributors, Fleet tracking &amp; On-Call Services. Its Crew application is used by a large U.S crew hauler serving several Fortune 500 U.S Railroads. The Company&rsquo;s Android based taxi dispatch system was the first of its kind in the Android Market when it was launched in 2010 and is used by customers worldwide. The solution works on all Android smart phones and tablets. The Company provides end-to-end scheduling; routing, optimization &amp; electronic dispatch across multiple platforms including in-vehicle devices as well as Android based smart phones and tablets. Its solutions support complex business logic and operational rules and has served several million GPS, Trips/Orders and other data through its system.</p>\r\n<div>We work with a number of leading telecom operators such as Romtelecom, Deutsche Telekom, Cell One, and several carriers in North America. Our taxi solution is also available via the Deutsche Telekom eCommerce marketplace.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We recently launched an Android smart phone based fleet tracking solution that obviates the need for a modem (http://www.pr.com/press-release/471409). &nbsp;Our On Call solution is a cost effective way for businesses to manage service delivery on the go and can be used among others by provider networks serving insurance sector and targets both emergency and non-emergency service requests. The Distribute solution is being tested with soft drink bottlers in multiple markets. Several sales initiatives are underway with all our products.</div>\r\n<div>OUR VISION</div>\r\n<div>The Company aims to be a leading player in the Machine to Machine (M2M) or &ldquo;Internet of Things&rdquo; space &amp; providing client&rsquo;s real-time access to information that helps drive decision making, revenues, cost savings and profitability. The primary focus is on transportation vertical but it has touch points that cover manufacturing, retail &amp; distribution, health care, services, etc.</div>', ''),
(1671, 1, 'www.SellYourEvents.com', 'questions@sellyourevents.com', '815-325 Bay St, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.sellyourevents.com ', '(416) 628-8053', '', '', '<p>Event planning and membership registration system helps event organizers to quickly build customized homepages that introduce and promote events, secure payments online and issue E-ticket confirmations.</p>\r\n<p>SellYourEvents online registration, management and event finances software integrates data with guest communications.</p>', ''),
(1672, 1, 'Wyatt Health Management', 'info@wyatthealth.com', '204-2904 South Sheridan Way, OAKVILLE,, Ontario, Canada', 'www.wyatthealth.com ', '(905) 257-5670', '(866) 252-4880', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are a Canadian full service market access consulting firm for the pharmaceutical and biotech industries.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our mission is to be the most respected pharmaceutical reimbursement consulting firm in Canada, going beyond commercial success, so patients are not left behind. Our goal is to showcase how your product adds real value for patients and payers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our job is to make it really easy for payers to say &ldquo;yes&rdquo; to your product.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>When you work with Wyatt Health Management, you will learn how to anticipate payers&rsquo; responses to new products. You will uncover innovative ways to negotiate with payers that don&rsquo;t include lowering your price. You and your team will begin to think more strategically. Business and market access teams will be more aligned, resulting in better commercial performance and therapy for eligible patients.</div>', ''),
(1673, 1, 'Wyckomar Inc.', 'sales@wyckomaruv.com', '111 Malcolm Rd., GUELPH, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.wyckomaruv.com ', '(519) 822-1886', '(519) 763-6580', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Wyckomar is your first choice for chemical-free UV water disinfection&nbsp; equipment and complete water systems integration. We have been manufacturing and selling worldwide since 1978<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The story of how ultraviolet (UV) light can guarantee safe drinking water is interesting. Many years ago scientists discovered that a special wavelength of UV light can kill disease-causing pathogens in our drinking water by attacking the cell DNA.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">It was discovered that UV light can effectively destroy all common bacteria, viruses and spores which are regularly found in drinking water including E. coli, Coliform, Hepatitis, Influenza, V. cholera, M. tuberculosis, Legionella, Salmonella, B. anthracis, Cryptosporidium, Giardia and many more. And UV light does all this without damaging our environment, and without any risk of overdose whatsoever.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The most common question we get is how to properly size a UV system for the intended use.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Whatever your system requirements, we can provide it and size it properly. From residential and commercial purification systems to large-volume UV\'s, extreme environment and military grade water systems, we\'ve done it for others and we can do it for you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Complete water treatment systems to kill e coli and other water-borne pathogens are available for your home, your business, your commercial facility, the cottage, the condo, and just about any other application you can think of. Visit our products page for more information.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1674, 1, 'WYK web Solutions', 'office@wykweb.com', '100 - 222 &#150; 58 Ave SW, CALGARY, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.wykweb.com', '(587) 333-4932', '', '', '<p>Affordable SEO (Search Engine Optimization) Monitoring and Social Media Monitoring.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We provide affordable SEO Monitoring &amp; Reports weekly &amp; monthly to be sure that your business is on the right track online. Also we do weekly and monthly reports and audits on Social Media to be sure that your online social presence also stays on the right track.</div>', ''),
(1675, 1, 'WZMH Architects', 'wzmhtor@wzmh.com', '1500-95 St Clair Ave W, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.wzmh.com ', '(416) 961-4111', '(416) 961-3176', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">WZMH Architects is an award-winning international architectural partnership. WZMH believes in a collaborative approach to all assignments, with all project participants working closely together in order to achieve a common goal: the delivery of the project to meet or exceed the expectations of the client.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The firm&rsquo;s expertise encompasses all aspects of the architectural process, from master planning, site evaluation and feasibility studies, through the design and construction documentation phases, to the final selection of finishes and fittings for building interiors.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The firm&rsquo;s experience includes significant institutional and corporate projects, courthouse design, hotel and conference facilities, data centres, retail and office developments, resort and entertainment complexes, educational and residential buildings, as well as a number of major master plan studies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In recent years, the firm has successfully incorporated sustainable principles into the majority of its projects, is currently involved in the LEED certification of over five million square feet of built space and has received numerous domestic and international LEED awards.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">At WZMH, we recognize that the final built form must achieve a balance between the practical and the aesthetic: that good design goes beyond superficial appearance and informs all aspects of achieving a built solution that is tailored to the intended use.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1676, 1, 'X-CD Technologies Inc.', 'sales@x-cd.com', '15 Coldwater Rd, NORTH YORK, Ontario , Canada', 'www.x-cd.com ', '(416) 410-2376', '(416) 444-5721', '', '<p>&nbsp;Conference and event technology and services including systems for online abstract collection, paper collection, peer reivew, attendee &amp; exhibitor registration systems, online hotel registration. Also conference proceedings and conference programs in hard copy, CD-Rom, DVD and flash drive. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1677, 1, 'Xact Solutions Group, Inc.', 'jvegh@sympatico.ca', '435 Heddle Cres., NEWMARKET, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xactsolutions.ca ', '(905) 954-0054', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Xact Solutions Group is able to offer you value that goes far beyond your technology needs. Xact Solutions Group has always emphasized a strong relationship with both the customer and the software vendor. One of our core philosophies is to partner with our customers in order to study and better understand their needs, and document the way they store, manage and use their vital business information.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Today, as a direct result of the numerous engagements we have had with some of the country`s leading commercial and public sector organizations, Xact Solutions Group is in a unique position to deliver the industry`s most comprehensive domain expertise, subject matter expertise, services and best practices for enterprise content management. Our expertise in document management solutions and our understanding of our customers`challenges and our software partner`s capabilities is unparalleled.</div>', ''),
(1678, 1, 'Xanatos Marine', 'sales@xanatosmarine.com', '370-18 Gostick Place, NORTH VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Canada', 'www.xanatosmarine.com ', '(604) 904-2200', '(604) 904-2210', '', '<p>&nbsp;Xanatos Holdings Ltd. founded in 1984, is the parent company of two subsidiaries, Xanatos Marine and Xanatos Consulting. In 1996 Xanatos added the consulting division to the company. Recognizing that different customers have different needs, Xanatos Consulting provides a personal and comprehensive approach to assisting you to meet your technological requirements in the marine industry. Added in 1999, Xanatos Marine strives to continually deliver state-of-the-art products and services to aid in the safety of mariners, their vessels and the waterways around the world. In addition to the world-class products that Xanatos Marine already offers, the research for new technology is consistently ongoing.</p>', ''),
(1679, 1, 'Xbase Tecnologies Corporation', 'info@xbase.com', '903-2225 Sheppard Ave, NORTH YORK, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.xbase.com ', '(416) 340-102', '(416) 340-1054', '', '<p>&nbsp;XBASE Technologies prides itself on offering cutting edge technology, hassle-free hosted solutions and industry acclaimed IT services. Whether you want disaster recovery or you&rsquo;d like a complete hosted solution on our infrastructure, XBASE is the company you can trust for all your managed service needs.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>It&rsquo;s Time to Get your Head in the Clouds</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Well, just the one cloud actually. All over the globe companies just like yours are turning to cloud based technology to host their IT. The advantages are plain to see:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Scalability: as your business grows, so too does your technology</div>\r\n<div>Customization: we build your cloud around your unique needs</div>\r\n<div>Mobility: access on the run from your mobile device</div>\r\n<div>Affordability: a pay-as-you-go structure allows you to maintain control</div>\r\n<div>Cut costs: stop blowing your budget on servers, hardware and software</div>\r\n<div>If you want to make the jump into the Cloud, contact one of our knowledgeable sales staff by phone at 416-340-1020 or by email at sales@xbase.com</div>', ''),
(1680, 1, 'XBI Software', 'info@xbisoftware.com', '5764 Wolseley Ave, CÔTE SAINT-LUC, Quebec, Canada ', 'www.xbisoftware.com ', '(514) 906-7886', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;XBI Software Inc uses XBRL, the standard for business reporting, to create applications for managing business information</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>for banks and financial institutions</div>\r\n<div>for the financial services industry</div>\r\n<div>for government agencies and departments</div>\r\n<div>for business</div>\r\n<div>XBI Software Inc, a member in good standing of XBRL Canada, the Canadian jurisdiction of XBRL International, also consults to help organisations understand and implement SBR (standard business reporting) and XBRL solutions.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>XBI Software Inc. is working on a pipeline of innovative products for the financial community based on the XBRL standard. XBI\'s lead product, CovenantWise, under development, helps banks alleviate one of their key problems, credit risk management for their borrowing customers.</div>', ''),
(1681, 1, 'Xceed Software Inc.', 'info@xceed.com', '200-10 De Mortagne Blvd, BOUCHERVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xceed.com ', '(450) 442-2626', '(450) 906-1385', '', '<p>&nbsp;Xceed has been creating top-of-the-line software components for nearly 20 years. Our current product line boasts over 135 professional components, which are used by more than 100,000 professional developers worldwide, including Microsoft in applications such as Visual Studio 2010 and 2012 and Microsoft Office. Our focus is on creating and marketing UI controls that help developers and designers create a compelling user experience (UX) with the Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF), the backbone of LOB solutions. Xceed DataGrid for WPF is our flagship product. Our extensive offering also includes some of the most popular UI controls and data manipulation libraries for .NET (such as Zip and FTP), as well as controls and libraries for Silverlight, Windows Phone, and ActiveX/COM.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Xceed is just a phone call away. Our development team doesn\'t only focus on creating expertly designed, extensible components. They also help our team of dedicated technical support staff provide the highest levels of support and customer service.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Contact us without hesitation from 9:00 AM to 4:30 PM EST. We\'ll be happy to answer questions and provide help!</div>', ''),
(1682, 1, 'Xcel Source Corp.', 'sales@xcel.on.ca', '7-2800 Argentia Rd, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xcelsource.com ', '(905) 564-9235', '(905) 564-3066', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Based in Mississauga, Ontario, Xcel Source is a privately held Canadian distributor specializing in digital lifestyle accessories for cellular devices, tablets, PC&rsquo;s and Macs.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our product categories include both fashion-forward and protective cases and sleeves, laptop bags and backpacks, power chargers and cables, mounting devices, and even audio headphones, earbuds and speakers. We offer over 2,000 branded products to our growing list of satisfied customers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In 1995 Xcel Source was founded based on the principle that we will go the extra mile to deliver what we promise.&nbsp; That tradition of trust between Xcel Source and our customers continues to this day, reflected in our dedication to provide a great selection of products , coupled with an unparalleled dedication to service.&nbsp; Our team specializes in and understands the needs of the independent channel. With an active customer base of over 1200 consumer electronics dealers, cellular dealers, computers stores, educational resellers and online e-tailers our primary focus is and has always been helping independent retailers across Canada.&nbsp; We are here to service you in both English and French as well as offering shipping Canada-wide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our dedicated account reps look forward to bringing you our unique product selection and &quot;boutique&quot; service to help you grow your business.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We invite you to discover the Xcel difference.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1683, 1, 'XE.com Inc', 'info@xe.com', '200-1145 Nicholson Rd., NEWMARKET, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xe.com', '(416) 214-5606', '(416) 214-5607', '', '<p>&nbsp;Founded in 1993, XE.com is the world\'s favorite currency site, providing Internet-based foreign exchange tools and services to individuals and corporations around the globe. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1684, 1, 'Xenon Pharmaceuticals Inc', 'info@xenon-pharma.com', '200-3650 Gilmore Way, BURNABY, British Columbia, ', 'www.xenon-pharma.com ', '(604) 484-3300', '(604) 484-3450', '', '<p>&nbsp;We are a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company discovering and developing a pipeline of differentiated therapeutics for orphan indications that we intend to commercialize on our own, and for larger market indications that we intend to partner with global pharmaceutical industry leaders. We have built a core platform, which we call Extreme Genetics&reg;, enabling the discovery of validated drug targets by studying rare human diseases with extreme traits, including diseases caused by mutations in ion channels, known as channelopathies. Our integrated platform has a full complement of in-house capabilities for human genetics and small molecule drug discovery, and for pre-clinical and clinical development.</p>', ''),
(1685, 1, 'XFI Logistics, Inc.', 'sales@xficanada.com', '205-810 Quayside Dr., NEW WESTMINSTER, British Columbia, Canada ', 'www.xficanada.com ', '(888) 256-7586', '', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">XFI Logistics, Inc. is a provider of freight and transportation logistics, global product sourcing and complete supply chain management worldwide.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Shippers, importers and exporters require skilled and experienced teams to keep their business moving across town, borders and overseas.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our focused industry approach combined with our passion for transportation and supply chain management provides our clients with world class service and excellence.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1686, 1, 'Xgestion Inc.', 'contact@xgestion.com', 'C.P. 474 , PLESSISVILLE, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xgestion.com ', '(888) 586-3950', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;X Management is a simple online website creation software to use, ideal for beginners. It will allow you to manage and make a website . X Management is a website Content Management System , CMS. To take full advantage of this tool, a basic knowledge of Microsoft Word is desirable. You must also be able to resize digital photos. A high speed internet connection is recommended. All websites created with the tool &nbsp;X Management are unique creations, see examples . If you have basic knowledge of computer graphics you\'ll be able to easily create visual design your website. If Photoshop is a mystery to you, you can use our graphics department . The realization of a custom template (&quot;template&quot;) takes on average 5 to 10 hours. Click here to learn more . To learn how to make a website without any programming and web pages, use the software cms Xgestion . &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1687, 1, 'Xibita', 'displays@theportables.com', '9-190 Colonnade Rd S, NEPEAN, Ontario, Canada', 'www.theportables.com ', '(613) 723-1849', '(613) 723-5489', '', '<p>&nbsp;Since 1979, The Portables has been helping our clients make their exhibiting challenges a bit easier. We start by manufacturing display products that won\'t let you down when you need them most. We added an easy purchasing process, access to a wealth of in-house expertise and great online resources. Finally we finish up with outstanding value. Let us show you why over 10,000 clients love to work with The Portables year after year!</p>', ''),
(1688, 1, 'Xilix Consulting Inc.', 'ccoleman@istar.ca', '3719 Sixth St, GLOUCESTER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xilixconsulting.com ', '(613) 521-5775', '(613) 521-9797', '', '<p>&nbsp;Founded in 1998, Xilix Consulting Inc. is a locally-owned and operated staffing organization and offers an in-depth knowledge of the unique characteristics of the National Capital Region\'s labour market. After a thorough analysis of your requirements, we provide you with a total solution approach to your staffing needs. Through our sister company, EYEDU Solutions Inc., we are able to supply full hardware, software and professional services solutions. &nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1689, 1, 'XL TOOL INC.', 'sales@xltool.com', '19 Crestview Place, KITCHENER, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xltool.com ', '(519) 578-6951', '(519) 578-5357', '', '<p>&nbsp;Today the Metal Stamping / Tool and Die Industry is facing global challenges that absolutely require innovative solutions to maintain competitive position and profitability. For more than 16 years, we at XL Tool have helped our customers by producing quality tooling in shorter lead times than our competitors. With Our new 22,000 sq. ft. state of the art facility, our dedicated team is well poised to fulfill your tooling needs. To maintain our high quality standards we have attained our ISO9001: 2000 designation. Let us have the opportunity to show you our advantages. Our job is to help you find a better way.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>In sixteen short years we have grown our team to more than forty &nbsp;experienced and competent die makers, machinists and design professionals. We regularly enhance our technology with the most up-to-date design software and CNC equipment. We are also very fortunate to have a tremendous depth of experience amongst our staff. XL Tool is in position to assist you with your most complex or basic tooling needs.</div>', ''),
(1690, 1, 'XLTEK', 'oakville_customer_service@natus.com', '2568 Bristol Circle, OAKVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.natus.com ', '(905) 829-5300', '(905) 829-5304', '', '<p>&nbsp;XLTEK is a manufacturer of high end, technologically advanced&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>neuromuscular and neurophysiological instruments for the&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>complete spectrum of diagnostics through monitoring and&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>therapeutic applications. Through 15 years of advancements in&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>multiple areas of Research and Development, such as electronic&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>layout and design, fully robotic surface mount technology&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>assembly, 3D mechanical design, fully robotic mechanical&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>manufacturing, and advanced process control, XLTEK has earned&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>the expertise to provide the most reliable, technologically&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>advanced, high performance systems available today.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>XLTEK is now an ISO-9001 registered company and is among&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Canada\'s 50 Best Managed Private Companies.&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1691, 1, 'XO Coffee Importers, Inc.', 'konstantinos@xocoffee.ca', '136 Balsamwood Rd, THORNHILL, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xocoffee.ca ', '(416) 301-3676', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;XO Coffee supplies premium coffee products and equipment to consumers, cafes, retailers, businesses, offices, restaurants, and hotels.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We make superior-tasting coffee experiences accessible through our online coffee store.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With distribution centers in Canada and the United States along with delivery services provided by Canada Post and United States Postal Service our coffee products are delivered fast and fresh right to your door.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our Mission:&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We want to be our customers first choice for coffee, delivering coffee products of outstanding quality and great service at a competitive cost. &nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1692, 1, 'Xogen Technologies Inc', 'info@xogen.ca', '40 Centennial Rd, ORANGEVILLE, Ontario, Canada', 'www.xogen.ca ', '(519) 941-9500', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;Xogen is in a research collaboration with Drs. Dorin Bejan and Nigel Bunce of the Electrochemical Technology Centre, University of Guelph, whose research program involves electrolytic methods for the remediation of wastes that are resistant to treatment by conventional technologies. This collaboration focuses on the assessment of electrochemical approaches to the destruction of Chemical Oxygen Demand (COD) in industrial wastewaters. The collaboration has been jointly funded by Xogen and the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC).</p>\r\n<p>Xogen has been involved in a research collaboration with the University of Toronto since 2007. This research has focused on the development of Advanced Electrode Materials with Dr. Harry Ruda, Professor and Stan Meek Chair in Advanced Nano-Technology, Department of Materials Science Engineering and Advanced Power Electronics development with Dr. Francis Dawson, Professor, Energy Systems Group in the Edward S. Rogers Sr. Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering. This collaboration has been jointly funded by Xogen, National Science and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC), Ontario Centres of Excellence (OCE) and Sustainable Development Technology Canada (SDTC).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1693, 1, 'Xpan Interactive Ltd', 'info@xpan.ca', '475-3553 31 St NW, Calgary, Alberta, Canada', 'www.xpan.ca ', '(403) 208-3848', '(403) 208-3858', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xpan is a tight-knit team of passionate eLearning experts devoted to helping you make sense of your training and professional development requirements.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We specialize in dynamic and engaging eLearning solutions, and pride ourselves on meeting and exceeding all of your learning objectives.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our specific focus is industrial training, courseware development and systems implementation in the Transportation, Oil &amp; Gas and Health industries, however, our experience and diverse skill set gives us the confidence to succeed in any industry or sector.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We create a dynamic partnership with you to help solve a specific need for eLearning within your organization. We become immersed in your subject matter, and create a learning environment where your trainees become properly qualified and obtain the credentials to perform tasks safely, productively, and exceed organizational standards.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:\r\nminor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:EN-CA;mso-fareast-language:\r\nEN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\">Through powerful collaborative relationships, a passion for lifelong learning and a streamlined workflow, we\'re committed to see you succeed. We exist to create stories and expand minds. Explore our diverse services and learn more about our process.</span></p>', ''),
(1694, 1, 'Xpress Automotive Supplies Limited', 'sales@xpressautomotive.com', '390 Deerhurst Dr., BRAMPTON, Ontario, Canada ', 'www.xpressautomotive.com ', '(905) 709-8100', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;SUPPLIER AND EXPORTER OF CHASSIS AND FRONT END SUSPENSION PARTS FOR JAPANESE, KOREAN AND NORTH AMERICAN VEHICLES.&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1695, 1, 'XTECH Explosive Decontamination Inc.', 'mail@xtech-uxo.com', '14-900 Village Lane Suite 412, OKOTOKS, Alberta, Canada ', 'www.xtech-uxo.com ', '(403) 938-3856', '(403) 938-6408', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">XTECH Explosive Decontamination Incorporated and sister company, XTECH Environmental Solutions Incorporated, provide total solutions for the management of explosives and explosive waste.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">XTECH Explosive Decontamination offers a focus on military munitions and unexploded ordnance. Site assessment, risk analysis, detection, excavation and disposal provide cradle to cradle solutions for the re-use of land affected by military use.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">XTECH Environmental Solutions ensures surplus and obsolete explosive disposal is provided at a licenced facility. The certification process for each item secures the guarantee of chain of custody and confirmation of destruction. Customized services provide a wide-range of options to meet both industry-specific and regulatory requirements.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">XTECH is an established leader in providing turn-key solutions to hazardous materials issues. Proactive problem solving provides the highest guarantee of success for each project; our solid core of expertise garnered from 20 years of industry-specific initiatives. We are confident that our team of experts are capable of fulfilling your requirements with customized solutions.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1696, 1, 'Xterra Wireless Inc.', 'sales@xterrawireless.com', '125 Cliffwood Dr., WINNIPEG, Manitoba, Canada', 'www.xterrawireless.com ', '(204) 480-0982', '(701) 347-8728', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xterra Wireless is your one-stop source for cost-effective, high quality, cellular wireless equipment and in-building coverage solutions. We specialize in supplying in-building coverage system components, such as repeaters (or bi-directional amplifiers), as well as complete coverage systems to meet your specific requirements.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Changing building requirements, and new energy-efficient materials and practices will often affect the ability of cellular signals to penetrate building exteriors and restrict propagation within the interior. Improving your in-building cell phone coverage will help increase security and emergency response within your property, improve mobile communications for employees and customers, as well as improve the over-all value of leased facilities.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xterra Wireless can also help with site planning and system configuration to help optimize your system\'s performance.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xterra Wireless can provide engineering services including link budget calculations, system wiring diagrams and equipment placement diagrams for in-building coverage applications.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our goal is to help system integrators and end users be successful with their wireless coverage projects.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1697, 1, 'XTR', 'dcarter@xtrenergy.ca', '2-5100 South Service Rd, BURLINGTON, Ontario , Canada ', 'www.xtrenergy.ca ', '(905) 335-9533', '(905) 319-7692', '', '<p>&nbsp;Established in 1999, XTR is Canada\'s only coast to coast independent retail petroleum supplier. From Cape Breton, Nova Scotia to Abbottsford, British Columbia, XTR has a track record of being a preferred supplier of gas for independent gas station owners. With over 150 stations and more signing up every month XTR has proven performance and a competitive brand solution.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>With both Canadian and international suppliers and access to most terminals across Canada, XTR can effectively supply and deliver all petroleum products at a cost effective price to both retail and wholesale customers.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>XTR strives to be the largest independent privately owned retail fuel marketer in Canada, by providing our fuel customers well priced produc</div>\r\n<div>ts, timely deliveries and innovative brand programs for independent gas stations.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To provide independent service station owners with a cutting edge fuel supply program designed to maximize site profitability and increase customer retention.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our personalized customer service and support team is the best in the industry at hassle-free communication. We are focused on helping our dealers succeed. Each dealer is provided with a dedicated representative who gains a thorough understanding of their business.</div>', ''),
(1698, 1, 'Xybion', 'info@Xybion.com', '530-400 Jean-Lesage Blvd, QUEBEC, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xybion.com ', '(418) 525-0606', '(418) 525-0909', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xybion Corporation is a global technology solutions provider that delivers interconnected solutions for companies operating in heavily regulated industries.&nbsp; Xybion today is the result of a successful execution of a strategic vision of creating a global solutions company with specialized software and services through strategic acquisitions and organic growth.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Started with the acquisition of Xybion Corporation in 2008 by The Banerjee Group controlled by Dr. Pradip K. Banerjee.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">For over 30 years, large pharmaceutical companies and CROs&nbsp; have been using Xybion&rsquo;s Pristima system for managing their preclinical R&amp;D and drug safety testing for FDA submissions.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">2009: Xybion acquired Amadeus International in Quebec City, Canada a 14 year old company with a state of the art software suite on quality, compliance, risk and governance processes for regulated industries.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">2010:&nbsp; Xybion acquired two companies from GE Healthcare, Stelex and Vital-Path, which offered validation services, implementation services for Enterprise Asset Management software like IBM Maximo, and provided a range of Enterprise Content migration and federation solutions capable of connecting disparate content platforms like Documentum, OpenText, FileNet,&nbsp; and SharePoint. This also resulted in strong business partnerships for Xybion with industry leaders IBM, EMC and OpenText.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">2011:Xybion India Ltd, a wholly Xybion owned Indian Corporation based in Chennai, was opened to make Xybion a truly global software and IT services company.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Xybion today is an enterprise system, consulting and services company offering interconnected and interdependent Enterprise Process Management software and implementation services for regulated industries with current customers in thirteen countries including USA, Canada, UK, Germany, France, Italy, Belgium. Finland, Switzerland, China, South Korea and Singapore.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1699, 1, 'Xytera Electronics', 'info@xytera.com', '16 Daudet St, CANDIAC, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xytera.com ', '4504445441', '(450) 444-2798', '', '<p>&nbsp;Xytera Electronics is a highly reputable broad line global component distributor specializing in highly allocated and obsolete products from integrated circuits to computer products. With a combined knowledge base of over 45 years of experience in electronics distribution (franchised &amp; non-franchised) and inventory management solutions, Xytera provides unmatched quality products and services to our customer base of OEMs, CEMs, brokers and distributors. Xytera currently manages inventory solutions for a wide range of clients from Fortune 500 companies to smaller manufacturers and distributors worldwide.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>One of Xytera\'s driving principles is to act as a trusted and reliable electronic distributor, world renowned for its customer service. Here at Xytera we understand the challenges buyers face when dealing with factory shortages to excess inventory. We have the necessary tools to develop customized solutions to fit your needs. We are considered one of the top Electronics Risk Management companies in the world.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', ''),
(1700, 1, 'XYZ Cultural Technology Inc', 'info@xyz-tc.com', '642, rue de Courcelle, 4e etage Local PH5, MONTREAL, Quebec, Canada', 'www.xyz-tc.com ', '(514) 340-7717', '(514) 658-1254', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Notre mission est de contribuer &agrave; la diffusion de la culture et des id&eacute;es. Pour ce faire, nous aidons les cr&eacute;ateurs de projets audiovisuels &agrave; outrepasser leurs propres limites en prenant la responsabilit&eacute; des aspects technique et logistique des exp&eacute;riences qu&rsquo;ils d&eacute;sirent cr&eacute;er.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nous concevons des solutions audiovisuelles et sc&eacute;nographiques qui r&eacute;pondent aux besoins des promoteurs, quels qu&rsquo;ils soient. Nos champs d&rsquo;expertise sont les suivants :<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Expositions, parcours interpr&eacute;tatifs et mus&eacute;es<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Salles de spectacles et th&eacute;&acirc;tres<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Environnements immersifs<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Installations audiovisuelles diverses (salle de conf&eacute;rence, ar&eacute;na, kiosque, signalisation, &eacute;clairage architectural, etc.)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nous cumulons plusieurs sp&eacute;cialit&eacute;s au sein d&rsquo;une m&ecirc;me &eacute;quipe, ce qui rend notre intervention efficace puisque nous pilotons l&rsquo;ensemble du dossier. Nous recherchons constamment de nouvelles technologies qui offrent un rapport qualit&eacute;/prix exceptionnel.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Le d&eacute;veloppement durable nous tient &agrave; c&oelig;ur. Nos concepteurs recherchent constamment des solutions &eacute;co-responsable afin de minimiser l&rsquo;empreinte environnementale de nos installations.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Nous offrons un service exceptionnel &agrave; tous nos clients, et ce, partout sur la plan&egrave;te. Nous avons &agrave; notre actif plusieurs projets dans diff&eacute;rents pays, dont le Canada, les &Eacute;tats-Unis, le Mexique, La Chine, Le Japon, Le Portugal, La R&eacute;publique Dominicaine, Cuba, la Colombie, Les &Eacute;mirats Arabes Unis, l&rsquo;Arabie Saoudite, l&rsquo;Espagne, l\'Italie.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1701, 1, 'Yachtsmiths International Inc', 'info@yachtsmiths.com', '2 Maitland St, DARTMOUTH, Nova Scotia, Canada', 'www.yachtsmiths.com ', '(902) 463-0741', '(902) 463-3664', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Yachtsmiths PEI Inc (formerly Yachtsmiths International)<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Experts in high quality steel, aluminum and FRP yacht construction, YachtSmiths PEI is building a reputation as impeccable as the quality yachts we build.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Our yachts can be found all over North America to Europe and beyond.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are meticulous designers and highly skilled craftsman, utilizing the latest technology to build custom yachts that are the stuff of our clients&rsquo; dreams. But we are equally pleased to work with the designer of your choice to ensure your yacht is everything you imagined. And with full launching and hauling capabilities, we are perfectly suited to undertake general and custom engineering repairs. We approach each contract with the same uncompromising care and dedication.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Present construction schedule consists of a 44&rsquo; aluminum schooner, a 65&rsquo; aluminum power yacht, 43&rsquo; steel trawler yacht and a Cabot 36&rsquo; Pilot House model blue water sailor. We would be proud to talk to you about how we can add your next yacht to this list, and to add you to our list of satisfied clients.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
