(1759, 1, 'Yolles', 'contact.us@halcrowyolles.com', 'Terminal Building 550-207 Queen Quay W, TORONTO, Ontario, Canada', 'www.ch2mhill.com ', '(416) 363-8123', '(416) 363-0341', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">As a global leader in consulting, design, design-build, operations, and program management, CH2M HILL has the human and technical resources, the international footprint, and the depth of know-how and experience to help clients achieve success in any corner of the world.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CH2M HILL has 26,000 employees on six continents working on some of the most complex and exciting projects on the planet. From our Colorado headquarters to the many large cities and small towns around the world where our employees live and work, we are committed to the vision and core values of our founders to build a better world and make a difference in the lives of others.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We partner with clients in energy, water, environment and infrastructure to design integrated solutions that deliver lasting value.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">From major sewerage programs in London and Abu Dhabi to super cleanrooms in China, from nuclear cleanup in Scotland to major highways and airports in the United States, CH2M HILL\'s project experience is as diverse as the world itself. Our talented staff works hard to provide clean drinking water, efficient transportation, lean production facilities, environmental remediation and safe energy, offering communities sustainable economic and social benefits. Our technical expertise is both broad and deep, servicing large and small clients across all sectors and leveraging our global reach and local presence.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CH2M HILL is the only engineer-procure-construct company that offers this wide spectrum of expertise, knowledge, and services across varied industries and government agencies. This scope and scale sets the firm apart in its capability to partner with clients and achieve strategic and operational goals.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The enterprise, dating back to 1946, is built on honesty, ethics, and morals; a global presence of 26,000 employees in regional offices worldwide; and financial stability. Whatever your current or future needs, CH2M HILL\'s full-service, worldwide resources are available to support you on your next critical project.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(1760, 1, 'York Hydraulics Ltd.', 'yorkhydraulics@rogers.com', '3-8481 Keele St, CONCORD, Ontario, Canada', 'www.yorkhydraulics.ca ', '(905) 738-1750', '(905) 738-9828', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>York Hydraulics was founded in 1981, primarily as a Fluid Power Distributor, specializing in the supply of air and hydraulic cylinders for the industrial markets across Canada. Our strong sense of customer service, dedication to offer only quality products and our ability to provide cooperative solutions at a reasonable price has resulted in continued growth and wide acceptance in the marketplace.</div>\r\n<div>Today our product line has expanded to cover most components of the fluid power industry including, pumps, valves, filters, motors, hose, and fittings, power units, gauges, pneumatic FRL\'s, air pumps, air tools and electronic position controls.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Our customer base comprises all types of industry, including steel and paper mills, plastic injection and blow moulders, shipbuilding, auto plants, material handling and robotics. Our ability to design and provide specialty cylinder products as well as the standard products we represent, make York Hydraulics a primary contact for your cylinder and fluid power requirements.</div>', ''),
