(77, 1, 'Fordia (Groupe Fordia Ltee)', 'marketing@fordia.com', '2745, Rue De Miniac,, St. Laurent â€“ Qc,, , ', 'www.fordia.com', '+1 (514) 336-9211', '+1 (514) 745-4125', '', '<p>Fordia has one clear focus &ndash; to provide the best diamond-drilling tools and equipment for the world&rsquo;s leading mineral drilling exploration companies. That is our mission. How we live it is our strength. We provide exceptional service, demonstrated daily by our worldwide representatives. Our distribution network ensures Fordia products can be delivered globally, right on schedule. We are committed to quality, innovation and technology. And we pride ourselves in being a team that is appreciated &ndash; internally by our colleagues and externally by our customers. Our mission is based on our core values &ndash; those guiding principles that characterize how we think and act. Communication. Recognition. Precision. Expansion. Financial Performance. This is what characterizes who we are and who we aim to be. They are the reasons that our customers stay with Fordia.</p>', ''),
(78, 1, 'Therapure Biopharma Inc.  ', 'info@therapurebio.com', '2585 Meadowpine Blvd., Mississauga, ON, , ', 'www.therapurebio.com', '+1 (905) 286-6200', '+1 (905) 286-6300', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Therapure Biopharma Inc. is a Canadian biopharmaceutical company committed to the development, manufacture, purification, and packaging of high-quality biological therapeutics. We provide our clients and partners with customized solutions for the development and manufacture of complex biological products, leveraging our flexible, modern cGMP manufacturing facility, our extensive quality systems and the dedication of our highly experienced staff. Our scientific, manufacturing, and downstream purification expertise, along with our intimate understanding of advanced biology, complex proteins, and regulatory processes allow us to develop effective and innovative solutions to advance our client&rsquo;s products from the lab to the market.</p>', ''),
(79, 1, 'Nicholson Manufacturing Ltd.', 'fengcy@nmbc.com', 'P.O. Box 2128, 9896 GALARAN ROAD, SIDNEY, British Columbia, , ', 'www.debarking.com', '+1-250-656-3131', '+1-250-656-3111', '', '<p>The Nicholson Forest Products Equipment Group is one of several Nicholson Industries groups that are involved with advancing technology in important basic industries around the world. The company was started in 1948 by T.W. &lsquo;Bill&quot; Nicholson and has been a leader of industrial innovation and development since that time.  The Forest Products Equipment Group provides advanced technology and machinery for the critical log processing phases that must occur before lumber, paper, composite boards and other wood based products can be made. The group has manufacturing plants in the United States and Canada. Our sales, service and parts units support every region that has a substantial Forest Products Industry. We design and manufacture high quality machinery that is reliable and productive for decades.  People depend on our equipment for their company&rsquo;s success and we take that responsibility very seriously.</p>', ''),
(80, 1, 'WCC Refurb Limited ', 'admin@winliegroup.com', 'P.O. Box 9015, Stn \"A\", HALIFAX, Nova Scotia, , ', 'www.winliegroup.com', '+1 (902) 454-9318 ', '+1 (902) 454-9310', '', '<p>The Winlie Group is 100% Canadian owned and operated company providing services tothe offshore oil and gas industry, and international intermodal shipping lines.Today we are one of the leading designers and fabricators of offshore containers in North America. With a team of specialized engineers, certified welders and fabricators, and a management team with more than 25 years of experience in the industry we offer a complete in-house service to meet the needs of the many diversified fields in the oil and gas industry. In addition to being an ISO 9001:2000 registered company, we hold the only North American Manufacturers Survey Agreement (MSA) with Det Norske Veritas (DNV). Working closely with these certifying authorities ensures that all equipment we manufacture will meet and exceed the standards required on offshore projects worldwide. While our core strength is the manufacture of DNV CN 2.7-1/EN12079 offshore cargo handling equipment.</p>', ''),
(81, 1, 'Moore and Franklin Engineering ', 'info@mfe.ca', '40 Airview Rd., ETOBICOKE, Ontario, , ', 'www.mfe.ca', '+1 (416) 742-7647', '+1 (416) 946-1486', '', '<p>Moore and Franklin is a division of Moore Telephone Corporation,  which was incorporated in Ontario primarily for R and D purposes.  Derek W. Moore, P.Eng was a consulting engineerwith patents in  communications and power systems. Howard Franklin, P.Eng, who  joined the company after the retirement of Ken Gentry also has  several patents and is a recognised expert in data management.  The company was established in 1974 and now owns a new 8000  square foot plant well equipped as described in the technology  profile. In the mid-1980\'s, in association with Moog Music in  Buffalo, we developed one of the first featurephones, the  \'Operator\'. Prior to this we had developed new concepts in  diagnostic and autocorrection devices for data processing loops,  airflow measurement and control systems, using a form of balanced  transistor anemometer; voting systems for councils and  conventions; peak-seeking diathermy equipment for use with low  dose chemotherapy.</p>', ''),
(82, 1, 'Yes Biotech Laboratories Ltd.', 'info@yesbiotech.co', '23-2355 Derry Rd. E., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, , ', 'www.yesbiotech.com', '+1 (905) 677-9221', '+1 (905) 677-0023', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Anogen - trade name of Yes Biotech Laboratories Ltd., a Canadian biopharmaceutical company located in Ontario, Canada. We have been producing antibody products for research, diagnostic and therapeutic applications for more than twenty-five years. Our broad technology platform enables us to design and develop a variety of products including monoclonal and polyclonal antibodies, immunoassay kits, matched antibody pairs, immunoglobulin, bioactive peptides, recombinant proteins and humanized monoclonal antibodies with high producers. We distribute our products world widely. Our name is a recognized quality supplier to many large antibody syndicates and suppliers.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">We are committed to developing and commercializing antibody-related therapeutics and diagnostics to combat various diseases including inflammatory and autoimmune disorders, cardiovascular diseases and cancer. Anogen\'s major project is advancing a New Bio-Defense Strategy to prevent &quot;Cytokine Storm&quot; using their anti-cytokine antibodies.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">To ensure that our customers are provided with the highest level of quality products and services, we have registered under the international organization for standards. We are certified ISO 13485 Medical Devices under the general practice of the ISO 9001 Quality System.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(83, 1, 'Control Skateboards Inc.', 'info@controlsk8.com ', '857, rue Alphonse-Desrochers, Centre industriel, SAINT-NICOLAS, Quebec, , ', 'www.controlmfg.com', '+1 (418) 836-9090 ', '+1 (418) 836-1423 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Skateboards at the best possible price. Early 1996 while skateboarding was becoming the next big thing, Carl and members of his family moved the shop into an industrial space big enough to hold the manufacturing and his new 5-0 skatepark located on the southside of Quebec. One year later Control Skateboards MFG supersizes the shop to 7000 square feet. In 2001, Carl decides to concentrate on manufacturing skateboards and closes the skatepark to use the extra space to his advantage by introducing innovative machinery with numeric equipement that places Control Skateboards MFG. in an even more competitive category on the worldwide market. Fall 2004, the shop is moved into the most high-tech setup to date, with computer controlled router, robotic machinery, high pressure molds and 55 presses, Control Skateboards MFG\'s dynamic ways make this shop the most efficient so far.</p>', ''),
(84, 1, 'Westeel Div. of Vicwest Operating Ltd Partnership ', 'westeel@westeel.com', 'P.O. Box 792, Main Station, WINNIPEG, Manitoba, , ', 'www.westeel.com', '+1 (204) 233-7133 ', '+1 (204) 235-0796 ', '', '<p>Westeel Agriculture and Westeel Petroleum are divisions of Vicwest Operating Limited Partnership.  The Westeel divisions are two of Canada\'s foremost manufacturers of steel storage products, offering a wide range of on-farm and commercial storage solutions for today&rsquo;s agricultural industry, as well as custom storage solutions to meet the needs of the petroleum and industrial sectors. Today, the company exports its products across North America and to more than 30 countries around the world.   Westeel&rsquo;s agricultural storage products include grain bins, bulk feed tanks and smooth wall hoppered bins for wet holding, seed and fertilizer. The industrial tank group manufactures petroleum storage tanks for the oil and gas industry, and custom engineered and fabricated products for specialized needs.  Established in 1905, Westeel maintains its head office and four production facilities in Western Canada as well as a branch office in St-Simon, Quebec and in Fargo, North Dakota &amp; USA.</p>', ''),
(85, 1, 'R T I Research Ltd.', 'jaremco@uniserve.com', '23749 72nd Ave, Langley, British Columbia, , ', 'www.accupro.com', '+1 (604) 888-7944 ', '+1 (604) 882-6943 ', '', '<p>RTI Research Ltd. is one of North America\'s foremost developers  of premier gun care products for the shooting sports industry,  military, and law enforcement applications. RTI manufactures  ACCUPRO gun care products under exacting standards of quality and  excellence. The product line is divided into three main  categories: 1) chemicals, 2) hardware and 3) accessories. These  include: cleaning fluids; rifle, shotgun and pistol cleaning  rods; bore jags; brushes and swabs; cotton patches; tactical gun  cases; shooting muffs; and ear plugs. RTI performs extensive R &amp;  D activities to continually improve product performance and  reliability. RTI utilizes state-of-the-art materials and CNC  machining capabilities for its components. The marketing program  is dealer/distributor driven and focuses on consumer needs. RTI  exports to the United States, Germany, Italy, France, Sweden,  Norway, Finland, and Iceland.</p>', ''),
(86, 1, 'Vorum Research Corporation ', 'canfit@vorum.com ', '6-8765 Ash St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, , ', 'www.vorum.com  ', '+1 (604) 321-7277 ', '+1 (604) 321-5345 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Vorum continues to lead the way in CAD/CAM innovation for the Prosthetics, Orthotics and Footwear industries. Today, Vorum is a well established provider of P&amp;O and Footwear CAD/CAM technology and leads market distribution of systems worldwide. Vorum currently supports over 600 installations for more than 250 customers across Asia, Europe and North America. Vorum develops and markets a comprehensive suite of CAD/CAM software and hardware under the brand CANFIT-PLUSTM Systems. Vorum provides both pre-packaged productivity tools and custom solutions. The CANFIT-PLUSTM product line includes shape scanning technology, design modification software and computer numerically controlled (CNC) milling machines. Our mission is to solve the automation needs of clients who fit devices to the human body. Our customers range in size from single practitioner clinics to large, central fabrication facilities and industrial manufacturers.</p>', ''),
(87, 1, 'Vorum Research Corporation ', 'canfit@vorum.com ', '6-8765 Ash St, VANCOUVER, British Columbia, , ', 'www.vorum.com  ', '+1 (604) 321-7277 ', '+1 (604) 321-5345 ', '', '<p>Vorum continues to lead the way in CAD/CAM innovation for the Prosthetics, Orthotics and Footwear industries. Today, Vorum is a well established provider of P&amp;O and Footwear CAD/CAM technology and leads market distribution of systems worldwide. Vorum currently supports over 600 installations for more than 250 customers across Asia, Europe and North America.  Vorum develops and markets a comprehensive suite of CAD/CAM software and hardware under the brand CANFIT-PLUSTM Systems. Vorum provides both pre-packaged productivity tools and custom solutions. The CANFIT-PLUSTM product line includes shape scanning technology, design modification software and computer numerically controlled (CNC) milling machines.  Our mission is to solve the automation needs of clients who fit devices to the human body. Our customers range in size from single practitioner clinics to large, central fabrication facilities and industrial manufacturers.</p>', ''),
(88, 1, 'Barrington Brolly ', 'joan@barringtonbrolly.com ', '664 Bay Road, GIBSONS - British Columbia, , ', 'www.barringtonbrolly.com  ', '+1 (604) 886-9205', '+1 (604) 886-9205', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">1) Hand-made umbrellas and ladies parasols. Water repellent fabrics includes silk, nylon, cotton. Import unique Italian-made handles, and some of our unique fabrics.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">2) Historical reproduction parasols and umbrellas for use in museums, living history museums, re-enactors, theatre, movies, role playing.  </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">3) Exporter world-wide</p>', ''),
(89, 1, 'Creative Canvas Co. ', 'PBrewster@creative-canvas.com ', '520 Windmill Rd, DARTMOUTH, Nova Scotia, , ', 'www.creative-canvas.com  ', '+1 (902) 482-3125 ', '+1 (902) 468-8948 ', '', '<p>Craetive Canvas Co. s a an industrial Textile Converter specializing in the design and manufacturing of industrial tarps, covers, bags and environmental protection products such as Silt Curtains (turbidity curtains/booms) and Soaker Bags (dewatering filter bags). In addition Creative Canvas Co. supports the sign and marketing industry with the manufacturing of custom banner blanks and the design and manufacturing of Aluminum Steelstitch Awnings.  Creative\'s modern, flexible manufacturing plant  features programmable sewing machines, fabric welding equipment, and multiple layer cutting machines. Products can be designed and manufactured to customer specifications.  Creative Canvas Co. is registered to ISO 9001:200 through their parent company, Bridgeport Wire Rope &amp; Chain Limited.</p>', ''),
(1907, 1, 'Kushies Baby ', 'dswan@kushies.com ', '555 Barton St., STONEY CREEK, Ontario, , ', 'www.kushies.com  ', '+1 (905) 643-9118', '+1 (905) 643-2102', '', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Kushies Baby designs,  manufactures and markets an innovative collection of quality baby  products and accessories. The company strives for excellence in all  areas to ensure its customers receive the highest attainable workmanship  and quality. This is exemplified in our continued dedication to service  - an uncompromising commitment maintained for more than 50 years.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The company was  established as Diana Dolls Wear Ltd. in 1953, by Mary Malinowski of  Stoney Creek, Ontario. Founded as a small &quot;cottage-style&quot; industry, it  grew to become the only Canadian manufacturer of doll clothing and  accessories, with a customer list that included all the major Canadian  department stores. In 1987, Mary Malinowski retired and on January 1st  1988, Susan Malinowski and Sam Perez purchased Diana Dolls Wear Ltd.  assets.</p>', ''),
(1908, 1, 'Lakefront Mfg. Inc. (LMI)', 'lmi@lakefrontmfg.com', '925 Prom Lakefront, MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, , ', 'www.lakefrontmfg.com', '+1 (905) 278-8777', '+1 (905) 278-9780', '', '<p>Lakefront Mfg. Inc. located in Mississauga, Ontario, Canada is an  employee owned company consisting of 4 divisions which provide  the  following services in the aerospace, automotive and other   commercial/military sectors. 1. Lakefront Manufacturing Division, 2.  Halpen Engineering Division, 3. Cleansweep Division, 4. Electronic  Illumination Division. With the skills and  facilities in place due the  acquisition of the assets of  Electronic Illumination Ltd., LMI can now  offer. - Sheet metal fabrication, edge-lit panels, chassis,  enclosures  and card cages for electronic equipment, name  plates and dials,  engraving and profiling as well as  backlighted assemblies.   L.M.I is  certified to the ISO Quality system through SGS ICS  Canada and holds  Certificate of approval # 43-99 from Transport  Canada as an approved  Maintenance Organization.   Lakefront Mfg. Inc. is presently exporting  indirectly through  aerospace and automotive contracts.</p>', ''),
(1909, 1, 'Larsen & Shaw Limited', 'sales@larsenhinge.com', 'P.O. Box 1420, WALKERTON, Ontario, , ', 'www.larsenhinge.com', '+1 (519) 881-1320', '+1 (519) 881-3593', '', '<p>A leading North American manufacturer of top quality custom and  standard continuous/piano hinges, architectural hinges,  butt/strap/tee/lift off/stop/spring hinges, and metal stampings  (brackets/braces) used in enclosure/cabinet/tool box, appliance, vehicle  hardware, industrial/agricultural/transportation equipment, furniture  and architectural hardware industries. We are The Hinge People&reg;, ISO  Quality Management certified, following LEAN manufacturing principles,  enabling us to focus on our customers&rsquo; requirements to be responsive  with short lead times, on time delivery , high quality and competitive  pricing. Our products are available in steel, stainless, aluminum,  galvanized and brass materials, in a variety of finishes, using our  in-house plating and tooling capabilities. Larsen &amp; Shaw, a family  owned business since 1919, has grown to a leadership position by  combining technology with a skilled and dedicated work force.</p>', ''),
(456, 1, 'Bohne Spring Industries Limited ', 'sales@bohnespring.ca', '60 Coronet Rd., Toronto - Ontario , , ', 'www.bohnespring.ca  ', '+1 (416) 231-9000 ', '+1 (416) 231-5365', '', '<p>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\r\n<meta name=\"ProgId\" content=\"PowerPoint.Slide\">\r\n<meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft PowerPoint 12\">     </meta>\r\n</meta>\r\n</meta>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt 0in; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Bohne Spring is a custom spring maker with a state of the art manufacturing facility in Toronto, Ontario. Our team of dedicated employees allow us to meet the high standards our customers demand. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt 0in; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt 0in; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Our spring manufacturing capabilities include: compression,&nbsp; extension, torsion, wire forming, four-slide, small stamping and light assembly. We are experts in custom spring manufacturing from prototypes to large production runs. At Bohne Spring we offer exceptional quality, on time delivery and a long traditional of spring design manufacturing excellence. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt 0in; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0pt 0in; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; font-variant: normal; color: black; text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Our mission is to be the leading manufacturer of quality precision springs, wire forms and metal stampings. Having established a solid reputation through continuous improvement, effective cost management and expansion of business opportunities, we strive to earn a reasonable return on investment thereby assuring long term security for our customers and employees.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(91, 1, 'Almita Manufacturing Ltd. ', 'joan.parkin@almita.com', '4201, 66 Street, PONOKA - Alberta, , ', 'www.almita.com', '+1(403)783-5800 ', '+1(403)783-2895 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Manufacture screw-in pilings and screw-in anchors. Steel pipe  shaft complete with one or more steel helical plates welded on  to the bottom end. Product can be used as a permanent or  removable and reusable foundation. We can supply the design and  engineering for your requirements. Shaft sizes range from 2-7/8&quot;  up to 16&quot; and helix diameters vary from 6&quot; to 42&quot;. Almita has  installation units capable of generating up to 90,000 Ft. Lbs.  of Torque. Our Screw-In Pilings have been used as a foundation  for pumpjacks, compressors, dehydrators, flare stacks, pipe  racking, skid buildings, tanks, silos, pre-engineered metal  buildings, arch-ribbed buildings, permanent foundations,  communication towers and various other applications.</p>', ''),
(92, 1, 'Patterson Industries (Canada) Limited ', 'process@pattersonindustries.com', '250 Danforth Rd., SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, , ', 'www.pattersonindustries.com', '+1 (416) 694-3381', '+1 (416) 691-2768', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">PATTERSON Industries (Canada) Limited designs, engineers and manufactures a wide range of process equipment and turnkey systems for the oil, gas and petro-chemicals; resins, coatings and adhesives; agricultural and general chemicals; plastics and rubber; steel; pulp and paper; mining and construction; pharmaceutical and food, and waste water treatment industries. Founded in the U.S., and Canadian owned since 1974, PATTERSON Industries (Canada) Limited serves a global marketplace of process industries. Our expertise in individual component and system design utilizes mechanical, heat transfer, pneumatic, hydraulic, electrical, and computerized control functions all under one roof. All aspects of PATTERSON\'s quality engineering, designing and manufacturing are customized to meet individual specifications and comply with internationally recognized codes and standards, including ASME, TEMA and CSA.</p>', ''),
(93, 1, 'IND Diagnostic Inc.', 'info@ind.ca ', '1629 Fosters Way, DELTA, British Columbia, , ', 'www.ind.ca  ', '+1 (604) 522-1619', '+1 (604) 522-6331', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">IND Diagnostic Inc. is a Canadian biotechnology company specializing in research, development and manufacturing of advanced in-vitro diagnostic (IVD) test systems. Our focus is to expand our markets internationally by forming strategic alliances and entering into partnerships with distributors worldwide. IND Diagnostic Inc. is a certified Canadian Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) of rapid diagnostic tests. We have established an international reputation for excellence in the manufacturing of quality medical diagnostic test kits. In addition, we have obtained approval licenses from the United States Food and Drug Administration (FDA), CE Mark in the European union as well as Health Canada for most of our products. Our corporate offices and manufacturing facilities are located in an ISO 13485 / ISO 9001 approved facility in British Columbia, Canada.</p>', ''),
