(134, 1, 'Philip Doyle Manufacturing Inc. ', 'info@philipdoyle.com', '95 Covington St, HAMILTON, Ontario, , ', 'www.philipdoyle.com', '+1 (905) 561-0545', '+1 (905) 561-5858 ', '', '<p>Philip Doyle Manufacturing specializes in the custom design and fabrication of industrial &amp; severe duty cooling systems and engineered controlled environments. Our company has been based in Hamilton, Ontario since 1966. Our company is dedicated to providing our customers the best in quality products and services. As an effort to showing our dedication to continuous quality improvements, we are proud to announce that Philip Doyle Manufacturing Inc, is an ISO9002 registered company for all our product lines. We have long term technical engineering experience in HVAC - heating, ventilating and air conditioning as well as in our building and enclosure product lines. We also offer complete autocad design capabilities. Essentially, our company offers two main product lines, they are categorized as industrial and severe duty HVAC products, and industrial duty Building Enclosure products.</p>', ''),
(135, 1, 'Nipissing Furniture Mfg Limited', 'info@nipissingfurniture.ca', '27 Wilhelm St., KITCHENER, Ontario, , ', 'www.nipissingfurniture.ca', '+1-519-576-4952', '+1-519-743-5490', '', '<p>Norm Harney has 27 years of experience crafting fine furniture.  He apprenticed for three years and continued to acquire his skills for six more years with a fourth generation Spanish craftsman.  Together they built fine custom furniture and manufactured wood pattern mold masters for plastic furniture components.        Norm further developed his skills working as a furniture draftsman/engineer for 11 years in both production and custom shop environments.  Recently, he coordinated the development and manufacturing of fine contract furniture for the hospitality industry, serving four and five star hotels.</p>', ''),
(136, 1, 'M.L.P. Cosmetiques Inc.', 'mlp@mlpcosmetiques.qc.ca', '1477, rue Nobel, SAINTE-JULIE, Quebec, , ', 'www.mlpcosmetiques.qc.ca', '+1 (450) 649-2455', '+1 (450) 649-8570', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Welcome: Founded in the early 80&rsquo;s, M.L.P. Cosmetics inc. manufactures cosmetics such as face and body care, make-up, leisure and hair care products. Our chemists are able to conceive a wide range of products directly from our laboratories to satisfy the specific requirements of each of our customers. Our professional expertise ranges from the elaboration of formulas to product manufacturing, bottling and/or tubing and packaging. Our brand names: Jean Murrat and Marcel de S&egrave;vres are proof of our expertise.</p>', ''),
(137, 1, 'ThermoTech Industries Inc.', 'thermotech@pei.aibn.com', 'P.O. Box 482, Cornwall Bus. Park, CORNWALL - Prince Edward Island, , ', 'www.vinyltechwindows.com', '+1 (902) 368-1616 ', '+1 (902) 892-1088', '', '<p>Welcome to the Vinyl Tech. Vinyl Tech Windows are manufactured in our new facility in the Town of Cornwall, Prince Edward Island. We offer the latest technology, equipment, and high quality raw materials to produce a new and exciting line of 2 7/8 &amp; 3 1/4 framed vinyl windows made to your exact specifications. We also manufacture a variety of Thermal Units with many options. Vinyl Tech also carries a wide assortment of vinyl siding products and patio doors. Our plan is to build a product that will bring peace of mind to our customers in the areas of health and security, but still be gentle on their pocket book. Please feel free to contact us should you require any further information. Vinyl Tech Windows PEI (902) 368-1616 info@vinyltechwindows.com</p>', ''),
(138, 1, 'Ramagex ', 'ramagex@abacom.com ', '192 route 222, RACINE, Quebec, , ', 'www.ramagex.com  ', '+1 (450) 532-3212 ', '+1 (450) 532-2742 ', '', '<p>Ramagex is a manufacturer of coloured and natural wood excelsior. We offer several different cuts of excelsior that vary in both width and thickness, which cater to the needs of our clients. For our coloured excelsior we use the \'\'PANTONE\'\' chart, which gives our clients the choice of 2000 colours. Our product is extremely versatile, being used in the casket industry as bedding, in gift baskets for its natural look an din both commercial and industrial packaging because of its superior protection and environmental qualities. Ramagex has developed a product that is similar to \'\'Spanish moss\'\', destined for the florist industry. As well companies that do both natural and artificial floral arrangements use this product. One of the growing markets is craft stores, selling our products in 2oz. bags. - Commercialization Activities by Geographical Sectors The majority of Ramagex`s sales are realized in Canada, particularly in Quebec and Ontario.</p>', ''),
(139, 1, 'Precimac Tool Ltd.', 'carolynm@precimactool.com', '374 Franklin Blvd., CAMBRIDGE, Ontario, , ', 'www.precimactool.com', '+1 (519) 621-5585', '+1 (519) 621-0087 ', '', '<p>EXCEPTIONAL CUTTING SOLUTIONS: Since 1969, Precimac Tool Ltd. has been providing North American manufactures with superior  custom metal cutting tools and fast, personalized service. Our precision tools are specifically   engineered for optimum performance, greater cost efficiency and longer life. We bring years of   dedicated experience to developing creative solutions for our customers through our technical   sales in the field. Our state-of-the-art CNC machines, quality assurance program and customer   service systems guarantee satisfaction with every order.     CUSTOM METAL CUTTING TOOLS FOR EVERY APPLICATION:  Precimac has built its reputation on the reliable supply of high performance carbide and HSS,   standard and custom tools. Our knowledgeable engineering and production team has perfected   a number of integrated design characteristics to improve tool performance.</p>', ''),
(140, 1, 'PPI Systems Inc.  (Process Photonics)', 'ewilliams@processphotonics.com', '1051 Baxter Road, Unit 21, Ottawa, Ontario, , ', 'www.processphotonics.com', '+1 (613) 236-8359 ', '+1 (613) 248-4820 ', '', '<p>Process Photonics is an innovative supplier of custom and standard, laser-based, material processing systems for PCB, Electronics Assembly, and Medical Device Industries. The company is uniquely positioned to address these opportunities with expertise in optics, motion and vision systems, part handling and integration of OEM equipment into industrially robust stand-alone machines. Current standard product offerings include systems for circuit board via drilling, flex circuit processing, general high-precision material removal, as well as machines for medical component manufacture. Customers benefit from Process Photonics&rsquo; extensive experience in light and material interactions in the development of custom manufacturing solutions. Our latest generation products include the integration of test capability to verify processing performance with visual inspection, precision measurement, and electrical parameter test.</p>', ''),
