(143, 1, 'Sackville Harness Limited ', 'sackvilleharness@eastlink.ca', '39 Main St, SACKVILLE, New Brunswick, , ', 'www.sackvilleharness.com', '+1 (506) 536-0642 ', '+1 (506) 536-4652', '', '<p>Sackville Harness Shop has a rich heritage and a unique past. Formed in 1919 this company has long been famous for a complete range of harness and handmade straw collars for draught horses in Canada and the United States. At one time, and for several years the infamous Budweiser Clydesdales were adorn with the shop&rsquo;s hand made collars. The building which houses the shop is also extraordinary due to its impressive longevity and history. Reported to be Sackville&rsquo;s oldest building, the rustic wooden shingled structure has stood since the 1700&rsquo;s, over 200 years in the community. The shop today is quite literally an operable museum with the same harness patterns in use today as was used 90 years ago, with the finest quality and attention to detail still embellished in every product. Bill Long, a previous employee of the shop purchased the company back in 1995. He is determined to provide the highest quality of equestrian and custom leather products and services available.</p>', ''),
(144, 1, 'Indus Automation Inc.', 'info@indusautomation.com', '460 Higgins Ave., WINNIPEG, Manitoba, , ', 'www.indusautomation.com', '+1 (204) 943-0050', '+1 (204) 943-0112', '', '<p>Indus owns and operates from a 6,400 square foot facility close to downtown Winnipeg.   History of Indus Automation: Indus was started in 1963 by John Rogalski, with Ted Glass and Jon Johnson as silent partners. John had a long history in the Electrical industry with Langley Electric which became Amalgamated Electric. John had apprenticed in Germany, and had a superb combination of electrical and mechanical skills. During this time he played a key role in the design of the Amalgamated Rotary handle switch from 30 Amperes to 1200 Amperes. This basic design is still manufactured today.  John had gone to work for Westinghouse as the head of a assembly shop to offer control panels and custom distribution equipment to local contractors. The shop was burdened by high overheads artificially imposed by the company and therefore appeared to Westinghouse to be unprofitable, in an accounting sense.</p>', ''),
(145, 1, 'La Mariposa Bathworks', 'lamariposabathwroks@yahoo.com', '50 Silver Linden Dr, RICHMOND HILL, Ontario, , ', 'www.lamariposa.bravehost.com', '+1 (905) 482-9418', '+1 (905) 482-9418', '', '<p>Unrefined shea butter contains an abundance of healing ingredients, including vitamins, minerals, proteins and a unique fatty acid profile, and is a superior active moisturizer. Unlike petroleum based moisturizers, shea butter actually restores the skin\'s natural elasticity. Shea butter actually enables your skin to absorb moisture from the air, and as a result, it becomes softer and stays moisturized for longer. In addition, shea butter has natural sunscreen properties and anti-inflammatory agents. Because of its amazing properties, shea butter is an excellent ingredient for soaps, lotions and creams. Perhaps it is most effective when applied to the skin in its pure state. Regular users of pure, unrefined shea butter notice softer, smoother, healthier skin. Shea butter has also been shown to help with skin conditions and ailments such as extreme dryness, eczema, dermatitis, skin allergies, fungal infections, blemishes, wrinkles, stretch marks, scars, scrapes, and more.</p>', ''),
(146, 1, 'Analytic Systems', 'billw@analyticsystems.com', '8128 River Way, DELTA - British Columbia, , ', 'www.analyticsystems.com', '+1(604)946-9981', '+1(604) 946-9983', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Analytic Systems,founded in 1976, designs and manufactures DC- AC Inverters, DC-DC Voltage Converters and AC-DC Power supplies  for the Marine, Automotive, Industrial, Heavy Equipment &amp;  Alternative energy markets.  Everything we manufacture is designed with rugged duty service in mind. Heavy gauge aluminum sheet metal or extruded cases feature stainless fasteners and heavy duty hardware.   Our products are backed with a 3-year parts and labour warranty.  Current markets include North America, the Middle East,  Latin America, and Australia. The company is interested in  expanding sales to Europe and to Asia.   A full line catalog is available upon request.</p>', '');
, VICTORIAVILLE, QuÃ©bec, , ', 'www.symcod.com', '+1 (819) 751-0095 ', '+1 (819) 751-1292', '', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Since 1990, Symcod has specialized in the development of data collection equipment. The mission of the company is:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">To develop and market  innovative data collection equipment in specialized fields through a  network of value added resellers in the software field.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Symcod is aware that a  company\'s data collection is more than just a question of installing  cables. The hardware must be appropriate, and installed with  professionalism on the network level as well as the ergonomic level. It  must be reliable, sturdy and affordable.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The application software  and the hardware must be transparent so the customer can work most  effectively and receive uninterrupted service.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The customer\'s personnel must be well-trained but a toll-free number is available for support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">For more than twelve years, this global vision driven by the customer\'s needs has brought worldwide success to Symcod.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The excellence of Symcod  products and its commitment to its mission are the best guarantees for  customers. Symcod does not develop application software, but pursuing  its mission, prefers to work with software resellers and partners.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1905, 1, 'G&V Snowshoes', 'info@gvsnowshoes.com', '605 Stanislas Koska St, WENDAKE, Quebec, , ', 'www.raquettesgv.com', '+1 (418) 842-0321', '+1 (418) 842-2003', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; unicode-bidi: embed; direction: ltr; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold\">What does it mean GV?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 3pt\"><br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt\">The  Wendat Huron reserve has always been recognized for the quality and  reliability of the traditional snowshoe models they were producing. Many  companies such as Gros-Louis Snowshoes, which was owned by Mr. Antoine  Gros-Louis and started manufacturing in 1959, have been in operation for  a long time . In 1982, Mr. Maurice Vincent partnered with Mr. Antoine  Gros-Louis and the GV brand name was created (</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold\">G</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt\">ros-Louis &amp; </span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold\">V</span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt\">incent). In 1983, Mr. Maurice Vincent became the soul owner of the company and it was named </span><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold\">GV SNOWSHOES.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(1906, 1, 'Images in Slate Inc.', 'info@iis.ca', 'P.O. Box 55, NORTH VALLEY, NFLd and Labrador, , ', 'www.iis.ca ', '+1 (709) 786-2171', '+1 (709) 786-2176', '', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Imagine</strong>...  using 500 million year old natural slate to craft premium products  suitable for any occasion. Timeless, durable and functional. Our slate  products are rich in appearance and unique in design.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">We manufacture a  complete line of products using 500 million year old slate. Our target  markets range from the premium and incentive markets in Canada and  abroad to the Architectural Signage markets of North America. We supply  customized slate craft products such as coaster sets, book ends, etc.  with company logo\'s imprinted into the slate. All of our products are  produced in Newfoundland, Canada.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">At this time we are looking for any interested parties that may want to distribute our product line in other countries.</p>', ''),
