(219, 1, 'Fordia (Groupe Fordia Ltee)', 'marketing@fordia.com', '2745, Rue De Miniac,, St. Laurent â€“ Qc,, , ', 'www.fordia.com', '+1 (514) 336-9211', '+1 (514) 745-4125', '', '<p>Fordia has one clear focus &ndash; to provide the best diamond-drilling tools and equipment for the world&rsquo;s leading mineral drilling exploration companies. That is our mission. How we live it is our strength. We provide exceptional service, demonstrated daily by our worldwide representatives. Our distribution network ensures Fordia products can be delivered globally, right on schedule. We are committed to quality, innovation and technology. And we pride ourselves in being a team that is appreciated &ndash; internally by our colleagues and externally by our customers. Our mission is based on our core values &ndash; those guiding principles that characterize how we think and act. Communication. Recognition. Precision. Expansion. Financial Performance. This is what characterizes who we are and who we aim to be. They are the reasons that our customers stay with Fordia.</p>', ''),
(220, 1, 'G&V Snowshoes', 'info@gvsnowshoes.com', '605 Stanislas Koska St, WENDAKE, Quebec, , ', 'www.raquettesgv.com', '+1 (418) 842-0321', '+1 (418) 842-2003', '', '<p>\r\n<meta content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" http-equiv=\"Content-Type\">\r\n<meta content=\"PowerPoint.Slide\" name=\"ProgId\">\r\n<meta content=\"Microsoft PowerPoint 12\" name=\"Generator\">  </meta>\r\n</meta>\r\n</meta>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">What does it mean GV?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 3pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black;\"><br />\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black;\">The Wendat Huron reserve has always been recognized for the quality and reliability of the traditional snowshoe models they were producing. Many companies such as Gros-Louis Snowshoes, which was owned by Mr. Antoine Gros-Louis and started manufacturing in 1959, have been in operation for a long time . In 1982, Mr. Maurice Vincent partnered with Mr. Antoine Gros-Louis and the GV brand name was created (</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">G</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black;\">ros-Louis &amp; </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">V</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black;\">incent). In 1983, Mr. Maurice Vincent became the soul owner of the company and it was named </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">GV SNOWSHOES.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
