(221, 1, 'H.D. Brown Enterprises Ltd. ', 'info@hdbrown.com ', 'P.O. Box 190, ST GEORGE BRANT, Ontario, , ', 'www.hdbrown.com  ', '+1 (519) 448-1381', '+1 (519) 448-3159', '', '<p>Hugh Douglas Brown owned a furniture manufacturing company that made, among other things, oak bars for automobile roof racks. When the contract was almost cancelled, Hugh turned the potential loss into an opportunity.   It was when the national retailer who sold the racks couldn&rsquo;t find a supplier to make the cotton straps usedto fasten the racks to car roofs that Hugh realized with the right set-up it would be easy to make the straps.   The customer would be serviced, the contract would be saved, and the product - the only one of its kind at the time - would continue to reach the market.   In 1971 H.D. Brown Enterprises Ltd. began operations as a small cut and sew business with two staff working out of a factory in St. George, Ontario. Over the years the furniture business was sold and H.D. Brown began importing products on a subcontractor basis.</p>', ''),
(227, 1, 'Halltech Inc.', 'halltech@halltech-inc.com', '465 Coronation Dr., SCARBOROUGH, Ontario, , ', 'www.halltech-inc.com', '+1 (416) 284-6111 ', '+1 (416) 284-6932', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">When you &quot;stick&quot; with Halltech you\'re sticking with quality<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">AN ISO 9001 REGISTERED COMPANY<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Halltech Inc. is a Canadian manufacturer of polymer emulsions and industrial adhesives, with manufacturing facilities in Ontario and sales office and warehouse in Quebec. Our products cover a broad spectrum of applications. We manufacture adhesives for the automotive, packaging, construction, and woodworking industries. We produce polymer emulsions for the paint, specialty paper, construction, adhesive and textile industries. (As you can see, we bond with our customers.) We ship products all over North America and, export to such places as Australia and France.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Halltech Inc. was created in 1981, although our business dates back to 1934 when the company was first established, in Ontario, as Stein-Hall Limited . In 1989, Saiden Chemical Industry Co. , Ltd. of Tokyo, Japan, purchased Halltech Inc. to establish a manufacturing base for their line of water based pressure sensitive polymer adhesives in North America.On July 25, 2008, The company changed ownership again, through a management buy-out and is once again 100% Canadian owned. The company continues to operate under the Halltech name, with its own independent Research and Development lab.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
(318, 1, 'CG Air Systemes Inc. ', 'cgair@cgair.com ', '207, rue Industrielle, STE-MARGUERITE-DE-DORCHESTER, QuÃ©bec, , ', 'www.cgair.com  ', '+1 (418) 935-7075 ', '+1 (418) 935-3507', '', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\">CG Air Syst&egrave;mes manufacture components for whirlpool and air massage systems for bathtubs and components for multi-jets systems for showers. As blower, pump, electronic control, jets, manifold, hoses, etc...<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><b><u>History:</u></b> It was in 1991 that CG Air Syst&egrave;mes revolutionized the North American hydrotherapy market by introducing the first air massage system that was safe, hygienic and perfectly adapted to the North American requirements. Co-owners of the company, Miguel A. Castellote and Dominique Ciechanowski had a vision of their own. To offer manufacturers all necessary components for manufacturing of air system bathtubs. Since then, CG Air Systems has expanded its range of products and now offer a vast range of components for various bathing massage systems and spas.<o:p></o:p></p>', '');
, DELTA, British Columbia, , ', 'www.ind.ca  ', '+1 (604) 522-1619', '+1 (604) 522-6331', '', '<p>IND Diagnostic Inc. is a Canadian biotechnology company specializing in research, development and manufacturing of advanced in-vitro diagnostic (IVD) test systems. Our focus is to expand our markets internationally by forming strategic alliances and entering into partnerships with distributors worldwide. IND Diagnostic Inc. is a certified Canadian Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) of rapid diagnostic tests. We have established an international reputation for excellence in the manufacturing of quality medical diagnostic test kits. In addition, we have obtained approval licenses from the United States Food and Drug Administration (FDA), CE Mark in the European union as well as Health Canada for most of our products. Our corporate offices and manufacturing facilities are located in an ISO 13485 / ISO 9001 approved facility in British Columbia, Canada.</p>', ''),
