(252, 1, 'Enerscan Engineering Incorporated.', 'info@enerscanengineering.com', ' 22 Julie\'s Walk, Halifax, Nova Scotia, , ', 'www.enerscanengineering.com', '+1 (902) 445.4433', '+1 (902) 457.3283', '', '<p>Enerscan Engineering Incorporated was incorporated in 1981.   Since then the company has been involved in a number of engineering ventures including consulting and study of manufacturing related issues.  An interest in line hardware and line tools developed following involvement in a project that identified the significant advances in plastics and composite materials over the last two decades.   This identified many opportunities for the use of plastics and composites to replace traditional materials such as metals.  The benefits can be numerous, but include higher strengths and durability, weight, electrical and heat conductivity.   Further benefits can result from more modern design.   Enerscan has a variety of products under development at present, most of which are following a rigid and thorough design - prototype - test - redesign system led by experienced, seasoned engineers.</p>', ''),
(253, 1, 'MegaResistors Corp.', 'info@megaresistors.com ', '39-6415 Northwest Dr., MISSISSAUGA, Ontario, , ', 'www.megaresistors.com', '+1-905-908-2376 ', '+1-905-908-2377', '', '<p>Are you having trouble finding a replacement power resistor?  Do you need technical support to configure a Neutral Grounding or a Motor Control Resistor?  Have you been looking for quality power resistors at reasonable prices?   You are in the right place!  At MegaResistors, we offer a full range of power resistors manufactured for both the OEM (original equipment manufacturer) and the end-user markets.  Our product line includes Neutral Grounding Resistors that incorporate high quality insulators, transformers and relays as well as a wide range of Dynamic Braking, Motor Starting, Motor Control, Harmonic Filter, Charge and Discharge Resistors.  Our top priorities are Customer Service and Product Quality.  Call us, fax us or send us an e-mail with your requirements.   You will not be disappointed!</p>', ''),
(254, 1, 'Simalex Manufacturing Company Ltd. ', 'sidn@simalex.com ', '19622 Telegraph Trail, LANGLEY, British Columbia, , ', 'www.simalex.com', '+1 (604) 888-1212', '+1 (604) 888-4387', '', '<p>Established in 1965, by Mr. George Wentworth and Mr. Alex Lyhne. Continued steady growth, made it possible to build our existing facilities on a 5 acre site in Langley, B.C. We have expanded our building and our capabilities to offer a complete in-plant mold making facility, secondary finishing, product deburring/ vibratory finishing, and up to 720 ton die casting machines.  Our QA department is certified to ISO 9003 (1994). We are an active member of both the Canadian Die Casting Association, and the North American Die Casting Association (NADCA).</p>', ''),
