(320, 1, 'Amalgamated Dairies Limited ', 'adl@adl.ca ', '79 Water St., SUMMERSIDE - Prince Edward Island, , ', 'www.adl.ca  ', '+1(902)888-5088 ', '+1(902)436-7609 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; color: black;\">Amalgamated Dairies Limited is a farmer owned cooperative style association formed in 1953. It is located in the province of Prince Edward Island situated in Eastern Canada. The purpose of the Association originally was to manufacture and<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; color: black;\"> process dairy products including milk, cream, butter, cheese, whey, buttermilk, and all other dairy products pertinent to the industry.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; color: black;\"><br />\r\nToday Amalgamated Dairies Limited has broadened its purpose to include a food distribution warehouse, two fluid milk outlets, an evaporated milk plant, an abattoir, and a tire, automotive &amp; truck centre. It also continues to uphold its tradition of producing excellent dairy products such as cheese, ice cream, butter and evaporated milk. It continues as a dairy cooperative owned by over 400 producers and its direction is still maintained by the elected board of 15 directors. Although the future of this industry will continue to set many challenges, Amalgamated Dairies Limited will continue to strengthen its position as a key player in the dairy industry.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Century Gothic&quot;; color: black;\"><br />\r\nOur head office coordinates six processing and distribution facilities. This is also the site of our main processing facility, which manufactures many dairy products including cheese and ice cream.</span></p>', ''),
(321, 1, 'Canadian Can-Tex Div Boa Holdings Ltd. ', 'gary@can-tex.com ', 'P.O. Box 451, NORTH BAY - Ontario, , ', 'www.can-tex.com ', '+1 (705) 776-7731', '+1 (705) 776-7611 ', '', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">Canadian Can-Tex has more than 40 years of continuous sales and service for a wide range of resource-based clients.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The aim of the company is to provide top quality, portable buildings and tents used in mine exploration, forestry and field camps. You will find Can-Tex tents and enclosures in use around the world, providing comfortable working and living quarters to people operating in the harshest conditions ranging from Arctic cold to extreme desert heat. Canadian Can-Tex prides itself in providing custom designs for individual clients such as portable garages, boat and ATV covers to protect the valuable equipment of outdoor enthusiasts. Large or small, every client is valuable to Canadian Can-Tex.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\" class=\"MsoNormal\">The heart of the company is the Jutland Portabuilding that is designed and manufactured at the company&rsquo;s plant in Rutherglen, Ontario. Jutland\'s aluminum framing system is compact, light-weight, strong, and easy to install. The high quality canvas shell breathes and maintains a healthy environment inside the structure. All structures pack up quickly and are highly portable. On a custom basis, Can-Tex designs large soft shelled structures for industrial, commercial, and recreational applications. Can-Tex also manufactures an assortment of canvas items ranging from awnings to sand bags.<o:p></o:p></p>', ''),
